131 #define MAX_SERIAL_INVARIANT 8
132 typedef struct serial_invariant SERIAL_INVARIANT;
133 
134 /* an invariant which serial must hold */
135 struct serial_invariant
136 {
137  DB_VALUE val1;
138  DB_VALUE val2;
139  PT_OP_TYPE cmp_op;
140  int val1_msgid; /* the proper message id for val1. 0 means val1 should not be responsible for the
141  * invariant voilation */
142  int val2_msgid; /* the proper message id for val2. 0 means val2 should not be responsible for the
143  * invariant voilation */
144  int error_type; /* ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW or ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE */
145 };

147 /*
148  * eval_insert_value -
149  * Structure is passed as argument to parser_walk_tree when insert values are
150  * evaluated and stores the information required for evaluation.
151  */
152 typedef struct eval_insert_value EVAL_INSERT_VALUE;
153 struct eval_insert_value
154 {
155  UINTPTR spec_id; /* insert spec_id */
156  PT_NODE *attr_list; /* list of insert attribute names */
157  PT_NODE *value_list; /* list of insert values values */
158  int crt_attr_index; /* current attribute index */
159  bool reevaluate_needed; /* currently evaluated insert value may need to be reevaluated with next execution */
160  bool replace_names; /* true if names may need to be replaced with each evaluation */
161 };

178 /*
179  * initialize_serial_invariant() - initialize a serial invariant
180  * return: None
181  * invariant(out):
182  * val1(in):
183  * val2(in):
184  * cmp_op(in):
185  * val1_msgid(in):
186  * val2_msgid(in):
187  * error_type(in):
188  *
189  * Note:
190  */
191 static void
192 initialize_serial_invariant (SERIAL_INVARIANT * invariant, DB_VALUE val1, DB_VALUE val2, PT_OP_TYPE cmp_op,
193  int val1_msgid, int val2_msgid, int error_type)
194 {
195  invariant->val1 = val1;
196  invariant->val2 = val2;
197  invariant->cmp_op = cmp_op;
198  invariant->val1_msgid = val1_msgid;
199  invariant->val2_msgid = val2_msgid;
200  invariant->error_type = error_type;
201 }
202 
203 /*
204  * check_serial_invariants() - check whether invariants have been violated
205  * return: Error code
206  * invariants(in):
207  * num_invariants(in):
208  * ret_msg_id(out):
209  *
210  * Note:
211  */
212 
213 static int
214 check_serial_invariants (SERIAL_INVARIANT * invariants, int num_invariants, int *ret_msg_id)
215 {
216  int i, c;
217  int error;
218  DB_VALUE cmp_result;
219 
220  for (i = 0; i < num_invariants; i++)
221  {
222 
223  error = numeric_db_value_compare (&invariants[i].val1, &invariants[i].val2, &cmp_result);
224  if (error != NO_ERROR)
225  {
226  return error;
227  }
228 
229  c = db_get_int (&cmp_result);
230  switch (invariants[i].cmp_op)
231  {
232  case PT_GT:
233  if (c > 0)
234  {
235  /* same as expected */
236  continue;
237  }
238  break;
239  case PT_GE:
240  if (c >= 0)
241  {
242  continue;
243  }
244  break;
245  case PT_LT:
246  if (c < 0)
247  {
248  continue;
249  }
250  break;
251  case PT_LE:
252  if (c <= 0)
253  {
254  continue;
255  }
256  break;
257  case PT_EQ:
258  if (c == 0)
259  {
260  continue;
261  }
262  break;
263  case PT_NE:
264  if (c != 0)
265  {
266  continue;
267  }
268  break;
269  default:
270  /* impossible to get here! */
271  assert (0);
272  break;
273  }
274 
275  /* get here means invariant violated! */
276  if (invariants[i].val1_msgid != 0)
277  {
278  *ret_msg_id = invariants[i].val1_msgid;
279  return invariants[i].error_type;
280  }
281 
282  if (invariants[i].val2_msgid != 0)
283  {
284  *ret_msg_id = invariants[i].val2_msgid;
285  return invariants[i].error_type;
286  }
287 
288  /* impossible to get here! */
289  assert (0);
290  }
291 
292  return NO_ERROR;
293 }
294 
295 /*
296  * truncate_need_repl_log() - check whether truncate stmt need a replicate log
297  * return: true if the table has primary key,
298  * otherwise false
299  * statement(in):
300  */
301 static bool
302 truncate_need_repl_log (PT_NODE * statement)
303 {
304  PT_NODE *entity_spec = NULL;
305  PT_NODE *entity_list = NULL;
306  PT_NODE *entity = NULL;
307  const char *class_name = NULL;
308  MOP class_mop = NULL;
309  SM_CLASS *class_ = NULL;
310  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *cons = NULL;
311  int error = NO_ERROR;
312 
313  assert (statement != NULL);
314 
315  entity_spec = statement->info.truncate.spec;
316  assert (entity_spec != NULL);
317 
318  entity_list = entity_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
319  assert (entity_list != NULL);
320 
321  for (entity = entity_list; entity != NULL; entity = entity->next)
322  {
323  class_name = entity->info.name.original;
324  class_mop = db_find_class (class_name);
325  if (class_mop == NULL)
326  {
327  return false;
328  }
329 
330  error = au_fetch_class (class_mop, &class_, AU_FETCH_READ, DB_AUTH_NONE);
331  if (error != NO_ERROR)
332  {
333  return false;
334  }
335 
336  cons = classobj_find_cons_primary_key (class_->constraints);
337  if (cons != NULL)
338  {
339  return true;
340  }
341  }
342 
343  return false;
344 }
345 
346 /*
347  * is_stmt_based_repl_type()
348  * return: true if it's a statement-based replication log statement
349  * otherwise false
350  * node(in):
351  */
352 bool
353 is_stmt_based_repl_type (const PT_NODE * node)
354 {
355  /* All DDLs will be replicated via schema replication */
356  if (pt_is_ddl_statement (node))
357  {
358  return true;
359  }
360 
361  /* some DMLs will also be replicated via schema replication instead of data replication */
362  switch (node->node_type)
363  {
364  case PT_DROP_VARIABLE:
365  case PT_TRUNCATE:
366  return true;
367  case PT_INSERT:
368  if (node->info.insert.hint & PT_HINT_USE_SBR)
369  {
370  return true;
371  }
372  break;
373  case PT_DELETE:
374  if (node->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_USE_SBR)
375  {
376  return true;
377  }
378  break;
379  case PT_UPDATE:
380  if (node->info.update.hint & PT_HINT_USE_SBR)
381  {
382  return true;
383  }
384  break;
385  default:
386  break;
387  }
388 
389  return false;
390 }
391 
392 /*
393  * do_evaluate_default_expr() - evaluates the default expressions, if any, for
394  * the attributes of a given class
395  * return: Error code
396  * parser(in):
397  * class_name(in):
398  */
399 int
400 do_evaluate_default_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * class_name)
401 {
402  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
403  SM_CLASS *smclass;
404  int error;
405  TP_DOMAIN_STATUS dom_status;
406  char *user_name;
407  DB_DATETIME *datetime;
408  int month, day, year, hour, minute, second, millisecond;
409  DB_VALUE default_value, format_val, lang_val;
410  char *lang_str = NULL;
411  int flag;
412  TP_DOMAIN *result_domain = NULL;
413  bool has_user_format;
414 
415  assert (class_name->node_type == PT_NAME);
416 
417  error = au_fetch_class_force (class_name->info.name.db_object, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ);
418  if (error != NO_ERROR)
419  {
420  return error;
421  }
422 
423  for (att = smclass->attributes; att != NULL; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
424  {
425  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type != DB_DEFAULT_NONE)
426  {
427  switch (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type)
428  {
429  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSTIME:
430  if (DB_IS_NULL (&parser->sys_datetime))
431  {
432  db_make_null (&default_value);
433  }
434  else
435  {
436  db_datetime_decode ((DB_DATETIME *) db_get_datetime (&parser->sys_datetime), &month, &day, &year,
437  &hour, &minute, &second, &millisecond);
438  db_make_time (&default_value, hour, minute, second);
439  }
440  break;
441  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTTIME:
442  if (DB_IS_NULL (&parser->sys_datetime))
443  {
444  db_make_null (&default_value);
445  }
446  else
447  {
448  DB_TIME cur_time, db_time;
449  const char *t_source, *t_dest;
450  DB_DATETIME *datetime;
451 
452  datetime = db_get_datetime (&parser->sys_datetime);
453  t_source = tz_get_system_timezone ();
454  t_dest = tz_get_session_local_timezone ();
455  db_time = datetime->time / 1000;
456  error = tz_conv_tz_time_w_zone_name (&db_time, t_source, strlen (t_source), t_dest,
457  strlen (t_dest), &cur_time);
458  db_value_put_encoded_time (&default_value, &cur_time);
459  }
460  break;
461  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSDATE:
462  if (DB_IS_NULL (&parser->sys_datetime))
463  {
464  db_make_null (&default_value);
465  }
466  else
467  {
468  datetime = db_get_datetime (&parser->sys_datetime);
469  error = db_value_put_encoded_date (&default_value, &datetime->date);
470  }
471  break;
472  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSDATETIME:
473  error = pr_clone_value (&parser->sys_datetime, &default_value);
474  break;
475  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSTIMESTAMP:
476  error = db_datetime_to_timestamp (&parser->sys_datetime, &default_value);
477  break;
478  case DB_DEFAULT_UNIX_TIMESTAMP:
479  error = db_unix_timestamp (&parser->sys_datetime, &default_value);
480  break;
481  case DB_DEFAULT_USER:
482  user_name = db_get_user_and_host_name ();
483  error = db_make_string (&default_value, user_name);
484  default_value.need_clear = true;
485  break;
486  case DB_DEFAULT_CURR_USER:
487  user_name = db_get_user_name ();
488  error = db_make_string (&default_value, user_name);
489  default_value.need_clear = true;
490  break;
491  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTDATE:
492  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTDATETIME:
493  if (DB_IS_NULL (&parser->sys_datetime))
494  {
495  db_make_null (&default_value);
496  }
497  else
498  {
499  TZ_REGION system_tz_region, session_tz_region;
500  DB_DATETIME dest_dt;
501  DB_DATETIME *src_dt;
502 
503  src_dt = db_get_datetime (&parser->sys_datetime);
504  tz_get_system_tz_region (&system_tz_region);
505  tz_get_session_tz_region (&session_tz_region);
506  error =
507  tz_conv_tz_datetime_w_region (src_dt, &system_tz_region, &session_tz_region, &dest_dt, NULL, NULL);
508  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type == DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTDATE)
509  {
510  db_value_put_encoded_date (&default_value, &dest_dt.date);
511  }
512  else
513  {
514  db_make_datetime (&default_value, &dest_dt);
515  }
516  }
517  break;
518  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTTIMESTAMP:
519  if (DB_IS_NULL (&parser->sys_datetime))
520  {
521  db_make_null (&default_value);
522  }
523  else
524  {
525  DB_DATE tmp_date;
526  DB_TIME tmp_time;
527  DB_TIMESTAMP tmp_timestamp;
528  DB_DATETIME *sys_datetime;
529 
530  sys_datetime = db_get_datetime (&parser->sys_datetime);
531  tmp_date = sys_datetime->date;
532  tmp_time = sys_datetime->time / 1000;
533  db_timestamp_encode_sys (&tmp_date, &tmp_time, &tmp_timestamp, NULL);
534  db_make_timestamp (&default_value, tmp_timestamp);
535  }
536  break;
537  default:
538  break;
539  }
540 
541  if (error != NO_ERROR)
542  {
543  break;
544  }
545 
546  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_op == T_TO_CHAR)
547  {
548  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format != NULL)
549  {
550  has_user_format = 1;
551  db_make_string (&format_val, att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format);
552  }
553  else
554  {
555  has_user_format = 0;
556  db_make_null (&format_val);
557  }
558 
559  lang_str = prm_get_string_value (PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG);
560  lang_set_flag_from_lang (lang_str, has_user_format, 0, &flag);
561  db_make_int (&lang_val, flag);
562 
563  if (!TP_IS_CHAR_TYPE (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (att->domain)))
564  {
565  /* TO_CHAR returns a string value, we need to pass an expected domain of the result */
566  if (TP_IS_CHAR_TYPE (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&default_value)))
567  {
568  result_domain = NULL;
569  }
570  else if (DB_IS_NULL (&format_val))
571  {
572  result_domain = tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_TYPE_STRING);
573  }
574  else
575  {
576  result_domain = tp_domain_resolve_value (&format_val, NULL);
577  }
578  }
579  else
580  {
581  result_domain = att->domain;
582  }
583 
584  error = db_to_char (&default_value, &format_val, &lang_val, &att->default_value.value, result_domain);
585 
586  if (has_user_format)
587  {
588  pr_clear_value (&format_val);
589  }
590 
591  if (error != NO_ERROR)
592  {
593  break;
594  }
595  }
596  else
597  {
598  pr_clone_value (&default_value, &att->default_value.value);
599  }
600 
601  db_value_clear (&default_value);
602 
603  /* make sure the default value can be used for this attribute */
604  dom_status = tp_value_cast (&att->default_value.value, &att->default_value.value, att->domain, false);
605  if (dom_status != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
606  {
607  error = tp_domain_status_er_set (dom_status, ARG_FILE_LINE, &att->default_value.value, att->domain);
608  assert_release (error != NO_ERROR);
609 
610  break;
611  }
612  }
613  }
614 
615  return error;
616 }
617 
618 /*
619  * do_create_serial_internal() -
620  * return: Error code
621  * serial_object(out):
622  * serial_name(in):
623  * current_val(in):
624  * inc_val(in):
625  * min_val(in):
626  * max_val(in):
627  * cyclic(in):
628  * started(in):
629  * comment(in):
630  * class_name(in):
631  * att_name(in):
632  *
633  * Note:
634  */
635 static int
636 do_create_serial_internal (MOP * serial_object, const char *serial_name, DB_VALUE * current_val, DB_VALUE * inc_val,
637  DB_VALUE * min_val, DB_VALUE * max_val, const int cyclic, const int cached_num,
638  const int started, const char *comment, const char *class_name, const char *att_name)
639 {
640  DB_OBJECT *ret_obj = NULL;
641  DB_OTMPL *obj_tmpl = NULL;
642  DB_VALUE value;
643  DB_OBJECT *serial_class = NULL;
644  int au_save, error = NO_ERROR;
645 
646  db_make_null (&value);
647 
648  /* temporarily disable authorization to access db_serial class */
649  AU_DISABLE (au_save);
650 
651  serial_class = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
652  if (serial_class == NULL)
653  {
654  error = ER_QPROC_DB_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
655  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
656  goto end;
657  }
658 
659  obj_tmpl = dbt_create_object_internal ((MOP) serial_class);
660  if (obj_tmpl == NULL)
661  {
662  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
663  error = er_errid ();
664  goto end;
665  }
666 
667  /* name */
668  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, serial_name);
669  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_NAME, &value);
670  pr_clear_value (&value);
671  if (error != NO_ERROR)
672  {
673  goto end;
674  }
675 
676  /* owner */
677  db_make_object (&value, Au_user);
678  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_OWNER, &value);
679  pr_clear_value (&value);
680  if (error != NO_ERROR)
681  {
682  goto end;
683  }
684 
685  /* current_val */
686  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CURRENT_VAL, current_val);
687  if (error != NO_ERROR)
688  {
689  goto end;
690  }
691 
692  /* increment_val */
693  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_INCREMENT_VAL, inc_val);
694  if (error != NO_ERROR)
695  {
696  goto end;
697  }
698 
699  /* min_val */
700  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_MIN_VAL, min_val);
701  if (error != NO_ERROR)
702  {
703  goto end;
704  }
705 
706  /* max_val */
707  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_MAX_VAL, max_val);
708  if (error != NO_ERROR)
709  {
710  goto end;
711  }
712 
713  /* cyclic */
714  db_make_int (&value, cyclic); /* always false */
715  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CYCLIC, &value);
716  pr_clear_value (&value);
717  if (error != NO_ERROR)
718  {
719  goto end;
720  }
721 
722  /* started */
723  db_make_int (&value, started);
724  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_STARTED, &value);
725  pr_clear_value (&value);
726  if (error != NO_ERROR)
727  {
728  goto end;
729  }
730 
731  /* comment */
732  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, comment);
733  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_COMMENT, &value);
734  pr_clear_value (&value);
735  if (error != NO_ERROR)
736  {
737  goto end;
738  }
739 
740  /* class name */
741  if (class_name)
742  {
743  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, class_name);
744  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CLASS_NAME, &value);
745  pr_clear_value (&value);
746  if (error != NO_ERROR)
747  {
748  goto end;
749  }
750  }
751 
752  /* att name */
753  if (att_name)
754  {
755  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, att_name);
756  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_ATT_NAME, &value);
757  pr_clear_value (&value);
758  if (error != NO_ERROR)
759  {
760  goto end;
761  }
762  }
763 
764  /* cached num */
765  if (cached_num > 0)
766  {
767  db_make_int (&value, cached_num);
768  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CACHED_NUM, &value);
769  pr_clear_value (&value);
770  if (error != NO_ERROR)
771  {
772  goto end;
773  }
774  }
775 
776  ret_obj = dbt_finish_object (obj_tmpl);
777 
778  if (ret_obj == NULL)
779  {
780  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
781  error = er_errid ();
782  }
783  else if (serial_object != NULL)
784  {
785  *serial_object = ret_obj;
786  }
787 
788 end:
789  if (obj_tmpl != NULL && ret_obj == NULL)
790  {
791  dbt_abort_object (obj_tmpl);
792  }
793  AU_ENABLE (au_save);
794  return error;
795 }
796 
797 /*
798  * do_update_auto_increment_serial_on_rename() -
799  * return: Error code
800  * serial_obj(in/out):
801  * class_name(in):
802  * att_name(in):
803  *
804  * Note:
805  */
806 int
807 do_update_auto_increment_serial_on_rename (MOP serial_obj, const char *class_name, const char *att_name)
808 {
809  int error = NO_ERROR;
810  DB_OBJECT *serial_object = NULL;
811  DB_VALUE value;
812  DB_OTMPL *obj_tmpl = NULL;
813  char *serial_name = NULL;
814  char att_downcase_name[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
815  size_t name_len;
816  int save;
817  bool au_disable_flag = false;
818 
819  if (!serial_obj || !class_name || !att_name)
820  {
821  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
822  }
823 
824  db_make_null (&value);
825 
826  serial_object = serial_obj;
827  sm_downcase_name (att_name, att_downcase_name, SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH);
828  att_name = att_downcase_name;
829 
830  /* serial_name : <class_name>_ai_<att_name> */
831  name_len = (strlen (class_name) + strlen (att_name) + AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_NAME_EXTRA_LENGTH + 1);
832  serial_name = (char *) malloc (name_len);
833  if (serial_name == NULL)
834  {
835  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, name_len);
836  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
837  }
838 
839  SET_AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_NAME (serial_name, class_name, att_name);
840 
841  AU_DISABLE (save);
842  au_disable_flag = true;
843 
844  /*
845  * after serial.next_value, the currect value maybe changed, but cub_cas
846  * still hold the old value. To get the new value. we need decache it
847  * then refetch it from server again.
848  */
849  assert (WS_ISDIRTY (serial_object) == false);
850 
851  ws_decache (serial_object);
852  /* no need to get last version for serial - actually, the purpose is AU_FETCH_WRITE, so fetch type is not relevant;
853  * the last version will be locked and it will be considered visibile only if delid is not set */
854  error = au_fetch_instance_force (serial_object, NULL, AU_FETCH_WRITE, LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION);
855  if (error != NO_ERROR)
856  {
857  goto update_auto_increment_error;
858  }
859 
860  obj_tmpl = dbt_edit_object (serial_object);
861  if (obj_tmpl == NULL)
862  {
863  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
864  error = er_errid ();
865  goto update_auto_increment_error;
866  }
867 
868  /* name */
869  db_make_string (&value, serial_name);
870  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_NAME, &value);
871  if (error != NO_ERROR)
872  {
873  goto update_auto_increment_error;
874  }
875 
876  /* class name */
877  pr_clear_value (&value);
878  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, class_name);
879  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CLASS_NAME, &value);
880  pr_clear_value (&value);
881  if (error != NO_ERROR)
882  {
883  goto update_auto_increment_error;
884  }
885 
886  /* att name */
887  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, att_name);
888  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_ATT_NAME, &value);
889  pr_clear_value (&value);
890  if (error != NO_ERROR)
891  {
892  goto update_auto_increment_error;
893  }
894 
895  serial_object = dbt_finish_object (obj_tmpl);
896 
897  AU_ENABLE (save);
898  au_disable_flag = false;
899 
900  if (serial_object == NULL)
901  {
902  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
903  error = er_errid ();
904  goto update_auto_increment_error;
905  }
906 
907  free_and_init (serial_name);
908  return NO_ERROR;
909 
910 update_auto_increment_error:
911  if (serial_name)
912  {
913  free_and_init (serial_name);
914  }
915 
916  if (au_disable_flag == true)
917  {
918  AU_ENABLE (save);
919  }
920 
921  /* if dbt_finish_object() succeeded, it would never come here, so we just check if obj_tmpl and clear it. */
922  if (obj_tmpl != NULL)
923  {
924  dbt_abort_object (obj_tmpl);
925  }
926 
927  return (error);
928 }
929 
930 /*
931  * do_reset_auto_increment_serial() -
932  * return: Error code
933  * serial_obj(in/out):
934  */
935 int
936 do_reset_auto_increment_serial (MOP serial_obj)
937 {
938  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
939  DB_OBJECT *const serial_object = serial_obj;
940  DB_OBJECT *edit_serial_object = NULL;
941  DB_OTMPL *obj_tmpl = NULL;
942  DB_VALUE start_value;
943  DB_VALUE started_flag;
944 
945  if (serial_object == NULL)
946  {
947  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
948  }
949 
950  db_make_null (&start_value);
951  db_make_null (&started_flag);
952 
953  error_code = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_MIN_VAL, &start_value);
954  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
955  {
956  goto error_exit;
957  }
958 
959  obj_tmpl = dbt_edit_object (serial_object);
960  if (obj_tmpl == NULL)
961  {
962  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
963  error_code = er_errid ();
964  goto error_exit;
965  }
966 
967  error_code = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CURRENT_VAL, &start_value);
968  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
969  {
970  goto error_exit;
971  }
972 
973  db_make_int (&started_flag, 0);
974  error_code = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_STARTED, &started_flag);
975  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
976  {
977  goto error_exit;
978  }
979 
980  edit_serial_object = dbt_finish_object (obj_tmpl);
981  if (edit_serial_object == NULL)
982  {
983  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
984  error_code = er_errid ();
985  goto error_exit;
986  }
987 
988  assert (edit_serial_object == serial_object);
989  obj_tmpl = NULL;
990 
991  error_code = locator_flush_instance (edit_serial_object);
992  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
993  {
994  goto error_exit;
995  }
996 
997  db_value_clear (&start_value);
998  db_value_clear (&started_flag);
999 
1000  return error_code;
1001 
1002 error_exit:
1003 
1004  /* We don't need to check return value of dbt_finish_object() since if it succeeded, it would never come here. */
1005  if (obj_tmpl != NULL)
1006  {
1007  dbt_abort_object (obj_tmpl);
1008  }
1009 
1010  db_value_clear (&start_value);
1011  db_value_clear (&started_flag);
1012 
1013  return error_code;
1014 }
1015 
1016 
1017 /*
1018  * do_change_auto_increment_serial() -
1019  * return: Error code
1020  * serial_obj(in/out):
1021  */
1022 int
1023 do_change_auto_increment_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * const parser, MOP serial_obj, PT_NODE * node_new_val)
1024 {
1025  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1026  DB_OBJECT *const serial_object = serial_obj;
1027  DB_OBJECT *edit_serial_object = NULL;
1028  DB_OTMPL *obj_tmpl = NULL;
1029 
1030  DB_VALUE max_val;
1031  DB_VALUE started;
1032  DB_VALUE new_val;
1033  DB_VALUE cmp_result;
1034  DB_VALUE *pval = NULL;
1035  DB_DATA_STATUS data_status;
1036 
1037 
1038  int cmp;
1039 
1040 
1041  /*
1042  * 1. obtain NUMERIC value from node_new_val
1043  * 2. obtain max value of the serial.
1044  * 3. if the new value is greater than max, throw an error
1045  * 4. reset the serial: started = 0, cur = min = new cur;
1046  */
1047 
1048 
1049  if (serial_object == NULL)
1050  {
1051  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
1052  }
1053 
1054  db_make_null (&max_val);
1055  db_make_null (&new_val);
1056  db_make_null (&started);
1057  db_make_int (&cmp_result, 0);
1058 
1059 
1060  /* create a NUMERIC value in new_val */
1061  db_value_domain_init (&new_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1062  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, node_new_val);
1063  if (pval == NULL)
1064  {
1065  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1066  error_code = er_errid ();
1067  goto error_exit;
1068  }
1069 
1070  error_code = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &new_val, &data_status);
1071  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1072  {
1073  goto error_exit;
1074  }
1075 
1076 
1077  /* get the serial's max from db. */
1078  error_code = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_MAX_VAL, &max_val);
1079  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1080  {
1081  goto error_exit;
1082  }
1083 
1084 
1085  /* The new value must be lower than the max value */
1086  error_code = numeric_db_value_compare (&new_val, &max_val, &cmp_result);
1087  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1088  {
1089  goto error_exit;
1090  }
1091 
1092  cmp = db_get_int (&cmp_result);
1093  if (cmp >= 0)
1094  {
1095  error_code = ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_NEWVAL_MUST_LT_MAXVAL;
1096  ERROR0 (error_code, ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_NEWVAL_MUST_LT_MAXVAL);
1097  goto error_exit;
1098  }
1099 
1100  /*
1101  * RESET serial: min = new_val; cur = new_val; started = 0 */
1102 
1103  obj_tmpl = dbt_edit_object (serial_object);
1104  if (obj_tmpl == NULL)
1105  {
1106  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1107  error_code = er_errid ();
1108  goto error_exit;
1109  }
1110 
1111  error_code = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CURRENT_VAL, &new_val);
1112  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1113  {
1114  goto error_exit;
1115  }
1116 
1117  error_code = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_MIN_VAL, &new_val);
1118  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1119  {
1120  goto error_exit;
1121  }
1122 
1123  db_make_int (&started, 0);
1124  error_code = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_STARTED, &started);
1125  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1126  {
1127  goto error_exit;
1128  }
1129 
1130  edit_serial_object = dbt_finish_object (obj_tmpl);
1131  if (edit_serial_object == NULL)
1132  {
1133  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1134  error_code = er_errid ();
1135  goto error_exit;
1136  }
1137 
1138  assert (edit_serial_object == serial_object);
1139  obj_tmpl = NULL;
1140 
1141  error_code = locator_flush_instance (edit_serial_object);
1142  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1143  {
1144  goto error_exit;
1145  }
1146 
1147  goto normal_exit;
1148 
1149 
1150 error_exit:
1151 
1152  if (obj_tmpl != NULL)
1153  {
1154  dbt_abort_object (obj_tmpl);
1155  }
1156 
1157 normal_exit:
1158 
1159  db_value_clear (&max_val);
1160  db_value_clear (&new_val);
1161  db_value_clear (&started);
1162  db_value_clear (&cmp_result);
1163 
1164  return error_code;
1165 }
1166 
1167 
1168 /*
1169  * do_get_serial_obj_id() -
1170  * return: serial object
1171  * serial_obj_id(out):
1172  * serial_class_mop(in):
1173  * serial_name(in):
1174  *
1175  * Note:
1176  */
1177 MOP
1178 do_get_serial_obj_id (DB_IDENTIFIER * serial_obj_id, DB_OBJECT * serial_class_mop, const char *serial_name)
1179 {
1180  DB_OBJECT *mop;
1181  DB_VALUE val;
1182  DB_IDENTIFIER *db_id;
1183  char *p;
1184  size_t serial_name_size;
1185  int save;
1186 
1187  OID_SET_NULL (serial_obj_id);
1188 
1189  if (serial_class_mop == NULL || serial_name == NULL)
1190  {
1191  return NULL;
1192  }
1193 
1194  serial_name_size = intl_identifier_lower_string_size (serial_name);
1195  p = (char *) malloc (serial_name_size + 1);
1196  if (p == NULL)
1197  {
1198  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (serial_name_size + 1));
1199  return NULL;
1200  }
1201 
1202  intl_identifier_lower (serial_name, p);
1203  db_make_string (&val, p);
1204 
1205  AU_DISABLE (save);
1206  mop = db_find_unique (serial_class_mop, SERIAL_ATTR_NAME, &val);
1207  AU_ENABLE (save);
1208 
1209  if (mop == NULL)
1210  {
1211  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1212 
1213  if (er_errid () == ER_OBJ_OBJECT_NOT_FOUND)
1214  {
1215  er_clear ();
1216  }
1217  }
1218  else
1219  {
1220  db_id = ws_identifier (mop);
1221 
1222  if (db_id != NULL)
1223  {
1224  *serial_obj_id = *db_id;
1225  }
1226  else
1227  {
1228  mop = NULL;
1229  }
1230  }
1231 
1232  pr_clear_value (&val);
1233  free_and_init (p);
1234 
1235  return mop;
1236 }

1238 /*
1239  * do_get_serial_cached_num() -
1240  * return: Error code
1241  * cached_num(out) :
1242  * serial_obj(in) :
1243  *
1244  * Note:
1245  */
1246 int
1247 do_get_serial_cached_num (int *cached_num, MOP serial_obj)
1248 {
1249  DB_VALUE cached_num_val;
1250  int error;
1251 
1252  error = db_get (serial_obj, SERIAL_ATTR_CACHED_NUM, &cached_num_val);
1253  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1254  {
1255  return error;
1256  }
1257 
1258  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&cached_num_val) == DB_TYPE_INTEGER);
1259 
1260  *cached_num = db_get_int (&cached_num_val);
1261 
1262  return NO_ERROR;
1263 }
1264 
1265 /*
1266  * do_create_serial() -
1267  * return: Error code
1268  * parser(in): Parser context
1269  * statement(in):
1270  *
1271  * Note:
1272  */
1273 int
1274 do_create_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
1275 {
1276  DB_OBJECT *serial_class = NULL, *serial_object = NULL;
1277  MOP serial_mop;
1278  DB_IDENTIFIER serial_obj_id;
1279  DB_VALUE value, *pval = NULL;
1280 
1281  char *name = NULL;
1282  PT_NODE *start_val_node;
1283  PT_NODE *inc_val_node;
1284  PT_NODE *max_val_node;
1285  PT_NODE *min_val_node;
1286  PT_NODE *cached_num_node;
1287 
1288  DB_VALUE zero, e37, under_e36;
1289  DB_VALUE start_val, inc_val, max_val, min_val, cached_num_val;
1290  DB_VALUE cmp_result;
1291  DB_VALUE result_val;
1292  DB_VALUE tmp_val, tmp_val2;
1293  DB_VALUE abs_inc_val, range_val;
1294 
1295  int min_val_msgid = 0;
1296  int max_val_msgid = 0;
1297  int start_val_msgid = 0;
1298  int inc_val_msgid = 0;
1299  int ret_msg_id = 0;
1300  SERIAL_INVARIANT invariants[MAX_SERIAL_INVARIANT];
1301  int ninvars = 0;
1302  unsigned char num[DB_NUMERIC_BUF_SIZE];
1303  int inc_val_flag = 0, cyclic;
1304  int cached_num;
1305  DB_DATA_STATUS data_stat;
1306  int error = NO_ERROR;
1307  int save;
1308  bool au_disable_flag = false;
1309  char *p = NULL;
1310  size_t name_size;
1311  const char *comment = NULL;
1312 
1313  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
1314 
1315  db_make_null (&value);
1316  db_make_null (&zero);
1317  db_make_null (&e37);
1318  db_make_null (&under_e36);
1319  db_make_null (&start_val);
1320  db_make_null (&inc_val);
1321  db_make_null (&max_val);
1322  db_make_null (&min_val);
1323  db_make_null (&abs_inc_val);
1324  db_make_null (&range_val);
1325 
1326  /*
1327  * find db_serial_class
1328  */
1329  serial_class = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
1330  if (serial_class == NULL)
1331  {
1332  error = ER_QPROC_DB_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
1333  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
1334  goto end;
1335  }
1336 
1337  /*
1338  * lookup if serial object name already exists?
1339  */
1340 
1341  name = (char *) PT_NODE_SR_NAME (statement);
1342  name_size = intl_identifier_lower_string_size (name);
1343  p = (char *) malloc (name_size + 1);
1344  if (p == NULL)
1345  {
1346  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
1347  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, (name_size + 1));
1348  goto end;
1349  }
1350  intl_identifier_lower (name, p);
1351 
1352  serial_mop = do_get_serial_obj_id (&serial_obj_id, serial_class, p);
1353  if (serial_mop != NULL)
1354  {
1355  error = ER_QPROC_SERIAL_ALREADY_EXIST;
1356  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, name);
1357  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_ALREADY_EXIST, name);
1358  goto end;
1359  }
1360 
1361  /* get all values as string */
1362  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("0", 1, INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &zero);
1363  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("10000000000000000000000000000000000000", DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION,
1364  INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &e37);
1365  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("-1000000000000000000000000000000000000", DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION,
1366  INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &under_e36);
1367  db_make_int (&cmp_result, 0);
1368 
1369  start_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_START_VAL (statement);
1370  inc_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_INCREMENT_VAL (statement);
1371  min_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_MIN_VAL (statement);
1372  max_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_MAX_VAL (statement);
1373 
1374  /* increment_val */
1375  db_value_domain_init (&inc_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1376  if (inc_val_node != NULL)
1377  {
1378  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, inc_val_node);
1379  if (pval == NULL)
1380  {
1381  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1382  error = er_errid ();
1383  goto end;
1384  }
1385 
1386  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &inc_val, &data_stat);
1387  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1388  {
1389  goto end;
1390  }
1391  pval = NULL;
1392 
1393  /* check if increment value is 0 */
1394  error = numeric_db_value_compare (&inc_val, &zero, &cmp_result);
1395  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1396  {
1397  goto end;
1398  }
1399 
1400  inc_val_flag = db_get_int (&cmp_result);
1401  if (inc_val_flag == 0)
1402  {
1403  error = ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE;
1404  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_INC_VAL_ZERO, 0);
1405  goto end;
1406  }
1407  inc_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_INC_VAL_INVALID;
1408  }
1409  else
1410  {
1411  /* inc_val = 1; */
1412  db_make_int (&value, 1);
1413  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &inc_val, &data_stat);
1414  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1415  {
1416  goto end;
1417  }
1418 
1419  inc_val_flag = +1;
1420  }
1421 
1422  /* start_val 1 */
1423  db_value_domain_init (&start_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1424  if (start_val_node != NULL)
1425  {
1426  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, start_val_node);
1427  if (pval == NULL)
1428  {
1429  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1430  error = er_errid ();
1431  goto end;
1432  }
1433  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &start_val, &data_stat);
1434  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1435  {
1436  goto end;
1437  }
1438  pval = NULL;
1439  start_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID;
1440  }
1441 
1442  db_value_domain_init (&min_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1443  /*
1444  * min_val comes from several sources, it can be one of them:
1445  * 1. user input
1446  * 2. start_val
1447  * 3. 1
1448  * 4. -e36
1449  * min_val_msgid is the proper message id. it's for error message generation
1450  * when min_val violates some invariants.
1451  * if min_val is 1 or -e36, min_val_msgid is set to 0 (default value) because
1452  * constants can't be the reason which violate invariants.
1453  * if min_val is from user input, min_val_msgid is set to
1454  * MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_INVALID.
1455  * if min_val is from start_val, min_val_msgid is set to
1456  * MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID.
1457  */
1458  if (min_val_node != NULL)
1459  {
1460  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, min_val_node);
1461  if (pval == NULL)
1462  {
1463  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1464  error = er_errid ();
1465  goto end;
1466  }
1467 
1468  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &min_val, &data_stat);
1469  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1470  {
1471  goto end;
1472  }
1473  pval = NULL;
1474  min_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_INVALID;
1475  }
1476  else
1477  {
1478  if (inc_val_flag > 0)
1479  {
1480  if (start_val_node != NULL)
1481  {
1482  db_value_clone (&start_val, &min_val);
1483  min_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID;
1484  }
1485  else
1486  {
1487  /* min_val = 1; */
1488  db_make_int (&value, 1);
1489  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &min_val, &data_stat);
1490  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1491  {
1492  goto end;
1493  }
1494  }
1495  }
1496  else
1497  {
1498  /* min_val = - 1.0e36; */
1499  db_value_clone (&under_e36, &min_val);
1500  }
1501  }
1502 
1503  /* max_val */
1504  db_value_domain_init (&max_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1505 
1506  if (max_val_node != NULL)
1507  {
1508  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, max_val_node);
1509  if (pval == NULL)
1510  {
1511  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
1512  error = er_errid ();
1513  goto end;
1514  }
1515 
1516  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &max_val, &data_stat);
1517  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1518  {
1519  goto end;
1520  }
1521  pval = NULL;
1522  max_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_INVALID;
1523  }
1524  else
1525  {
1526  if (inc_val_flag > 0)
1527  {
1528  /* max_val = 1.0e37; */
1529  db_value_clone (&e37, &max_val);
1530  }
1531  else
1532  {
1533  if (start_val_node != NULL)
1534  {
1535  /* max_val = start_val */
1536  db_value_clone (&start_val, &max_val);
1537  max_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID;
1538  }
1539  else
1540  {
1541  /* max_val = -1; */
1542  db_make_int (&value, -1);
1543  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &max_val, &data_stat);
1544  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1545  {
1546  goto end;
1547  }
1548  }
1549  }
1550  }
1551 
1552  /* start_val 2 */
1553  if (start_val_node == NULL)
1554  {
1555  pr_clear_value (&start_val);
1556  if (inc_val_flag > 0)
1557  {
1558  /* start_val = min_val; */
1559  db_value_clone (&min_val, &start_val);
1560  start_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_INVALID;
1561  }
1562  else
1563  {
1564  /* start_val = max_val; */
1565  db_value_clone (&max_val, &start_val);
1566  start_val_msgid = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_INVALID;
1567  }
1568  }
1569 
1570 
1571  /* cyclic */
1572  cyclic = PT_NODE_SR_CYCLIC (statement);
1573 
1574  /*
1575  * check values
1576  * min_val start_val max_val
1577  * |--^--^--^--o--^--^--^--^---|
1578  * <--> inc_val
1579  */
1580 
1581  /*
1582  * the following invariants must hold:
1583  * min_val >= under_e36
1584  * max_val <= e37
1585  * min_val < max_val
1586  * min_val <= start_val
1587  * max_val >= start_val
1588  * inc_val != zero
1589  * abs(inc_val) <= (max_val - min_val)
1590  */
1591 
1592  /*
1593  * invariant for min_val >= under_e36.
1594  * if min_val_msgid == MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID,
1595  * that means the value of min_val is from start_val, if the invariant
1596  * is voilated, start_val invalid error message should be displayed
1597  * instead of min_val underflow. the val2_msgid is 0 because under_e36
1598  * cannot be the reason which voilates the invariant.
1599  */
1600  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], min_val, under_e36, PT_GE,
1601  ((min_val_msgid == MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID)
1602  ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID : MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_UNDERFLOW),
1603  0, ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW);
1604 
1605  /*
1606  * invariant for max_val <= e37. Like the above invariant, if
1607  * max_val_msgid == MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID,
1608  * start_val invalid error message should be displayed if the invariant
1609  * is voilated.
1610  */
1611  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], max_val, e37, PT_LE,
1612  ((max_val_msgid == MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID)
1613  ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID : MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_OVERFLOW),
1614  0, ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW);
1615 
1616  /* invariant for min_val < max_val. */
1617  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], min_val, max_val, PT_LT, min_val_msgid, max_val_msgid,
1618  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
1619 
1620  /* invariant for min_val <= start_val */
1621  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], min_val, start_val, PT_LE, min_val_msgid, start_val_msgid,
1622  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
1623 
1624  /* invariant for max_val >= start_val */
1625  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], max_val, start_val, PT_GE, max_val_msgid, start_val_msgid,
1626  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
1627 
1628  /* invariant for inc_val != zero */
1629  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], inc_val, zero, PT_NE, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_INC_VAL_ZERO, 0,
1630  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
1631 
1632  /*
1633  * invariant for abs(inc_val) <= (max_val - min_val).
1634  * if this invariant is voilated, inc_val, min_val or max_val should be
1635  * responsible for it. If max_val_msgid == 0, which means max_val is
1636  * initialized from a constant, not inputted by user, in this case, we don't
1637  * expect max_val should be responsible for the violation.
1638  */
1639  numeric_db_value_sub (&max_val, &min_val, &range_val);
1640  db_abs_dbval (&abs_inc_val, &inc_val);
1641  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], abs_inc_val, range_val, PT_LE, inc_val_msgid,
1642  (max_val_msgid == 0) ? min_val_msgid : max_val_msgid, ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
1643 
1644 
1645  /* cached num */
1646  cached_num_node = PT_NODE_SR_CACHED_NUM_VAL (statement);
1647  if (cached_num_node != NULL)
1648  {
1649  assert (cached_num_node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER);
1650 
1651  cached_num = cached_num_node->info.value.data_value.i;
1652 
1653  /* result_val = ABS(CEIL((max_val - min_val) / inc_val)) */
1654  error = numeric_db_value_sub (&max_val, &min_val, &tmp_val);
1655  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1656  {
1657  goto end;
1658  }
1659  error = numeric_db_value_div (&tmp_val, &inc_val, &tmp_val2);
1660  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1661  {
1662  goto end;
1663  }
1664  error = db_abs_dbval (&tmp_val, &tmp_val2);
1665  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1666  {
1667  goto end;
1668  }
1669  error = db_ceil_dbval (&result_val, &tmp_val);
1670  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1671  {
1672  goto end;
1673  }
1674 
1675  pr_clear_value (&tmp_val);
1676  pr_clear_value (&tmp_val2);
1677 
1678  numeric_coerce_int_to_num (cached_num, num);
1679  db_make_numeric (&cached_num_val, num, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1680 
1681  /*
1682  * must holds: cached_num_val <= result_val
1683  * invariant for cached_num_val <= ABS(CEIL((max_val - min_val) / inc_val))
1684  */
1685  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], cached_num_val, result_val, PT_LE,
1686  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_CACHED_NUM_INVALID_RANGE, 0, ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
1687  }
1688  else
1689  {
1690  cached_num = 0;
1691  }
1692 
1693  assert (ninvars <= MAX_SERIAL_INVARIANT);
1694  error = check_serial_invariants (invariants, ninvars, &ret_msg_id);
1695 
1696  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1697  {
1698  if (error == ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW || error == ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE)
1699  {
1700  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, ret_msg_id, 0);
1701  }
1702  goto end;
1703  }
1704 
1705  /* comment */
1706  if (statement->info.serial.comment != NULL)
1707  {
1708  assert (statement->info.serial.comment->node_type == PT_VALUE);
1709  comment = (char *) PT_VALUE_GET_BYTES (statement->info.serial.comment);
1710  if (comment == NULL)
1711  {
1712  error = (er_errid () != NO_ERROR) ? er_errid () : ER_FAILED;
1713  goto end;
1714  }
1715  }
1716 
1717  /* now create serial object which is insert into db_serial */
1718  AU_DISABLE (save);
1719  au_disable_flag = true;
1720 
1721  error =
1722  do_create_serial_internal (&serial_object, p, &start_val, &inc_val, &min_val, &max_val, cyclic, cached_num, 0,
1723  comment, NULL, NULL);
1724 
1725  AU_ENABLE (save);
1726  au_disable_flag = false;
1727 
1728  if (error < 0)
1729  {
1730  goto end;
1731  }
1732 
1733 
1734  if (p != NULL)
1735  {
1736  free_and_init (p);
1737  }
1738 
1739  return NO_ERROR;
1740 
1741 end:
1742  if (au_disable_flag == true)
1743  {
1744  AU_ENABLE (save);
1745  }
1746 
1747  if (p != NULL)
1748  {
1749  free_and_init (p);
1750  }
1751 
1752  return error;
1753 }
1754 
1755 /*
1756  * do_create_auto_increment_serial() -
1757  * return: Error code
1758  * parser(in): Parser context
1759  * serial_object(out):
1760  * class_name(in):
1761  * att(in):
1762  *
1763  * Note:
1764  */
1765 int
1766 do_create_auto_increment_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, MOP * serial_object, const char *class_name, PT_NODE * att)
1767 {
1768  MOP serial_class = NULL, serial_mop;
1769  DB_IDENTIFIER serial_obj_id;
1770  DB_DATA_STATUS data_stat;
1771  int error = NO_ERROR;
1772  PT_NODE *auto_increment_node, *start_val_node, *inc_val_node;
1773  PT_NODE *dtyp;
1774  char *att_name = NULL, *serial_name = NULL;
1775  DB_VALUE start_val, inc_val, max_val, min_val;
1776  DB_VALUE zero, value, *pval = NULL;
1777  DB_VALUE cmp_result;
1778  int i;
1779  DB_VALUE e38;
1780  char *p, num[DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 1];
1781  char att_downcase_name[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
1782  size_t name_len;
1783 
1784  db_make_null (&e38);
1785  db_make_null (&value);
1786  db_make_null (&zero);
1787  db_make_null (&cmp_result);
1788  db_make_null (&start_val);
1789  db_make_null (&inc_val);
1790  db_make_null (&max_val);
1791  db_make_null (&min_val);
1792 
1793  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("0", 1, INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &zero);
1794  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("99999999999999999999999999999999999999", DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION,
1795  INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &e38);
1796 
1797  assert_release (att->info.attr_def.auto_increment != NULL);
1798  auto_increment_node = att->info.attr_def.auto_increment;
1799  if (auto_increment_node == NULL)
1800  {
1801  goto end;
1802  }
1803 
1804  /*
1805  * find db_serial
1806  */
1807  serial_class = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
1808  if (serial_class == NULL)
1809  {
1810  error = ER_QPROC_DB_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
1811  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
1812  goto end;
1813  }
1814 
1815  att_name = (char *) (att->info.attr_def.attr_name->alias_print
1816  ? att->info.attr_def.attr_name->alias_print : att->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original);
1817 
1818  sm_downcase_name (att_name, att_downcase_name, SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH);
1819  att_name = att_downcase_name;
1820 
1821  /* serial_name : <class_name>_ai_<att_name> */
1822  name_len = (strlen (class_name) + strlen (att_name) + AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_NAME_EXTRA_LENGTH + 1);
1823  serial_name = (char *) malloc (name_len);
1824  if (serial_name == NULL)
1825  {
1826  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
1827  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, name_len);
1828  goto end;
1829  }
1830 
1831  SET_AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_NAME (serial_name, class_name, att_name);
1832 
1833  serial_mop = do_get_serial_obj_id (&serial_obj_id, serial_class, serial_name);
1834  if (serial_mop != NULL)
1835  {
1836  error = ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_ALREADY_EXIST;
1837  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
1838  goto end;
1839  }
1840 
1841  error = er_errid ();
1842  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1843  {
1844  goto end;
1845  }
1846 
1847  start_val_node = auto_increment_node->info.auto_increment.start_val;
1848  inc_val_node = auto_increment_node->info.auto_increment.increment_val;
1849 
1850  /* increment_val */
1851  db_value_domain_init (&inc_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1852 
1853  if (inc_val_node != NULL)
1854  {
1855  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, inc_val_node);
1856  if (pval == NULL)
1857  {
1858  error = ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE;
1859  goto end;
1860  }
1861 
1862  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &inc_val, &data_stat);
1863  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1864  {
1865  goto end;
1866  }
1867 
1868  pval = NULL;
1869 
1870  /* check increment value */
1871  error = numeric_db_value_compare (&inc_val, &zero, &cmp_result);
1872  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1873  {
1874  goto end;
1875  }
1876 
1877  if (db_get_int (&cmp_result) <= 0)
1878  {
1879  error = ER_INCREMENT_VALUE_CANNOT_BE_ZERO;
1880  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
1881  goto end;
1882  }
1883  }
1884  else
1885  {
1886  /* set to 1 */
1887  db_make_int (&value, 1);
1888  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &inc_val, &data_stat);
1889  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1890  {
1891  goto end;
1892  }
1893  }
1894 
1895  /* start_val */
1896  db_value_domain_init (&start_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1897  if (start_val_node != NULL)
1898  {
1899  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, start_val_node);
1900  if (pval == NULL)
1901  {
1902  error = ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE;
1903  goto end;
1904  }
1905  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &start_val, &data_stat);
1906  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1907  {
1908  goto end;
1909  }
1910  pval = NULL;
1911  }
1912  else
1913  {
1914  /* set to 1 */
1915  db_make_int (&value, 1);
1916  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &start_val, &data_stat);
1917  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1918  {
1919  goto end;
1920  }
1921  }
1922 
1923  /* min value = start_val */
1924  db_value_clone (&start_val, &min_val);
1925 
1926  /* max value - depends on att's domain */
1927  db_value_domain_init (&max_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
1928 
1929  dtyp = att->data_type;
1930  switch (att->type_enum)
1931  {
1932  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1933  db_make_int (&value, DB_INT32_MAX);
1934  break;
1935  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1936  db_make_bigint (&value, DB_BIGINT_MAX);
1937  break;
1938  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1939  db_make_int (&value, DB_INT16_MAX);
1940  break;
1941  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1942  memset (num, '\0', DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 1);
1943  for (i = 0, p = num; i < dtyp->info.data_type.precision; i++, p++)
1944  {
1945  *p = '9';
1946  }
1947 
1948  *p = '\0';
1949 
1950  (void) numeric_coerce_string_to_num (num, dtyp->info.data_type.precision, INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &value);
1951  break;
1952  default:
1953  /* max numeric */
1954  db_value_clone (&e38, &value);
1955  }
1956 
1957  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &max_val, &data_stat);
1958  if (error != NO_ERROR)
1959  {
1960  goto end;
1961  }
1962 
1963  /* check (start_val < max_val) */
1964  if (tp_value_compare (&start_val, &max_val, 1, 0) != DB_LT)
1965  {
1966  error = ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_STARTVAL_MUST_LT_MAXVAL;
1967  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
1968  goto end;
1969  }
1970 
1971  /* create auto increment serial object */
1972  error =
1973  do_create_serial_internal (serial_object, serial_name, &start_val, &inc_val, &min_val, &max_val, 0, 0, 0, NULL,
1974  class_name, att_name);
1975  if (error < 0)
1976  {
1977  goto end;
1978  }
1979 
1980  pr_clear_value (&e38);
1981  pr_clear_value (&value);
1982  pr_clear_value (&zero);
1983  pr_clear_value (&cmp_result);
1984  pr_clear_value (&start_val);
1985  pr_clear_value (&inc_val);
1986  pr_clear_value (&max_val);
1987  pr_clear_value (&min_val);
1988 
1989  free_and_init (serial_name);
1990 
1991  return NO_ERROR;
1992 
1993 end:
1994  pr_clear_value (&e38);
1995  pr_clear_value (&value);
1996  pr_clear_value (&zero);
1997  pr_clear_value (&cmp_result);
1998  pr_clear_value (&start_val);
1999  pr_clear_value (&inc_val);
2000  pr_clear_value (&max_val);
2001  pr_clear_value (&min_val);
2002 
2003  if (serial_name)
2004  free_and_init (serial_name);
2005 
2006  return error;
2007 }
2008 
2009 /*
2010  * do_update_maxvalue_of_auto_increment_serial()
2011  * usage: update max_val of serial object
2012  * return: Error code
2013  * parser(in): Parser context
2014  * serial_object(out):
2015  * class_name(in):
2016  * att(in):
2017  *
2018  * Note:
2019  */
2020 int
2021 do_update_maxvalue_of_auto_increment_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, MOP * serial_object, const char *class_name,
2022  PT_NODE * att)
2023 {
2024  MOP serial_class, serial_mop;
2025  DB_OTMPL *obj_tmpl = NULL;
2026  DB_IDENTIFIER serial_obj_id;
2027  DB_DATA_STATUS data_stat;
2028  int error = NO_ERROR;
2029  PT_NODE *dtyp;
2030  char *att_name = NULL, *serial_name = NULL;
2031  DB_VALUE e38, current_val, max_val, value;
2032  int i, compare_result, save;
2033  char *p, num[DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 1];
2034  char att_downcase_name[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
2035  size_t name_len;
2036  bool au_disable_flag = false;
2037 
2038  db_make_null (&e38);
2039  db_make_null (&value);
2040  db_make_null (&current_val);
2041  db_make_null (&max_val);
2042  OID_SET_NULL (&serial_obj_id);
2043 
2044  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("99999999999999999999999999999999999999", DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION,
2045  INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &e38);
2046 
2047  assert_release (att->info.attr_def.auto_increment != NULL);
2048  assert (serial_object != NULL);
2049 
2050  /* find db_serial */
2051  serial_class = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
2052  if (serial_class == NULL)
2053  {
2054  error = ER_QPROC_DB_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
2055  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
2056  goto end;
2057  }
2058 
2059  att_name = (char *) (att->info.attr_def.attr_name->alias_print
2060  ? att->info.attr_def.attr_name->alias_print : att->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original);
2061 
2062  sm_downcase_name (att_name, att_downcase_name, SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH);
2063  att_name = att_downcase_name;
2064 
2065  /* serial_name : <class_name>_ai_<att_name> */
2066  name_len = (strlen (class_name) + strlen (att_name) + AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_NAME_EXTRA_LENGTH + 1);
2067  serial_name = (char *) malloc (name_len);
2068  if (serial_name == NULL)
2069  {
2070  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
2071  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, name_len);
2072  goto end;
2073  }
2074 
2075  SET_AUTO_INCREMENT_SERIAL_NAME (serial_name, class_name, att_name);
2076 
2077  /* get serial mop by serial name */
2078  serial_mop = do_get_serial_obj_id (&serial_obj_id, serial_class, serial_name);
2079  if (serial_mop == NULL)
2080  {
2081  error = ER_QPROC_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
2082  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, serial_name);
2083  goto end;
2084  }
2085 
2086  /*
2087  * after serial.next_value, the currect value maybe changed, but cub_cas
2088  * still hold the old value. To get the new value. we need decache it
2089  * then refetch it from server again.
2090  */
2091  assert (WS_ISDIRTY (serial_mop) == false);
2092 
2093  ws_decache (serial_mop);
2094 
2095  /* no need to get the last version for serial - actually, AU_FETCH_WRITE will get only last version, for locking */
2096  error = au_fetch_instance_force (serial_mop, NULL, AU_FETCH_WRITE, LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION);
2097  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2098  {
2099  goto end;
2100  }
2101 
2102  /* get current value */
2103  error = db_get (serial_mop, SERIAL_ATTR_CURRENT_VAL, &current_val);
2104  if (error < 0)
2105  {
2106  goto end;
2107  }
2108 
2109  /* max value - depends on att's domain */
2110  db_value_domain_init (&max_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
2111 
2112  dtyp = att->data_type;
2113  switch (att->type_enum)
2114  {
2115  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
2116  db_make_int (&value, DB_INT32_MAX);
2117  break;
2118  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
2119  db_make_bigint (&value, DB_BIGINT_MAX);
2120  break;
2121  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
2122  db_make_int (&value, DB_INT16_MAX);
2123  break;
2124  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
2125  memset (num, '\0', DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 1);
2126  for (i = 0, p = num; i < dtyp->info.data_type.precision; i++, p++)
2127  {
2128  *p = '9';
2129  }
2130 
2131  *p = '\0';
2132 
2133  (void) numeric_coerce_string_to_num (num, dtyp->info.data_type.precision, INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &value);
2134  break;
2135  default:
2136  /* max numeric */
2137  db_value_clone (&e38, &value);
2138  }
2139 
2140  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &max_val, &data_stat);
2141  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2142  {
2143  goto end;
2144  }
2145 
2146  /* check (current_val <= max_val) */
2147  compare_result = tp_value_compare (&current_val, &max_val, 1, 0);
2148  if (compare_result != DB_LT && compare_result != DB_EQ)
2149  {
2150  error = ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_STARTVAL_MUST_LT_MAXVAL;
2151  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
2152  goto end;
2153  }
2154 
2155  /* update serial object in db_serial */
2156  AU_DISABLE (save);
2157  au_disable_flag = true;
2158 
2159  obj_tmpl = dbt_edit_object (serial_mop);
2160  if (obj_tmpl == NULL)
2161  {
2162  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2163  error = er_errid ();
2164  goto end;
2165  }
2166 
2167  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_MAX_VAL, &max_val);
2168  if (error < 0)
2169  {
2170  goto end;
2171  }
2172 
2173  serial_mop = dbt_finish_object (obj_tmpl);
2174  if (serial_mop == NULL)
2175  {
2176  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2177  error = er_errid ();
2178  goto end;
2179  }
2180  else
2181  {
2182  *serial_object = serial_mop;
2183  /* obj_tmpl has been released by dbt_finish_object() */
2184  obj_tmpl = NULL;
2185  }
2186 
2187 end:
2188  if (!OID_ISNULL (&serial_obj_id))
2189  {
2190  (void) serial_decache ((OID *) (&serial_obj_id));
2191  }
2192 
2193  if (au_disable_flag == true)
2194  {
2195  AU_ENABLE (save);
2196  }
2197 
2198  pr_clear_value (&e38);
2199  pr_clear_value (&value);
2200  pr_clear_value (&current_val);
2201  pr_clear_value (&max_val);
2202 
2203  if (serial_name != NULL)
2204  {
2205  free_and_init (serial_name);
2206  }
2207 
2208  if (obj_tmpl != NULL)
2209  {
2210  dbt_abort_object (obj_tmpl);
2211  }
2212 
2213  return error;
2214 }
2215 
2216 /*
2217  * do_alter_serial() -
2218  * return: Error code
2219  * parser(in): Parser context
2220  * statement(in):
2221  *
2222  * Note:
2223  */
2224 int
2225 do_alter_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
2226 {
2227  DB_OBJECT *serial_class = NULL, *serial_object = NULL;
2228  DB_IDENTIFIER serial_obj_id;
2229  DB_OTMPL *obj_tmpl = NULL;
2230  DB_VALUE value, *pval;
2231 
2232  char *name = NULL;
2233  PT_NODE *start_val_node;
2234  PT_NODE *inc_val_node;
2235  PT_NODE *max_val_node;
2236  PT_NODE *min_val_node;
2237  PT_NODE *cached_num_node;
2238 
2239  DB_VALUE zero, e37, under_e36;
2240  DB_DATA_STATUS data_stat;
2241  DB_VALUE old_inc_val, old_max_val, old_min_val, old_cached_num;
2242  DB_VALUE current_val, start_val, cached_num_val;
2243  DB_VALUE new_inc_val, new_max_val, new_min_val;
2244  DB_VALUE cmp_result;
2245  DB_VALUE result_val;
2246  DB_VALUE class_name_val;
2247  DB_VALUE tmp_val, tmp_val2;
2248  DB_VALUE abs_inc_val, range_val;
2249  int cached_num;
2250  int ret_msg_id = 0;
2251  const char *comment = NULL;
2252 
2253  unsigned char num[DB_NUMERIC_BUF_SIZE];
2254 
2255  int new_inc_val_flag = 0, new_cyclic;
2256  int cur_val_change, inc_val_change, max_val_change, min_val_change, cyclic_change, cached_num_change;
2257 
2258  int error = NO_ERROR;
2259  int save;
2260  bool au_disable_flag = false;
2261 
2262  SERIAL_INVARIANT invariants[MAX_SERIAL_INVARIANT];
2263  int ninvars = 0;
2264 
2265  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
2266 
2267  db_make_null (&value);
2268  db_make_null (&zero);
2269  db_make_null (&e37);
2270  db_make_null (&under_e36);
2271  db_make_null (&old_inc_val);
2272  db_make_null (&old_max_val);
2273  db_make_null (&old_min_val);
2274  db_make_null (&new_inc_val);
2275  db_make_null (&new_max_val);
2276  db_make_null (&new_min_val);
2277  db_make_null (&current_val);
2278  db_make_null (&start_val);
2279  db_make_null (&class_name_val);
2280  db_make_null (&abs_inc_val);
2281  db_make_null (&range_val);
2282  OID_SET_NULL (&serial_obj_id);
2283 
2284 
2285  /*
2286  * find db_serial_class
2287  */
2288  serial_class = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
2289  if (serial_class == NULL)
2290  {
2291  error = ER_QPROC_DB_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
2292  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
2293  goto end;
2294  }
2295 
2296  /*
2297  * lookup if serial object name already exists?
2298  */
2299 
2300  name = (char *) PT_NODE_SR_NAME (statement);
2301 
2302  serial_object = do_get_serial_obj_id (&serial_obj_id, serial_class, name);
2303  if (serial_object == NULL)
2304  {
2305  error = ER_QPROC_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
2306  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, name);
2307  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RT_SERIAL_NOT_DEFINED, name);
2308  goto end;
2309  }
2310 
2311  /*
2312  * after serial.next_value, the currect value maybe changed, but cub_cas
2313  * still hold the old value. To get the new value. we need decache it
2314  * then refetch it from server again.
2315  */
2316  assert (WS_ISDIRTY (serial_object) == false);
2317 
2318  ws_decache (serial_object);
2319 
2320  /* no need to get the last version for serial - actually, AU_FETCH_WRITE will get only last version, for locking */
2321  error = au_fetch_instance_force (serial_object, NULL, AU_FETCH_WRITE, LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION);
2322  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2323  {
2324  goto end;
2325  }
2326 
2327  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_CLASS_NAME, &class_name_val);
2328  if (error < 0)
2329  {
2330  goto end;
2331  }
2332 
2333  /*
2334  * check if user is creator or DBA
2335  */
2336  error = au_check_serial_authorization (serial_object);
2337  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2338  {
2339  if (error == ER_QPROC_CANNOT_UPDATE_SERIAL)
2340  {
2341  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RT_SERIAL_ALTER_NOT_ALLOWED, 0);
2342  }
2343  goto end;
2344  }
2345 
2346  /* get old values */
2347  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_CURRENT_VAL, &current_val);
2348  if (error < 0)
2349  {
2350  goto end;
2351  }
2352 
2353  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_INCREMENT_VAL, &old_inc_val);
2354  if (error < 0)
2355  {
2356  goto end;
2357  }
2358 
2359  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_MAX_VAL, &old_max_val);
2360  if (error < 0)
2361  goto end;
2362 
2363  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_MIN_VAL, &old_min_val);
2364  if (error < 0)
2365  {
2366  goto end;
2367  }
2368 
2369  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_CACHED_NUM, &old_cached_num);
2370  if (error < 0)
2371  {
2372  cached_num = 0;
2373  }
2374  else
2375  {
2376  cached_num = db_get_int (&old_cached_num);
2377  }
2378 
2379  /* Now, get new values from node */
2380 
2381  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("0", 1, INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &zero);
2382  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("10000000000000000000000000000000000000", DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION,
2383  INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &e37);
2384  numeric_coerce_string_to_num ("-1000000000000000000000000000000000000", DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION,
2385  INTL_CODESET_ISO88591, &under_e36);
2386  db_make_int (&cmp_result, 0);
2387 
2388  db_value_domain_init (&new_inc_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
2389  inc_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_INCREMENT_VAL (statement);
2390  if (inc_val_node != NULL)
2391  {
2392  inc_val_change = 1;
2393  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, inc_val_node);
2394  if (pval == NULL)
2395  {
2396  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2397  error = er_errid ();
2398  goto end;
2399  }
2400  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &new_inc_val, &data_stat);
2401  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2402  {
2403  goto end;
2404  }
2405  pval = NULL;
2406 
2407  error = numeric_db_value_compare (&new_inc_val, &zero, &cmp_result);
2408  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2409  {
2410  goto end;
2411  }
2412 
2413  new_inc_val_flag = db_get_int (&cmp_result);
2414  /* new_inc_val == 0 */
2415  if (new_inc_val_flag == 0)
2416  {
2417  error = ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE;
2418  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_INC_VAL_ZERO, 0);
2419  goto end;
2420  }
2421  }
2422  else
2423  {
2424  inc_val_change = 0;
2425  /* new_inc_val = old_inc_val; */
2426  db_value_clone (&old_inc_val, &new_inc_val);
2427  error = numeric_db_value_compare (&new_inc_val, &zero, &cmp_result);
2428  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2429  {
2430  goto end;
2431  }
2432 
2433  new_inc_val_flag = db_get_int (&cmp_result);
2434  }
2435 
2436  /* start_val */
2437  db_value_domain_init (&start_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
2438  start_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_START_VAL (statement);
2439  if (start_val_node != NULL)
2440  {
2441  cur_val_change = 1;
2442  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, start_val_node);
2443  if (pval == NULL)
2444  {
2445  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2446  error = er_errid ();
2447  goto end;
2448  }
2449  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &start_val, &data_stat);
2450  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2451  {
2452  goto end;
2453  }
2454  pval = NULL;
2455  }
2456  else
2457  {
2458  cur_val_change = 0;
2459  db_value_clone (&current_val, &start_val);
2460  }
2461 
2462  /* max_val */
2463  db_value_domain_init (&new_max_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
2464  max_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_MAX_VAL (statement);
2465  if (max_val_node != NULL)
2466  {
2467  max_val_change = 1;
2468  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, max_val_node);
2469  if (pval == NULL)
2470  {
2471  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2472  error = er_errid ();
2473  goto end;
2474  }
2475  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &new_max_val, &data_stat);
2476  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2477  {
2478  goto end;
2479  }
2480  pval = NULL;
2481  }
2482  else
2483  {
2484  if (PT_NODE_SR_NO_MAX (statement) == 1)
2485  {
2486  max_val_change = 1;
2487  if (new_inc_val_flag > 0)
2488  {
2489  /* new_max_val = 1.0e37; */
2490  db_value_clone (&e37, &new_max_val);
2491  }
2492  else
2493  {
2494  /* new_max_val = -1; */
2495  db_make_int (&value, -1);
2496  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &new_max_val, &data_stat);
2497  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2498  {
2499  goto end;
2500  }
2501  }
2502  }
2503  else
2504  {
2505  max_val_change = 0;
2506  /* new_max_val = old_max_val; */
2507  db_value_clone (&old_max_val, &new_max_val);
2508  }
2509  }
2510 
2511  /* min_val */
2512  db_value_domain_init (&new_min_val, DB_TYPE_NUMERIC, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
2513  min_val_node = PT_NODE_SR_MIN_VAL (statement);
2514  if (min_val_node != NULL)
2515  {
2516  min_val_change = 1;
2517  pval = pt_value_to_db (parser, min_val_node);
2518  if (pval == NULL)
2519  {
2520  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2521  error = er_errid ();
2522  goto end;
2523  }
2524  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (pval, &new_min_val, &data_stat);
2525  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2526  {
2527  goto end;
2528  }
2529  pval = NULL;
2530  }
2531  else
2532  {
2533  if (PT_NODE_SR_NO_MIN (statement) == 1)
2534  {
2535  min_val_change = 1;
2536 
2537  if (new_inc_val_flag > 0)
2538  {
2539  /* new_min_val = 1; */
2540  db_make_int (&value, 1);
2541  error = numeric_db_value_coerce_to_num (&value, &new_min_val, &data_stat);
2542  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2543  {
2544  goto end;
2545  }
2546  }
2547  else
2548  {
2549  /* new_min_val = - 1.0e36; */
2550  db_value_clone (&under_e36, &new_min_val);
2551  }
2552  }
2553  else
2554  {
2555  min_val_change = 0;
2556  /* new_min_val = old_min_val; */
2557  db_value_clone (&old_min_val, &new_min_val);
2558  }
2559  }
2560 
2561 
2562  /* cyclic */
2563  new_cyclic = PT_NODE_SR_CYCLIC (statement);
2564  if ((new_cyclic == 1) || (PT_NODE_SR_NO_CYCLIC (statement) == 1))
2565  {
2566  cyclic_change = 1;
2567  }
2568  else
2569  {
2570  cyclic_change = 0;
2571  }
2572 
2573 
2574  /*
2575  * check values
2576  * min_val start_val max_val
2577  * |--^--^--^--o--^--^--^--^---|
2578  * <--> inc_val
2579  */
2580 
2581  /* invariant for min_val >= under_e36. */
2582  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], new_min_val, under_e36, PT_GE,
2583  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_UNDERFLOW, 0, ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW);
2584 
2585  /* invariant for max_val <= e37. */
2586  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], new_max_val, e37, PT_LE, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_OVERFLOW,
2587  0, ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW);
2588 
2589  /* invariant for min_val < max_val. */
2590  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], new_min_val, new_max_val, PT_LT,
2591  (min_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_INVALID : 0,
2592  (max_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_INVALID : 0, ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
2593 
2594  /* invariant for min_val <= start_val */
2595  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], new_min_val, start_val, PT_LE,
2596  (min_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_INVALID : 0,
2597  (cur_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID : 0,
2598  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
2599 
2600  /* invariant for max_val >= start_val */
2601  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], new_max_val, start_val, PT_GE,
2602  (max_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_INVALID : 0,
2603  (cur_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_START_VAL_INVALID : 0,
2604  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
2605 
2606  /* invariant for inc_val != zero */
2607  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], new_inc_val, zero, PT_NE, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_INC_VAL_ZERO, 0,
2608  ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
2609 
2610  /* invariant for abs(inc_val) <= (max_val - min_val). */
2611  numeric_db_value_sub (&new_max_val, &new_min_val, &range_val);
2612  db_abs_dbval (&abs_inc_val, &new_inc_val);
2613  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], abs_inc_val, range_val, PT_LE,
2614  (inc_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_INC_VAL_INVALID : 0,
2615  (max_val_change) ? MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MAX_VAL_INVALID :
2616  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_MIN_VAL_INVALID, ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
2617 
2618 
2619  /* cached num */
2620  cached_num_node = PT_NODE_SR_CACHED_NUM_VAL (statement);
2621  if (cached_num_node != NULL)
2622  {
2623  assert (cached_num_node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER);
2624 
2625  cached_num_change = 1;
2626  cached_num = cached_num_node->info.value.data_value.i;
2627 
2628  /* result_val = ABS(CEIL((max_val - min_val) / inc_val)) */
2629  error = numeric_db_value_sub (&new_max_val, &new_min_val, &tmp_val);
2630  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2631  {
2632  goto end;
2633  }
2634  error = numeric_db_value_div (&tmp_val, &new_inc_val, &tmp_val2);
2635  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2636  {
2637  goto end;
2638  }
2639  error = db_abs_dbval (&tmp_val, &tmp_val2);
2640  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2641  {
2642  goto end;
2643  }
2644  error = db_ceil_dbval (&result_val, &tmp_val);
2645  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2646  {
2647  goto end;
2648  }
2649  pr_clear_value (&tmp_val);
2650  pr_clear_value (&tmp_val2);
2651 
2652  numeric_coerce_int_to_num (cached_num, num);
2653  db_make_numeric (&cached_num_val, num, DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION, 0);
2654 
2655  /*
2656  * must holds: cached_num_val <= result_val
2657  * invariant for cached_num_val <= ABS(CEIL((max_val - min_val) / inc_val))
2658  */
2659  initialize_serial_invariant (&invariants[ninvars++], cached_num_val, result_val, PT_LE,
2660  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SERIAL_CACHED_NUM_INVALID_RANGE, 0, ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE);
2661  }
2662  else
2663  {
2664  if (PT_NODE_SR_NO_CACHE (statement) == 1)
2665  {
2666  cached_num_change = 1;
2667  cached_num = 0;
2668  }
2669  else
2670  {
2671  cached_num_change = 0;
2672  }
2673  }
2674 
2675  assert (ninvars <= MAX_SERIAL_INVARIANT);
2676  error = check_serial_invariants (invariants, ninvars, &ret_msg_id);
2677 
2678  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2679  {
2680  if (error == ER_QPROC_SERIAL_RANGE_OVERFLOW || error == ER_INVALID_SERIAL_VALUE)
2681  {
2682  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, ret_msg_id, 0);
2683  }
2684  goto end;
2685  }
2686  /* now update serial object in db_serial */
2687  AU_DISABLE (save);
2688  au_disable_flag = true;
2689 
2690  obj_tmpl = dbt_edit_object (serial_object);
2691  if (obj_tmpl == NULL)
2692  {
2693  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2694  error = er_errid ();
2695  goto end;
2696  }
2697 
2698  /* current_val */
2699  if (cur_val_change)
2700  {
2701  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CURRENT_VAL, &start_val);
2702  if (error < 0)
2703  {
2704  goto end;
2705  }
2706  /* reset started flag because current_val changed */
2707  db_make_int (&value, 0);
2708  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_STARTED, &value);
2709  if (error < 0)
2710  {
2711  goto end;
2712  }
2713  pr_clear_value (&value);
2714  }
2715 
2716  /* increment_val */
2717  if (inc_val_change)
2718  {
2719  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_INCREMENT_VAL, &new_inc_val);
2720  if (error < 0)
2721  {
2722  goto end;
2723  }
2724  }
2725 
2726  /* max_val */
2727  if (max_val_change)
2728  {
2729  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_MAX_VAL, &new_max_val);
2730  if (error < 0)
2731  {
2732  goto end;
2733  }
2734  }
2735 
2736  /* min_val */
2737  if (min_val_change)
2738  {
2739  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_MIN_VAL, &new_min_val);
2740  if (error < 0)
2741  {
2742  goto end;
2743  }
2744  }
2745 
2746  /* cyclic */
2747  if (cyclic_change)
2748  {
2749  db_make_int (&value, new_cyclic);
2750  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CYCLIC, &value);
2751  if (error < 0)
2752  {
2753  goto end;
2754  }
2755  pr_clear_value (&value);
2756  }
2757 
2758  /* cached num */
2759  if (cached_num_change)
2760  {
2761 
2762  /* Here we need class_name and att_name to see if this serial is auto_increment. Cause for an auto_increment
2763  * serial, it is not allowed to change the cached_num for it. */
2764  if (!DB_IS_NULL (&class_name_val))
2765  {
2766 
2767  error = MSGCAT_RUNTIME_INVALID_AUTO_INCREMENT_ALTER;
2768 
2769  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, error, name);
2770 
2771  goto end;
2772 
2773  }
2774 
2775  db_make_int (&value, cached_num);
2776  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_CACHED_NUM, &value);
2777  if (error < 0)
2778  {
2779  goto end;
2780  }
2781  pr_clear_value (&value);
2782  }
2783 
2784  /* comment */
2785  if (statement->info.serial.comment != NULL)
2786  {
2787  assert (statement->info.serial.comment->node_type == PT_VALUE);
2788  comment = (char *) PT_VALUE_GET_BYTES (statement->info.serial.comment);
2789  db_make_string_by_const_str (&value, comment);
2790  error = dbt_put_internal (obj_tmpl, SERIAL_ATTR_COMMENT, &value);
2791  pr_clear_value (&value);
2792  if (error < 0)
2793  {
2794  goto end;
2795  }
2796  }
2797 
2798  serial_object = dbt_finish_object (obj_tmpl);
2799  if (serial_object == NULL)
2800  {
2801  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2802  error = er_errid ();
2803  goto end;
2804  }
2805 
2806  /* obj_tmpl has been released by dbt_finish_object */
2807  obj_tmpl = NULL;
2808 
2809 end:
2810  if (!OID_ISNULL (&serial_obj_id))
2811  {
2812  (void) serial_decache ((OID *) (&serial_obj_id));
2813  }
2814 
2815  if (au_disable_flag == true)
2816  {
2817  AU_ENABLE (save);
2818  }
2819 
2820  if (obj_tmpl != NULL)
2821  {
2822  dbt_abort_object (obj_tmpl);
2823  }
2824 
2825  return error;
2826 }
2827 
2828 /*
2829  * do_drop_serial() -
2830  * return: Error code
2831  * parser(in): Parser context
2832  * statement(in):
2833  *
2834  * Note:
2835  */
2836 int
2837 do_drop_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
2838 {
2839  DB_OBJECT *serial_class = NULL, *serial_object = NULL;
2840  DB_IDENTIFIER serial_obj_id;
2841  DB_VALUE class_name_val;
2842  char *name;
2843  int error = NO_ERROR;
2844  int save;
2845  bool au_disable_flag = false;
2846 
2847  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
2848 
2849  db_make_null (&class_name_val);
2850  OID_SET_NULL (&serial_obj_id);
2851 
2852  serial_class = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
2853  if (serial_class == NULL)
2854  {
2855  error = ER_QPROC_DB_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
2856  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
2857  goto end;
2858  }
2859 
2860  name = (char *) PT_NODE_SR_NAME (statement);
2861 
2862  serial_object = do_get_serial_obj_id (&serial_obj_id, serial_class, name);
2863  if (serial_object == NULL)
2864  {
2865  if (statement->info.serial.if_exists)
2866  {
2867  return NO_ERROR;
2868  }
2869  error = ER_QPROC_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND;
2870  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, name);
2871  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RT_SERIAL_NOT_DEFINED, name);
2872  goto end;
2873  }
2874 
2875  error = db_get (serial_object, SERIAL_ATTR_CLASS_NAME, &class_name_val);
2876  if (error < 0)
2877  {
2878  goto end;
2879  }
2880 
2881  if (!DB_IS_NULL (&class_name_val))
2882  {
2883  error = ER_QPROC_CANNOT_UPDATE_SERIAL;
2884  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_SERIAL_IS_AUTO_INCREMENT_OBJ, name);
2885  pr_clear_value (&class_name_val);
2886  goto end;
2887  }
2888 
2889  /*
2890  * check if user is creator or DBA
2891  */
2892  error = au_check_serial_authorization (serial_object);
2893  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2894  {
2895  if (error == ER_QPROC_CANNOT_UPDATE_SERIAL)
2896  {
2897  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RT_SERIAL_ALTER_NOT_ALLOWED, 0);
2898  }
2899  goto end;
2900  }
2901 
2902  AU_DISABLE (save);
2903  au_disable_flag = true;
2904 
2905  error = db_drop (serial_object);
2906  if (error < 0)
2907  {
2908  goto end;
2909  }
2910 
2911 end:
2912  if (!OID_ISNULL (&serial_obj_id))
2913  {
2914  (void) serial_decache (&serial_obj_id);
2915  }
2916 
2917  if (au_disable_flag == true)
2918  {
2919  AU_ENABLE (save);
2920  }
2921 
2922  return error;
2923 }

2928  * Function Group:
2929  * Entry functions to do execute

2931  */
2932 
2933 #define ER_PT_UNKNOWN_STATEMENT ER_GENERIC_ERROR
