2938 /*
2939  * do_statement() -
2940  * return: Error code
2941  * parser(in): Parser context
2942  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
2943  *
2944  * Note: Side effects can exist at the statement, especially schema information
2945  */
2946 int
2947 do_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
2948 {
2949  int error = NO_ERROR;
2950  bool need_stmt_replication = false;
2951  int suppress_repl_error = NO_ERROR;
2952  LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE read_fetch_instance_version;
2953 
2954  /* save old read fetch instance version */
2955  read_fetch_instance_version = TM_TRAN_READ_FETCH_VERSION ();
2956  /* If it is an internally created statement, set its host variable info again to search host variables at parent
2957  * parser */
2958  SET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT (parser);
2959 
2960  if (statement)
2961  {
2962  /* skip ddl execution in case of parameter or opt. level */
2963  if (pt_is_ddl_statement (statement) != 0)
2964  {
2965  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_BLOCK_DDL_STATEMENT))
2966  {
2967  const char *cp = statement->sql_user_text;
2968  if (cp == NULL)
2969  {
2970  cp = statement->alias_print;
2971  }
2972 
2973  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BLOCK_DDL_STMT, 1, cp ? cp : "unknown");
2974  error = ER_BLOCK_DDL_STMT;
2975  goto end;
2976  }
2977 
2978  /* if QO_PARAM_LEVEL indicate no execution, just return */
2979  if (qo_need_skip_execution ())
2980  {
2981  error = NO_ERROR;
2982  goto end;
2983  }
2984  }
2985 
2986  /* for the subset of nodes which represent top level statements, process them. For any other node, return an
2987  * error. */
2988 
2989  /* disable data replication log for schema replication log types in HA mode */
2990  if (!HA_DISABLED () && is_stmt_based_repl_type (statement))
2991  {
2992  need_stmt_replication = true;
2993 
2994  /* since we are going to suppress writing replication logs, we need to flush all dirty objects to server not
2995  * to lose them. */
2996  error = locator_all_flush ();
2997  if (error != NO_ERROR)
2998  {
2999  /* restore execution flag */
3000  goto end;
3001  }
3002 
3003  suppress_repl_error = db_set_suppress_repl_on_transaction (true);
3004  if (suppress_repl_error != NO_ERROR)
3005  {
3006  goto end;
3007  }
3008  }
3009 
3010  switch (statement->node_type)
3011  {
3012  case PT_GET_TRIGGER:
3013  case PT_GET_XACTION:
3014  case PT_SAVEPOINT:
3015  case PT_PREPARE_TO_COMMIT:
3016  case PT_COMMIT_WORK:
3017  case PT_ROLLBACK_WORK:
3018  case PT_SCOPE:
3019  case PT_INSERT:
3020  case PT_SELECT:
3021  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
3022  case PT_INTERSECTION:
3023  case PT_UNION:
3024  case PT_EVALUATE:
3025  case PT_GET_STATS:
3026  case PT_GET_OPT_LVL:
3027  case PT_SET_OPT_LVL:
3028  case PT_SET_SYS_PARAMS:
3029  case PT_DO:
3030  case PT_EXECUTE_PREPARE:
3031  case PT_VACUUM:
3032  case PT_QUERY_TRACE:
3033  case PT_KILL_STMT:
3034  db_set_read_fetch_instance_version (LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION);
3035  break;
3036 
3037  case PT_EXECUTE_TRIGGER:
3038  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
3039  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
3040  case PT_CREATE_SERIAL:
3041  case PT_CREATE_TRIGGER:
3042  case PT_CREATE_USER:
3043  case PT_ALTER:
3044  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
3045  case PT_ALTER_SERIAL:
3046  case PT_ALTER_TRIGGER:
3047  case PT_ALTER_USER:
3048  case PT_DROP:
3049  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
3050  case PT_DROP_SERIAL:
3051  case PT_DROP_TRIGGER:
3052  case PT_DROP_USER:
3053  case PT_DROP_VARIABLE:
3054  case PT_RENAME:
3055  case PT_RENAME_TRIGGER:
3056  case PT_SET_TRIGGER:
3057  case PT_REMOVE_TRIGGER:
3058  case PT_GRANT:
3059  case PT_REVOKE:
3060  case PT_2PC_ATTACH:
3061  case PT_SET_XACTION:
3062  case PT_DELETE:
3063  case PT_UPDATE:
3064  case PT_MERGE:
3065  case PT_METHOD_CALL:
3066  case PT_UPDATE_STATS:
3067  case PT_CREATE_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3068  case PT_ALTER_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3069  case PT_DROP_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3070  case PT_TRUNCATE:
3071  case PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES:
3072  case PT_DROP_SESSION_VARIABLES:
3073  case PT_SET_NAMES:
3074  case PT_SET_TIMEZONE:
3075

3082  break;

3100 
3101  case PT_COMMIT_WORK:

3108  do_create_entity);
3109  break;
3110 
3111  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
3112  error = do_create_index (parser, statement);
3113  break;
3114 
3115  case PT_EVALUATE:
3116  error = do_evaluate (parser, statement);
3117  break;
3118 
3119  case PT_SCOPE:
3120  error = do_scope (parser, statement);
3121  break;
3122 
3123  case PT_DELETE:
3124  error = do_check_delete_trigger (parser, statement, do_delete);
3125  break;
3126 
3127  case PT_DROP:
3128  error = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement,
3129  /* statement->info.drop. internal_stmts, */
3130  do_drop);

3141  case PT_DROP_VARIABLE:

3146  error = do_grant (parser, statement);

3303 
3304  default:
3305  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_PT_UNKNOWN_STATEMENT, 1, statement->node_type);
3306  break;
3307  }
3308 
3309  /* enable data replication log */
3310  if (need_stmt_replication)
3311  {
3312  int repl_error = NO_ERROR;
3313 
3314  /* before enable data replication log, we have to flush all dirty objects to server not to write redundant
3315  * data replication logs for DDLs */
3316  if (error >= 0)
3317  {
3318  repl_error = locator_all_flush ();
3319  }
3320 
3321  suppress_repl_error = db_set_suppress_repl_on_transaction (false);
3322 
3323  /* write schema replication log */
3324  if (error >= 0 && repl_error == NO_ERROR && suppress_repl_error == NO_ERROR)
3325  {
3326  repl_error = do_replicate_statement (parser, statement);
3327  }
3328 
3329  if (repl_error != NO_ERROR)
3330  {
3331  error = repl_error;
3332  }
3333  }
3334  }
3335 
3336 end:
3337  /* restore old read fetch instance version */
3338  db_set_read_fetch_instance_version (read_fetch_instance_version);
3339  /* There may be parse tree fragments that were collected during the execution of the statement that should be freed
3340  * now. */
3341  pt_free_orphans (parser);
3342 
3343  /* During query execution, if current transaction was rollbacked by the system, abort transaction on client side
3344  * also. */
3345  if (er_errid () == ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
3346  {
3347  error = ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED;
3348  }
3349 
3350  if (error == ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED || tran_was_latest_query_aborted ())
3351  {
3352  (void) tran_abort_only_client (false);
3353  }
3354 
3355  RESET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT (parser);
3356 
3357  if (error == ER_FAILED)
3358  {
3359  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
3360  error = er_errid ();
3361  if (error == NO_ERROR)
3362  {
3363  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
3364  }
3365  }
3366  return error;
3367 }
3368 
3369 /*
3370  * do_prepare_statement() - Prepare a given statement for execution
3371  * return: Error code
3372  * parser(in): Parser context
3373  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
3374  *
3375  * Note:
3376  * PREPARE includes query optimization and plan generation (XASL) for the SQL
3377  * statement. EXECUTE means requesting the server to execute the given XASL.
3378  *
3379  * Some type of statement is not necessary or not able to do PREPARE stage.
3380  * They can or must be EXECUTEd directly without PREPARE. For those types of
3381  * statements, this function will return NO_ERROR.
3382  */
3383 int
3384 do_prepare_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
3385 {
3386  int err = NO_ERROR;
3387 
3388  init_compile_context (parser);
3389 
3390  switch (statement->node_type)
3391  {
3392  case PT_DELETE:
3393  err = do_prepare_delete (parser, statement, NULL);
3394  break;
3395  case PT_INSERT:
3396  err = do_prepare_insert (parser, statement);
3397  break;
3398  case PT_UPDATE:
3399  err = do_prepare_update (parser, statement);
3400  break;
3401  case PT_MERGE:
3402  err = do_prepare_merge (parser, statement);
3403  break;
3404  case PT_SELECT:
3405  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
3406  case PT_INTERSECTION:
3407  case PT_UNION:
3408  err = do_prepare_select (parser, statement);
3409  break;
3410  case PT_EXECUTE_PREPARE:
3411  err = do_prepare_session_statement (parser, statement);
3412  break;
3413  default:
3414  /* there are no actions for other types of statements */
3415  break;
3416  }
3417 
3418  return ((err == ER_FAILED && (err = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_GENERIC_ERROR : err);
3419 } /* do_prepare_statement() */
3420 
3421 /*
3422  * do_execute_statement() - Execute a prepared statement
3423  * return: Error code
3424  * parser(in): Parser context
3425  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
3426  *
3427  * Note:
3428  * The statement should be PREPAREd before to EXECUTE. But, some type of
3429  * statement will be EXECUTEd directly without PREPARE stage because we can
3430  * decide the fact that they should be executed using query plan (XASL)
3431  * at the time of execution stage.
3432  */
3433 int
3434 do_execute_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
3435 {
3436  int err = NO_ERROR;
3437  bool need_stmt_based_repl = false;
3438  int suppress_repl_error;
3439  LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE read_fetch_instance_version;
3440 
3441  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
3442  /* save old read fetch instance version */
3443  read_fetch_instance_version = TM_TRAN_READ_FETCH_VERSION ();
3444 
3445  /* If it is an internally created statement, set its host variable info again to search host variables at parent
3446  * parser */
3447  SET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT (parser);
3448 
3449  /* skip ddl execution in case of parameter or opt. level */
3450  if (pt_is_ddl_statement (statement) != 0)
3451  {
3452  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_BLOCK_DDL_STATEMENT))
3453  {
3454  const char *cp = statement->sql_user_text;
3455  if (cp == NULL)
3456  {
3457  cp = statement->alias_print;
3458  }
3459 
3460  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BLOCK_DDL_STMT, 1, cp ? cp : "unknown");
3461  err = ER_BLOCK_DDL_STMT;
3462  goto end;
3463  }
3464 
3465  /* if QO_PARAM_LEVEL indicate no execution, just return */
3466  if (qo_need_skip_execution ())
3467  {
3468  err = NO_ERROR;
3469  goto end;
3470  }
3471  }
3472 
3473  /* for the subset of nodes which represent top level statements, process them; for any other node, return an error */
3474 
3475  /* disable data replication log for schema replication log types in HA mode */
3476  if (!HA_DISABLED () && is_stmt_based_repl_type (statement))
3477  {
3478  need_stmt_based_repl = true;
3479 
3480  /* since we are going to suppress writing replication logs, we need to flush all dirty objects to server not to
3481  * lose them */
3482  err = locator_all_flush ();
3483  if (err != NO_ERROR)
3484  {
3485  goto end;
3486  }
3487 
3488  suppress_repl_error = db_set_suppress_repl_on_transaction (true);
3489  if (suppress_repl_error != NO_ERROR)
3490  {
3491  goto end;
3492  }
3493  }
3494 
3495  switch (statement->node_type)
3496  {
3497  case PT_GET_TRIGGER:
3498  case PT_GET_XACTION:
3499  case PT_SAVEPOINT:
3500  case PT_PREPARE_TO_COMMIT:
3501  case PT_COMMIT_WORK:
3502  case PT_ROLLBACK_WORK:
3503  case PT_SCOPE:
3504  case PT_INSERT:
3505  case PT_SELECT:
3506  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
3507  case PT_INTERSECTION:
3508  case PT_UNION:
3509  case PT_EVALUATE:
3510  case PT_GET_STATS:
3511  case PT_GET_OPT_LVL:
3512  case PT_SET_OPT_LVL:
3513  case PT_SET_SYS_PARAMS:
3514  case PT_DO:
3515  case PT_EXECUTE_PREPARE:
3516  case PT_VACUUM:
3517  case PT_QUERY_TRACE:
3518  case PT_KILL_STMT:
3519 
3520  db_set_read_fetch_instance_version (LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION);
3521  break;
3522 
3523  case PT_EXECUTE_TRIGGER:
3524  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
3525  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
3526  case PT_CREATE_SERIAL:
3527  case PT_CREATE_TRIGGER:
3528  case PT_CREATE_USER:
3529  case PT_ALTER:
3530  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
3531  case PT_ALTER_SERIAL:
3532  case PT_ALTER_TRIGGER:
3533  case PT_ALTER_USER:
3534  case PT_DROP:
3535  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
3536  case PT_DROP_SERIAL:
3537  case PT_DROP_TRIGGER:
3538  case PT_DROP_USER:
3539  case PT_DROP_VARIABLE:
3540  case PT_RENAME:
3541  case PT_RENAME_TRIGGER:
3542  case PT_SET_TRIGGER:
3543  case PT_REMOVE_TRIGGER:
3544  case PT_GRANT:
3545  case PT_REVOKE:
3546  case PT_2PC_ATTACH:
3547  case PT_SET_XACTION:
3548  case PT_DELETE:
3549  case PT_UPDATE:
3550  case PT_MERGE:
3551  case PT_METHOD_CALL:
3552  case PT_UPDATE_STATS:
3553  case PT_CREATE_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3554  case PT_ALTER_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3555  case PT_DROP_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3556  case PT_TRUNCATE:
3557  case PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES:
3558  case PT_DROP_SESSION_VARIABLES:
3559  case PT_SET_NAMES:
3560  case PT_SET_TIMEZONE:
3561  /* Need to get dirty version when fetch the instance. That's because we are in an update command. */
3562  db_set_read_fetch_instance_version (LC_FETCH_DIRTY_VERSION);
3563  break;
3564 
3565  default:
3566  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_PT_UNKNOWN_STATEMENT, 1, statement->node_type);
3567  break;
3568  }
3569 
3570  switch (statement->node_type)
3571  {
3572  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
3573  /* err = do_create_entity(parser, statement); */
3574  /* execute internal statements before and after do_create_entity() */
3575  err = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement,
3576  /* statement->info.create_entity. internal_stmts, */
3577  do_create_entity);
3578  break;
3579  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
3580  err = do_create_index (parser, statement);
3581  break;
3582  case PT_CREATE_SERIAL:
3583  err = do_create_serial (parser, statement);
3584  break;
3585  case PT_CREATE_TRIGGER:
3586  err = do_create_trigger (parser, statement);
3587  break;
3588  case PT_CREATE_USER:
3589  err = do_create_user (parser, statement);
3590  break;
3591  case PT_ALTER:
3592  /* err = do_alter(parser, statement); */
3593  /* execute internal statements before and after do_alter() */
3594  err = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement,
3595  /* statement->info.alter. internal_stmts, */ do_alter);
3596  break;
3597  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
3598  err = do_alter_index (parser, statement);
3599  break;
3600  case PT_ALTER_SERIAL:
3601  err = do_alter_serial (parser, statement);
3602  break;
3603  case PT_ALTER_TRIGGER:
3604  err = do_alter_trigger (parser, statement);
3605  break;
3606  case PT_ALTER_USER:
3607  err = do_alter_user (parser, statement);
3608  break;
3609  case PT_DROP:
3610  /* err = do_drop(parser, statement); */
3611  /* execute internal statements before and after do_drop() */
3612  err = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement,
3613  /* statement->info.drop.internal_stmts, */
3614  do_drop);
3615  break;
3616  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
3617  err = do_drop_index (parser, statement);
3618  break;
3619  case PT_DROP_SERIAL:
3620  err = do_drop_serial (parser, statement);
3621  break;
3622  case PT_DROP_TRIGGER:
3623  err = do_drop_trigger (parser, statement);
3624  break;
3625  case PT_DROP_USER:
3626  err = do_drop_user (parser, statement);
3627  break;
3628  case PT_DROP_VARIABLE:
3629  err = do_drop_variable (parser, statement);
3630  break;
3631  case PT_RENAME:
3632  err = do_rename (parser, statement);
3633  break;
3634  case PT_RENAME_TRIGGER:
3635  err = do_rename_trigger (parser, statement);
3636  break;
3637  case PT_SET_TRIGGER:
3638  err = do_set_trigger (parser, statement);
3639  break;
3640  case PT_GET_TRIGGER:
3641  err = do_get_trigger (parser, statement);
3642  break;
3643  case PT_EXECUTE_TRIGGER:
3644  err = do_execute_trigger (parser, statement);
3645  break;
3646  case PT_REMOVE_TRIGGER:
3647  err = do_remove_trigger (parser, statement);
3648  break;
3649  case PT_GRANT:
3650  err = do_grant (parser, statement);
3651  break;
3652  case PT_REVOKE:
3653  err = do_revoke (parser, statement);
3654  break;
3655  case PT_2PC_ATTACH:
3656  err = do_attach (parser, statement);
3657  break;
3658  case PT_GET_XACTION:
3659  err = do_get_xaction (parser, statement);
3660  break;
3661  case PT_SET_XACTION:
3662  err = do_set_xaction (parser, statement);
3663  break;
3664  case PT_SAVEPOINT:
3665  err = do_savepoint (parser, statement);
3666  break;
3667  case PT_PREPARE_TO_COMMIT:
3668  err = do_prepare_to_commit (parser, statement);
3669  break;
3670  case PT_COMMIT_WORK:
3671  err = do_commit (parser, statement);
3672  break;
3673  case PT_ROLLBACK_WORK:
3674  err = do_rollback (parser, statement);
3675  break;
3676  case PT_SCOPE:
3677  err = do_scope (parser, statement);
3678  break;
3679  case PT_DELETE:
3680  err = do_check_delete_trigger (parser, statement, do_execute_delete);
3681  break;
3682  case PT_INSERT:
3683  err = do_check_insert_trigger (parser, statement, do_execute_insert);
3684  break;
3685  case PT_UPDATE:
3686  err = do_check_update_trigger (parser, statement, do_execute_update);
3687  break;
3688  case PT_MERGE:
3689  err = do_check_merge_trigger (parser, statement, do_execute_merge);
3690  break;
3691  case PT_SELECT:
3692  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
3693  case PT_INTERSECTION:
3694  case PT_UNION:
3695  err = do_execute_select (parser, statement);
3696  break;
3697  case PT_EVALUATE:
3698  err = do_evaluate (parser, statement);
3699  break;
3700  case PT_METHOD_CALL:
3701  err = do_call_method (parser, statement);
3702  break;
3703  case PT_GET_STATS:
3704  err = do_get_stats (parser, statement);
3705  break;
3706  case PT_UPDATE_STATS:
3707  err = do_update_stats (parser, statement);
3708  break;
3709  case PT_GET_OPT_LVL:
3710  err = do_get_optimization_param (parser, statement);
3711  break;
3712  case PT_SET_OPT_LVL:
3713  err = do_set_optimization_param (parser, statement);
3714  break;
3715  case PT_SET_SYS_PARAMS:
3716  err = do_set_sys_params (parser, statement);
3717  break;
3718  case PT_CREATE_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3719  err = jsp_create_stored_procedure (parser, statement);
3720  break;
3721  case PT_ALTER_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3722  err = jsp_alter_stored_procedure (parser, statement);
3723  break;
3724  case PT_DROP_STORED_PROCEDURE:
3725  err = jsp_drop_stored_procedure (parser, statement);
3726  break;
3727  case PT_TRUNCATE:
3728  err = do_truncate (parser, statement);
3729  break;
3730  case PT_DO:
3731  err = do_execute_do (parser, statement);
3732  break;
3733  case PT_EXECUTE_PREPARE:
3734  err = do_execute_session_statement (parser, statement);
3735  break;
3736  case PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES:
3737  err = do_set_session_variables (parser, statement);
3738  break;
3739  case PT_DROP_SESSION_VARIABLES:
3740  err = do_drop_session_variables (parser, statement);
3741  break;
3742  case PT_SET_NAMES:
3743  err = do_set_names (parser, statement);
3744  break;
3745  case PT_VACUUM:
3746  err = do_vacuum (parser, statement);
3747  break;
3748  case PT_QUERY_TRACE:
3749  err = do_set_query_trace (parser, statement);
3750  break;
3751  case PT_KILL_STMT:
3752  err = do_kill (parser, statement);
3753  break;

3755  err = do_set_timezone (parser, statement);
3756  break;
3757  default:
3758  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_PT_UNKNOWN_STATEMENT, 1, statement->node_type);
3759  break;
3760  }
3761 
3762  /* enable data replication log */
3763  if (need_stmt_based_repl)
3764  {
3765  int repl_error = NO_ERROR;
3766 
3767  /* before enable data replication log we have to flush all dirty objects to server not to write redundant data
3768  * replication logs for DDLs and SBR statements */
3769  if (err >= 0)
3770  {
3771  repl_error = locator_all_flush ();
3772  }
3773 
3774  suppress_repl_error = db_set_suppress_repl_on_transaction (false);
3775 
3776  /* write schema replication log */
3777  if (err >= 0 && repl_error == NO_ERROR && suppress_repl_error == NO_ERROR)
3778  {
3779  repl_error = do_replicate_statement (parser, statement);
3780  }
3781 
3782  if (repl_error != NO_ERROR)
3783  {
3784  err = repl_error;
3785  }
3786  }
3787 
3788 end:
3789 
3790  /* restore old read fetch instance version */
3791  db_set_read_fetch_instance_version (read_fetch_instance_version);
3792 
3793  /* There may be parse tree fragments that were collected during the execution of the statement that should be freed
3794  * now. */
3795  pt_free_orphans (parser);
3796 
3797  /* During query execution, if current transaction was rollbacked by the system, abort transaction on client side
3798  * also. */
3799  if (er_errid () == ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
3800  {
3801  err = ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED;
3802  }
3803 
3804  if (err == ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED || tran_was_latest_query_aborted ())
3805  {
3806  (void) tran_abort_only_client (false);
3807  }
3808 
3809  RESET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT (parser);
3810 
3811  return ((err == ER_FAILED && (err = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_GENERIC_ERROR : err);
3812 } /* do_execute_statement() */
3813 
3814 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3815 /*
3816  * do_statements() - Execute a prepared statement
3817  * return: Error code
3818  * parser(in): Parser context
3819  * statement_list(in): Parse tree of a statement list
3820  *
3821  * Note: Side effects can exist at the statement list
3822  */
3823 int
3824 do_statements (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement_list)
3825 {
3826  int error = 0;
3827  PT_NODE *statement;
3828 
3829  /* for each of a list of statement nodes, process it. */
3830  for (statement = statement_list; statement != NULL; statement = statement->next)
3831  {
3832  do_Trigger_involved = false;
3833  error = do_statement (parser, statement);
3834  do_Trigger_involved = false;
3835  if (error)
3836  {
3837  break;
3838  }
3839  }
3840 
3841  return error;
3842 }
3843 #endif
3844 
3845 /*
3846  * do_check_internal_statements() -
3847  * return: Error code
3848  * parser(in): Parser context
3849  * statement_list(in): Parse tree of a statement
3850  * internal_stmt_list(in):
3851  * do_func(in):
3852  *
3853  * Note:
3854  * Do savepoint and execute statements before and after do_func()
3855  * if an error happens, rollback to the savepoint.
3856  */
3857 int
3858 do_check_internal_statements (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement,
3859  /* PT_NODE * internal_stmt_list, */
3860  PT_DO_FUNC do_func)
3861 {
3862 #if 0 /* to disable TEXT */
3863  const char *savepoint_name = UNIQUE_SAVEPOINT_EXTERNAL_STATEMENT;
3864  int error = NO_ERROR, num_rows = NO_ERROR;
3865 
3866  if (internal_stmt_list == NULL)
3867  {
3868 #endif
3869  return do_func (parser, statement);
3870 #if 0 /* to disable TEXT */
3871  }
3872  else
3873  {
3874  error = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
3875  if (error != NO_ERROR)
3876  return error;
3877 
3878  error = do_internal_statements (parser, internal_stmt_list, 0);
3879  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
3880  {
3881  /* The main statement cas use out parameters from internal statements, and the internal statements generate
3882  * the parameters at execution time. So, it need to bind the parameters again */
3883  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_bind_param_node, NULL, NULL, NULL);
3884  num_rows = error = do_func (parser, statement);
3885 #if defined(CUBRID_DEBUG)
3886  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "do_check_internal_statements : execute %s statement, %s\n", "main",
3887  parser_print_tree (parser, statement));
3888 #endif
3889  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
3890  {
3891  error = do_internal_statements (parser, internal_stmt_list, 1);
3892  }
3893  }
3894  if (error < NO_ERROR)
3895  {
3896  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
3897  return error;
3898  }
3899  return num_rows;
3900  }
3901 #endif
3902 }
3903 
3904 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3905 /*
3906  * do_internal_statements() -
3907  * return: Error code
3908  * parser(in): Parser context
3909  * internal_stmt_list(in):
3910  * phase(in):
3911  *
3912  * Note:
3913  * For input statements, find the statements to do now and
3914  * using new parser, parse, check semantics and execute these.
3915  *
3916  */
3917 int
3918 do_internal_statements (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * internal_stmt_list, const int phase)
3919 {
3920  PT_NODE *stmt_str;
3921  DB_QUERY_RESULT *query_result;
3922  DB_QUERY_ERROR query_error;
3923  PARSER_CONTEXT *save_parser;
3924  DB_OBJECT *save_user;
3925  int au_save;
3926  int error = NO_ERROR;
3927 
3928  save_user = Au_user;
3929  Au_user = Au_dba_user;
3930  AU_DISABLE (au_save);
3931 
3932  for (stmt_str = internal_stmt_list; stmt_str != NULL; stmt_str = stmt_str->next)
3933  {
3934  if ((phase == 0 && stmt_str->etc == NULL) || (phase == 1 && stmt_str->etc != NULL))
3935  {
3936  /* To get host variable info from parent parser, set the parent parser */
3937  save_parser = parent_parser;
3938  parent_parser = parser;
3939  error = db_compile_and_execute_local (stmt_str->info.value.text, &query_result, &query_error);
3940  /* restore the parent parser */
3941  parent_parser = save_parser;
3942  if (error < NO_ERROR)
3943  break;
3944  }
3945  }
3946 
3947  Au_user = save_user;
3948  AU_ENABLE (au_save);
3949 
3950  return error;
3951 }

4000 /*
4001  * do_update_stats() - Updates the statistics of a list of classes or ALL classes
4002  * return: Error code
4003  * parser(in): Parser context
4004  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a update statistics statement
4005  */
4006 int
4007 do_update_stats (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4008 {
4009  int error = NO_ERROR;
4010 
4011  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
4012 
4013  if (statement->info.update_stats.all_classes > 0)
4014  {
4015  // ALL CLASSES
4016  if (!au_is_dba_group_member (Au_user))
4017  {
4018  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_AU_DBA_ONLY, 1, "update statistics on all classes");
4019  return ER_AU_DBA_ONLY;
4020  }
4021 
4022  error = sm_update_all_statistics (statement->info.update_stats.with_fullscan
4023  ? STATS_WITH_FULLSCAN : STATS_WITH_SAMPLING);
4024  return error;
4025  }
4026  else if (statement->info.update_stats.all_classes < 0)
4027  {
4028  // CATALOG CLASSES
4029  if (!au_is_dba_group_member (Au_user))
4030  {
4031  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_AU_DBA_ONLY, 1, "update statistics on catalog classes");
4032  return ER_AU_DBA_ONLY;
4033  }
4034 
4035  error = sm_update_all_catalog_statistics (statement->info.update_stats.with_fullscan
4036  ? STATS_WITH_FULLSCAN : STATS_WITH_SAMPLING);
4037  return error;
4038  }
4039  else
4040  {
4041  // CLASS LISTS
4042 
4043  PT_NODE *cls = NULL;
4044  DB_OBJECT *class_mop;
4045 
4046  // fetch classes and check authorization
4047  for (cls = statement->info.update_stats.class_list; cls != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; cls = cls->next)
4048  {
4049  class_mop = db_find_class (cls->info.name.original);
4050  if (class_mop != NULL)
4051  {
4052  cls->info.name.db_object = class_mop;
4053  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, cls);
4054  }
4055  else
4056  {
4057  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error);
4058  return error;
4059  }
4060 
4061  error = au_check_authorization (class_mop, AU_ALTER);
4062  if (error != NO_ERROR)
4063  {
4064  // set an error since only warning was set.
4065  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_AU_ALTER_FAILURE, 0);
4066  return error;
4067  }
4068  }
4069 
4070  // update stats
4071  for (cls = statement->info.update_stats.class_list; cls != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; cls = cls->next)
4072  {
4073  class_mop = cls->info.name.db_object;
4074 
4075  error = sm_update_statistics (class_mop, (statement->info.update_stats.with_fullscan
4076  ? STATS_WITH_FULLSCAN : STATS_WITH_SAMPLING));
4077  }
4078 
4079  return error;
4080  }
4081 }

4083 /*
4084  * extract_att_name() -
4085  * return:
4086  * str(in):
4087  */
4088 static char *
4089 extract_att_name (const char *str)
4090 {
4091  char *s, *t, *att = NULL;
4092  int size;
4093 
4094  s = intl_mbs_chr (str, '(');
4095  if (s && *(++s))
4096  {
4097  t = intl_mbs_chr (s, ':');
4098  if (!t)
4099  {
4100  t = intl_mbs_chr (s, ')');
4101  }
4102  if (t && t != s)
4103  {
4104  size = CAST_STRLEN (t - s);
4105  att = (char *) malloc (size + 1);
4106  if (att)
4107  {
4108  if (intl_mbs_ncpy (att, s, size + 1) != NULL)
4109  {
4110  att[size] = '\0';
4111  }
4112  else
4113  {
4114  free_and_init (att);
4115  }
4116  }
4117  }
4118  }
4119  return att;
4120 }

4122 /*
4123  * extract_bt_idx() -
4124  * return:
4125  * str(in):
4126  */
4127 static int
4128 extract_bt_idx (const char *str)
4129 {
4130  char *s, *t;
4131  int idx = -1;
4132 
4133  t = intl_mbs_chr (str, '(');
4134  if (t && *(++t))
4135  {
4136  s = intl_mbs_chr (t, ':');
4137  if (s && s != t && *(++s))
4138  {
4139  t = intl_mbs_chr (s, ')');
4140  if (t && t != s)
4141  {
4142  idx = atoi (s);
4143  }
4144  }
4145  }
4146  return idx;
4147 }

4149 /*
4150  * make_cst_item_value() -
4151  * return: Error code
4152  * obj(in):
4153  * str(in):
4154  * db_val(in):
4155  */
4156 static int
4157 make_cst_item_value (DB_OBJECT * obj, const char *str, DB_VALUE * db_val)
4158 {
4159  CST_ITEM cst_item = { CST_UNDEFINED, "", -1, -1 };
4160  char *att_name = NULL;
4161  int bt_idx;
4162  CLASS_STATS *class_statsp = NULL;
4163  ATTR_STATS *attr_statsp = NULL;
4164  BTREE_STATS *bt_statsp = NULL;
4165  int i;
4166  int error;
4167 
4168  for (i = 0; i < (signed) DIM (cst_item_tbl); i++)
4169  {
4170  if (intl_mbs_ncasecmp (str, cst_item_tbl[i].string, strlen (cst_item_tbl[i].string)) == 0)
4171  {
4172  cst_item = cst_item_tbl[i];
4173  if (cst_item.att_id >= 0)
4174  {
4175  att_name = extract_att_name (str);
4176  if (att_name == NULL)
4177  {
4178  cst_item.item = CST_UNDEFINED;
4179  break;
4180  }
4181  cst_item.att_id = sm_att_id (obj, att_name);
4182  if (cst_item.att_id < 0)
4183  {
4184  cst_item.item = CST_UNDEFINED;
4185  break;
4186  }
4187  free_and_init (att_name);
4188  if (cst_item.bt_idx >= 0)
4189  {
4190  bt_idx = extract_bt_idx (str);
4191  if (bt_idx <= 0)
4192  {
4193  cst_item.item = CST_UNDEFINED;
4194  break;
4195  }
4196  cst_item.bt_idx = bt_idx;
4197  }
4198  }
4199  break;
4200  }
4201  }
4202  if (cst_item.item == CST_UNDEFINED)
4203  {
4204  db_make_null (db_val);
4205  error = ER_DO_UNDEFINED_CST_ITEM;
4206  er_set (ER_SYNTAX_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
4207  return error;
4208  }
4209 
4210  class_statsp = sm_get_statistics_force (obj);
4211  if (class_statsp == NULL)
4212  {
4213  db_make_null (db_val);
4214 
4215  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4216  return er_errid ();
4217  }
4218  if (cst_item.att_id >= 0)
4219  {
4220  for (i = 0; i < class_statsp->n_attrs; i++)
4221  {
4222  if (class_statsp->attr_stats[i].id == cst_item.att_id)
4223  {
4224  attr_statsp = &class_statsp->attr_stats[i];
4225  break;
4226  }
4227  }
4228  }
4229  if (attr_statsp && cst_item.bt_idx > 0 && cst_item.bt_idx <= attr_statsp->n_btstats)
4230  {
4231  for (i = 0; i < cst_item.bt_idx; i++)
4232  {
4233  ;
4234  }
4235  bt_statsp = &attr_statsp->bt_stats[i];
4236  }
4237 
4238  switch (cst_item.item)
4239  {
4240  case CST_NOBJECTS:
4241  db_make_int (db_val, class_statsp->heap_num_objects);
4242  break;
4243  case CST_NPAGES:
4244  db_make_int (db_val, class_statsp->heap_num_pages);
4245  break;
4246  case CST_NATTRIBUTES:
4247  db_make_int (db_val, class_statsp->n_attrs);
4248  break;
4249 #if 0
4250  case CST_ATTR_MIN:
4251  db_make_null (db_val); /* not support */
4252  break;
4253  case CST_ATTR_MAX:
4254  db_make_null (db_val); /* not support */
4255  break;
4256  case CST_ATTR_NINDEXES:
4257  if (!attr_statsp)
4258  {
4259  db_make_null (db_val);
4260  }
4261  else
4262  {
4263  db_make_int (db_val, attr_statsp->n_btstats);
4264  }
4265  break;
4266  case CST_BT_NLEAFS:
4267  if (!attr_statsp || !bt_statsp)
4268  {
4269  db_make_null (db_val);
4270  }
4271  else
4272  {
4273  db_make_int (db_val, bt_statsp->leafs);
4274  }
4275  break;
4276  case CST_BT_NPAGES:
4277  if (!attr_statsp || !bt_statsp)
4278  {
4279  db_make_null (db_val);
4280  }
4281  else
4282  {
4283  db_make_int (db_val, bt_statsp->pages);
4284  }
4285  break;
4286  case CST_BT_HEIGHT:
4287  if (!attr_statsp || !bt_statsp)
4288  {
4289  db_make_null (db_val);
4290  }
4291  else
4292  {
4293  db_make_int (db_val, bt_statsp->height);
4294  }
4295  break;
4296 #endif
4297  case CST_BT_NKEYS:
4298  if (!attr_statsp || !bt_statsp)
4299  {
4300  db_make_null (db_val);
4301  }
4302  else
4303  {
4304  db_make_int (db_val, bt_statsp->keys);
4305  }
4306  break;
4307  default:
4308  break;
4309  }
4310 
4311  return NO_ERROR;
4312 } /* make_cst_item_value() */

4314 /*
4315  * do_get_stats() -
4316  * return: Error code
4317  * parser(in): Parser context
4318  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a get statistics statement
4319  */
4320 int
4321 do_get_stats (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4322 {
4323  PT_NODE *cls, *arg, *into;
4324  DB_OBJECT *obj;
4325  DB_VALUE *ret_val, db_val;
4326  int error;
4327 
4328  db_make_null (&db_val);
4329 
4330  cls = statement->info.get_stats.class_;
4331  arg = statement->info.get_stats.args;
4332  into = statement->info.get_stats.into_var;
4333  if (!cls || !arg)
4334  {
4335  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4336  }
4337 
4338  obj = db_find_class (cls->info.name.original);
4339  if (!obj)
4340  {
4341  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4342  }
4343 
4344  cls->info.name.db_object = obj;
4345  (void) pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, cls);
4346 
4347  ret_val = db_value_create ();
4348  if (ret_val == NULL)
4349  {
4350  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4351  return er_errid ();
4352  }
4353 
4354  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, arg, &db_val, 1);
4355  if (pt_has_error (parser) || DB_IS_NULL (&db_val))
4356  {
4357  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4358  }
4359 
4360  error = make_cst_item_value (obj, db_get_string (&db_val), ret_val);
4361  pr_clear_value (&db_val);
4362  if (error != NO_ERROR)
4363  {
4364  return error;
4365  }
4366 
4367  statement->etc = (void *) ret_val;
4368 
4369  if (into && into->node_type == PT_NAME && into->info.name.original)
4370  {
4371  return pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into->info.name.original, db_value_copy (ret_val));
4372  }
4373 
4374  return NO_ERROR;
4375 }

4430 /*

4432  * return: Error code

4434  * statement(in): Parse tree of a commit statement
4435  *
4436  * Note:
4437  */
4438 int
4439 do_commit (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4440 {
4441  /* Row count should be reset to -1 for explicit commits (i.e: commit statements) but should not be reset in
4442  * AUTO_COMMIT mode. This is the best place to reset it for commit statements. */
4443  db_update_row_count_cache (-1);

4447 /*
4448  * do_rollback() - Rollbacks a transaction
4449  * return: Error code
4450  * parser(in): Parser context
4451  * statement(in): Parse tree of a rollback statement (for regularity)
4452  *
4453  * Note: If a savepoint name is given, the transaction is rolled back to
4454  * the savepoint, otherwise the entire transaction is rolled back.
4455  */
4456 int
4457 do_rollback (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4458 {
4459  int error = NO_ERROR;
4460  const char *save_name;
4461  PT_NODE *name;
4462  DB_VALUE val;
4463 
4464  db_make_null (&val);
4465 
4466  name = statement->info.rollback_work.save_name;
4467  if (name == NULL)
4468  {
4469  error = tran_abort ();
4470  }
4471  else
4472  {
4473  if (name->node_type == PT_NAME && name->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
4474  {
4475  save_name = name->info.name.original;
4476  error = db_abort_to_savepoint_internal (save_name);
4477  }
4478  else
4479  {
4480  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, name, &val, 1);
4481  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4482  {
4483  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4484  }
4485  save_name = get_savepoint_name_from_db_value (&val);
4486  if (save_name == NULL)
4487  {
4488  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4489  return er_errid ();
4490  }
4491  error = db_abort_to_savepoint_internal (save_name);
4492  db_value_clear (&val);
4493  }
4494  }
4495 
4496  return error;
4497 }

4499 /*
4500  * do_savepoint() - Creates a transaction savepoint
4501  * return: Error code if savepoint fails
4502  * parser(in): Parser context of a savepoint statement
4503  * statement(in): Parse tree of a rollback statement (for regularity)
4504  *
4505  * Note: If a savepoint name is given, the savepoint is created
4506  * with that name, if no savepoint name is given, we generate a unique one.
4507  */
4508 int
4509 do_savepoint (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4510 {
4511  int error = NO_ERROR;
4512  const char *save_name;
4513  PT_NODE *name;
4514  DB_VALUE val;
4515 
4516  db_make_null (&val);
4517 
4518  name = statement->info.savepoint.save_name;
4519  if (name == NULL)
4520  {
4521  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "transactions");
4522  }
4523  else
4524  {
4525  if (name->node_type == PT_NAME && name->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
4526  {
4527  save_name = name->info.name.original;
4528  error = db_savepoint_transaction_internal (save_name);
4529  }
4530  else
4531  {
4532  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, name, &val, 1);
4533  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4534  {
4535  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4536  }
4537  save_name = get_savepoint_name_from_db_value (&val);
4538  if (save_name == NULL)
4539  {
4540  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4541  return er_errid ();
4542  }
4543  error = db_savepoint_transaction_internal (save_name);
4544  db_value_clear (&val);
4545  }
4546  }
4547 
4548  return error;
4549 }

4551 /*
4552  * do_get_xaction() - Gets the isolation level and/or timeout value for
4553  * a transaction
4554  * return: Error code if it fails
4555  * parser(in): Parser context
4556  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a get transaction statement
4557  *
4558  * Note:
4559  */
4560 int
4561 do_get_xaction (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4562 {
4563  int lock_timeout_in_msecs = 0;
4564  DB_TRAN_ISOLATION tran_isolation = TRAN_UNKNOWN_ISOLATION;
4565  bool async_ws;
4566  int tran_num;
4567  const char *into_label;
4568  DB_VALUE *ins_val;
4569  PT_NODE *into_var;
4570  int error = NO_ERROR;
4571 
4572  (void) tran_get_tran_settings (&lock_timeout_in_msecs, &tran_isolation, &async_ws);
4573 
4574  /* create a DB_VALUE to hold the result */
4575  ins_val = db_value_create ();
4576  if (ins_val == NULL)
4577  {
4578  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4579  return er_errid ();
4580  }
4581 
4582  db_make_int (ins_val, 0);
4583 
4584  switch (statement->info.get_xaction.option)
4585  {
4586  case PT_ISOLATION_LEVEL:
4587  tran_num = (int) tran_isolation;
4588  if (async_ws)
4589  {
4590  tran_num |= TRAN_ASYNC_WS_BIT;
4591  }
4592  db_make_int (ins_val, tran_num);
4593  break;
4594 
4595  case PT_LOCK_TIMEOUT:
4596  if (lock_timeout_in_msecs > 0)
4597  {
4598  db_make_float (ins_val, (float) lock_timeout_in_msecs / 1000);
4599  }
4600  else
4601  {
4602  db_make_float (ins_val, (float) lock_timeout_in_msecs);
4603  }
4604  break;
4605 
4606  default:
4607  break;
4608  }
4609 
4610  statement->etc = (void *) ins_val;
4611 
4612  into_var = statement->info.get_xaction.into_var;
4613  if (into_var != NULL && into_var->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_label = into_var->info.name.original) != NULL)
4614  {
4615  /*
4616  * create another DB_VALUE of the new instance for
4617  * the label_table
4618  */
4619  ins_val = db_value_create ();
4620  if (ins_val == NULL)
4621  {
4622  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4623  return er_errid ();
4624  }
4625 
4626  db_make_int (ins_val, 0);
4627 
4628  switch (statement->info.get_xaction.option)
4629  {
4630  case PT_ISOLATION_LEVEL:
4631  tran_num = (int) tran_isolation;
4632  if (async_ws)
4633  {
4634  tran_num |= TRAN_ASYNC_WS_BIT;
4635  }
4636  db_make_int (ins_val, tran_num);
4637  break;
4638 
4639  case PT_LOCK_TIMEOUT:
4640  if (lock_timeout_in_msecs > 0)
4641  {
4642  db_make_float (ins_val, (float) (lock_timeout_in_msecs / 1000.0));
4643  }
4644  else
4645  {
4646  db_make_float (ins_val, (float) lock_timeout_in_msecs);
4647  }
4648  break;
4649 
4650  default:
4651  break;
4652  }
4653 
4654  /* enter {label, ins_val} pair into the label_table */
4655  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, ins_val);
4656  }
4657 
4658  return error;
4659 }
4660 
4661 /*
4662  * do_set_xaction() - Sets the isolation level and/or timeout value for
4663  * a transaction
4664  * return: Error code if it fails
4665  * parser(in): Parser context
4666  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set transaction statement
4667  *
4668  * Note:
4669  */
4670 int
4671 do_set_xaction (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4672 {
4673  DB_TRAN_ISOLATION tran_isolation;
4674  DB_VALUE val;
4675  PT_NODE *mode = statement->info.set_xaction.xaction_modes;
4676  int error = NO_ERROR;
4677  bool async_ws;
4678  float wait_secs;
4679 
4680  db_make_null (&val);
4681 
4682  while ((error == NO_ERROR) && (mode != NULL))
4683  {
4684  switch (mode->node_type)
4685  {
4686  case PT_ISOLATION_LVL:
4687  if (mode->info.isolation_lvl.level == NULL)
4688  {
4689  /* map schema/instance pair to level */
4690  error = map_iso_levels (parser, statement, &tran_isolation, mode);
4691  async_ws = mode->info.isolation_lvl.async_ws ? true : false;
4692  }
4693  else
4694  {
4695  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, mode->info.isolation_lvl.level, &val, 1);
4696 
4697  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4698  {
4699  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4700  }
4701 
4702  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&val) != DB_TYPE_INTEGER)
4703  {
4704  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_MVCC_RUNTIME_XACT_ISO_LVL_MSG);
4705  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4706  }
4707 
4708  error = set_iso_level (parser, &tran_isolation, &async_ws, statement, &val);
4709  }
4710 
4711  if (error == NO_ERROR)
4712  {
4713  error = tran_reset_isolation (tran_isolation, async_ws);
4714  }
4715  break;
4716  case PT_TIMEOUT:
4717  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, mode->info.timeout.val, &val, 1);
4718  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4719  {
4720  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4721  }
4722 
4723  if (check_timeout_value (parser, statement, &val) != NO_ERROR)
4724  {
4725  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4726  }
4727  else
4728  {
4729  wait_secs = db_get_float (&val);
4730  if (wait_secs > 0)
4731  {
4732  wait_secs *= 1000;
4733  }
4734  (void) tran_reset_wait_times ((int) wait_secs);
4735  }
4736  break;
4737  default:
4738  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4739  }
4740 
4741  mode = mode->next;
4742  }
4743 
4744  return error;
4745 }
4746 
4747 /*
4748  * do_get_optimization_level() - Determine the current optimization and
4749  * return it through the statement parameter.
4750  * return: Error code if it fails
4751  * parser(in): Parser context
4752  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a get transaction statement
4753  *
4754  * Note:
4755  */
4756 int
4757 do_get_optimization_param (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4758 {
4759  DB_VALUE *val;
4760  PT_NODE *into_var;
4761  const char *into_name;
4762  char *cost;
4763  int error = NO_ERROR;
4764 
4765  val = db_value_create ();
4766  if (val == NULL)
4767  {
4768  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4769  return er_errid ();
4770  }
4771 
4772  switch (statement->info.get_opt_lvl.option)
4773  {
4774  case PT_OPT_LVL:
4775  {
4776  int i;
4777  qo_get_optimization_param (&i, QO_PARAM_LEVEL);
4778  db_make_int (val, i);
4779  break;
4780  }
4781  case PT_OPT_COST:
4782  {
4783  DB_VALUE plan;
4784 
4785  db_make_null (&plan);
4786 
4787  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, statement->info.get_opt_lvl.args, &plan, 1);
4788  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4789  {
4790  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4791  }
4792 
4793  /* 'cost' is referenced by 'val', it should be allocated from heap, and will be freed when free 'val' if set
4794  * 'need_clear' to 'true' */
4795  cost = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, 2);
4796  if (cost == NULL)
4797  {
4798  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
4799  }
4800 
4801  qo_get_optimization_param (cost, QO_PARAM_COST, db_get_string (&plan));
4802  pr_clear_value (&plan);
4803  db_make_string (val, cost);
4804  val->need_clear = true;
4805  }
4806  default:
4807  /*
4808  * Default ok; nothing else can get in here.
4809  */
4810  break;
4811  }
4812 
4813  statement->etc = (void *) val;
4814 
4815  into_var = statement->info.get_opt_lvl.into_var;
4816  if (into_var != NULL && into_var->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_name = into_var->info.name.original) != NULL)
4817  {
4818  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_name, db_value_copy (val));
4819  }
4820 
4821  return error;
4822 }
4823 
4824 /*
4825  * do_set_optimization_param() - Set the optimization level to the indicated
4826  * value and return the old value through the
4827  * statement parameter.
4828  * return: Error code if it fails
4829  * parser(in): Parser context
4830  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set transaction statement
4831  *
4832  * Note:
4833  */
4834 int
4835 do_set_optimization_param (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
4836 {
4837  PT_NODE *p1, *p2;
4838  DB_VALUE val1, val2;
4839  char *plan, *cost;
4840 
4841  db_make_null (&val1);
4842  db_make_null (&val2);
4843 
4844  p1 = statement->info.set_opt_lvl.val;
4845 
4846  if (p1 == NULL)
4847  {
4848  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, __FILE__, __LINE__, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
4849  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4850  }
4851 
4852  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, p1, &val1, 1);
4853  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4854  {
4855  pr_clear_value (&val1);
4856  return NO_ERROR;
4857  }
4858 
4859  switch (statement->info.set_opt_lvl.option)
4860  {
4861  case PT_OPT_LVL:
4862  qo_set_optimization_param (NULL, QO_PARAM_LEVEL, (int) db_get_int (&val1));
4863  break;
4864  case PT_OPT_COST:
4865  plan = db_get_string (&val1);
4866  p2 = p1->next;
4867  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, p2, &val2, 1);
4868  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4869  {
4870  pr_clear_value (&val1);
4871  pr_clear_value (&val2);
4872  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4873  }
4874  switch (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&val2))
4875  {
4876  case DB_TYPE_INTEGER:
4877  qo_set_optimization_param (NULL, QO_PARAM_COST, plan, db_get_int (&val2));
4878  break;
4879  case DB_TYPE_CHAR:
4880  case DB_TYPE_NCHAR:
4881  case DB_TYPE_VARCHAR:
4882  case DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
4883  cost = db_get_string (&val2);
4884  qo_set_optimization_param (NULL, QO_PARAM_COST, plan, (int) cost[0]);
4885  break;
4886  default:
4887  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, __FILE__, __LINE__, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
4888  pr_clear_value (&val1);
4889  pr_clear_value (&val2);
4890  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4891  }
4892  break;
4893  default:
4894  /*
4895  * Default ok; no other options available.
4896  */
4897  break;
4898  }
4899 
4900  pr_clear_value (&val1);
4901  pr_clear_value (&val2);
4902  return NO_ERROR;
4903 }

4905 /*
4906  * do_set_sys_params() - Set the system parameters defined in 'cubrid.conf'.
4907  * return: Error code if it fails
4908  * parser(in): Parser context
4909  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set transaction statement
4910  *
4911  * Note:
4912  */
4913 int
4914 do_set_sys_params (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)

4916  PT_NODE *val;

4919

4923  if (val == NULL)
4924  {
4925  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
4926  }
4927

4930  {
4931  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, val, &db_val, 1);
4932

4934  {
4935  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4936  }

4940  }
4941 
4942  pr_clear_value (&db_val);
4943  val = val->next;
4944  }
4945

4949 /*
4950  * map_iso_levels() - Maps the schema/instance isolation level to the
4951  * DB_TRAN_ISOLATION enumerated type.
4952  * return: Error code if it fails
4953  * parser(in): Parser context
4954  * tran_isolation(out):
4955  * node(in): Parse tree of a set transaction statement
4956  *
4957  * Note: Initializes isolation_levels array
4958  */
4959 static int
4960 map_iso_levels (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, DB_TRAN_ISOLATION * tran_isolation, PT_NODE * node)
4961 {
4962  PT_MISC_TYPE instances = node->info.isolation_lvl.instances;
4963  PT_MISC_TYPE schema = node->info.isolation_lvl.schema;
4964 
4965  switch (schema)
4966  {
4967  case PT_SERIALIZABLE:
4968  if (instances == PT_SERIALIZABLE)
4969  {
4970  *tran_isolation = TRAN_SERIALIZABLE;
4971  }
4972  else
4973  {
4974  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_XACT_INVALID_ISO_LVL_MSG,
4975  pt_show_misc_type (schema), pt_show_misc_type (instances));
4976  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4977  }
4978  break;
4979  case PT_REPEATABLE_READ:
4980  if (instances == PT_READ_COMMITTED)
4981  {
4982  *tran_isolation = TRAN_READ_COMMITTED;
4983  }
4984  else if (instances == PT_REPEATABLE_READ)
4985  {
4986  *tran_isolation = TRAN_REPEATABLE_READ;
4987  }
4988  else
4989  {
4990  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_XACT_INVALID_ISO_LVL_MSG,
4991  pt_show_misc_type (schema), pt_show_misc_type (instances));
4992  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
4993  }
4994  break;
4995  case PT_READ_COMMITTED:
4996  if (instances == PT_READ_COMMITTED)
4997  {
4998  *tran_isolation = TRAN_READ_COMMITTED;
4999  }
5000  else
5001  {
5002  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_XACT_INVALID_ISO_LVL_MSG,
5003  pt_show_misc_type (schema), pt_show_misc_type (instances));
5004  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5005  }
5006  break;
5007  default:
5008  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5009  }
5010 
5011  return NO_ERROR;
5012 }
5013 
5014 /*
5015  * set_iso_level() -
5016  * return: Error code if it fails
5017  * parser(in): Parser context
5018  * tran_isolation(out): Isolation level set as a side effect
5019  * async_ws(out):
5020  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set transaction statement
5021  * level(in):
5022  *
5023  * Note: Translates the user entered isolation level (1,2,3,4,5) into
5024  * the enumerated type.
5025  */
5026 static int
5027 set_iso_level (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_TRAN_ISOLATION * tran_isolation, bool * async_ws, PT_NODE * statement,
5028  const DB_VALUE * level)
5029 {
5030  int error = NO_ERROR;
5031  int isolvl = db_get_int (level) & 0x0F;
5032  *async_ws = (db_get_int (level) & 0xF0) ? true : false;
5033 
5034  /* translate to the enumerated type */
5035  switch (isolvl)
5036  {
5037  case TRAN_READ_COMMITTED:
5038  *tran_isolation = TRAN_READ_COMMITTED;
5039  fprintf (stdout,
5040  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_ISO_LVL_SET_TO_MSG));
5041  fprintf (stdout,
5042  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_REPREAD_S_READCOM_I));
5043  break;
5044  case TRAN_REPEATABLE_READ:
5045  *tran_isolation = TRAN_REPEATABLE_READ;
5046  fprintf (stdout,
5047  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_ISO_LVL_SET_TO_MSG));
5048  fprintf (stdout,
5049  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_REPREAD_S_REPREAD_I));
5050  break;
5051  case TRAN_SERIALIZABLE:
5052  *tran_isolation = TRAN_SERIALIZABLE;
5053  fprintf (stdout,
5054  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_ISO_LVL_SET_TO_MSG));
5055  fprintf (stdout,
5056  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_SERIAL_S_SERIAL_I));
5057  break;
5058  case 0:
5059  if (*async_ws == true)
5060  { /* only async workspace is given */
5061  int dummy_lktimeout;
5062  bool dummy_aws;
5063  tran_get_tran_settings (&dummy_lktimeout, tran_isolation, &dummy_aws);
5064  break;
5065  }
5066  /* fall through */
5067  case 1: /* unsupported ones */
5068  case 2:
5069  case 3:
5070  default:
5071  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_MVCC_RUNTIME_XACT_ISO_LVL_MSG);
5072  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5073  }
5074 
5075  return error;
5076 }
5077 
5078 /*
5079  * check_timeout_value() -
5080  * return: Error code if it fails
5081  * parser(in): Parser context
5082  * statement(in):
5083  * val(in): DB_VALUE with the value to set
5084  *
5085  * Note: Checks the user entered isolation level. Valid values are:
5086  * -1 : Infinite
5087  * 0 : Don't wait
5088  * >0 : Wait this number of seconds
5089  */
5090 static int
5091 check_timeout_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, DB_VALUE * val)
5092 {
5093  float timeout;
5094 
5095  if (db_value_coerce (val, val, &tp_Float_domain) == DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
5096  {
5097  timeout = db_get_float (val);
5098  if ((timeout == -1) || (timeout >= 0))
5099  {
5100  return NO_ERROR;
5101  }
5102  }
5103  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_TIMEOUT_VALUE_MSG);
5104  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5105 }

5107 /*
5108  * get_savepoint_name_from_db_value() -
5109  * return: a NULL if the value doesn't properly describe the name
5110  * of a savepoint.
5111  * val(in):
5112  *
5113  * Note: Mutates the contents of val to hold a NULL terminated string
5114  * holding a valid savepoint name. If the value is already of
5115  * type string, a NULL termination will be assumed since the
5116  * name came from a parse tree.
5117  */
5118 static char *
5119 get_savepoint_name_from_db_value (DB_VALUE * val)
5120 {
5121  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (val) != DB_TYPE_CHAR && DB_VALUE_TYPE (val) != DB_TYPE_VARCHAR
5122  && DB_VALUE_TYPE (val) != DB_TYPE_NCHAR && DB_VALUE_TYPE (val) != DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR)
5123  {
5124  if (tp_value_cast (val, val, tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_TYPE_VARCHAR), false) != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
5125  {
5126  return (char *) NULL;
5127  }
5128  }
5129 
5130  return db_get_string (val);
5131 }

5149 /*

5190 #define PT_TR_ATTR_NAME(attr) \
5191  ((attr)->info.name.original)
5192

5194  ((node)->info.create_trigger.trigger_condition)

5196  (convert_misc_to_tr_time((node)->info.create_trigger.condition_time))
5197

5221 /*
5222  * merge_mop_list_extension() -
5223  * return: Number of MOPs to be added
5224  * new(in):
5225  * list(in):
5226  *
5227  * Note:
5228  */
5229 static int
5230 merge_mop_list_extension (DB_OBJLIST * new_objlist, DB_OBJLIST ** list)
5231 {
5232  DB_OBJLIST *obj, *next;
5233  int added = 0;
5234 
5235  for (obj = new_objlist, next = NULL; obj != NULL; obj = next)
5236  {
5237  next = obj->next;
5238  if (ml_find (*list, obj->op))
5239  {
5240  obj->next = NULL;
5241  ml_ext_free (obj);
5242  }
5243  else
5244  {
5245  obj->next = *list;
5246  *list = obj;
5247  added++;
5248  }
5249  }
5250 
5251  return added;
5252 }

5254 /*
5255  * These translate parse tree things into corresponding trigger things.
5256  */
5257 
5258 /*
5259  * convert_event_to_tr_event() - Converts a PT_EV type into the corresponding
5260  * TR_EVENT_ type.
5261  * return: DB_TRIGER_EVENT
5262  * ev(in): One of PT_EVENT_TYPE
5263  *
5264  * Note:
5265  */
5266 static DB_TRIGGER_EVENT
5267 convert_event_to_tr_event (const PT_EVENT_TYPE ev)
5268 {
5269  DB_TRIGGER_EVENT event = TR_EVENT_NULL;
5270 
5271  switch (ev)
5272  {
5273  case PT_EV_INSERT:
5274  event = TR_EVENT_INSERT;
5275  break;
5276  case PT_EV_STMT_INSERT:
5277  event = TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT;
5278  break;
5279  case PT_EV_DELETE:
5280  event = TR_EVENT_DELETE;
5281  break;
5282  case PT_EV_STMT_DELETE:
5283  event = TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE;
5284  break;
5285  case PT_EV_UPDATE:
5286  event = TR_EVENT_UPDATE;
5287  break;
5288  case PT_EV_STMT_UPDATE:
5289  event = TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE;
5290  break;
5291  case PT_EV_ALTER:
5292  event = TR_EVENT_ALTER;
5293  break;
5294  case PT_EV_DROP:
5295  event = TR_EVENT_DROP;
5296  break;
5297  case PT_EV_COMMIT:
5298  event = TR_EVENT_COMMIT;
5299  break;
5300  case PT_EV_ROLLBACK:
5301  event = TR_EVENT_ROLLBACK;
5302  break;
5303  case PT_EV_ABORT:
5304  event = TR_EVENT_ABORT;
5305  break;
5306  case PT_EV_TIMEOUT:
5307  event = TR_EVENT_TIMEOUT;
5308  break;
5309  default:
5310  break;
5311  }
5312 
5313  return event;
5314 }
5315 
5316 /*
5317  * convert_misc_to_tr_time() - Converts a PT_MISC_TYPE into a corresponding
5318  * TR_TYPE_TYPE constant.
5319  * return: DB_TRIGGER_TIME
5320  * pt_time(in): One of PT_MISC_TYPE
5321  *
5322  * Note:
5323  */
5324 static DB_TRIGGER_TIME
5325 convert_misc_to_tr_time (const PT_MISC_TYPE pt_time)
5326 {
5327  DB_TRIGGER_TIME time;
5328 
5329  switch (pt_time)
5330  {
5331  case PT_AFTER:
5332  time = TR_TIME_AFTER;
5333  break;
5334  case PT_BEFORE:
5335  time = TR_TIME_BEFORE;
5336  break;
5337  case PT_DEFERRED:
5338  time = TR_TIME_DEFERRED;
5339  break;
5340  default:
5341  time = TR_TIME_NULL;
5342  break;
5343  }
5344 
5345  return time;
5346 }
5347 
5348 /*
5349  * convert_misc_to_tr_status() - Converts a PT_MISC_TYPE into the corresponding
5350  * TR_STATUE_TYPE.
5351  * return: DB_TRIGGER_STATUS
5352  * pt_status(in): One of PT_MISC_TYPE
5353  *
5354  * Note:
5355  */
5356 static DB_TRIGGER_STATUS
5357 convert_misc_to_tr_status (const PT_MISC_TYPE pt_status)
5358 {
5359  DB_TRIGGER_STATUS status;
5360 
5361  switch (pt_status)
5362  {
5363  case PT_ACTIVE:
5364  status = TR_STATUS_ACTIVE;
5365  break;
5366  case PT_INACTIVE:
5367  status = TR_STATUS_INACTIVE;
5368  break;
5369  default: /* if we get bogus input, should it be inactive ? */
5370  status = TR_STATUS_ACTIVE;
5371  break;
5372  }
5373 
5374  return status;
5375 }
5376 
5377 /*
5378  * convert_speclist_to_objlist() - Converts a PT_MISC_TYPE into the
5379  * corresponding TR_STATUE_TYPE.
5380  * return: Error code
5381  * triglist(out): Returned trigger object list
5382  * specnode(in): Node with PT_TRIGGER_SPEC_LIST_INFO
5383  *
5384  * Note:
5385  * This function converts a trigger specification list in PT format
5386  * into a list of the corresponding trigger objects.
5387  * This is used by a variety of the functions that accept trigger
5388  * specifications.
5389  * The list is an external MOP list and must be freed with ml_ext_free()
5390  * or db_objlist_free.
5391  * The alter flag is set for operations that alter triggers based
5392  * on the WITH EVENT and ALL TRIGGERS specification. In these cases
5393  * we need to automatically filter out the triggers in the list for
5394  * which we don't have authorization.
5395  */
5396 static int
5397 convert_speclist_to_objlist (DB_OBJLIST ** triglist, PT_NODE * specnode)
5398 {
5399  int error = NO_ERROR;
5400  DB_OBJLIST *triggers, *etrigs;
5401  PT_NODE *names, *n, *events, *e;
5402  PT_EVENT_SPEC_INFO *espec;
5403  PT_EVENT_TARGET_INFO *target;
5404  const char *str, *attribute;
5405  DB_TRIGGER_EVENT tr_event;
5406  DB_OBJECT *trigger, *class_;
5407 
5408  triggers = NULL;
5409 
5410  if (specnode != NULL)
5411  {
5412  if (specnode->info.trigger_spec_list.all_triggers)
5413  {
5414  error = tr_find_all_triggers (&triggers);
5415  }
5416 
5417  else if ((names = specnode->info.trigger_spec_list.trigger_name_list) != NULL)
5418  {
5419  /* since this is an explicitly specified list, if we do not have alter authorization for any of the specified
5420  * triggers, we need to make sure the statement is not executed (no triggers are dropped). Use
5421  * tr_check_authorization to find out. */
5422  for (n = names; n != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; n = n->next)
5423  {
5424  str = n->info.name.original;
5425  trigger = tr_find_trigger (str);
5426  if (trigger == NULL)
5427  {
5428  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5429  error = er_errid ();
5430  }
5431  else
5432  {
5433  error = ml_ext_add (&triggers, trigger, NULL);
5434  }
5435  }
5436  }
5437  else if ((events = specnode->info.trigger_spec_list.event_list) != NULL)
5438  {
5439  for (e = events; e != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; e = e->next)
5440  {
5441  class_ = NULL;
5442  attribute = NULL;
5443  espec = &(e->info.event_spec);
5444  tr_event = convert_event_to_tr_event (espec->event_type);
5445 
5446  if (espec->event_target != NULL)
5447  {
5448  target = &(espec->event_target->info.event_target);
5449  class_ = db_find_class (target->class_name->info.name.original);
5450  if (class_ == NULL)
5451  {
5452  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5453  error = er_errid ();
5454  }
5455  else
5456  {
5457  if (target->attribute != NULL)
5458  {
5459  attribute = target->attribute->info.name.original;
5460  }
5461 
5462  error = tr_find_event_triggers (tr_event, class_, attribute, true, &etrigs);
5463  if (error == NO_ERROR)
5464  {
5465  merge_mop_list_extension (etrigs, &triggers);
5466  }
5467  }
5468  }
5469  }
5470  }
5471  }
5472 
5473  if (error)
5474  {
5475  ml_ext_free (triggers);
5476  }
5477  else
5478  {
5479  *triglist = triggers;
5480  }
5481 
5482  return error;
5483 }
5484 
5485 /*
5486  * get_priority() -
5487  * return: Double value
5488  * parser(in): Parser context
5489  * node(in): Priority value node
5490  *
5491  * Note:
5492  * Shorthand function for getting the priority value out of the parse
5493  * tree. Formerly, we just assumed that this would be represented
5494  * with a double value. Now we use coersion.
5495  */
5496 static double
5497 get_priority (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
5498 {
5499  DB_VALUE *src, value;
5500  double priority;
5501 
5502  priority = TR_LOWEST_PRIORITY;
5503 
5504  src = pt_value_to_db (parser, node);
5505  if (src != NULL && (tp_value_coerce (src, &value, &tp_Double_domain) == DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE))
5506  {
5507  priority = db_get_double (&value);
5508  }
5509  /* else, should be setting some kind of error */
5510 
5511  return priority;
5512 }
5513 
5514 /*
5515  * INSERT, UPDATE, & DELETE STATEMENTS
5516  */
5517 
5518 /*
5519  * check_trigger() -
5520  * return: Error code
5521  * event(in): Trigger event type
5522  * do_func(in): Function to do
5523  * parser(in): Parser context used by do_func
5524  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement used by do_func
5525  *
5526  * Note: The function checks if there is any active trigger defined on
5527  * the targets. If there is one, raise the trigger. Otherwise,
5528  * perform the given do_ function.
5529  */
5530 static int
5531 check_trigger (DB_TRIGGER_EVENT event, PT_DO_FUNC * do_func, PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
5532 {
5533  int err, result = NO_ERROR;
5534  TR_STATE *state;
5535  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
5536  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *flat = NULL;
5537  DB_OBJECT *class_ = NULL;
5538 
5539  /* Prepare a trigger state for any triggers that must be raised in this statement */
5540 
5541  state = NULL;
5542 
5543  switch (event)
5544  {
5545  case TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE:
5546  node = statement->info.delete_.spec;
5547  while (node != NULL)
5548  {
5549  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
5550  {
5551  flat = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
5552  class_ = (flat ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL);
5553  if (class_ == NULL)
5554  {
5555  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid spec id");
5556  result = ER_FAILED;
5557  goto exit;
5558  }
5559  result = tr_prepare_statement (&state, event, class_, 0, NULL);
5560  if (result != NO_ERROR)
5561  {
5562  goto exit;
5563  }
5564  }
5565  node = node->next;
5566  }
5567  break;
5568 
5569  case TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT:
5570  flat = (statement->info.insert.spec) ? statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list : NULL;
5571  class_ = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
5572  result = tr_prepare_statement (&state, event, class_, 0, NULL);
5573  break;
5574 
5575  case TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE:
5576  {
5577  /* If this is an "update object" statement, we may not have a spec list yet. This may have been fixed due to
5578  * the recent changes in pt_exec_trigger_stmt to do name resolution each time. */
5579  char **columns = NULL;
5580  int count = pt_count_assignments (parser, statement->info.update.assignment);
5581  int idx;
5582  PT_ASSIGNMENTS_HELPER ea;
5583  PT_NODE *assign = NULL;
5584  PT_SPEC_FLAG flag;
5585 
5586  columns = (char **) (malloc (count * sizeof (char *)));
5587  if (columns == NULL)
5588  {
5589  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, count * sizeof (char *));
5590  result = ER_FAILED;
5591  goto exit;
5592  }
5593 
5594  /* prepare trigger state structures */
5595  node = statement->info.update.spec;
5596  do
5597  {
5598  /* flag is set to UPDATE to make sure triggers are checked for statement->info.update.object_parameter too */
5599  flag = PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE;
5600 
5601  if (node != NULL)
5602  {
5603  flat = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
5604  flag = node->info.spec.flag;
5605  node = node->next;
5606  }
5607  else
5608  {
5609  flat = statement->info.update.object_parameter;
5610  }
5611 
5612  if (flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
5613  {
5614  idx = 0;
5615  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, statement->info.update.assignment);
5616  while ((assign = pt_get_next_assignment (&ea)) != NULL)
5617  {
5618  if (assign->info.name.spec_id == flat->info.name.spec_id)
5619  {
5620  columns[idx++] = (char *) assign->info.name.original;
5621  }
5622  }
5623 
5624  class_ = flat ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
5625  if (class_ == NULL)
5626  {
5627  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid spec id");
5628  result = ER_FAILED;
5629  goto exit;
5630  }
5631 
5632  result = tr_prepare_statement (&state, event, class_, idx, (const char **) columns);
5633  }
5634  }
5635  while (node);
5636  if (columns)
5637  {
5638  free_and_init (columns);
5639  }
5640  break;
5641  }
5642  default:
5643  break;
5644  }
5645 
5646  if (result == NO_ERROR)
5647  {
5648  if (state == NULL)
5649  {
5650  /* no triggers, just do it */
5651  /* result = do_func(parser, statement); */
5652  /* execute internal statements before and after do_func() */
5653  result = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement, do_func);
5654  }
5655  else
5656  {
5657  /* the operations performed in 'tr_before', 'do_check_internal_statements' and 'tr_after' should be all
5658  * contained in one transaction */
5659  if (tr_Current_depth <= 1)
5660  {
5661  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UtrP", &tr_savepoint_number);
5662  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
5663  {
5664  result = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5665  goto exit;
5666  }
5667  result = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
5668  if (result != NO_ERROR)
5669  {
5670  goto exit;
5671  }
5672  }
5673 
5674  /* fire BEFORE STATEMENT triggers */
5675  result = tr_before (state);
5676  if (result == NO_ERROR)
5677  {
5678  /* note, do_insert, do_update, & do_delete don't return just errors, they can also return positive result
5679  * counts. Need to specifically check for result < 0 */
5680  /* result = do_func(parser, statement); */
5681  /* execute internal statements before and after do_func() */
5682  result = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement, do_func);
5683  if (result < NO_ERROR)
5684  {
5685  tr_abort (state);
5686  state = NULL; /* state was freed */
5687  }
5688  else
5689  {
5690  /* try to preserve the usual result value */
5691  err = tr_after (state);
5692  if (err)
5693  {
5694  result = err;
5695  }
5696  if (tr_get_execution_state ())
5697  {
5698  state = NULL; /* state was freed */
5699  }
5700 
5701  }
5702  }
5703  else
5704  {
5705  state = NULL;
5706  }
5707  }
5708  }
5709 
5710 exit:
5711  if (state)
5712  {
5713  /* We need to free state and decrease the tr_Current_depth. */
5714  tr_abort (state);
5715  }
5716 
5717  if (result < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name != NULL && (result != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
5718  {
5719  /* savepoint from tran_savepoint() */
5720  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
5721  }
5722  return result;
5723 }
5724 
5725 /*
5726  * do_check_for_empty_classes_in_delete() - check empty tables
5727  * return: Error code, NO_ERROR or 1 if there is at least one empty class
5728  * parser(in): Parser context
5729  * statement(in): Delete statement
5730  *
5731  * Note: The function checks if the original join, which was splitted, would
5732  * have returned 0 elements. If so then the original DELETE statement
5733  * would have deleted no records. After split this behaviour will change.
5734  * So we check that there is at least one splitted table with no records.
5735  * For compatibility reasons we must preserve the behaviour of the
5736  * original DELETE statement.
5737  */
5738 static int
5739 do_check_for_empty_classes_in_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
5740 {
5741  int error = NO_ERROR, num_classes = 0, idx, partition_type = 0;
5742  PT_NODE *node = statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list, *flat = NULL;
5743  char **classes_names = NULL;
5744  LOCK *locks = NULL;
5745  int *need_subclasses = NULL, au_save = 0;
5746  MOP *partitions = NULL;
5747  HFID *hfid = NULL;
5748  bool has_rows = false;
5749  LC_PREFETCH_FLAGS *flags = NULL;
5750 
5751  /* count the number of new DELETE statements */
5752  while (node != NULL)
5753  {
5754  num_classes++;
5755  node = node->next;
5756  }
5757 
5758  /* allocate classes_names array */
5759  classes_names = (char **) db_private_alloc (NULL, num_classes * sizeof (char *));
5760  if (classes_names == NULL)
5761  {
5762  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5763  goto cleanup;
5764  }
5765 
5766  /* allocate locks array */
5767  locks = (LOCK *) db_private_alloc (NULL, num_classes * sizeof (LOCK));
5768  if (locks == NULL)
5769  {
5770  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5771  goto cleanup;
5772  }
5773 
5774  /* allocate need_subclasses array */
5775  need_subclasses = (int *) db_private_alloc (NULL, num_classes * sizeof (int));
5776  if (need_subclasses == NULL)
5777  {
5778  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5779  goto cleanup;
5780  }
5781 
5782  flags = (LC_PREFETCH_FLAGS *) db_private_alloc (NULL, num_classes * sizeof (LC_PREFETCH_FLAGS));
5783  if (flags == NULL)
5784  {
5785  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5786  goto cleanup;
5787  }
5788 
5789  /* prepare information for locking */
5790  node = statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list;
5791  for (idx = 0; idx < num_classes && node != NULL; idx++, node = node->next)
5792  {
5793  if (node->info.delete_.spec == NULL || node->info.delete_.spec->info.spec.entity_name == NULL
5794  || node->info.delete_.spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original == NULL)
5795  {
5796  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5797  goto cleanup;
5798  }
5799  classes_names[idx] = (char *) node->info.delete_.spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original;
5800  locks[idx] = X_LOCK;
5801  if (node->info.delete_.spec->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL)
5802  {
5803  need_subclasses[idx] = true;
5804  }
5805  else
5806  {
5807  need_subclasses[idx] = false;
5808  }
5809  flags[idx] = LC_PREF_FLAG_LOCK;
5810  }
5811 
5812  /* lock splitted classes with X_LOCK */
5813  if (locator_lockhint_classes (num_classes, (const char **) classes_names, locks, need_subclasses, flags, 1, NULL_LOCK)
5814  != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
5815  {
5816  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5817  error = er_errid ();
5818  goto cleanup;
5819  }
5820 
5821  AU_DISABLE (au_save);
5822  /* Check if we have a splitted spec that has no records */
5823  for (node = statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list; node != NULL; node = node->next)
5824  {
5825  flat = node->info.delete_.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
5826  if (flat == NULL)
5827  {
5828  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5829  goto cleanup;
5830  }
5831 
5832  has_rows = false;
5833  /* we check subclasses and partitions including the class itself */
5834  do
5835  {
5836  error = locator_flush_all_instances (flat->info.name.db_object, DONT_DECACHE);
5837  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5838  {
5839  goto cleanup;
5840  }
5841 
5842  error = sm_partitioned_class_type (flat->info.name.db_object, &partition_type, NULL, &partitions);
5843  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5844  {
5845  goto cleanup;
5846  }
5847  if (partition_type == DB_PARTITIONED_CLASS && partitions != NULL)
5848  {
5849  for (idx = 0; partitions[idx] != NULL && !has_rows; idx++)
5850  {
5851  hfid = sm_get_ch_heap (partitions[idx]);
5852  if (hfid == NULL)
5853  {
5854  free_and_init (partitions);
5855  goto cleanup;
5856  }
5857  error = heap_has_instance (hfid, ws_oid (partitions[idx]), 1);
5858  if (error < NO_ERROR)
5859  {
5860  free_and_init (partitions);
5861  goto cleanup;
5862  }
5863  if (error > 0)
5864  {
5865  has_rows = true;
5866  }
5867  }
5868  }
5869  else
5870  {
5871  hfid = sm_get_ch_heap (flat->info.name.db_object);
5872  if (hfid == NULL)
5873  {
5874  goto cleanup;
5875  }
5876  error = heap_has_instance (hfid, ws_oid (flat->info.name.db_object), 1);
5877  if (error < NO_ERROR)
5878  {
5879  goto cleanup;
5880  }
5881  if (error > 0)
5882  {
5883  has_rows = true;
5884  }
5885  }
5886  if (partitions != NULL)
5887  {
5888  free_and_init (partitions);
5889  }
5890  flat = flat->next;
5891  }
5892  while (flat != NULL && !has_rows);
5893  if (!has_rows)
5894  {
5895  break;
5896  }
5897  }
5898 
5899  /* if we have a splitted class from wich all records will be deleted and it has no records then the join will have no
5900  * records so we can abort the deletion. */
5901  error = (node == NULL ? NO_ERROR : 1);
5902 
5903 cleanup:
5904 
5905  AU_ENABLE (au_save);
5906 
5907  /* free allocated resources */
5908  if (classes_names != NULL)
5909  {
5910  db_private_free (NULL, classes_names);
5911  }
5912 
5913  if (locks != NULL)
5914  {
5915  db_private_free (NULL, locks);
5916  }
5917 
5918  if (need_subclasses != NULL)
5919  {
5920  db_private_free (NULL, need_subclasses);
5921  }
5922 
5923  if (flags != NULL)
5924  {
5925  db_private_free (NULL, flags);
5926  }
5927 
5928  return error;
5929 }
5930 
5931 /*
5932  * do_check_delete_trigger() -
5933  * return: Error code
5934  * parser(in): Parser context
5935  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
5936  * do_func(in): Function to do
5937  *
5938  * Note: The function checks if there is any active trigger with event
5939  * TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE defined on the target.
5940  * If there is one, raise the trigger. Otherwise, perform the
5941  * given do_ function.
5942  */
5943 int
5944 do_check_delete_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_DO_FUNC * do_func)
5945 {
5946  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
5947  int affected_count, error = 0;
5948  PT_NODE *next = NULL;
5949 
5950  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STATEMENT) && statement->info.delete_.search_cond == NULL)
5951  {
5952  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STMT, 0);
5953  return ER_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STMT;
5954  }
5955 
5956  if (statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list != NULL)
5957  {
5958  error = do_check_for_empty_classes_in_delete (parser, statement);
5959  if (error < 0)
5960  {
5961  return error;
5962  }
5963  if (error > 0)
5964  {
5965  return 0;
5966  }
5967  }
5968 
5969  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
5970  {
5971  /* No active trigger is involved. Avoid lock and fetch request. */
5972  error = do_func (parser, statement);
5973  }
5974  else
5975  {
5976  error = check_trigger (TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE, do_func, parser, statement);
5977  }
5978 
5979  /* if the statement that contains joins with conditions deletes no record then we skip the deletion in the subsequent
5980  * classes beacuse the original join would have deleted no record */
5981  if (error <= NO_ERROR)
5982  {
5983  return error;
5984  }
5985 
5986  affected_count = error;
5987 
5988  if (!statement->use_auto_commit)
5989  {
5990  node = statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list;
5991  while (node != NULL)
5992  {
5993  next = node->next;
5994  node->next = NULL;
5995  error = check_trigger (TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE, do_func, parser, node);
5996  node->next = next;
5997  if (error < NO_ERROR)
5998  {
5999  return error;
6000  }
6001  affected_count += error;
6002 
6003  node = node->next;
6004  }
6005  }
6006 
6007  return affected_count;
6008 }
6009 
6010 /*
6011  * do_check_insert_trigger() -
6012  * return: Error code
6013  * parser(in): Parser context
6014  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
6015  * do_func(in): Function to do
6016  *
6017  * Note: The function checks if there is any active trigger with event
6018  * TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT defined on the target.
6019  * If there is one, raise the trigger. Otherwise, perform the
6020  * given do_ function.
6021  */
6022 int
6023 do_check_insert_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_DO_FUNC * do_func)
6024 {
6025  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
6026  {
6027  /* no active trigger is involved. Avoid lock and fetch request. */
6028  return do_func (parser, statement);
6029  }
6030  else
6031  {
6032  return check_trigger (TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT, do_func, parser, statement);
6033  }
6034 }
6035 
6036 /*
6037  * find_update_columns() -
6038  * return: Attribute (column) name array
6039  * count_ptr(out): Returned name count
6040  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement to examine
6041  *
6042  * Note:
6043  * This is used to to find the attribute/column names referenced in
6044  * the statement. It builds a array of strings and returns the length of
6045  * the array.
6046  */
6047 static char **
6048 find_update_columns (int *count_ptr, PT_NODE * statement)
6049 {
6050  PT_NODE *assign;
6051  char **columns;
6052  int count, size, i;
6053  PT_NODE *lhs, *att;
6054 
6055  assign = statement->info.update.assignment;
6056  for (count = 0; assign; assign = assign->next)
6057  {
6058  lhs = assign->info.expr.arg1;
6059  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
6060  {
6061  /* multicolumn update */
6062  count += pt_length_of_list (lhs->info.expr.arg1);
6063  }
6064  else
6065  {
6066  count++;
6067  }
6068  }
6069  size = sizeof (char *) * count;
6070 
6071  columns = (char **) (malloc (size));
6072  if (columns == NULL)
6073  {
6074  return NULL;
6075  }
6076 
6077  assign = statement->info.update.assignment;
6078  for (i = 0; i < count; assign = assign->next)
6079  {
6080  lhs = assign->info.expr.arg1;
6081  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
6082  {
6083  for (att = lhs->info.expr.arg1; att; att = att->next)
6084  {
6085  columns[i++] = (char *) att->info.name.original;
6086  }
6087  }
6088  else
6089  {
6090  columns[i++] = (char *) lhs->info.name.original;
6091  }
6092  }
6093 
6094  *count_ptr = count;
6095  return columns;
6096 }
