6098 /*
6099  * do_check_update_trigger() -
6100  * return: Error code
6101  * parser(in): Parser context
6102  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
6103  *
6104  * Note: The function checks if there is any active trigger with event
6105  * TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE defined on the target.
6106  * If there is one, raise the trigger. Otherwise, perform the
6107  * given do_ function.
6108  */
6109 int
6110 do_check_update_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_DO_FUNC * do_func)
6111 {
6112  int err;
6113 
6114  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STATEMENT) && statement->info.update.search_cond == NULL)
6115  {
6116  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STMT, 0);
6117  return ER_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STMT;
6118  }
6119 
6120  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
6121  {
6122  /* no active trigger is involved. Avoid lock and fetch request. */
6123  err = do_func (parser, statement);
6124  }
6125  else
6126  {
6127  err = check_trigger (TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE, do_func, parser, statement);
6128  }
6129 
6130  return err;
6131 }
6132 
6133 /*
6134  * CREATE TRIGGER STATEMENT
6135  */
6136 
6137 /*
6138  * get_activity_info() - Works for do_create_trigger
6139  * return: None
6140  * parser(in): Parse context for the create trigger statement
6141  * type(out): Returned type of the activity
6142  * source(out) : Returned source of the activity (sometimes NULL)
6143  * statement(in): Sub-tree for the condition or action expression
6144  *
6145  * Note:
6146  * This is used to convert a parser sub-tree into the corresponding
6147  * pair of DB_TRIGGER_ACTIVITY and source string suitable for use
6148  * with tr_create_trigger.
6149  * Since we can't use this parsed representation of the expressions
6150  * anyway (they aren't inside the proper scope), we just convert
6151  * them back into strings with parser_print_tree and let the trigger manager
6152  * call pt_compile_trigger_stmt when necessary.
6153  */
6154 static void
6155 get_activity_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_TRIGGER_ACTION * type, const char **source, PT_NODE * statement)
6156 {
6157  PT_NODE *str;
6158 
6159  *type = TR_ACT_NULL;
6160  *source = NULL;
6161 
6162  if (statement != NULL)
6163  {
6164  if (IS_REJECT_ACTION_STATEMENT (statement))
6165  {
6166  *type = TR_ACT_REJECT;
6167  }
6168  else if (IS_INVALIDATE_ACTION_STATEMENT (statement))
6169  {
6170  *type = TR_ACT_INVALIDATE;
6171  }
6172  else if (IS_PRINT_ACTION_STATEMENT (statement))
6173  {
6174  *type = TR_ACT_PRINT;
6175 
6176  /* extract the print string from the parser node, not sure if I should be looking at the "data_value.s" field
6177  * or the "text" field, they seem to be the same always. */
6178  str = statement->info.trigger_action.string;
6179  if (str->node_type == PT_VALUE)
6180  {
6181  *source = (char *) str->info.value.data_value.str->bytes;
6182  }
6183  }
6184  else
6185  {
6186  /* complex expression */
6187  *type = TR_ACT_EXPRESSION;
6188  *source = parser_print_tree_with_quotes (parser, statement);
6189  }
6190  }
6191 }
6192 
6193 /*
6194  * do_create_trigger() -
6195  * return: Error code
6196  * parser(in): Parse context
6197  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
6198  *
6199  * Note: The function creates a trigger object by calling the trigger
6200  * create function.
6201  */
6202 int
6203 do_create_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6204 {
6205  PT_NODE *cond, *action, *target, *attr, *pri, *comment_node;
6206  const char *name, *comment;
6207  DB_TRIGGER_STATUS status;
6208  double priority;
6209  DB_TRIGGER_EVENT event;
6210  DB_OBJECT *class_;
6211  const char *attribute;
6212  DB_TRIGGER_ACTION cond_type, action_type;
6213  DB_TRIGGER_TIME cond_time, action_time;
6214  const char *cond_source, *action_source;
6215  DB_OBJECT *trigger;
6216  SM_CLASS *smclass = NULL;
6217  int error = NO_ERROR;
6218  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
6219 
6220  name = PT_NODE_TR_NAME (statement);
6221  status = PT_NODE_TR_STATUS (statement);
6222 
6223  comment_node = statement->info.create_trigger.comment;
6224  if (comment_node != NULL)
6225  {
6226  assert (comment_node->node_type == PT_VALUE);
6227  comment = (char *) comment_node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes;
6228  }
6229  else
6230  {
6231  comment = NULL;
6232  }
6233 
6234  pri = PT_NODE_TR_PRI (statement);
6235  if (pri != NULL)
6236  {
6237  priority = get_priority (parser, pri);
6238  }
6239  else
6240  {
6241  priority = TR_LOWEST_PRIORITY;
6242  }
6243 
6244  event = PT_NODE_TR_EVENT_TYPE (statement);
6245  class_ = NULL;
6246  attribute = NULL;
6247  target = PT_NODE_TR_TARGET (statement);
6248  if (target)
6249  {
6250  class_ = db_find_class (PT_TR_TARGET_CLASS (target));
6251  if (class_ == NULL)
6252  {
6253  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6254  return er_errid ();
6255  }
6256 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
6257  if (sm_has_text_domain (db_get_attributes (class_), 1))
6258  {
6259  /* prevent to create a trigger at the class to contain TEXT */
6260  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_REGU_NOT_IMPLEMENTED, 1, rel_major_release_string ());
6261  return er_errid ();
6262  }
6263 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
6264  attr = PT_TR_TARGET_ATTR (target);
6265  if (attr)
6266  {
6267  attribute = PT_TR_ATTR_NAME (attr);
6268  }
6269  error = au_fetch_class (class_, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT);
6270  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6271  {
6272  return error;
6273  }
6274  if (smclass->partition != NULL && smclass->users == NULL)
6275  {
6276  /* Triggers must be created on the partitioned table, not on a specific partition */
6277  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST, 0);
6278  return ER_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST;
6279  }
6280  }
6281  cond = PT_NODE_COND (statement);
6282  cond_time = PT_NODE_COND_TIME (statement);
6283  /* note that cond_type can only be TR_ACT_EXPRESSION, if there is no conditino node, cond_source will be left NULL */
6284  get_activity_info (parser, &cond_type, &cond_source, cond);
6285 
6286  action = PT_NODE_ACTION (statement);
6287  action_time = PT_NODE_ACTION_TIME (statement);
6288  get_activity_info (parser, &action_type, &action_source, action);
6289 
6290  trigger =
6291  tr_create_trigger (name, status, priority, event, class_, attribute, cond_time, cond_source, action_time,
6292  action_type, action_source, comment);
6293 
6294  if (trigger == NULL)
6295  {
6296  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6297  return er_errid ();
6298  }
6299 
6300  /* Save the new trigger object in the parse tree. Actually, we probably should also allow INTO variable sub-clause to
6301  * be compatible with INSERT statement. In that case, the portion of code in do_insert() for saving the new object and
6302  * creating a label table entry needs to be made a extern function. */
6303 
6304  /* This should be treated like a "create class" statement not like an "insert" statement. The trigger object that
6305  * gets created can't be assigned with an INTO clause so there's no need to return it. Assuming this doesn't host
6306  * anything, delete the commented out lines below. */
6307 #if 0
6308  if ((value = db_value_create ()) == NULL)
6309  {
6310  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6311  return er_errid ();
6312  }
6313  db_make_object (value, trigger);
6314  statement->etc = (void *) value;
6315 #endif
6316 
6317  if (smclass != NULL && smclass->users != NULL && TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () < TRAN_REP_READ)
6318  {
6319  /* We have to flush the newly created trigger if the class it belongs to has subclasses. This is because the same
6320  * trigger is assigned to the whole hierarchy and we have to make sure it does not remain a temporary object when
6321  * it is first compiled. Since the class that this trigger belongs to might also be a temporary object, we
6322  * actually have to flush the whole workspace. No need to flush in isolation levels >= repeatable read since
6323  * already flushed in tr_create_trigger */
6324  error = locator_all_flush ();
6325  }
6326 
6327  return error;
6328 }
6329 
6330 /*
6331  * MISC TRIGGER OPERATIONS
6332  */
6333 
6334 /*
6335  * do_drop_trigger() - Drop one or more triggers based on a trigger spec list.
6336  * return: Error code
6337  * parser(in): Parse context
6338  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
6339  *
6340  * Note:
6341  */
6342 int
6343 do_drop_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6344 {
6345  int error = NO_ERROR;
6346  PT_NODE *speclist;
6347  DB_OBJLIST *triggers, *t;
6348 
6349  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
6350 
6351  /* The grammar has beem define such that DROP TRIGGER can only be used with an explicit list of named triggers.
6352  * Although convert_speclist_to_objlist will handle the WITH EVENT and ALL TRIGGERS cases we shouldn't see those
6353  * here. If for some reason they do sneak in, we may get errors when we call tr_drop_triggger() on triggers we don't
6354  * own. */
6355 
6356  speclist = statement->info.drop_trigger.trigger_spec_list;
6357  if (convert_speclist_to_objlist (&triggers, speclist))
6358  {
6359  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6360  return er_errid ();
6361  }
6362 
6363  if (triggers != NULL)
6364  {
6365  /* make sure we have ALTER authorization on all the triggers before proceeding */
6366 
6367  for (t = triggers; t != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; t = t->next)
6368  {
6369  error = tr_check_authorization (t->op, true);
6370  }
6371 
6372  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6373  {
6374  /* shouldn't encounter errors in this loop, if we do, may have to abort the transaction */
6375  for (t = triggers; t != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; t = t->next)
6376  {
6377  error = tr_drop_trigger (t->op, false);
6378  if (error == ER_TR_TRIGGER_NOT_FOUND)
6379  {
6380  /* another transaction has drop the trigger before me */
6381  break;
6382  }
6383  }
6384  }
6385 
6386  /* always free this */
6387  ml_ext_free (triggers);
6388  }
6389 
6390  return error;
6391 }
6392 
6393 /*
6394  * do_alter_trigger() - Alter the priority or status of one or more triggers.
6395  * return: Error code
6396  * parser(in): Parse context
6397  * statement(in): Parse tree with alter trigger node
6398  *
6399  * Note:
6400  */
6401 int
6402 do_alter_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6403 {
6404  int error = NO_ERROR;
6405  PT_NODE *speclist, *p_node, *comment_node;
6406  DB_OBJLIST *triggers, *t;
6407  double priority = TR_LOWEST_PRIORITY;
6408  DB_TRIGGER_STATUS status;
6409  PT_NODE *trigger_owner, *trigger_name = NULL;
6410  const char *trigger_owner_name = NULL, *trigger_comment;
6411  DB_VALUE returnval, trigger_name_val, user_val;
6412  bool has_trigger_comment = false;
6413  TR_TRIGGER *trigger;
6414  int count;
6415  bool has_savepoint = false;
6416 
6417  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
6418 
6419  triggers = NULL;
6420  p_node = statement->info.alter_trigger.trigger_priority;
6421  trigger_owner = statement->info.alter_trigger.trigger_owner;
6422  speclist = statement->info.alter_trigger.trigger_spec_list;
6423  if (convert_speclist_to_objlist (&triggers, speclist))
6424  {
6425  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6426  return er_errid ();
6427  }
6428 
6429  comment_node = statement->info.alter_trigger.comment;
6430  if (comment_node != NULL)
6431  {
6432  has_trigger_comment = true;
6433  assert (comment_node->node_type == PT_VALUE);
6434  trigger_comment = (char *) comment_node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes;
6435  }
6436 
6437  /* currently, we can' set the status and priority at the same time. The existance of p_node determines which type of
6438  * alter statement this is. */
6439  status = TR_STATUS_INVALID;
6440 
6441  if (trigger_owner != NULL)
6442  {
6443  trigger_owner_name = trigger_owner->info.name.original;
6444  trigger_name = speclist->info.trigger_spec_list.trigger_name_list;
6445  }
6446  else if (p_node != NULL)
6447  {
6448  priority = get_priority (parser, p_node);
6449  }
6450  else if (statement->info.alter_trigger.trigger_status == PT_ACTIVE
6451  || statement->info.alter_trigger.trigger_status == PT_INACTIVE)
6452  {
6453  status = convert_misc_to_tr_status (statement->info.alter_trigger.trigger_status);
6454  }
6455  else
6456  {
6457  /* here, means user intends to alter comment only, which must exist */
6458  assert (has_trigger_comment);
6459  }
6460 
6461  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6462  {
6463  /* make sure we have ALTER authorization on all the triggers before proceeding */
6464  count = 0;
6465  for (t = triggers; t != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; t = t->next)
6466  {
6467  error = tr_check_authorization (t->op, true);
6468  count++;
6469  }
6470 
6471  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6472  {
6473  if (count > 0 || TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ)
6474  {
6475  /* need atomic operation */
6476  error = tran_system_savepoint (UNIQUE_SAVEPOINT_ALTER_TRIGGER);
6477  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6478  {
6479  goto cleanup;
6480  }
6481  has_savepoint = true;
6482  }
6483 
6484  for (t = triggers; t != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; t = t->next)
6485  {
6486  if (status != TR_STATUS_INVALID)
6487  {
6488  error = tr_set_status (t->op, status, false);
6489  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6490  {
6491  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6492  break;
6493  }
6494  }
6495 
6496  if (p_node != NULL)
6497  {
6498  error = tr_set_priority (t->op, priority, false);
6499  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6500  {
6501  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6502  break;
6503  }
6504  }
6505 
6506  if (trigger_owner != NULL)
6507  {
6508  assert (trigger_name != NULL);
6509 
6510  db_make_null (&returnval);
6511 
6512  db_make_string_by_const_str (&trigger_name_val, trigger_name->info.name.original);
6513  db_make_string_by_const_str (&user_val, trigger_owner_name);
6514 
6515  au_change_trigger_owner_method (t->op, &returnval, &trigger_name_val, &user_val);
6516 
6517  pr_clear_value (&trigger_name_val);
6518  pr_clear_value (&user_val);
6519 
6520  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&returnval) == DB_TYPE_ERROR)
6521  {
6522  error = db_get_error (&returnval);
6523  break;
6524  }
6525 
6526  trigger_name = trigger_name->next;
6527  }
6528 
6529  if (has_trigger_comment)
6530  {
6531  error = tr_set_comment (t->op, trigger_comment, false);
6532  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6533  {
6534  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6535  break;
6536  }
6537  }
6538 
6539  error = locator_flush_instance (t->op);
6540  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6541  {
6542  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6543  break;
6544  }
6545 
6546  /* If trigger is on a class, lock it (S_LOCK) to block concurrent DML statements. */
6547  trigger = tr_map_trigger (t->op, false);
6548  if (trigger->class_mop != NULL)
6549  {
6550  if (locator_fetch_class (trigger->class_mop, DB_FETCH_SCAN) == NULL)
6551  {
6552  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error);
6553  break;
6554  }
6555  }
6556  }
6557  }
6558  }
6559 
6560  if (has_savepoint && error != NO_ERROR && error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
6561  {
6562  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (UNIQUE_SAVEPOINT_ALTER_TRIGGER);
6563  }
6564 
6565 cleanup:
6566  if (triggers != NULL)
6567  {
6568  ml_ext_free (triggers);
6569  }
6570 
6571  return error;
6572 }
6573 
6574 /*
6575  * do_execute_trigger() - Execute the deferred activities for one or more
6576  * triggers.
6577  * return: Error code
6578  * parser(in): Parse context
6579  * statement(in): Parse tree of a execute trigger statement
6580  *
6581  * Note:
6582  */
6583 int
6584 do_execute_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6585 {
6586  int error = NO_ERROR;
6587  PT_NODE *speclist;
6588  DB_OBJLIST *triggers, *t;
6589 
6590  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
6591 
6592  speclist = statement->info.execute_trigger.trigger_spec_list;
6593  error = convert_speclist_to_objlist (&triggers, speclist);
6594 
6595  if (error == NO_ERROR && triggers != NULL)
6596  {
6597  for (t = triggers; t != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; t = t->next)
6598  {
6599  error = tr_execute_deferred_activities (t->op, NULL);
6600  }
6601  ml_ext_free (triggers);
6602  }
6603 
6604  return error;
6605 }
6606 
6607 /*
6608  * do_remove_trigger() - Remove the deferred activities for one or more triggers
6609  * return: Error code
6610  * parser(in): Parse context
6611  * statement(in): Parse tree of a remove trigger statement
6612  *
6613  * Note:
6614  */
6615 int
6616 do_remove_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6617 {
6618  int error = NO_ERROR;
6619  PT_NODE *speclist;
6620  DB_OBJLIST *triggers, *t;
6621 
6622  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
6623 
6624  speclist = statement->info.remove_trigger.trigger_spec_list;
6625  error = convert_speclist_to_objlist (&triggers, speclist);
6626 
6627  if (error == NO_ERROR && triggers != NULL)
6628  {
6629  for (t = triggers; t != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; t = t->next)
6630  {
6631  error = tr_drop_deferred_activities (t->op, NULL);
6632  }
6633 
6634  ml_ext_free (triggers);
6635  }
6636 
6637  return error;
6638 }
6639 
6640 /*
6641  * do_rename_trigger() - Rename a trigger
6642  * return: Error code
6643  * parser(in): Parse context
6644  * statement(in): Parse tree of a rename trigger statement
6645  *
6646  * Note:
6647  */
6648 int
6649 do_rename_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6650 {
6651  int error = NO_ERROR;
6652  const char *old_name, *new_name;
6653  DB_OBJECT *trigger;
6654 
6655  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
6656 
6657  old_name = statement->info.rename_trigger.old_name->info.name.original;
6658  new_name = statement->info.rename_trigger.new_name->info.name.original;
6659 
6660  trigger = tr_find_trigger (old_name);
6661  if (trigger == NULL)
6662  {
6663  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6664  error = er_errid ();
6665  }
6666  else
6667  {
6668  error = tr_rename_trigger (trigger, new_name, false);
6669  }
6670 
6671  return error;
6672 }
6673 
6674 /*
6675  * do_set_trigger() - Set one of the trigger options
6676  * return: Error code
6677  * parser(in): Parse context
6678  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set trigger statement
6679  *
6680  * Note:
6681  */
6682 int
6683 do_set_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6684 {
6685  int error = NO_ERROR;
6686  DB_VALUE src, dst;
6687  TP_DOMAIN_STATUS dom_status;
6688 
6689  db_make_null (&src);
6690  db_make_null (&dst);
6691 
6692  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, statement->info.set_trigger.val, &src, 1);
6693  if (pt_has_error (parser))
6694  {
6695  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SEMANTIC);
6696  error = er_errid ();
6697  if (error == ER_TP_CANT_COERCE || error == ER_IT_DATA_OVERFLOW)
6698  {
6699  char buf1[MAX_DOMAIN_NAME_SIZE];
6700  char buf2[MAX_DOMAIN_NAME_SIZE];
6701  (void) tp_value_domain_name (&src, buf1, sizeof (buf1));
6702  (void) tp_domain_name (&tp_Integer_domain, buf2, sizeof (buf2));
6703  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 2, buf1, buf2);
6704  }
6705  }
6706  else
6707  {
6708  dom_status = tp_value_coerce (&src, &dst, &tp_Integer_domain);
6709  if (dom_status != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
6710  {
6711  error = tp_domain_status_er_set (dom_status, ARG_FILE_LINE, &src, &tp_Integer_domain);
6712  /* already set error */
6713  }
6714  }
6715 
6716  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6717  {
6718  PT_MISC_TYPE option;
6719  int v;
6720 
6721  option = statement->info.set_trigger.option;
6722  v = db_get_int (&dst);
6723 
6724  if (option == PT_TRIGGER_TRACE)
6725  {
6726  error = tr_set_trace ((bool) v);
6727  }
6728  else if (option == PT_TRIGGER_DEPTH)
6729  {
6730  error = tr_set_depth (v);
6731  }
6732  }
6733 
6734  /*
6735  * No need to clear dst, because it's either NULL or an integer at
6736  * this point. src could be arbitrarily complex, and it was created
6737  * by pt_evaluate_tree, so we need to clear it before we leave.
6738  */
6739  db_value_clear (&src);
6740 
6741  return error;
6742 }
6743 
6744 /*
6745  * do_get_trigger() - Get one of the trigger option values.
6746  * return: Error code
6747  * parser(in): Parse context
6748  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a get trigger statement
6749  *
6750  * Note:
6751  */
6752 int
6753 do_get_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6754 {
6755  int error = NO_ERROR;
6756  const char *into_label;
6757  DB_VALUE *ins_val;
6758  PT_NODE *into;
6759  PT_MISC_TYPE option;
6760 
6761  /* create a value to hold the result */
6762  ins_val = db_value_create ();
6763  if (ins_val == NULL)
6764  {
6765  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6766  return er_errid ();
6767  }
6768 
6769  option = statement->info.set_trigger.option;
6770  switch (option)
6771  {
6772  case PT_TRIGGER_DEPTH:
6773  db_make_int (ins_val, tr_get_depth ());
6774  break;
6775  case PT_TRIGGER_TRACE:
6776  db_make_int (ins_val, tr_get_trace ());
6777  break;
6778  default:
6779  db_make_null (ins_val); /* can't happen */
6780  break;
6781  }
6782 
6783  statement->etc = (void *) ins_val;
6784 
6785  into = statement->info.get_trigger.into_var;
6786  if (into != NULL && into->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_label = into->info.name.original) != NULL)
6787  {
6788  /* create another DB_VALUE for the label table */
6789  ins_val = db_value_copy (ins_val);
6790 
6791  /* enter the value into the table */
6792  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, ins_val);
6793  }
6794 
6795  return error;
6796 }

6810 typedef enum
