6850 /*
6851  * unlink_list - Unlinks next pointer shortcut of lhs, rhs assignments
6852  * return: None
6853  * list(in): Node list to cut
6854  *
6855  * Note:
6856  */
6857 static void
6858 unlink_list (PT_NODE * list)
6859 {
6860  PT_NODE *next;
6861 
6862  while (list)
6863  {
6864  next = list->next;
6865  list->next = NULL;
6866  list = next;
6867  }
6868 }
6869 
6870 /*
6871  * get_select_list_to_update -
6872  * return: List file if success, otherwise NULL
6873  * parser(in): Parser context
6874  * from(in): Parse tree of an FROM class
6875  * column_values(in): Column list in SELECT clause
6876  * with(in): WITH clause
6877  * where(in): WHERE clause
6878  * order_by(in): ORDER BY clause
6879  * orderby_num(in): converted from ORDER BY with LIMIT
6880  * using_index(in): USING INDEX clause
6881  * class_specs(in): Another class specs in FROM clause
6882  *
6883  * Note:
6884  */
6885 static QFILE_LIST_ID *
6886 get_select_list_to_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * from, PT_NODE * column_names, PT_NODE * column_values,
6887  PT_NODE * with, PT_NODE * where, PT_NODE * order_by, PT_NODE * orderby_for,
6888  PT_NODE * using_index, PT_NODE * class_specs, PT_NODE * update_stmt)
6889 {
6890  PT_NODE *statement = NULL;
6891  QFILE_LIST_ID *result = NULL;
6892  int err = NO_ERROR;
6893 
6894  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
6895 
6896  if (from && (from->node_type == PT_SPEC) && from->info.spec.range_var
6897  && ((statement =
6898  pt_to_upd_del_query (parser, column_names, column_values, from, with, class_specs, where, using_index,
6899  order_by, orderby_for, 0 /* not server update */ , S_UPDATE)) != NULL))
6900  {
6901  err = pt_copy_upddel_hints_to_select (parser, update_stmt, statement);
6902  if (err != NO_ERROR)
6903  {
6904  parser_free_tree (parser, statement);
6905  return NULL;
6906  }
6907 
6908  /* If we are updating a proxy, the select is not yet fully translated. If we are updating anything else, this is
6909  * a no-op. */
6910  statement = mq_translate (parser, statement);
6911 
6912  if (statement)
6913  {
6914  /* This enables authorization checking during methods in queries */
6915  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
6916 
6917  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
6918  if (do_select (parser, statement) < NO_ERROR)
6919  {
6920  /* query failed, an error has already been set */
6921  statement = NULL;
6922  }
6923 
6924  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
6925  }
6926  }
6927 
6928  if (statement)
6929  {
6930  result = (QFILE_LIST_ID *) statement->etc;
6931  parser_free_tree (parser, statement);
6932  }
6933 
6934  return result;
6935 }
6936 
6937 /*
6938  * update_object_attribute -
6939  * return: Error code
6940  * parser(in): Parser context
6941  * otemplate(in/out): Class template to be edited
6942  * name(in): Parse tree of a attribute name
6943  * attr_desc(in): Descriptor of attribute to update
6944  * value(in): New attribute value
6945  *
6946  * Note: If db_put fails, return an error
6947  */
6948 static int
6949 update_object_attribute (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OTMPL * otemplate, PT_NODE * name, DB_ATTDESC * attr_desc,
6950  DB_VALUE * value)
6951 {
6952  int error = NO_ERROR;
6953 
6954  if (name->info.name.db_object)
6955  {
6956  error = db_is_vclass (name->info.name.db_object);
6957  if (error < 0)
6958  {
6959  return error;
6960  }
6961  if (error > 0)
6962  {
6963  /* this is a shared attribute of a view. this means this cannot be updated in the template for this real
6964  * class. Its simply done separately by a db_put. */
6965  error = obj_set_shared (name->info.name.db_object, name->info.name.original, value);
6966  return error;
6967  }
6968  }
6969 
6970  /* the normal case */
6971  error = dbt_dput_internal (otemplate, attr_desc, value);
6972 
6973  return error;
6974 }
6975 
6976 /*
6977  * update_object_tuple - Updates object attributes with db_values
6978  * return: Error code
6979  * assigns(in): array of assignments
6980  * assigns_count(in): no of assignments
6981  * upd_classes_info(in): array of classes info
6982  * classes_cnt(in): no of classes
6983  * turn_off_unique_check(in):
6984  * turn_off_serializable_conflict_check(in): true, if turn off SERIALIZABLE
6985  * conflict checking
6986  * update_type(in):
6987  * should_delete(in):
6988  *
6989  * Note:
6990  */
6991 static int
6992 update_object_tuple (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO * assigns, int assigns_count,
6993  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO * upd_classes_info, int classes_cnt, const int turn_off_unique_check,
6994  const int turn_off_serializable_conflict_check, UPDATE_TYPE update_type, bool should_delete)
6995 {
6996  int error = NO_ERROR;
6997  DB_OTMPL *otemplate = NULL;
6998  int idx = 0, upd_tpl_cnt = 0;
6999  DB_OBJECT *real_object = NULL, *object = NULL;
7000  SM_CLASS *smclass = NULL;
7001  CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO *assign = NULL;
7002  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO *cls_info = NULL;
7003  bool flush_del = false;
7004  MOP object_class_mop;
7005 
7006  for (idx = 0; idx < classes_cnt && error == NO_ERROR; idx++)
7007  {
7008  cls_info = &upd_classes_info[idx];
7009 
7010  if (DB_IS_NULL (cls_info->oid))
7011  {
7012  continue;
7013  }
7014 
7015  object = db_get_object (cls_info->oid);
7016  error = db_is_deleted (object);
7017  if (error < 0)
7018  {
7019  return error;
7020  }
7021  if (error > 0)
7022  {
7023  error = NO_ERROR;
7024  continue;
7025  }
7026 
7027  real_object = db_real_instance (object);
7028  if (real_object == NULL)
7029  { /* real_object's fail */
7030  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7031  error = er_errid ();
7032  if (error == NO_ERROR)
7033  {
7034  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
7035  }
7036  return error;
7037  }
7038 
7039  /* if this is the first tuple or the class has changed to a new subclass then fetch new class */
7040  object_class_mop = ws_class_mop (object);
7041  if (cls_info->class_mop == NULL
7042  || (object_class_mop != NULL && ws_mop_compare (object_class_mop, cls_info->class_mop) != 0))
7043  {
7044  cls_info->class_mop = object_class_mop;
7045 
7046  if (object_class_mop != NULL)
7047  {
7048  error = au_fetch_class (object_class_mop, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT);
7049  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7050  {
7051  return error;
7052  }
7053  cls_info->smclass = smclass;
7054  }
7055  }
7056  else
7057  {
7058  /* otherwise use old class */
7059  smclass = cls_info->smclass;
7060  }
7061 
7062  otemplate = dbt_edit_object (real_object);
7063  if (otemplate == NULL)
7064  {
7065  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7066  return er_errid ();
7067  }
7068 
7069  if (turn_off_unique_check)
7070  {
7071  obt_disable_unique_checking (otemplate);
7072  }
7073 
7074  if (turn_off_serializable_conflict_check)
7075  {
7076  obt_disable_serializable_conflict_checking (otemplate);
7077  }
7078 
7079  /* this is an update - force NOT NULL constraint check */
7080  otemplate->force_check_not_null = 1;
7081 
7082  otemplate->pruning_type = cls_info->pruning_type;
7083 
7084  /* If this update came from INSERT ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE, flush the object on updating it. */
7085  if (update_type == ON_DUPLICATE_KEY_UPDATE || otemplate->pruning_type != DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS)
7086  {
7087  obt_set_force_flush (otemplate);
7088  }
7089 
7090  /* iterate through class assignments and update template with new values */
7091  for (assign = cls_info->first_assign; assign != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; assign = assign->next)
7092  {
7093  /* if this is the first update, get the attribute descriptor */
7094  if (assign->attr_desc == NULL)
7095  {
7096  int is_vclass = 0;
7097 
7098  /* don't get descriptors for shared attrs of views */
7099  if (assign->upd_col_name->info.name.db_object != NULL)
7100  {
7101  is_vclass = db_is_vclass (assign->upd_col_name->info.name.db_object);
7102 
7103  if (is_vclass < 0)
7104  {
7105  error = is_vclass;
7106  }
7107  }
7108  if (!is_vclass)
7109  {
7110  error =
7111  db_get_attribute_descriptor (real_object, assign->upd_col_name->info.name.original, 0, 1,
7112  &assign->attr_desc);
7113  }
7114  }
7115 
7116  if (error == NO_ERROR)
7117  {
7118  /* update tuple's template */
7119  error =
7120  update_object_attribute (parser, otemplate, assign->upd_col_name, assign->attr_desc, assign->db_val);
7121 
7122  /* clear not constant values */
7123  if (!assign->is_const)
7124  {
7125  db_value_clear (assign->db_val);
7126  }
7127  }
7128  }
7129 
7130  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7131  {
7132  /* abort if an error has occurred */
7133  (void) dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
7134  }
7135  else
7136  {
7137  /* update tuple with new values */
7138  object = dbt_finish_object (otemplate);
7139  if (object == NULL)
7140  {
7141  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7142  error = er_errid ();
7143  (void) dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
7144  return error;
7145  }
7146  else
7147  {
7148  /* check condition for 'with check option' */
7149  error = mq_evaluate_check_option (parser,
7150  (cls_info->check_where != NULL
7151  ? cls_info->check_where->info.check_option.expr : NULL), object,
7152  cls_info->spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
7153  }
7154  }
7155 
7156  /* handle delete only after update to give a chance to triggers */
7157  if (should_delete && error == NO_ERROR)
7158  {
7159  error = locator_flush_instance (object);
7160  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7161  {
7162  continue;
7163  }
7164  flush_del = has_unique_constraint (object);
7165  error = delete_object_tuple (object);
7166  if (error == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT && do_Trigger_involved)
7167  {
7168  er_clear ();
7169  error = NO_ERROR;
7170  continue;
7171  }
7172  if (flush_del && error == NO_ERROR)
7173  {
7174  error = locator_flush_instance (object);
7175  }
7176  }
7177  upd_tpl_cnt++;
7178  }
7179 
7180  return error == NO_ERROR ? upd_tpl_cnt : error;
7181 }
7182 
7183 /*
7184  * update_object_by_oid - Updates attributes of object by oid
7185  * return: 1 if success, otherwise returns error code
7186  * parser(in): Parser context
7187  * statement(in): Parse tree of a update statement
7188  * update_type(in): denote whether the update comes from normal update stmt,
7189  * update object stmt or insert on duplicate key update stmt.
7190  *
7191  * Note:
7192  */
7193 static int
7194 update_object_by_oid (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, UPDATE_TYPE update_type)
7195 {
7196  int error = NO_ERROR;
7197  DB_OBJECT *oid = statement->info.update.object;
7198  int i = 0;
7199  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
7200  int vals_cnt = 0;
7201  PT_NODE *class_;
7202  PT_NODE *lhs;
7203 
7204  if (!statement->info.update.spec || !(class_ = statement->info.update.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list)
7205  || !(class_->info.name.db_object) || statement->info.update.spec->next != NULL)
7206  {
7207  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
7208  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
7209  }
7210 
7211  /* fetch classes that will be updated */
7212  node = statement->info.update.spec;
7213  while (node)
7214  {
7215  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
7216  {
7217  if (!locator_fetch_class (node->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object, DB_FETCH_CLREAD_INSTWRITE))
7218  {
7219  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7220  return er_errid ();
7221  }
7222  }
7223 
7224  node = node->next;
7225  }
7226 
7227  /* get first argument of first assignment */
7228  lhs = statement->info.update.assignment->info.expr.arg1;
7229  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
7230  {
7231  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
7232  }
7233 
7234  if (lhs->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR)
7235  {
7236  /* if left argument of first assignment is an attribute then all other assignments are to class attributes */
7237  error = update_class_attributes (parser, statement);
7238  }
7239  else
7240  {
7241  /* update object */
7242  int assigns_count = 0, upd_cls_cnt = 0, multi_assign_cnt = 0;
7243  CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO *assigns = NULL;
7244  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO *cls_info = NULL;
7245  DB_VALUE *dbvals = NULL;
7246  PT_ASSIGNMENTS_HELPER ea;
7247  PT_NODE *rhs = NULL, *lhs = NULL;
7248 
7249  /* Before we start evaluating assignments, we need to first lock the object. Assignments may depend on current
7250  * object values which cannot be modified by others. */
7251  error = obj_inst_lock (oid, 1);
7252  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7253  {
7254  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update_object_by_oid failed to lock object.");
7255  return error;
7256  }
7257 
7258  /* load structures for update */
7259  error =
7260  init_update_data (parser, statement, &assigns, &assigns_count, &cls_info, &upd_cls_cnt, &dbvals, &vals_cnt,
7261  false);
7262 
7263  if (error == NO_ERROR)
7264  {
7265  db_make_object (&dbvals[0], oid);
7266 
7267  /* iterate through assignments and evaluate right side of each assignment */
7268  i = 0;
7269  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, statement->info.update.assignment);
7270  while (pt_get_next_assignment (&ea) && error == NO_ERROR)
7271  {
7272  rhs = ea.rhs;
7273  lhs = ea.lhs;
7274  multi_assign_cnt = 1;
7275  /* for multi-column assignments with common right side count number of attributes to assign to */
7276  if (ea.is_n_column)
7277  {
7278  while (pt_get_next_assignment (&ea) && rhs == ea.rhs)
7279  {
7280  multi_assign_cnt++;
7281  }
7282  }
7283 
7284  error =
7285  mq_evaluate_expression_having_serial (parser, rhs, assigns[i].db_val, multi_assign_cnt, oid,
7286  lhs->info.name.spec_id);
7287  i += multi_assign_cnt;
7288  }
7289 
7290  /* update tuple */
7291  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
7292  {
7293  error =
7294  update_object_tuple (parser, assigns, assigns_count, cls_info, upd_cls_cnt, 0, 0, update_type, false);
7295  }
7296 
7297  }
7298 
7299  /* free assignments array */
7300  if (assigns != NULL)
7301  {
7302  /* free attribute descriptors */
7303  for (i = assigns_count - 1; i >= 0; i--)
7304  {
7305  if (assigns[i].attr_desc)
7306  {
7307  db_free_attribute_descriptor (assigns[i].attr_desc);
7308  }
7309  }
7310  db_private_free (NULL, assigns);
7311  }
7312 
7313  /* free classes information */
7314  if (cls_info != NULL)
7315  {
7316  db_private_free (NULL, cls_info);
7317  }
7318 
7319  /* free dbvals array */
7320  if (dbvals != NULL)
7321  {
7322  db_private_free (NULL, dbvals);
7323  }
7324  }
7325 
7326  if (error < NO_ERROR)
7327  return error;
7328  else
7329  return 1; /* we successfully updated 1 object */
7330 }
7331 
7332 /*
7333  * do_set_pruning_type () - set pruning type for a spec
7334  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
7335  * parser (in) : parser context
7336  * spec (in) : spec
7337  * cls (in) : update class info
7338  */
7339 static int
7340 do_set_pruning_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO * cls)
7341 {
7342  int error = NO_ERROR;
7343  MOP class_mop = NULL;
7344  PT_NODE *derived = NULL;
7345  if (cls == NULL || spec == NULL)
7346  {
7347  return NO_ERROR;
7348  }
7349  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
7350  {
7351  return NO_ERROR;
7352  }
7353  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec))
7354  {
7355  if (spec->info.spec.entity_name->node_type == PT_NAME)
7356  {
7357  class_mop = spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object;
7358  if (class_mop == NULL)
7359  {
7360  PT_ERROR (parser, spec, "Generic error");
7361  return ER_FAILED;
7362  }
7363  error = sm_partitioned_class_type (class_mop, &cls->pruning_type, NULL, NULL);
7364  return error;
7365  }
7366  else if (spec->info.spec.entity_name->node_type == PT_SPEC)
7367  {
7368  /* (classA, classB) specification. We do not allow partitions in this context */
7369  PT_NODE *node = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
7370  while (node)
7371  {
7372  error = do_set_pruning_type (parser, node, cls);
7373  if (cls->pruning_type == DB_PARTITION_CLASS)
7374  {
7375  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_NOT_ALLOWED_ACCESS_TO_PARTITION,
7376  node->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original);
7377  return ER_FAILED;
7378  }
7379  node = node->next;
7380  }
7381  return NO_ERROR;
7382  }
7383  }
7384 
7385  if (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec))
7386  {
7387  PT_ERROR (parser, spec, "CTE not handled");
7388  return ER_FAILED;
7389  }
7390 
7391  /* We're in the context of a table update/insert etc. This is possible only if the derived table is a SELECT and has
7392  * only one updated class */
7393  derived = spec->info.spec.derived_table;
7394  error = NO_ERROR;
7395  if (derived->node_type == PT_SELECT)
7396  {
7397  for (spec = derived->info.query.q.select.from; spec != NULL; spec = spec->next)
7398  {
7399  if (error == NO_ERROR && (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE))
7400  {
7401  error = do_set_pruning_type (parser, spec, cls);
7402  }
7403  }
7404  }
7405  else if (derived->node_type == PT_UNION)
7406  {
7407  if (derived->info.query.q.union_.arg1 != NULL && derived->info.query.q.union_.arg1->node_type == PT_SELECT)
7408  {
7409  for (spec = derived->info.query.q.union_.arg1->info.query.q.select.from; spec != NULL; spec = spec->next)
7410  {
7411  if (error == NO_ERROR && (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE))
7412  {
7413  error = do_set_pruning_type (parser, spec, cls);
7414  }
7415  }
7416  }
7417 
7418  if (derived->info.query.q.union_.arg2 != NULL && derived->info.query.q.union_.arg2->node_type == PT_SELECT)
7419  {
7420  for (spec = derived->info.query.q.union_.arg2->info.query.q.select.from; spec != NULL; spec = spec->next)
7421  {
7422  if (error == NO_ERROR && (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE))
7423  {
7424  error = do_set_pruning_type (parser, spec, cls);
7425  }
7426  }
7427  }
7428  }
7429  else
7430  {
7431  PT_ERROR (parser, spec, "Generic error");
7432  return ER_FAILED;
7433  }
7434 
7435  return error;
7436 }
7437 
7438 /*
7439  * init_update_data () - init update data structures
7440  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
7441  * parser(in): Parser context
7442  * assigns_data(out): address of a pointer variable that will receive the
7443  * array for assignments info. This array must be
7444  * released by the caller
7445  * assigns_no(out): address of a int variable that will receive number of
7446  * assignments
7447  * cls_data(out): address of a pointer that will receive information about
7448  * classes that will be updated
7449  * cls_count(out): address of a integer variable that will receive number of
7450  * classes that will be updated
7451  * values(out): address of a pointer that will receive an array of DB_VALUE
7452  * that represents runtime computed values and constants.
7453  * This array is referenced by elements of assigns_data.
7454  * values_cnt(out): number of classes OIDs + values computed at
7455  * runtime for assignments.
7456  * has_delete(in): update/delete
7457  *
7458  * Note:
7459  */
7460 static int
7461 init_update_data (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO ** assigns_data, int *assigns_count,
7462  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO ** cls_data, int *cls_count, DB_VALUE ** values, int *values_cnt,
7463  bool has_delete)
7464 {
7465  int error = NO_ERROR;
7466  int assign_cnt = 0, upd_cls_cnt = 0, vals_cnt = 0, idx, idx2, idx3, i;
7467  PT_ASSIGNMENTS_HELPER ea;
7468  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *assignments, *spec, *class_spec, *check_where;
7469  DB_VALUE *dbvals = NULL;
7470  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO *cls_info = NULL, *cls_info_tmp = NULL;
7471  CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO *assigns = NULL, *assign = NULL, *assign2 = NULL;
7472 
7473  assign_cnt = vals_cnt = 0;
7474  assignments =
7475  statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.update.assignment : statement->info.update.assignment;
7476  spec = statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.into : statement->info.update.spec;
7477  class_spec = statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? NULL : statement->info.update.class_specs;
7478  check_where =
7479  statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.check_where : statement->info.update.check_where;
7480 
7481  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, assignments);
7482  while (pt_get_next_assignment (&ea))
7483  {
7484  if (!ea.is_rhs_const)
7485  {
7486  /* count values that are not constants */
7487  vals_cnt++;
7488  }
7489  /* count number of assignments */
7490  assign_cnt++;
7491  }
7492 
7493  /* allocate memory for assignment structures */
7494  assigns = (CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO *) db_private_alloc (NULL, assign_cnt * sizeof (CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO));
7495  if (assigns == NULL)
7496  {
7497  error = ER_REGU_NO_SPACE;
7498  goto error_return;
7499  }
7500  memset (assigns, 0, assign_cnt * sizeof (CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO));
7501 
7502  node = spec;
7503  while (node)
7504  {
7505  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
7506  {
7507  /* count classes that will be updated */
7508  upd_cls_cnt++;
7509  }
7510 
7511  node = node->next;
7512  }
7513 
7514  node = class_spec;
7515  while (node)
7516  {
7517  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
7518  {
7519  /* count classes that will be updated */
7520  upd_cls_cnt++;
7521  }
7522  node = node->next;
7523  }
7524 
7525  /* allocate array of classes information structures */
7526  cls_info = (CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO *) db_private_alloc (NULL, upd_cls_cnt * sizeof (CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO));
7527  if (cls_info == NULL)
7528  {
7529  error = ER_REGU_NO_SPACE;
7530  goto error_return;
7531  }
7532  memset (cls_info, 0, upd_cls_cnt * sizeof (CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO));
7533 
7534  /* add number of class oid's */
7535  vals_cnt += upd_cls_cnt;
7536  vals_cnt += has_delete;
7537  /* allocate array of DB_VALUE's. The length of the array must be equal to that of select statement's list */
7538  dbvals = (DB_VALUE *) db_private_alloc (NULL, (assign_cnt + upd_cls_cnt + has_delete) * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
7539  if (dbvals == NULL)
7540  {
7541  error = ER_REGU_NO_SPACE;
7542  goto error_return;
7543  }
7544 
7545  for (i = 0; i < assign_cnt + upd_cls_cnt + has_delete; i++)
7546  {
7547  db_make_null (&dbvals[i]);
7548  }
7549 
7550  /* initialize classes info array */
7551  idx = 0;
7552  node = spec;
7553  while (node)
7554  {
7555  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
7556  {
7557  PT_NODE *save = check_where;
7558 
7559  cls_info_tmp = &cls_info[idx++];
7560  cls_info_tmp->spec = node;
7561  cls_info_tmp->first_assign = NULL;
7562  cls_info_tmp->class_mop = NULL;
7563  cls_info_tmp->pruning_type = DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
7564  error = do_set_pruning_type (parser, node, cls_info_tmp);
7565  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7566  {
7567  goto error_return;
7568  }
7569  /* condition to check for 'with check option' option */
7570  while (check_where != NULL && check_where->info.check_option.spec_id != node->info.spec.id)
7571  {
7572  check_where = check_where->next;
7573  }
7574  cls_info_tmp->check_where = check_where;
7575 
7576  check_where = save;
7577  }
7578 
7579  node = node->next;
7580  }
7581 
7582  /* initialize classes info array */
7583  node = class_spec;
7584  while (node)
7585  {
7586  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
7587  {
7588  PT_NODE *save = check_where;
7589 
7590  cls_info_tmp = &cls_info[idx++];
7591  cls_info_tmp->spec = node;
7592  cls_info_tmp->first_assign = NULL;
7593  cls_info_tmp->class_mop = NULL;
7594  cls_info_tmp->pruning_type = DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
7595  error = do_set_pruning_type (parser, node, cls_info_tmp);
7596  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7597  {
7598  goto error_return;
7599  }
7600 
7601  /* condition to check for 'with check option' option */
7602  while (check_where != NULL && check_where->info.check_option.spec_id != node->info.spec.id)
7603  {
7604  check_where = check_where->next;
7605  }
7606  cls_info_tmp->check_where = check_where;
7607 
7608  check_where = save;
7609  }
7610 
7611  node = node->next;
7612  }
7613 
7614  /* Fill assignment structures */
7615  idx = 0;
7616  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, assignments);
7617  for (idx3 = 1, assign = assigns; pt_get_next_assignment (&ea); assign++)
7618  {
7619  assign->attr_desc = NULL;
7620  assign->upd_col_name = ea.lhs;
7621  /* Distribution of dbvals array. The array must match the select list of the generated select statement: first
7622  * upd_cls_cnt elements must be associated with OID representing tuple from a class, followed by values that must
7623  * be calculated at runtime for assignment and then by constants */
7624  if (ea.is_rhs_const)
7625  {
7626  /* constants */
7627  assign->db_val = &dbvals[assign_cnt + upd_cls_cnt + has_delete - idx3++];
7628  *assign->db_val = *pt_value_to_db (parser, ea.rhs);
7629  assign->is_const = true;
7630  }
7631  else
7632  {
7633  /* not constants */
7634  assign->db_val = &dbvals[upd_cls_cnt + has_delete + idx++];
7635  assign->is_const = false;
7636  }
7637 
7638  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < upd_cls_cnt; idx2++)
7639  {
7640  if (cls_info[idx2].spec->info.spec.id == ea.lhs->info.name.spec_id)
7641  {
7642  /* OIDs are in reverse order */
7643  cls_info[idx2].oid = &dbvals[upd_cls_cnt - idx2 - 1];
7644  /* attach class information to assignment */
7645  assign->cls_info = &cls_info[idx2];
7646  /* link assignment to its class info */
7647  if (cls_info[idx2].first_assign)
7648  {
7649  assign2 = cls_info[idx2].first_assign;
7650  while (assign2->next)
7651  {
7652  assign2 = assign2->next;
7653  }
7654  assign2->next = assign;
7655  }
7656  else
7657  {
7658  cls_info[idx2].first_assign = assign;
7659  }
7660  assign->next = NULL;
7661  break;
7662  }
7663  }
7664  }
7665 
7666  /* output computed data */
7667  *assigns_data = assigns;
7668  *assigns_count = assign_cnt;
7669  *cls_data = cls_info;
7670  *cls_count = upd_cls_cnt;
7671  *values = dbvals;
7672  *values_cnt = vals_cnt;
7673 
7674  return error;
7675 
7676 error_return:
7677  /* free class information array */
7678  if (cls_info)
7679  {
7680  db_private_free (NULL, cls_info);
7681  }
7682 
7683  /* free assignments information */
7684  if (assigns != NULL)
7685  {
7686  /* free attribute descriptors */
7687  for (idx = 0; idx < assign_cnt; idx++)
7688  {
7689  assign = &assigns[idx];
7690  if (assign->attr_desc)
7691  {
7692  db_free_attribute_descriptor (assign->attr_desc);
7693  }
7694  }
7695  db_private_free (NULL, assigns);
7696  }
7697 
7698  /* free dbvals array */
7699  if (dbvals != NULL)
7700  {
7701  db_private_free (NULL, dbvals);
7702  }
7703 
7704  return error;
7705 }
7706 
7707 /*
7708  * update_objs_for_list_file - Updates oid attributes for every oid
7709  * in a list file
7710  * return: Number of affected objects if success, otherwise an error code
7711  * parser(in): Parser context
7712  * list_id(in): A list file of oid's and values
7713  * statement(in): update statement
7714  * savepoint_started(in): true, if savepoint started
7715  *
7716  * Note:
7717  */
7718 static int
7719 update_objs_for_list_file (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, QFILE_LIST_ID * list_id, PT_NODE * statement,
7720  bool savepoint_started)
7721 {
7722  int error = NO_ERROR;
7723  int idx = 0, count = 0, assign_count = 0;
7724  int upd_cls_cnt = 0, vals_cnt = 0;
7725  CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO *assigns = NULL, *assign = NULL;
7726  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO *cls_info = NULL;
7727  int turn_off_unique_check;
7728  int turn_off_server_serializable_conflict_check;
7729  CURSOR_ID cursor_id;
7730  DB_VALUE *dbvals = NULL;
7731  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
7732  int cursor_status;
7733  PT_NODE *check_where;
7734  bool has_unique, has_trigger;
7735  bool has_delete, should_delete = false;
7736  bool client_check_serializable_conflict = false;
7737 
7738  if (list_id == NULL || statement == NULL)
7739  {
7740  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, __FILE__, __LINE__, ER_REGU_SYSTEM, 0);
7741  error = ER_REGU_SYSTEM;
7742  goto done;
7743  }
7744 
7745  check_where =
7746  statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.check_where : statement->info.update.check_where;
7747  has_unique =
7748  statement->node_type ==
7749  PT_MERGE ? (statement->info.merge.flags & PT_MERGE_INFO_HAS_UNIQUE) : statement->info.update.has_unique;
7750  /* For merge stmt, the savepoint has already been added in do_merge() or do_execute_merge(). we do not need to check
7751  * the trigger any more. */
7752  has_trigger = (statement->node_type == PT_UPDATE && statement->info.update.has_trigger);
7753  has_delete = (statement->node_type == PT_MERGE && statement->info.merge.update.has_delete);
7754 
7755  /* load data in update structures */
7756  error =
7757  init_update_data (parser, statement, &assigns, &assign_count, &cls_info, &upd_cls_cnt, &dbvals, &vals_cnt,
7758  has_delete);
7759  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7760  {
7761  goto done;
7762  }
7763 
7764  /* if the list file contains more than 1 object we need to savepoint the statement to guarantee statement atomicity. */
7765  if (list_id->tuple_cnt > 1 || check_where || has_unique || has_trigger || TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ)
7766  {
7767  if (savepoint_started == false)
7768  {
7769  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UusP", &update_savepoint_number);
7770  error = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
7771  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7772  {
7773  goto done;
7774  }
7775  }
7776  }
7777 
7778  /* 'turn_off_unique_check' is used when call update_object_tuple(). */
7779  if (list_id->tuple_cnt == 1 && upd_cls_cnt == 1)
7780  {
7781  /* Instance level uniqueness and SERIALIZABLE conflict checking is performed on the server when a new single row
7782  * is inserted. */
7783  turn_off_unique_check = 0;
7784  turn_off_server_serializable_conflict_check = 0;
7785  }
7786  else
7787  {
7788  /* list_id->tuple_cnt > 1 : multiple row update Statement level uniqueness checking and SERIALIZABLE conflict is
7789  * performed on the client */
7790  turn_off_unique_check = 1;
7791  turn_off_server_serializable_conflict_check = 1;
7792  }
7793 
7794  /* open cursor */
7795  if (!cursor_open (&cursor_id, list_id, false, false))
7796  {
7797  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
7798  if (savepoint_name && (error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
7799  {
7800  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
7801  }
7802  goto done;
7803  }
7804  cursor_id.query_id = parser->query_id;
7805 
7806  /* set prefetching lock mode to WRITE access since we'll be updating all the objects in the list file. */
7807  (void) cursor_set_prefetch_lock_mode (&cursor_id, DB_FETCH_WRITE);
7808 
7809  cursor_status = cursor_next_tuple (&cursor_id);
7810 
7811  while (cursor_status == DB_CURSOR_SUCCESS)
7812  {
7813  /* read OIDs and runtime computed values */
7814  if (cursor_get_tuple_value_list (&cursor_id, vals_cnt, dbvals) != NO_ERROR)
7815  {
7816  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7817  error = er_errid ();
7818  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
7819  if (savepoint_name && (error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
7820  {
7821  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
7822  }
7823  goto done;
7824  }
7825 
7826  if (has_delete)
7827  {
7828  /* We may get NULL as an expr value. See pt_to_merge_update_query(...). */
7829  if (DB_IS_NULL (&dbvals[upd_cls_cnt]))
7830  {
7831  should_delete = false;
7832  }
7833  else
7834  {
7835  should_delete = db_get_int (&dbvals[upd_cls_cnt]);
7836  }
7837  }
7838 
7839  /* perform update for current tuples */
7840  error =
7841  update_object_tuple (parser, assigns, assign_count, cls_info, upd_cls_cnt, turn_off_unique_check,
7842  turn_off_server_serializable_conflict_check, NORMAL_UPDATE, should_delete);
7843 
7844  /* close cursor and restore to savepoint in case of error */
7845  if (error < NO_ERROR)
7846  {
7847 #if 0 /* TODO */
7848  /* mq_evaluate_check_option () do not er_set () */
7849  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7850 #endif
7851  error = er_errid ();
7852  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
7853  if (savepoint_name && (error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
7854  {
7855  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
7856  }
7857  goto done;
7858  }
7859 
7860  count += error; /* number of objects affected. Incorrect for multi-table update !!! */
7861  cursor_status = cursor_next_tuple (&cursor_id);
7862  }
7863 
7864  /* close cursor and restore to savepoint in case of error */
7865  if (cursor_status != DB_CURSOR_END)
7866  {
7867  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
7868  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
7869  if (savepoint_name && (error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
7870  {
7871  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
7872  }
7873  goto done;
7874  }
7875  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
7876 
7877  if (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ && turn_off_server_serializable_conflict_check)
7878  {
7879  /* activate SERIALIZABLE conflict checks */
7880  client_check_serializable_conflict = true;
7881  }
7882 
7883  /* check uniques or SERIALIZABLE conflicts if not already checked */
7884  if (has_unique || client_check_serializable_conflict)
7885  {
7886  /* need to check unique or SERIALIZABLE conflicts */
7887  for (idx = upd_cls_cnt - 1; idx >= 0; idx--)
7888  {
7889  if (!(cls_info[idx].spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_HAS_UNIQUE) && !client_check_serializable_conflict)
7890  {
7891  /* if not unique and don't want to check SERIALIZABLE conflict */
7892  continue;
7893  }
7894  error = sm_flush_for_multi_update (cls_info[idx].spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object);
7895  /* if error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
7896  * transaction itself. */
7897  if ((error < NO_ERROR) && savepoint_name && (error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
7898  {
7899  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
7900  break;
7901  }
7902  }
7903  }
7904 
7905 done:
7906  /* free classes information array */
7907  if (cls_info)
7908  {
7909  db_private_free (NULL, cls_info);
7910  }
7911 
7912  /* free assignments information */
7913  if (assigns != NULL)
7914  {
7915  /* free attributes descriptors */
7916  for (idx = 0; idx < assign_count; idx++)
7917  {
7918  assign = &assigns[idx];
7919  if (assign->attr_desc)
7920  {
7921  db_free_attribute_descriptor (assign->attr_desc);
7922  }
7923  }
7924  db_private_free (NULL, assigns);
7925  }
7926 
7927  /* free values array */
7928  if (dbvals != NULL)
7929  {
7930  db_private_free (NULL, dbvals);
7931  }
7932 
7933  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
7934  {
7935  return count;
7936  }
7937  else
7938  {
7939  return error;
7940  }
7941 }
7942 
7943 /*
7944  * update_class_attributes - Returns corresponding lists of names and expressions
7945  * return: Error code
7946  * parser(in): Parser context
7947  * statement(in): update statement
7948  *
7949  * Note:
7950  */
7951 static int
7952 update_class_attributes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
7953 {
7954  int error = NO_ERROR;
7955  DB_OTMPL *otemplate = NULL;
7956  PT_NODE *rhs = NULL, *assignments = NULL;
7957  PT_ASSIGNMENTS_HELPER ea;
7958  int idx = 0, assigns_count = 0;
7959  int upd_cls_cnt = 0, vals_cnt = 0, multi_assign_cnt = 0;
7960  CLIENT_UPDATE_INFO *assigns = NULL, *assign = NULL;
7961  CLIENT_UPDATE_CLASS_INFO *cls_info = NULL, *cls = NULL;
7962  DB_VALUE *dbvals = NULL;
7963 
7964  assignments =
7965  statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.update.assignment : statement->info.update.assignment;
7966 
7967  /* load data for update */
7968  error =
7969  init_update_data (parser, statement, &assigns, &assigns_count, &cls_info, &upd_cls_cnt, &dbvals, &vals_cnt, false);
7970  if (error == NO_ERROR)
7971  {
7972  /* evaluate values for assignment */
7973  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, assignments);
7974  for (idx = 0; idx < assigns_count && error == NO_ERROR; idx += multi_assign_cnt)
7975  {
7976  assign = &assigns[idx];
7977  cls = assign->cls_info;
7978 
7979  pt_get_next_assignment (&ea);
7980  rhs = ea.rhs;
7981  multi_assign_cnt = 1;
7982  if (ea.is_n_column)
7983  {
7984  while (pt_get_next_assignment (&ea) && rhs == ea.rhs)
7985  {
7986  multi_assign_cnt++;
7987  }
7988  }
7989 
7990  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, rhs, assign->db_val, multi_assign_cnt);
7991  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7992  {
7993  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
7994  }
7995  }
7996  }
7997 
7998  /* execute assignments */
7999  if (error == NO_ERROR)
8000  {
8001  for (idx = 0; idx < upd_cls_cnt && error == NO_ERROR; idx++)
8002  {
8003  cls = &cls_info[idx];
8004 
8005  otemplate = dbt_edit_object (cls->spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object);
8006  for (assign = cls->first_assign; assign != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; assign = assign->next)
8007  {
8008  error = dbt_put_internal (otemplate, assign->upd_col_name->info.name.original, assign->db_val);
8009  }
8010  if (error == NO_ERROR && dbt_finish_object (otemplate) == NULL)
8011  {
8012  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8013  error = er_errid ();
8014  (void) dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
8015  }
8016  }
8017  }
8018 
8019  /* free assignments array */
8020  if (assigns != NULL)
8021  {
8022  /* free attributes descriptors */
8023  for (idx = assigns_count - 1; idx >= 0; idx--)
8024  {
8025  if (assigns[idx].attr_desc)
8026  {
8027  db_free_attribute_descriptor (assigns[idx].attr_desc);
8028  }
8029  }
8030  db_private_free (NULL, assigns);
8031  }
8032 
8033  /* free classes info array */
8034  if (cls_info != NULL)
8035  {
8036  db_private_free (NULL, cls_info);
8037  }
8038 
8039  /* free values array */
8040  if (dbvals != NULL)
8041  {
8042  db_private_free (NULL, dbvals);
8043  }
8044 
8045  return error;
8046 }
8047 
8048 /*
8049  * statement_to_update_xasl - Converts an update parse tree to
8050  * an XASL graph for an update
8051  * parser(in): Parser context
8052  * statement(in): Parse tree of a update statement
8053  * non_null_attrs(in):
8054  *
8055  * Note:
8056  */
8057 static XASL_NODE *
8058 statement_to_update_xasl (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_NODE ** non_null_attrs)
8059 {
8060  return pt_to_update_xasl (parser, statement, non_null_attrs);
8061 }
8062 
8063 /*
8064  * init_compile_context() -
8065  *
8066  * parser (in/out):
8067  *
8068  */
8069 static void
8070 init_compile_context (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
8071 {
8072  memset (&parser->context, 0x00, sizeof (COMPILE_CONTEXT));
8073  parser->context.is_xasl_pinned_reference = (bool) parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference;
8074  parser->context.recompile_xasl_pinned = (bool) parser->recompile_xasl_pinned;
8075 }
8076 
8077 /*
8078  * init_xasl_stream() - init XASL_STREAM
8079  *
8080  * stream (in): initialized parameter
8081  *
8082  */
8083 static void
8084 init_xasl_stream (XASL_STREAM * stream)
8085 {
8086  memset (stream, 0x00, sizeof (XASL_STREAM));
8087 }
8088 
8089 /*
8090  * update_at_server - Build an xasl tree for a server update and execute it
8091  * return: Tuple count if success, otherwise an error code
8092  * parser(in): Parser context
8093  * from(in): Class spec to update
8094  * statement(in): Parse tree of a update statement
8095  * non_null_attrs(in):
8096  * has_uniques(in):
8097  *
8098  * Note:
8099  * The xasl tree has an UPDATE_PROC node as the top node and
8100  * a BUILDLIST_PROC as its aptr. The BUILDLIST_PROC selects the
8101  * instance OID and any update attribute expression values.
8102  * The UPDATE_PROC node scans the BUILDLIST_PROC results.
8103  * The UPDATE_PROC node contains the attribute ID's and values
8104  * for update constants. The server executes the aptr and then
8105  * for each instance selected, updates it with the attribute expression
8106  * values and constants. The result information is sent back to the
8107  * client as a list file without any pages. The list file tuple count
8108  * is used as the return value from this routine.
8109  *
8110  * The instances for the class are flushed from the client before the
8111  * update is executed. If any instances are updated, the instances are
8112  * decached from the client after the update is executed.
8113  *
8114  * It is assumed that class attributes and regular attributes
8115  * are not mixed in the same update statement.
8116  */
8117 static int
8118 update_at_server (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * from, PT_NODE * statement, PT_NODE ** non_null_attrs,
8119  int has_uniques)
8120 {
8121  int error = NO_ERROR;
8122  int i;
8123  XASL_NODE *xasl = NULL;
8124  int count = 0;
8125  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
8126  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
8127  PT_NODE *cl_name_node = NULL, *spec = NULL;
8128 
8129  XASL_STREAM stream;
8130 
8131  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
8132 
8133  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
8134 
8135  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
8136  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
8137 
8138  xasl = statement_to_update_xasl (parser, statement, non_null_attrs);
8139  if (xasl)
8140  {
8141  UPDATE_PROC_NODE *update = &xasl->proc.update;
8142 
8143  error = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (xasl, &stream);
8144  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8145  {
8146  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
8147  }
8148 
8149  for (i = 0; i < update->num_assigns; i++)
8150  {
8151  if (update->assigns[i].constant)
8152  {
8153  pr_clear_value (update->assigns[i].constant);
8154  }
8155  }
8156  }
8157  else
8158  {
8159  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8160  error = er_errid ();
8161  }
8162 
8163  if (error == NO_ERROR)
8164  {
8165  int au_save;
8166  QUERY_FLAG query_flag;
8167 
8168  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
8169 
8170  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
8171  {
8172  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
8173  }
8174 
8175  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
8176 
8177  error =
8178  prepare_and_execute_query (stream.buffer, stream.buffer_size, &parser->query_id,
8179  parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count, parser->host_variables, &list_id,
8180  query_flag);
8181  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
8182  }
8183 
8184  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
8185  if (stream.buffer)
8186  {
8187  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
8188  }
8189 
8190  if (list_id)
8191  {
8192  count = list_id->tuple_cnt;
8193  if (count > 0)
8194  {
8195  spec = statement->info.update.spec;
8196  while (spec)
8197  {
8198  for (cl_name_node = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list; cl_name_node && error == NO_ERROR;
8199  cl_name_node = cl_name_node->next)
8200  {
8201  if (statement->use_auto_commit && tran_was_latest_query_committed ())
8202  {
8203  /* Nothing to flush. Avoids flush, since may fetch the class. */
8204  error = sm_decache_instances_after_query_executed_with_commit (cl_name_node->info.name.db_object);
8205  }
8206  else
8207  {
8208  error = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (cl_name_node->info.name.db_object, true);
8209  }
8210 
8211  }
8212  spec = spec->next;
8213  }
8214  }
8215  regu_free_listid (list_id);
8216  }
8217  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
8218 
8219  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
8220  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
8221 
8222  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
8223  {
8224  return count;
8225  }
8226  else
8227  {
8228  return error;
8229  }
8230 }
8231 
8232 /*
8233  * update_check_for_constraints - Determine whether attributes of the target
8234  * classes have UNIQUE and/or NOT NULL
8235  * constraints, and return a list of NOT NULL
8236  * attributes if exist
8237  * return: Error code
8238  * parser(in): Parser context
8239  * has_unique(out): Indicator representing there is UNIQUE constraint, 1 or 0
8240  * not_nulls(out): A list of pointers to NOT NULL attributes, or NULL
8241  * statement(in): Parse tree of an UPDATE or MERGE statement
8242  *
8243  * Note:
8244  */
8245 static int
8246 update_check_for_constraints (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, int *has_unique, PT_NODE ** not_nulls, const PT_NODE * statement)
8247 {
8248  int error = NO_ERROR;
8249  PT_NODE *lhs = NULL, *att = NULL, *pointer = NULL, *spec = NULL;
8250  PT_NODE *assignment = NULL;
8251  DB_OBJECT *class_obj = NULL;
8252 
8253  assignment =
8254  statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.update.assignment : statement->info.update.assignment;
8255 
8256  *has_unique = 0;
8257  *not_nulls = NULL;
8258 
8259  for (; assignment; assignment = assignment->next)
8260  {
8261  lhs = assignment->info.expr.arg1;
8262  if (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME)
8263  {
8264  att = lhs;
8265  }
8266  else if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
8267  {
8268  att = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
8269  }
8270  else
8271  {
8272  /* bullet proofing, should not get here */
8273 #if defined(CUBRID_DEBUG)
8274  fprintf (stdout, "system error detected in %s, line %d.\n", __FILE__, __LINE__);
8275 #endif
8276  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
8277  goto exit_on_error;
8278  }
8279 
8280  for (; att; att = att->next)
8281  {
8282  if (att->node_type != PT_NAME)
8283  {
8284  /* bullet proofing, should not get here */
8285 #if defined(CUBRID_DEBUG)
8286  fprintf (stdout, "system error detected in %s, line %d.\n", __FILE__, __LINE__);
8287 #endif
8288  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
8289  goto exit_on_error;
8290  }
8291 
8292  spec = pt_find_spec_in_statement (parser, statement, att);
8293  if (spec == NULL || (class_obj = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object) == NULL)
8294  {
8295  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
8296  goto exit_on_error;
8297  }
8298 
8299  if ((spec->info.spec.flag & (PT_SPEC_FLAG_HAS_UNIQUE | PT_SPEC_FLAG_DOESNT_HAVE_UNIQUE)) == 0)
8300  {
8301  bool has_unique_temp = false;
8302  bool check_subclasses = (spec->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL);
8303 
8304  error = sm_class_has_unique_constraint (NULL, class_obj, check_subclasses, &has_unique_temp);
8305  if (error == NO_ERROR)
8306  {
8307  if (has_unique_temp)
8308  {
8309  *has_unique = 1;
8310  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_HAS_UNIQUE);
8311  }
8312  else
8313  {
8314  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_DOESNT_HAVE_UNIQUE);
8315  }
8316  }
8317  else
8318  {
8319  goto exit_on_error;
8320  }
8321 
8322  }
8323  if (sm_att_constrained (class_obj, att->info.name.original, SM_ATTFLAG_NON_NULL))
8324  {
8325  pointer = pt_point (parser, att);
8326  if (pointer == NULL)
8327  {
8328  PT_ERRORm (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
8329  error = MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED;
8330  goto exit_on_error;
8331  }
8332  *not_nulls = parser_append_node (pointer, *not_nulls);
8333  }
8334  } /* for ( ; attr; ...) */
8335  } /* for ( ; assignment; ...) */
8336 
8337  return NO_ERROR;
8338 
8339 exit_on_error:
8340  if (*not_nulls)
8341  {
8342  parser_free_tree (parser, *not_nulls);
8343  *not_nulls = NULL;
8344  }
8345  return error;
8346 }
8347 
8348 /*
8349  * update_check_for_meta_attr () -
8350  * return: true if update assignment clause has class or shared attribute
8351  * parser(in): Parser context
8352  * assignment(in): Parse tree of an assignment clause
8353  *
8354  * Note:
8355  */
8356 static bool
8357 update_check_having_meta_attr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * assignment)
8358 {
8359  PT_NODE *lhs, *att;
8360 
8361  for (; assignment; assignment = assignment->next)
8362  {
8363  lhs = assignment->info.expr.arg1;
8364  if (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME)
8365  {
8366  att = lhs;
8367  }
8368  else if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
8369  {
8370  att = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
8371  }
8372  else
8373  {
8374  att = NULL;
8375  }
8376 
8377  for (; att; att = att->next)
8378  {
8379  if (att->node_type == PT_NAME && att->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
8380  {
8381  return true;
8382  }
8383  }
8384  }
8385 
8386  return false;
8387 }
8388 
8389 /*
8390  * update_real_class() -
8391  * return: Error code if update fails
8392  * parser(in): Parser context
8393  * statement(in): Parse tree of a update statement
8394  * savepoint_started(in): true, if savepoint started
8395  *
8396  * Note: If the statement is of type "update class foo ...", this
8397  * routine updates class attributes of foo. If the statement is of
8398  * type "update foo ...", this routine updates objects or rows in foo.
8399  * It is assumed that class attributes and regular attributes
8400  * are not mixed in the same update statement.
8401  */
8402 static int
8403 update_real_class (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, bool savepoint_started)
8404 {
8405  int error = NO_ERROR;
8406  PT_NODE *non_null_attrs = NULL, *spec = statement->info.update.spec;
8407  DB_OBJECT *class_obj = NULL;
8408  int server_allowed = 0;
8409  int has_uniques = 0;
8410  PT_NODE **links = NULL;
8411 
8412  /* update a "real" class in this database */
8413 
8414  while (spec)
8415  {
8416  /* Safety check: make sure that we have access to the class. We're only setting a weak lock here which guarantees
8417  * that the schema for the classes which are updated in this query is not changed. The correct lock for this
8418  * operation will be set server side when the SELECT part of the operation is being performed. */
8419  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
8420  {
8421  class_obj = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
8422  if (!locator_fetch_class (class_obj, DB_FETCH_READ))
8423  {
8424  goto exit_on_error;
8425  }
8426  }
8427  spec = spec->next;
8428  }
8429 
8430  if (is_server_update_allowed (parser, &non_null_attrs, &has_uniques, &server_allowed, statement) != NO_ERROR)
8431  {
8432  goto exit_on_error;
8433  }
8434 
8435  if (server_allowed)
8436  {
8437  /* do update on server */
8438  error = update_at_server (parser, spec, statement, &non_null_attrs, has_uniques);
8439  }
8440  else
8441  {
8442  PT_NODE *lhs = NULL;
8443  PT_NODE *select_names = NULL;
8444  PT_NODE *select_values = NULL;
8445  PT_NODE *const_names = NULL;
8446  PT_NODE *const_values = NULL;
8447  QFILE_LIST_ID *oid_list = NULL;
8448  int no_vals = 0;
8449  int no_consts = 0;
8450  int wait_msecs = -2;
8451  int old_wait_msecs = -2;
8452  float hint_waitsecs;
8453 
8454  /* do update on client */
8455  lhs = statement->info.update.assignment->info.expr.arg1;
8456  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
8457  {
8458  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
8459  }
8460  if (lhs->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_ATTR)
8461  {
8462  QUERY_ID query_id_self;
8463  PT_NODE *hint_arg;
8464 
8465  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
8466  parser->query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
8467 
8468  hint_arg = statement->info.update.waitsecs_hint;
8469  if (statement->info.update.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
8470  {
8471  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
8472  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
8473  {
8474  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
8475  }
8476  else
8477  {
8478  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
8479  }
8480  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
8481  {
8482  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
8483  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
8484  }
8485  }
8486  if (error == NO_ERROR)
8487  {
8488  error =
8489  pt_get_assignment_lists (parser, &select_names, &select_values, &const_names, &const_values, &no_vals,
8490  &no_consts, statement->info.update.assignment, &links);
8491  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8492  {
8493  goto exit_on_error;
8494  }
8495  /* get the oid's and new values */
8496  oid_list =
8497  get_select_list_to_update (parser, statement->info.update.spec, select_names, select_values,
8498  statement->info.update.with, statement->info.update.search_cond,
8499  statement->info.update.order_by, statement->info.update.orderby_for,
8500  statement->info.update.using_index, statement->info.update.class_specs,
8501  statement);
8502 
8503  /* restore tree structure */
8504  pt_restore_assignment_links (statement->info.update.assignment, links, -1);
8505  }
8506  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
8507  {
8508  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
8509  }
8510 
8511  if (!oid_list)
8512  {
8513  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
8514  /* an error should be set already, don't lose it */
8515  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
8516  goto exit_on_error;
8517  }
8518 
8519  /* update each oid */
8520  error = update_objs_for_list_file (parser, oid_list, statement, savepoint_started);
8521 
8522  regu_free_listid (oid_list);
8523  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
8524  }
8525  else
8526  {
8527  /* we are updating class attributes */
8528  error = update_class_attributes (parser, statement);
8529  }
8530  }
8531 
8532  if (non_null_attrs != NULL)
8533  {
8534  parser_free_tree (parser, non_null_attrs);
8535  non_null_attrs = NULL;
8536  }
8537 
8538  return error;
8539 
8540 exit_on_error:
8541 
8542  if (error == NO_ERROR)
8543  {
8544  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8545  error = er_errid ();
8546  }
8547  if (non_null_attrs != NULL)
8548  {
8549  parser_free_tree (parser, non_null_attrs);
8550  non_null_attrs = NULL;
8551  }
8552  return error;
8553 }
8554 
8555 /*
8556  * is_server_update_allowed() - Checks to see if a server-side update is
8557  * allowed
8558  * return: NO_ERROR or error code on failure
8559  * parser(in): Parser context
8560  * non_null_attrs(in/out): Parse tree for attributes with the NOT NULL
8561  * constraint
8562  * has_uniques(in/out): whether unique indexes are affected by the update
8563  * server_allowed(in/out): whether the update can be executed on the server
8564  * statement(in): Parse tree of an update statement
8565  */
8566 static int
8567 is_server_update_allowed (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE ** non_null_attrs, int *has_uniques,
8568  int *const server_allowed, const PT_NODE * statement)
8569 {
8570  int error = NO_ERROR;
8571  int is_partition = 0;
8572  int trigger_involved = 0, ti = 0, is_virt = 0;
8573  PT_NODE *spec = statement->info.update.spec;
8574  DB_OBJECT *class_obj = NULL;
8575  int save_au;
8576 
8577  *has_uniques = 0;
8578  *server_allowed = 0;
8579 
8580  AU_DISABLE (save_au);
8581 
8582  /* check if at least one spec that will be updated is virtual or has triggers */
8583  while (spec && !trigger_involved && !is_virt)
8584  {
8585  if (!(spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE))
8586  {
8587  spec = spec->next;
8588  continue;
8589  }
8590  class_obj = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
8591  error = sm_partitioned_class_type (class_obj, &is_partition, NULL, NULL);
8592  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8593  {
8594  goto error_exit;
8595  }
8596 
8597  /* If the class is partitioned and has any type of trigger, the update must be executed on the client. */
8598  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &ti, (is_partition ? TR_EVENT_ALL : TR_EVENT_UPDATE));
8599  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8600  {
8601  goto error_exit;
8602  }
8603 
8604  if (ti)
8605  {
8606  trigger_involved = ti;
8607  }
8608 
8609  is_virt = (spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.virt_object != NULL);
8610 
8611  spec = spec->next;
8612  }
8613 
8614  error = update_check_for_constraints (parser, has_uniques, non_null_attrs, statement);
8615  if (error < NO_ERROR)
8616  {
8617  goto error_exit;
8618  }
8619 
8620  /* Check to see if the update can be done on the server */
8621  *server_allowed = ((!trigger_involved && !is_virt)
8622  && !update_check_having_meta_attr (parser, statement->info.update.assignment));
8623 
8624  AU_ENABLE (save_au);
8625  return error;
8626 
8627 error_exit:
8628  if (non_null_attrs != NULL && *non_null_attrs != NULL)
8629  {
8630  parser_free_tree (parser, *non_null_attrs);
8631  *non_null_attrs = NULL;
8632  }
8633  AU_ENABLE (save_au);
8634  return error;
8635 }
8636 
8637 /*
8638  * do_update() - Updates objects or rows
8639  * return: Error code if update fails
8640  * parser(in): Parser context
8641  * statement(in): Parse tree of a update statement
8642  *
8643  * Note:
8644  */
8645 int
8646 do_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
8647 {
8648  int error = NO_ERROR;
8649  int result = NO_ERROR;
8650  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
8651  bool savepoint_started = false;
8652 
8653  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
8654 
8655  /* DON'T REMOVE this, correct authorization validation of views depends on this. DON'T return from the body of this
8656  * function. Break out of the loop if necessary. */
8657  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
8658 
8659  /* savepoint for statement atomicity */
8660  if ((statement != NULL && statement->next != NULL)
8661  || (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ
8662  && (statement->info.update.object != NULL || !statement->info.update.server_update)))
8663  {
8664  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UmusP", &update_savepoint_number);
8665  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
8666  {
8667  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
8668  goto end;
8669  }
8670  error = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
8671  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8672  {
8673  goto end;
8674  }
8675 
8676  savepoint_started = true;
8677  }
8678 
8679  while (statement && (error >= 0))
8680  {
8681  if (statement->node_type != PT_UPDATE || statement->info.update.assignment == NULL)
8682  {
8683  /* bullet proofing, should not get here */
8684  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
8685  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
8686  break;
8687  }
8688 
8689  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
8690  {
8691  /* nothing to update, where part is false */
8692  }
8693  else if (statement->info.update.object != NULL)
8694  {
8695  /* this is a update object if it has an object */
8696  error = update_object_by_oid (parser, statement, UPDATE_OBJECT);
8697  }
8698  else
8699  {
8700  /* the following is the "normal" sql type execution */
8701  error = update_real_class (parser, statement, savepoint_started);
8702  }
8703 
8704  if (error < NO_ERROR && er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
8705  {
8706  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number,
8707  er_msg (), NULL);
8708  }
8709 
8710  result += error;
8711  statement = statement->next;
8712  }
8713 
8714  /* if error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
8715  * transaction. */
8716  if (error < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
8717  {
8718  db_abort_to_savepoint (savepoint_name);
8719  }
8720 
8721 end:
8722  if (error < 0)
8723  {
8724  result = error;
8725  }
8726 
8727  /* DON'T REMOVE this, correct authorization validation of views depends on this. */
8728  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
8729 
8730  return result;
8731 }
8732 
8733 /*
8734  * do_prepare_update() - Prepare the UPDATE statement
8735  * return: Error code
8736  * parser(in): Parser context
8737  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a update statement
8738  *
8739  * Note:
8740  */
8741 int
8742 do_prepare_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
8743 {
8744  int err;
8745  PT_NODE *flat, *not_nulls, *lhs, *spec = NULL;
8746  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
8747  int has_trigger, has_unique, has_any_update_trigger, au_save, has_virt = 0;
8748  bool server_update;
8749 
8750  if (parser == NULL || statement == NULL)
8751  {
8752  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
8753  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
8754  }
8755 
8756  for (err = NO_ERROR; statement && (err >= NO_ERROR); statement = statement->next)
8757  {
8758  COMPILE_CONTEXT *contextp;
8759  XASL_STREAM stream;
8760 
8761  contextp = &parser->context;
8762 
8763  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
8764 
8765  contextp->sql_user_text = statement->sql_user_text;
8766  contextp->sql_user_text_len = statement->sql_user_text_len;
8767 
8768  /* there can be no results, this is a compile time false where clause */
8769  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
8770  {
8771  /* tell to the execute routine that there's no XASL to execute */
8772  statement->xasl_id = NULL;
8773  err = NO_ERROR;
8774  continue; /* continue to next UPDATE statement */
8775  }
8776 
8777  /*
8778  * Update object case:
8779  * this is a update object if it has an object
8780  */
8781  if (statement->info.update.object)
8782  {
8783  statement->etc = NULL;
8784  err = NO_ERROR;
8785  continue; /* continue to next UPDATE statement */
8786  }
8787 
8788  /* if already prepared */
8789  if (statement->xasl_id)
8790  {
8791  continue; /* continue to next UPDATE statement */
8792  }
8793 
8794  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save); /* because sm_class_has_trigger() calls au_fetch_class() */
8795 
8796  /* check if at least one spec to be updated has triggers. If none has triggers then see if at least one is
8797  * virtual */
8798  spec = statement->info.update.spec;
8799  has_trigger = 0;
8800  has_any_update_trigger = 0;
8801  while (spec && !has_trigger && err == NO_ERROR)
8802  {
8803  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
8804  {
8805  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
8806  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
8807  assert (class_obj); /* safeguard */
8808  /* the presence of a proxy trigger should force the update to be performed through the workspace */
8809  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_UPDATE);
8810 
8811  if (err == NO_ERROR)
8812  {
8813  if (has_trigger)
8814  {
8815  has_any_update_trigger = has_trigger;
8816  }
8817  else if (!has_any_update_trigger)
8818  {
8819  /* Check for statement delete triggerrs. */
8820  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_any_update_trigger, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE);
8821  }
8822  }
8823 
8824  if (!has_virt)
8825  {
8826  has_virt = (flat->info.name.virt_object != NULL);
8827  }
8828  }
8829 
8830  spec = spec->next;
8831  }
8832  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
8833 
8834  /* err = has_proxy_trigger(flat, &has_trigger); */
8835  if (err != NO_ERROR)
8836  {
8837  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
8838  break; /* stop while loop if error */
8839  }
8840  /* sm_class_has_triggers() checked if the class has active triggers */
8841  statement->info.update.has_trigger = (bool) has_trigger;
8842 
8843  /* check if the target class has UNIQUE constraint and get attributes that has NOT NULL constraint */
8844  err = update_check_for_constraints (parser, &has_unique, &not_nulls, statement);
8845  if (err < NO_ERROR)
8846  {
8847  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
8848  break; /* stop while loop if error */
8849  }
8850 
8851  statement->info.update.has_unique = (bool) has_unique;
8852 
8853  /* determine whether it can be server-side or OID list update */
8854  server_update = (!has_trigger && !has_virt
8855  && !update_check_having_meta_attr (parser, statement->info.update.assignment));
8856 
8857  lhs = statement->info.update.assignment->info.expr.arg1;
8858  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
8859  {
8860  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
8861  }
8862  statement->info.update.server_update = server_update;
8863  if (server_update && !has_any_update_trigger)
8864  {
8865  statement->info.update.execute_with_commit_allowed = 1;
8866  }
8867 
8868  /* if we are updating class attributes, not need to prepare */
8869  if (lhs->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR)
8870  {
8871  statement->info.update.do_class_attrs = true;
8872  continue; /* continue to next UPDATE statement */
8873  }
8874 
8875  if (server_update)
8876  {
8877  /*
8878  * Server-side update case: (by requesting server to execute XASL)
8879  * build UPDATE_PROC XASL
8880  */
8881 
8882  /* make query string */
8883  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 1;
8884  parser->long_string_skipped = 0;
8885  parser->print_type_ambiguity = 0;
8886  PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS (parser, statement, (PT_CONVERT_RANGE | PT_PRINT_QUOTES | PT_PRINT_USER));
8887  contextp->sql_hash_text = (char *) statement->alias_print;
8888  err =
8889  SHA1Compute ((unsigned char *) contextp->sql_hash_text, (unsigned) strlen (contextp->sql_hash_text),
8890  &contextp->sha1);
8891  if (err != NO_ERROR)
8892  {
8893  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8894  return err;
8895  }
8896  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 0;
8897  if (parser->long_string_skipped || parser->print_type_ambiguity)
8898  {
8899  statement->cannot_prepare = 1;
8900  return NO_ERROR;
8901  }
8902  }
8903 
8904  stream.xasl_id = NULL;
8905  if (server_update)
8906  {
8907  /*
8908  * Server-side update case: (by requesting server to execute XASL)
8909  * build UPDATE_PROC XASL
8910  */
8911 
8912  /* look up server's XASL cache for this query string and get XASL file id (XASL_ID) returned if found */
8913  contextp->recompile_xasl = statement->recompile;
8914  if (statement->recompile == 0)
8915  {
8916  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
8917 
8918  if (err != NO_ERROR)
8919  {
8920  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (err);
8921  }
8922  else if (contextp->recompile_xasl == true)
8923  {
8924  /* recompile requested by server */
8925  if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
8926  {
8927  free_and_init (stream.xasl_id);
8928  }
8929  }
8930  }
8931 
8932  if (stream.xasl_id == NULL && err == NO_ERROR)
8933  {
8934  /* cache not found; make XASL from the parse tree including query optimization and plan generation */
8935 
8936  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
8937  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
8938 
8939  /* this prevents authorization checking during generating XASL */
8940  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
8941 
8942  /* pt_to_update_xasl() will build XASL tree from parse tree */
8943  contextp->xasl = pt_to_update_xasl (parser, statement, &not_nulls);
8944  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
8945 
8946  if (contextp->xasl && (err >= NO_ERROR))
8947  {
8948  int i;
8949  UPDATE_PROC_NODE *update = &contextp->xasl->proc.update;
8950 
8951  /* convert the created XASL tree to the byte stream for transmission to the server */
8952  err = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (contextp->xasl, &stream);
8953  if (err != NO_ERROR)
8954  {
8955  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
8956  }
8957  for (i = update->num_assigns - 1; i >= 0; i--)
8958  {
8959  if (update->assigns[i].constant)
8960  {
8961  pr_clear_value (update->assigns[i].constant);
8962  }
8963  }
8964  }
8965  else
8966  {
8967  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8968  err = er_errid ();
8969  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number,
8970  er_msg (), NULL);
8971  }
8972 
8973  /* request the server to prepare the query; give XASL stream generated from the parse tree and get XASL
8974  * file id returned */
8975  if (stream.buffer && (err >= NO_ERROR))
8976  {
8977  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
8978 
8979  if (err != NO_ERROR)
8980  {
8981  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8982  err = er_errid ();
8983  }
8984  }
8985 
8986  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
8987  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
8988 
8989  /* As a result of query preparation of the server, the XASL cache for this query will be created or
8990  * updated. */
8991 
8992  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
8993  if (stream.buffer)
8994  {
8995  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
8996  }
8997  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
8998  }
8999  else
9000  { /* if (!xasl_id) */
9001  spec = statement->info.update.spec;
9002  while (spec && err == NO_ERROR)
9003  {
9004  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
9005  while (flat)
9006  {
9007  if (locator_flush_class (flat->info.name.db_object) != NO_ERROR)
9008  {
9009  stream.xasl_id = NULL;
9010  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9011  err = er_errid ();
9012  break;
9013  }
9014  flat = flat->next;
9015  }
9016  spec = spec->next;
9017  }
9018  if (err == NO_ERROR)
9019  {
9020  statement->use_plan_cache = 1;
9021  }
9022  else
9023  {
9024  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
9025  }
9026  }
9027  }
9028  else
9029  { /* if (server_update) */
9030  /*
9031  * OID list update case: (by selecting OIDs to update)
9032  * make SELECT statement for this UPDATE statement
9033  */
9034  PT_NODE *select_statement = NULL;
9035  PT_NODE *select_names = NULL, *select_values = NULL;
9036  PT_NODE *const_names = NULL, *const_values = NULL;
9037  PT_NODE **links = NULL;
9038  int no_vals = 0, no_consts = 0;
9039 
9040  PT_NODE *assigns = statement->info.update.assignment;
9041  PT_NODE *from = statement->info.update.spec;
9042 
9043  if (statement->info.update.with != NULL)
9044  {
9045  /* client-side updates with CTEs are not supported for now */
9046  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
9047  break;
9048  }
9049 
9050  err = pt_append_omitted_on_update_expr_assignments (parser, assigns, from);
9051  if (err != NO_ERROR)
9052  {
9053  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
9054  break; /* stop while loop if error */
9055  }
9056 
9057  err = pt_get_assignment_lists (parser, &select_names, &select_values, &const_names, &const_values, &no_vals,
9058  &no_consts, statement->info.update.assignment, &links);
9059  if (err != NO_ERROR)
9060  {
9061  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "update");
9062  break; /* stop while loop if error */
9063  }
9064 
9065  /* make sure that lhs->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_ATTR */
9066  select_statement =
9067  pt_to_upd_del_query (parser, select_names, select_values, statement->info.update.spec,
9068  statement->info.update.with, statement->info.update.class_specs,
9069  statement->info.update.search_cond, statement->info.update.using_index,
9070  statement->info.update.order_by, statement->info.update.orderby_for, 0, S_UPDATE);
9071 
9072  /* restore tree structure; pt_get_assignment_lists() */
9073  pt_restore_assignment_links (statement->info.update.assignment, links, -1);
9074 
9075  /* translate views or virtual classes into base classes; If we are updating a proxy, the SELECT is not yet
9076  * fully translated. If we are updating anything else, this is a no-op. */
9077 
9078  /* this prevents authorization checking during view transformation */
9079  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
9080 
9081  if (select_statement != NULL)
9082  {
9083  err = pt_copy_upddel_hints_to_select (parser, statement, select_statement);
9084  if (err != NO_ERROR)
9085  {
9086  parser_free_tree (parser, select_statement);
9087  break;
9088  }
9089  }
9090  select_statement = mq_translate (parser, select_statement);
9091  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
9092  if (select_statement)
9093  {
9094  /* get XASL_ID by calling do_prepare_select() */
9095  err = do_prepare_select (parser, select_statement);
9096  stream.xasl_id = select_statement->xasl_id;
9097  select_statement->xasl_id = NULL;
9098  parser_free_tree (parser, select_statement);
9099  }
9100  else
9101  {
9102  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
9103  err = er_errid ();
9104  }
9105 
9106  } /* else (server_update) */
9107 
9108  /* save the XASL_ID that is allocated and returned by prepare_query() into 'statement->xasl_id' to be used by
9109  * do_execute_update() */
9110  statement->xasl_id = stream.xasl_id;
9111 
9112  if (not_nulls)
9113  {
9114  parser_free_tree (parser, not_nulls);
9115  }
9116  }
9117 
9118  return err;
9119 }
9120 
9121 /*
9122  * do_execute_update() - Execute the prepared UPDATE statement
9123  * return: Error code
9124  * parser(in): Parser context
9125  * statement(in): Parse tree of a update statement
9126  *
9127  * Note:
9128  */
9129 int
9130 do_execute_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
9131 {
9132  int err, result = 0;
9133  PT_NODE *flat, *spec = NULL;
9134  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
9135  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
9136  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id;
9137  int au_save;
9138  int wait_msecs = -2, old_wait_msecs = -2;
9139  float hint_waitsecs;
9140  PT_NODE *hint_arg;
9141  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
9142  bool savepoint_started = false;
9143 
9144  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
9145 
9146  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
9147 
9148  /* savepoint for statement atomicity */
9149  if ((statement != NULL && statement->next != NULL)
9150  || (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ
9151  && (statement->info.update.object != NULL || !statement->info.update.server_update)))
9152  {
9153  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UmusP", &update_savepoint_number);
9154  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
9155  {
9156  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
9157  }
9158  err = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
9159  if (err != NO_ERROR)
9160  {
9161  return err;
9162  }
9163  savepoint_started = true;
9164  }
9165 
9166  for (err = NO_ERROR, result = 0; statement && (err >= NO_ERROR); statement = statement->next)
9167  {
9168  /*
9169  * Update object case:
9170  * update object by OID
9171  */
9172  if (statement->info.update.object)
9173  {
9174  err = update_object_by_oid (parser, statement, UPDATE_OBJECT);
9175  continue; /* continue to next UPDATE statement */
9176  }
9177 
9178  /* check if it is not necessary to execute this statement, e.g. false where or not prepared correctly */
9179  if (!statement->info.update.do_class_attrs && !statement->xasl_id)
9180  {
9181  statement->etc = NULL;
9182  err = NO_ERROR;
9183  continue; /* continue to next UPDATE statement */
9184  }
9185 
9186  /*
9187  * Server-side update or OID list update case:
9188  * execute the prepared(stored) XASL (UPDATE_PROC or SELECT statement)
9189  */
9190  if (statement->info.update.server_update || !statement->info.update.do_class_attrs)
9191  {
9192  /* Request that the server executes the stored XASL, which is the execution plan of the prepared query, with
9193  * the host variables given by users as parameter values for the query. As a result, query id and result file
9194  * id (QFILE_LIST_ID) will be returned. do_prepare_update() has saved the XASL file id (XASL_ID) in
9195  * 'statement->xasl_id' */
9196 
9197  int query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
9198 
9199  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
9200  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
9201 
9202  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
9203  {
9204  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
9205  }
9206 
9207  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
9208  {
9209  query_flag |= EXECUTE_QUERY_WITH_COMMIT;
9210  }
9211 
9212  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
9213  {
9214  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
9215  }
9216 
9217  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
9218  {
9219  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
9220  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
9221  }
9222 
9223  // When a transaction is under auto-commit mode, flush all dirty objects to server.
9224  // Otherwise, flush associated objects.
9225  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
9226  {
9227  err = tran_flush_to_commit ();
9228  }
9229  else
9230  {
9231  /* flush necessary objects before execute */
9232  for (spec = statement->info.update.spec; spec != NULL && err == NO_ERROR; spec = spec->next)
9233  {
9234  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
9235  {
9236  err = sm_flush_objects (spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object);
9237  }
9238  }
9239  }
9240 
9241  if (err != NO_ERROR)
9242  {
9243  // flush error
9244  break;
9245  }
9246 
9247  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
9248 
9249  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
9250  list_id = NULL;
9251 
9252  /* check host variables are filled : values from orderby_for may not have been auto-parameterized as host
9253  * variables; if that is the case, do it now */
9254  if (statement->info.update.orderby_for != NULL && parser->auto_param_count == 0)
9255  {
9256  assert ((parser->host_variables == NULL && parser->host_var_count == 0)
9257  || (parser->host_variables != NULL && parser->host_var_count > 0));
9258 
9259  qo_do_auto_parameterize (parser, statement->info.update.orderby_for);
9260  }
9261 
9262  err = execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
9263  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, NULL, NULL);
9264 
9265  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
9266  if (err != NO_ERROR)
9267  {
9268  break; /* stop while loop if error */
9269  }
9270  }
9271 
9272  if (!statement->info.update.server_update)
9273  {
9274  hint_arg = statement->info.update.waitsecs_hint;
9275  if (statement->info.update.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
9276  {
9277  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
9278  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
9279  {
9280  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
9281  }
9282  else
9283  {
9284  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
9285  }
9286  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
9287  {
9288  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
9289  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
9290  }
9291  }
9292  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save); /* this prevents authorization checking during execution */
9293  if (statement->info.update.do_class_attrs)
9294  {
9295  /* in case of update class attributes, */
9296  err = update_class_attributes (parser, statement);
9297  }
9298  else
9299  {
9300  /* in the case of OID list update, now update the selected OIDs */
9301  err = update_objs_for_list_file (parser, list_id, statement, savepoint_started);
9302  }
9303 
9304  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
9305  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
9306  {
9307  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
9308  }
9309  }
9310 
9311  if (statement->info.update.server_update || !statement->info.update.do_class_attrs)
9312  {
9313  /* free returned QFILE_LIST_ID */
9314  if (list_id)
9315  {
9316  if (list_id->tuple_cnt > 0 && statement->info.update.server_update)
9317  {
9318  spec = statement->info.update.spec;
9319  while (spec && err == NO_ERROR)
9320  {
9321  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
9322  {
9323  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
9324  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
9325  if (statement->use_auto_commit && tran_was_latest_query_committed ())
9326  {
9327  /* Nothing to flush. Avoids flush, since may fetch the class. */
9328  err = sm_decache_instances_after_query_executed_with_commit (class_obj);
9329  }
9330  else
9331  {
9332  err = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (class_obj, true);
9333  }
9334  }
9335 
9336  spec = spec->next;
9337  }
9338  }
9339  if (err >= NO_ERROR && statement->info.update.server_update)
9340  {
9341  err = list_id->tuple_cnt; /* as a result */
9342  }
9343  regu_free_listid (list_id);
9344  }
9345  /* end the query; reset query_id and call qmgr_end_query() */
9346  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
9347  }
9348 
9349  /* accumulate intermediate results */
9350  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
9351  {
9352  result += err;
9353  }
9354 
9355  spec = statement->info.update.spec;
9356  while (spec && err == NO_ERROR)
9357  {
9358  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE)
9359  {
9360  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
9361  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
9362 
9363  if (class_obj && (statement->use_auto_commit == false || !tran_was_latest_query_committed ()))
9364  {
9365  err = db_is_vclass (class_obj);
9366  if (err > 0)
9367  {
9368  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
9369  }
9370  }
9371 
9372  }
9373 
9374  spec = spec->next;
9375  }
9376 
9377  if ((err < NO_ERROR) && er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
9378  {
9379  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number,
9380  er_msg (), NULL);
9381  }
9382  }
9383 
9384  /* If error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
9385  * transaction. */
9386  if (err < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && err != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
9387  {
9388  db_abort_to_savepoint (savepoint_name);
9389  }
9390 
9391  return (err < NO_ERROR) ? err : result;
9392 }
9393

9395 /*
9396  * Function Group:
9397  * DO functions for delete statements
9398  *
9399  */
9400 
9401 /* used to generate unique savepoint names */
9402 static int delete_savepoint_number = 0;
9403 
9404 static int select_delete_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, QFILE_LIST_ID ** result_p, PT_NODE * delete_stmt);
9405 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
9406 static int delete_object_by_oid (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * statement);
9407 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
9408 static int delete_list_by_oids (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, QFILE_LIST_ID * list_id,
9409  bool savepoint_started);
9410 static int build_xasl_for_server_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement);
9411 static int delete_real_class (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement);
