9413 /*
9414  * select_delete_list() -
9415  * return: Error code
9416  * parser(in/out): Parser context
9417  * result(out): QFILE_LIST_ID for query result
9418  * delete_stmt(in): delete statement
9419  *
9420  * Note : The list_id is allocated during query execution
9421  */
9422 static int
9423 select_delete_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, QFILE_LIST_ID ** result_p, PT_NODE * delete_stmt)
9424 {
9425  PT_NODE *statement = NULL;
9426  QFILE_LIST_ID *result = NULL;
9427  int ret = NO_ERROR;
9428 
9429  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
9430  assert (delete_stmt->info.delete_.with == NULL);
9431 
9432  statement = pt_to_upd_del_query (parser, NULL, NULL, delete_stmt->info.delete_.spec, delete_stmt->info.delete_.with,
9433  delete_stmt->info.delete_.class_specs, delete_stmt->info.delete_.search_cond,
9434  delete_stmt->info.delete_.using_index, NULL, NULL,
9435  0 /* not server update */ , S_DELETE);
9436  if (statement != NULL)
9437  {
9438  ret = pt_copy_upddel_hints_to_select (parser, delete_stmt, statement);
9439  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
9440  {
9441  parser_free_tree (parser, statement);
9442  return ret;
9443  }
9444  /* If we are updating a proxy, the select is not yet fully translated. if we are updating anything else, this is
9445  * a no-op. */
9446  statement = mq_translate (parser, statement);
9447 
9448  if (statement)
9449  {
9450  /* This enables authorization checking during methods in queries */
9451  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
9452 
9453  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
9454  if (do_select (parser, statement) < NO_ERROR)
9455  {
9456  /* query failed, an error has already been set */
9457  statement = NULL;
9458  }
9459 
9460  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
9461  }
9462  }
9463 
9464  if (statement)
9465  {
9466  result = (QFILE_LIST_ID *) statement->etc;
9467  parser_free_tree (parser, statement);
9468  }
9469 
9470  *result_p = result;
9471 
9472  if (ret == NO_ERROR)
9473  {
9474  if (er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
9475  {
9476  ret = er_errid ();
9477  }
9478  }
9479 
9480  return ret;
9481 }
9482 
9483 /*
9484  * delete_object_tuple() - Deletes object attributes with db_values
9485  * return: Error code if db_put fails
9486  * object(in): object to delete
9487  */
9488 static int
9489 delete_object_tuple (DB_OBJECT * object)
9490 {
9491  int error = NO_ERROR;
9492  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
9493  DB_ATTRIBUTE *attr;
9494  if (object == NULL)
9495  {
9496  error = ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
9497  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
9498  }
9499 
9500  /* authorizations checked in compiler--turn off but remember in parser so we can re-enable in case we run out of
9501  * memory and longjmp to the cleanup routine. */
9502 
9503  /* delete blob or clob data files if exist */
9504  class_obj = db_get_class (object);
9505  attr = db_get_attributes (class_obj);
9506  while (attr)
9507  {
9508  if (attr->type->id == DB_TYPE_BLOB || attr->type->id == DB_TYPE_CLOB)
9509  {
9510  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
9511  error = db_get (object, attr->header.name, &dbvalue);
9512  if (error == NO_ERROR && !DB_IS_NULL (&dbvalue))
9513  {
9514  DB_ELO *elo;
9515 
9516  assert (db_value_type (&dbvalue) == DB_TYPE_BLOB || db_value_type (&dbvalue) == DB_TYPE_CLOB);
9517  elo = db_get_elo (&dbvalue);
9518  if (elo)
9519  {
9520  error = db_elo_delete (elo);
9521  }
9522  db_value_clear (&dbvalue);
9523  error = (error >= 0 ? NO_ERROR : error);
9524  }
9525  if (error != NO_ERROR)
9526  {
9527  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
9528  return error;
9529  }
9530  }
9531  attr = db_attribute_next (attr);
9532  }
9533  /* TODO: to delete blob or clob at db api call */
9534  error = db_drop (object);
9535 
9536  return error;
9537 }
9538 
9539 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
9540 /*
9541  * delete_object_by_oid() - Deletes db object by oid.
9542  * return: Error code if delete fails
9543  * parser(in): Parser context
9544  * statement(in): Parse tree representing object to delete
9545  */
9546 static int
9547 delete_object_by_oid (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * statement)
9548 {
9549  int error = NO_ERROR;
9550 
9551  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR; /* unimplemented */
9552 
9553  return error;
9554 }
9555 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
9556 
9557 /*
9558  * delete_list_by_oids() - Deletes every oid in a list file
9559  * return: Error code if delete fails
9560  * parser(in): Parser context
9561  * statement(in): Delete statement
9562  * list_id(in): A list file of oid's
9563  * savepoint_started(in): true, if savepoint already started
9564  */
9565 static int
9566 delete_list_by_oids (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, QFILE_LIST_ID * list_id, bool savepoint_started)
9567 {
9568  int error = NO_ERROR;
9569  int cursor_status;
9570  DB_VALUE *oids = NULL;
9571  CURSOR_ID cursor_id;
9572  int count = 0, attrs_cnt = 0, idx; /* how many objects were deleted? */
9573  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
9574  int *flush_to_server = NULL;
9575  DB_OBJECT *mop = NULL, *class_obj = NULL;
9576  bool has_savepoint = false, is_cursor_open = false;
9577  PT_NODE *spec;
9578 
9579  if (list_id == NULL)
9580  {
9581  return NO_ERROR;
9582  }
9583 
9584  assert (parser->query_id != NULL_QUERY_ID);
9585  assert (parser->query_id == list_id->query_id);
9586 
9587  spec = statement->info.delete_.spec;
9588  while (spec)
9589  {
9590  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
9591  {
9592  class_obj = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
9593  /* place IX lock on the class. This should have been done already when the list_id was produced but this is
9594  * the last opportunity we have before actually deleting objects. */
9595  if (locator_fetch_class (class_obj, DB_FETCH_CLREAD_INSTWRITE) == NULL)
9596  {
9597  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9598  return er_errid ();
9599  }
9600  }
9601  spec = spec->next;
9602  }
9603 
9604  /* if the list file contains more than 1 object we need to savepoint the statement to guarantee statement atomicity. */
9605  if (list_id->tuple_cnt >= 1 || TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ)
9606  {
9607  if (savepoint_started == false)
9608  {
9609  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UdsP", &delete_savepoint_number);
9610 
9611  error = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
9612  if (error != NO_ERROR)
9613  {
9614  goto cleanup;
9615  }
9616  has_savepoint = true;
9617  }
9618  }
9619 
9620  if (!cursor_open (&cursor_id, list_id, false, false))
9621  {
9622  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
9623  goto cleanup;
9624  }
9625  is_cursor_open = true;
9626  attrs_cnt = list_id->type_list.type_cnt;
9627 
9628  oids = (DB_VALUE *) db_private_alloc (NULL, attrs_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
9629  if (oids == NULL)
9630  {
9631  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
9632  goto cleanup;
9633  }
9634  flush_to_server = (int *) db_private_alloc (NULL, attrs_cnt * sizeof (int));
9635  if (flush_to_server == NULL)
9636  {
9637  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
9638  goto cleanup;
9639  }
9640  for (idx = 0; idx < attrs_cnt; idx++)
9641  {
9642  flush_to_server[idx] = -1;
9643  }
9644 
9645  cursor_id.query_id = parser->query_id;
9646  cursor_status = cursor_next_tuple (&cursor_id);
9647 
9648  while ((error >= NO_ERROR) && cursor_status == DB_CURSOR_SUCCESS)
9649  {
9650  error = cursor_get_tuple_value_list (&cursor_id, attrs_cnt, oids);
9651  /* The select list contains instance OID - class OID pairs */
9652  for (idx = 0; idx < attrs_cnt && error >= NO_ERROR; idx++)
9653  {
9654  if (DB_IS_NULL (&oids[idx]))
9655  {
9656  continue;
9657  }
9658 
9659  mop = db_get_object (&oids[idx]);
9660 
9661  error = db_is_deleted (mop);
9662  if (error < 0)
9663  {
9664  return error;
9665  }
9666  if (error > 0)
9667  {
9668  /* if the object is an invalid object (was already deleted) then skip the delete, instance flush and
9669  * count steps */
9670  error = NO_ERROR;
9671  continue;
9672  }
9673 
9674  if (flush_to_server[idx] == -1)
9675  {
9676  /* the following code may be improved to not flush every time */
9677  if (has_unique_constraint (mop) || TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ)
9678  {
9679  flush_to_server[idx] = 1;
9680  }
9681  else
9682  {
9683  flush_to_server[idx] = 0;
9684  }
9685  }
9686  error = delete_object_tuple (mop);
9687  if (error == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT && do_Trigger_involved)
9688  {
9689  er_clear ();
9690  error = NO_ERROR;
9691  continue;
9692  }
9693 
9694  if ((error >= NO_ERROR) && flush_to_server[idx])
9695  {
9696  error = (locator_flush_instance (mop) == NO_ERROR) ? 0 : (er_errid () != NO_ERROR ? er_errid () : -1);
9697  }
9698 
9699  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
9700  {
9701  count++; /* another object has been deleted */
9702  }
9703  }
9704 
9705  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
9706  {
9707  cursor_status = cursor_next_tuple (&cursor_id);
9708  }
9709  }
9710 
9711  if ((error >= NO_ERROR) && cursor_status != DB_CURSOR_END)
9712  {
9713  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
9714  }
9715 
9716 cleanup:
9717  if (is_cursor_open)
9718  {
9719  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
9720  }
9721 
9722  /* if error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the transaction
9723  * itself. */
9724  if (has_savepoint && (error < NO_ERROR) && savepoint_name && error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
9725  {
9726  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
9727  }
9728 
9729  if (oids != NULL)
9730  {
9731  db_private_free (NULL, oids);
9732  }
9733 
9734  if (flush_to_server != NULL)
9735  {
9736  db_private_free (NULL, flush_to_server);
9737  }
9738 
9739  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
9740  {
9741  return count;
9742  }
9743  else
9744  {
9745  return error;
9746  }
9747 }
9748 
9749 /*
9750  * build_xasl_for_server_delete() - Build an xasl tree for a server delete
9751  * and execute it.
9752  * return: Error code if delete fails
9753  * parser(in/out): Parser context
9754  * statement(in): Parse tree of a delete statement.
9755  *
9756  * Note:
9757  * The xasl tree has an DELETE_PROC node as the top node and
9758  * a BUILDLIST_PROC as its aptr. The BUILDLIST_PROC selects the
9759  * instance OID. The DELETE_PROC node scans the BUILDLIST_PROC results.
9760  * The server executes the aptr and then for each instance selected,
9761  * deletes it. The result information is sent back to the
9762  * client as a list file without any pages. The list file tuple count
9763  * is used as the return value from this routine.
9764  *
9765  * The instances for the class are flushed from the client before the
9766  * delete is executed. If any instances are deleted, the instances are
9767  * decached from the client after the delete is executed.
9768  */
9769 static int
9770 build_xasl_for_server_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
9771 {
9772  int error = NO_ERROR;
9773  XASL_NODE *xasl = NULL;
9774  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
9775  int count = 0;
9776  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
9777  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
9778  const PT_NODE *node;
9779 
9780  XASL_STREAM stream;
9781 
9782  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
9783 
9784  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
9785 
9786  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
9787  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
9788 
9789  xasl = pt_to_delete_xasl (parser, statement);
9790 
9791  if (xasl)
9792  {
9793  error = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (xasl, &stream);
9794  if (error != NO_ERROR)
9795  {
9796  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
9797  }
9798  }
9799  else
9800  {
9801  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9802  error = er_errid ();
9803  }
9804 
9805  if (error == NO_ERROR)
9806  {
9807  int au_save;
9808  QUERY_FLAG query_flag;
9809 
9810  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
9811 
9812  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
9813  {
9814  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
9815  }
9816 
9817  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
9818 
9819  error =
9820  prepare_and_execute_query (stream.buffer, stream.buffer_size, &parser->query_id,
9821  parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count, parser->host_variables, &list_id,
9822  query_flag);
9823  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
9824  }
9825 
9826  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
9827  if (stream.buffer)
9828  {
9829  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
9830  }
9831 
9832  if (list_id)
9833  {
9834  count = list_id->tuple_cnt;
9835  if (count > 0)
9836  {
9837  node = statement->info.delete_.spec;
9838  while (node && error == NO_ERROR)
9839  {
9840  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
9841  {
9842  class_obj = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
9843  if (statement->use_auto_commit && tran_was_latest_query_committed ())
9844  {
9845  /* Nothing to flush. Avoids flush, since may fetch the class. */
9846  error = sm_decache_instances_after_query_executed_with_commit (class_obj);
9847  }
9848  else
9849  {
9850  error = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (class_obj, true);
9851  }
9852  }
9853 
9854  node = node->next;
9855  }
9856  }
9857  regu_free_listid (list_id);
9858  }
9859 
9860  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
9861 
9862  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
9863  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
9864 
9865  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
9866  {
9867  return count;
9868  }
9869  else
9870  {
9871  return error;
9872  }
9873 }
9874 
9875 /*
9876  * has_unique_constraint() - Check if class has an unique constraint
9877  * return: 1 if the class has an unique constraint, otherwise 0
9878  * mop(in/out): Class object to be checked
9879  */
9880 static int
9881 has_unique_constraint (DB_OBJECT * mop)
9882 {
9883  DB_CONSTRAINT *constraint_list, *c;
9884  SM_CONSTRAINT_TYPE ctype;
9885 
9886  if (mop == NULL)
9887  {
9888  return 0;
9889  }
9890 
9891  constraint_list = db_get_constraints (mop);
9892  for (c = constraint_list; c; c = c->next)
9893  {
9894  ctype = c->type;
9895  if (SM_IS_CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE_FAMILY (ctype))
9896  {
9897  return 1;
9898  }
9899  }
9900 
9901  return 0;
9902 }
9903 
9904 /*
9905  * delete_real_class() - Deletes objects or rows
9906  * return: Error code if delete fails
9907  * parser(in/out): Parser context
9908  * statement(in): Delete statement
9909  */
9910 static int
9911 delete_real_class (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
9912 {
9913  int error = NO_ERROR;
9914  QFILE_LIST_ID *oid_list = NULL;
9915  int trigger_involved = 0;
9916  MOBJ class_;
9917  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
9918  int wait_msecs = -2, old_wait_msecs = -2;
9919  float hint_waitsecs;
9920  PT_NODE *hint_arg = NULL, *spec = NULL;
9921  bool has_virt_object = false;
9922 
9923  /* delete a "real" class in this database */
9924 
9925  spec = statement->info.delete_.spec;
9926  while (spec)
9927  {
9928  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
9929  {
9930  class_obj = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
9931 
9932  if (spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.virt_object)
9933  {
9934  has_virt_object = true;
9935  }
9936  /* place weak lock here, we will upgrade it once the actual DELETE operation starts */
9937  class_ = locator_fetch_class (class_obj, DB_FETCH_READ);
9938  if (class_ == NULL)
9939  {
9940  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9941  return er_errid ();
9942  }
9943 
9944  if (!trigger_involved)
9945  {
9946  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &trigger_involved, TR_EVENT_DELETE);
9947  if (error != NO_ERROR)
9948  {
9949  return error;
9950  }
9951  }
9952  }
9953 
9954  spec = spec->next;
9955  }
9956 
9957  /* do delete on server if there is no trigger involved and the class is a real class */
9958  if (!trigger_involved && !has_virt_object)
9959  {
9960  error = build_xasl_for_server_delete (parser, statement);
9961  }
9962  else
9963  {
9964  QUERY_ID query_id_self;
9965 
9966  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
9967  parser->query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
9968 
9969  hint_arg = statement->info.delete_.waitsecs_hint;
9970  if (statement->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
9971  {
9972  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
9973  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
9974  {
9975  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
9976  }
9977  else
9978  {
9979  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
9980  }
9981  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
9982  {
9983  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
9984  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
9985  }
9986  }
9987  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
9988  {
9989  /* get the oid's and new values */
9990  error = select_delete_list (parser, &oid_list, statement);
9991  }
9992  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
9993  {
9994  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
9995  }
9996 
9997  if (!oid_list)
9998  {
9999  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
10000  /* an error should be set already, don't lose it */
10001  return error;
10002  }
10003 
10004  /* delete each oid */
10005  error = delete_list_by_oids (parser, statement, oid_list, false);
10006  regu_free_listid (oid_list);
10007  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
10008  }
10009 
10010  return error;
10011 }
10012 
10013 /*
10014  * do_delete() - Deletes objects or rows
10015  * return: Error code if delete fails
10016  * parser(in/out): Parser context
10017  * statement(in): Delete statement
10018  *
10019  * Note: Returning the number of deleted object on success is a bug fix!
10020  * uci_static expects do_execute_statement to return the number of
10021  * affected objects for a successful DELETE, UPDATE, INSERT, SELECT.
10022  */
10023 int
10024 do_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
10025 {
10026  int error = NO_ERROR;
10027  int result = NO_ERROR;
10028  PT_NODE *spec;
10029  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
10030 
10031  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
10032 
10033  /* DON'T REMOVE this, correct authorization validation of views depends on this.
10034  *
10035  * DON'T return from the body of this function. Break out of the loop if necessary. */
10036 
10037  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
10038 
10039  /* savepoint for statement atomicity */
10040  if (statement != NULL && statement->next != NULL)
10041  {
10042  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UmdsP", &delete_savepoint_number);
10043  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
10044  {
10045  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10046  goto end;
10047  }
10048  error = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
10049  if (error != NO_ERROR)
10050  {
10051  goto end;
10052  }
10053  }
10054 
10055  while (statement && error >= 0)
10056  {
10057  if (statement->node_type != PT_DELETE)
10058  {
10059  /* bullet proofing, should not get here */
10060  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "delete");
10061  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10062  break;
10063  }
10064 
10065  spec = statement->info.delete_.spec;
10066 
10067  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
10068  {
10069  /* nothing to delete, where part is false */
10070  }
10071 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
10072  else if (!spec)
10073  {
10074  /* this is an delete object if it has no spec */
10075  error = delete_object_by_oid (parser, statement);
10076  }
10077 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
10078  else
10079  {
10080  /* the following is the "normal" sql type execution */
10081  error = delete_real_class (parser, statement);
10082  }
10083 
10084  result += error;
10085  statement = statement->next;
10086  }
10087 
10088  /* if error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
10089  * transaction. */
10090 
10091  if (error < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
10092  {
10093  db_abort_to_savepoint (savepoint_name);
10094  }
10095 
10096 end:
10097  if (error < 0)
10098  {
10099  result = error;
10100  }
10101 
10102  /* DON'T REMOVE this, correct authorization validation of views depends on this. */
10103 
10104  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
10105 
10106  return result;
10107 }
10108 
10109 /*
10110  * do_prepare_delete() - Prepare the DELETE statement
10111  * return: Error code
10112  * parser(in/out): Parser context
10113  * statement(in/out): Delete statement
10114  * parent(in): Parent statement if using multi-delete list
10115  */
10116 int
10117 do_prepare_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_NODE * parent)
10118 {
10119  int err;
10120  PT_NODE *flat;
10121  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
10122  int has_trigger, au_save, has_any_delete_trigger;
10123  bool server_delete, has_virt_obj;
10124  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
10125  PT_NODE *save_stmt = statement;
10126 
10127  if (parser == NULL)
10128  {
10129  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
10130  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
10131  }
10132 
10133  for (err = NO_ERROR; statement && (err >= NO_ERROR); statement = statement->next)
10134  {
10135  COMPILE_CONTEXT *contextp;
10136  XASL_STREAM stream;
10137 
10138  contextp = &parser->context;
10139 
10140  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
10141 
10142  contextp->sql_user_text = statement->sql_user_text;
10143  contextp->sql_user_text_len = statement->sql_user_text_len;
10144 
10145  /* there can be no results, this is a compile time false where clause */
10146  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
10147  {
10148  /* tell to the execute routine that there's no XASL to execute */
10149  statement->xasl_id = NULL;
10150  err = NO_ERROR;
10151  continue; /* continue to next DELETE statement */
10152  }
10153 
10154  /* Delete object case: this is an delete object if it has no spec */
10155  if (!statement->info.delete_.spec)
10156  {
10157  statement->etc = NULL;
10158  err = NO_ERROR;
10159  continue; /* continue to next DELETE statement */
10160  }
10161 
10162  /* if already prepared */
10163  if (statement->xasl_id)
10164  {
10165  continue; /* continue to next DELETE statement */
10166  }
10167 
10168  err = pt_split_delete_stmt (parser, statement);
10169  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10170  {
10171  break;
10172  }
10173 
10174  /* the presence of a proxy trigger should force the delete to be performed through the workspace */
10175  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save); /* because sm_class_has_trigger() calls au_fetch_class() */
10176  has_virt_obj = false;
10177  has_trigger = 0;
10178  has_any_delete_trigger = 0;
10179  node = (PT_NODE *) statement->info.delete_.spec;
10180  while (node && err == NO_ERROR && !has_trigger)
10181  {
10182  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
10183  {
10184  flat = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
10185  if (flat)
10186  {
10187  if (flat->info.name.virt_object)
10188  {
10189  has_virt_obj = true;
10190  }
10191  class_obj = flat->info.name.db_object;
10192  }
10193  else
10194  {
10195  class_obj = NULL;
10196  }
10197  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_DELETE);
10198 
10199  if (err == NO_ERROR)
10200  {
10201  if (has_trigger)
10202  {
10203  has_any_delete_trigger = has_trigger;
10204  }
10205  else if (!has_any_delete_trigger)
10206  {
10207  /* Check for statement delete triggerrs. */
10208  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_any_delete_trigger, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE);
10209  }
10210  }
10211  }
10212 
10213  node = node->next;
10214  }
10215 
10216  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
10217  /* err = has_proxy_trigger(flat, &has_trigger); */
10218  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10219  {
10220  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "delete");
10221  break; /* stop while loop if error */
10222  }
10223  /* sm_class_has_triggers() checked if the class has active triggers */
10224  statement->info.delete_.has_trigger = has_trigger;
10225 
10226  /* determine whether it can be server-side or OID list deletion */
10227  server_delete = (!has_trigger && !has_virt_obj);
10228 
10229  statement->info.delete_.server_delete = server_delete;
10230  if (server_delete && !has_any_delete_trigger)
10231  {
10232  statement->info.delete_.execute_with_commit_allowed = 1;
10233  }
10234 
10235  stream.xasl_id = NULL;
10236  if (server_delete)
10237  {
10238  /* Server-side deletion case: (by requesting server to execute XASL) build DELETE_PROC XASL */
10239 
10240  /* make query string */
10241  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 1;
10242  parser->long_string_skipped = 0;
10243  parser->print_type_ambiguity = 0;
10244  PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS (parser, statement, (PT_CONVERT_RANGE | PT_PRINT_QUOTES | PT_PRINT_USER));
10245  contextp->sql_hash_text = (char *) statement->alias_print;
10246  err =
10247  SHA1Compute ((unsigned char *) contextp->sql_hash_text, (unsigned) strlen (contextp->sql_hash_text),
10248  &contextp->sha1);
10249  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10250  {
10251  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10252  return err;
10253  }
10254  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 0;
10255  if (parser->long_string_skipped || parser->print_type_ambiguity)
10256  {
10257  statement->cannot_prepare = 1;
10258  err = NO_ERROR;
10259  break;
10260  }
10261 
10262  /* look up server's XASL cache for this query string and get XASL file id (XASL_ID) returned if found */
10263  contextp->recompile_xasl = statement->recompile;
10264  if (statement->recompile == 0)
10265  {
10266  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
10267  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10268  {
10269  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (err);
10270  }
10271  else if (contextp->recompile_xasl == true)
10272  {
10273  /* recompile requested by server */
10274  if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
10275  {
10276  free_and_init (stream.xasl_id);
10277  }
10278  }
10279  }
10280  if (stream.xasl_id == NULL && err == NO_ERROR)
10281  {
10282  /* cache not found; make XASL from the parse tree including query optimization and plan generation */
10283 
10284  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
10285  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
10286 
10287  /* this prevents authorization checking during generating XASL */
10288  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
10289 
10290  /* pt_to_delete_xasl() will build XASL tree from parse tree */
10291  contextp->xasl = pt_to_delete_xasl (parser, statement);
10292  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
10293 
10294  if (contextp->xasl && (err >= NO_ERROR))
10295  {
10296  /* convert the created XASL tree to the byte stream for transmission to the server */
10297  err = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (contextp->xasl, &stream);
10298  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10299  {
10300  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
10301  }
10302  }
10303  else
10304  {
10305  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10306  err = er_errid ();
10307  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number,
10308  er_msg (), NULL);
10309  }
10310 
10311  /* request the server to prepare the query; give XASL stream generated from the parse tree and get XASL
10312  * file id returned */
10313  if (stream.buffer && (err >= NO_ERROR))
10314  {
10315  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
10316  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10317  {
10318  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10319  err = er_errid ();
10320  }
10321  }
10322 
10323  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
10324  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
10325 
10326  /* As a result of query preparation of the server, the XASL cache for this query will be created or
10327  * updated. */
10328 
10329  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
10330  if (stream.buffer)
10331  {
10332  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
10333  }
10334  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
10335  }
10336  else
10337  {
10338  if (err == NO_ERROR)
10339  {
10340  statement->use_plan_cache = 1;
10341  }
10342  else
10343  {
10344  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
10345  }
10346  }
10347  }
10348  else
10349  {
10350  /* OID list deletion case: (by selecting OIDs to delete) make SELECT statement for this DELETE statement */
10351 
10352  PT_NODE *select_statement;
10353  PT_DELETE_INFO *delete_info;
10354 
10355  delete_info = &statement->info.delete_;
10356 
10357  assert (delete_info->with == NULL);
10358 
10359  select_statement =
10360  pt_to_upd_del_query (parser, NULL, NULL, delete_info->spec, delete_info->with, delete_info->class_specs,
10361  delete_info->search_cond, delete_info->using_index, NULL, NULL, 0, S_DELETE);
10362  err = pt_copy_upddel_hints_to_select (parser, statement, select_statement);
10363  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10364  {
10365  parser_free_tree (parser, select_statement);
10366  break;
10367  }
10368  /* translate views or virtual classes into base classes; If we are updating a proxy, the SELECT is not yet
10369  * fully translated. If we are updating anything else, this is a no-op. */
10370 
10371  /* this prevents authorization checking during view transformation */
10372  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
10373 
10374  select_statement = mq_translate (parser, select_statement);
10375  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
10376  if (select_statement)
10377  {
10378  /* get XASL_ID by calling do_prepare_select() */
10379  err = do_prepare_select (parser, select_statement);
10380  stream.xasl_id = select_statement->xasl_id;
10381  select_statement->xasl_id = NULL;
10382  parser_free_tree (parser, select_statement);
10383  }
10384  else
10385  {
10386  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
10387  err = er_errid ();
10388  }
10389  }
10390 
10391  if (statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list != NULL)
10392  {
10393  err = do_prepare_delete (parser, statement->info.delete_.del_stmt_list, statement);
10394  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10395  {
10396  break;
10397  }
10398  }
10399 
10400  /* save the XASL_ID that is allocated and returned by prepare_query() into 'statement->xasl_id' to be used by
10401  * do_execute_delete() */
10402  statement->xasl_id = stream.xasl_id;
10403  }
10404 
10405  /* if something failed or cannot be prepared in in del_stmt_list clear all statement->xasl_id */
10406  if (err != NO_ERROR || (statement != NULL && statement->cannot_prepare == 1))
10407  {
10408  for (node = save_stmt; node != statement; node = node->next)
10409  {
10410  pt_free_statement_xasl_id (node);
10411  }
10412  if (err == NO_ERROR && parent != NULL)
10413  {
10414  /* set cannot_prepare to parent */
10415  parent->cannot_prepare = 1;
10416  }
10417  }
10418 
10419  return err;
10420 }
10421 
10422 /*
10423  * do_execute_delete() - Execute the prepared DELETE statement
10424  * return: Tuple count if success, otherwise an error code
10425  * parser(in): Parser context
10426  * statement(in): Delete statement
10427  */
10428 int
10429 do_execute_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
10430 {
10431  int err, result = 0;
10432  PT_NODE *flat, *node;
10433  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
10434  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
10435  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id;
10436  int au_save;
10437  int wait_msecs = -2, old_wait_msecs = -2;
10438  float hint_waitsecs;
10439  PT_NODE *hint_arg;
10440  int query_flag;
10441  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
10442  bool savepoint_started = false;
10443 
10444  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
10445 
10446  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
10447 
10448  /* savepoint for statement atomicity */
10449  if ((statement != NULL && statement->next != NULL)
10450  || (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ && !statement->info.delete_.server_delete))
10451  {
10452  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UmdsP", &delete_savepoint_number);
10453  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
10454  {
10455  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10456  }
10457  err = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
10458  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10459  {
10460  return err;
10461  }
10462 
10463  savepoint_started = true;
10464  }
10465 
10466  for (err = NO_ERROR, result = 0; statement && (err >= NO_ERROR); statement = statement->next)
10467  {
10468 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
10469  /* Delete object case: delete object by OID */
10470 
10471  if (!statement->info.delete_.spec)
10472  {
10473  err = delete_object_by_oid (parser, statement);
10474  continue; /* continue to next DELETE statement */
10475  }
10476 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
10477 
10478  /* check if it is not necessary to execute this statement, e.g. false where or not prepared correctly */
10479  if (!statement->xasl_id)
10480  {
10481  statement->etc = NULL;
10482  err = NO_ERROR;
10483  continue; /* continue to next DELETE statement */
10484  }
10485 
10486  /* Server-side deletion or OID list deletion case: execute the prepared(stored) XASL (DELETE_PROC or SELECT
10487  * statement) */
10488 
10489  /* Request that the server executes the stored XASL, which is the execution plan of the prepared query, with the
10490  * host variables given by users as parameter values for the query. As a result, query id and result file id
10491  * (QFILE_LIST_ID) will be returned. do_prepare_delete() has saved the XASL file id (XASL_ID) in
10492  * 'statement->xasl_id' */
10493 
10494  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
10495  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
10496  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
10497 
10498  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
10499  {
10500  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
10501  }
10502 
10503  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
10504  {
10505  query_flag |= EXECUTE_QUERY_WITH_COMMIT;
10506  }
10507 
10508  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
10509  {
10510  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
10511  }
10512 
10513  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
10514  {
10515  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
10516  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
10517  }
10518 
10519  // When a transaction is under auto-commit mode, flush all dirty objects to server.
10520  // Otherwise, flush associated objects.
10521  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
10522  {
10523  err = tran_flush_to_commit ();
10524  }
10525  else
10526  {
10527  for (node = statement->info.delete_.spec; node && err == NO_ERROR; node = node->next)
10528  {
10529  flat = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
10530  if (flat != NULL)
10531  {
10532  /* flush necessary objects before execute */
10533  err = sm_flush_objects (flat->info.name.db_object);
10534  }
10535  }
10536  }
10537 
10538  if (err != NO_ERROR)
10539  {
10540  // flush error
10541  break;
10542  }
10543 
10544  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
10545 
10546  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
10547  list_id = NULL;
10548  err = execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
10549  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, NULL, NULL);
10550 
10551  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
10552 
10553  /* in the case of OID list deletion, now delete the selected OIDs */
10554  if ((err >= NO_ERROR) && list_id)
10555  {
10556  if (statement->info.delete_.server_delete)
10557  {
10558  err = list_id->tuple_cnt;
10559  }
10560  else
10561  {
10562  hint_arg = statement->info.delete_.waitsecs_hint;
10563  if (statement->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
10564  {
10565  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
10566  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
10567  {
10568  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
10569  }
10570  else
10571  {
10572  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
10573  }
10574  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
10575  {
10576  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
10577  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
10578  }
10579  }
10580  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save); /* this prevents authorization checking during execution */
10581  /* delete each oid */
10582  err = delete_list_by_oids (parser, statement, list_id, savepoint_started);
10583  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
10584  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
10585  {
10586  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
10587  }
10588  }
10589  }
10590 
10591  /* free returned QFILE_LIST_ID */
10592  if (list_id)
10593  {
10594  if (list_id->tuple_cnt > 0 && statement->info.delete_.server_delete)
10595  {
10596  int err2 = NO_ERROR;
10597  node = statement->info.delete_.spec;
10598 
10599  while (node && err2 >= NO_ERROR)
10600  {
10601  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
10602  {
10603  flat = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
10604  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
10605 
10606  if (statement->use_auto_commit && tran_was_latest_query_committed ())
10607  {
10608  /* Nothing to flush. Avoids flush, since may fetch the class. */
10609  err2 = sm_decache_instances_after_query_executed_with_commit (class_obj);
10610  }
10611  else
10612  {
10613  err2 = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (class_obj, true);
10614  }
10615  }
10616 
10617  node = node->next;
10618  }
10619  if (err2 != NO_ERROR)
10620  {
10621  err = err2;
10622  }
10623  }
10624  regu_free_listid (list_id);
10625  }
10626 
10627  /* end the query; reset query_id and call qmgr_end_query() */
10628  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
10629 
10630  /* accumulate intermediate results */
10631  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
10632  {
10633  result += err;
10634  }
10635 
10636  node = statement->info.delete_.spec;
10637 
10638  while (node && err >= NO_ERROR)
10639  {
10640  if (node->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE)
10641  {
10642  flat = node->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
10643  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
10644 
10645  if (class_obj && (statement->use_auto_commit == false || !tran_was_latest_query_committed ()))
10646  {
10647  err = db_is_vclass (class_obj);
10648  if (err > 0)
10649  {
10650  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
10651  }
10652  }
10653  }
10654 
10655  node = node->next;
10656  }
10657  }
10658 
10659  /* If error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
10660  * transaction. */
10661  if (err < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && err != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
10662  {
10663  db_abort_to_savepoint (savepoint_name);
10664  }
10665 
10666  return (err < NO_ERROR) ? err : result;
10667 }
10668

10670 /*
10671  * Function Group:
10672  * Implements the evaluate statement.
10673  *
10674  */
10675 
10676 
10677 /*
10678  * do_evaluate() - Evaluates an expression
10679  * return: Error code
10680  * parser(in): Parser context
10681  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a insert statement
10682  */
10683 int
10684 do_evaluate (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
10685 {
10686  int error = NO_ERROR;
10687  DB_VALUE expr_value, *into_val;
10688  PT_NODE *expr, *into_var;
10689  const char *into_label;
10690 
10691  db_make_null (&expr_value);
10692 
10693  if (!statement || !((expr = statement->info.evaluate.expression)))
10694  {
10695  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10696  }
10697 
10698  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, expr, &expr_value, 1);
10699  if (pt_has_error (parser))
10700  {
10701  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SEMANTIC);
10702  return ER_PT_SEMANTIC;
10703  }
10704 
10705  statement->etc = (void *) db_value_copy (&expr_value);
10706  into_var = statement->info.evaluate.into_var;
10707 
10708  if (into_var && into_var->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_label = into_var->info.name.original) != NULL)
10709  {
10710  /* create another DB_VALUE of the new instance for the label_table */
10711  into_val = db_value_copy (&expr_value);
10712 
10713  /* enter {label, ins_val} pair into the label_table */
10714  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, into_val);
10715  }
10716 
10717  pr_clear_value (&expr_value);
10718  return error;
10719 }

10739  * prm_insert_mode_upper is still left as 31 for backward compatibility.
10740  *
10741  */
10742  INSERT_DEFAULT = 4,
10743  INSERT_REPLACE = 8,
10744  INSERT_ON_DUP_KEY_UPDATE = 16
10745 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
10746 } SERVER_PREFERENCE;

10752  CURSOR_ID *cursor_p; /* select cursor id */

10758 static int insert_object_attr (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OTMPL * otemplate, DB_VALUE * value, PT_NODE * name,
10759  DB_ATTDESC * attr_desc);
10760 static int check_for_cons (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, int *has_unique, PT_NODE ** non_null_attrs,
10761  const PT_NODE * attr_list, DB_OBJECT * class_obj);

10763 static int do_insert_at_server (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement);
10764 static int insert_subquery_results (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_NODE * values_list,
10765  PT_NODE * class_, const char **savepoint_name);
10766 static int is_attr_not_in_insert_list (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * name_list, const char *name);
10767 static int check_missing_non_null_attrs (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * attr_list,
10768  const bool has_default_values_list);
10769 static PT_NODE *make_vmops (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk);
10770 static PT_NODE *test_check_option (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk);
10771 static int insert_local (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement);
10772 static PT_NODE *do_create_odku_stmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert);
10773 static int do_find_unique_constraint_violations (DB_OTMPL * tmpl, bool for_update, OID ** oids, int *oids_count);
10774 static int do_create_midxkey_for_constraint (DB_OTMPL * tmpl, SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT * constraint, DB_VALUE * key);

10781  int *continue_walk);
10782 /*
10783  * insert_object_attr()
10784  * return: Error code if db_put fails
10785  * parser(in): Short description of the param1
10786  * otemplate(in/out): Short description of the param2
10787  * value(in/out): New attr value
10788  * name(in): Name to update
10789  * attr_desc(in): Attr descriptor of attribute to update
10790  */
10791 static int
10792 insert_object_attr (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OTMPL * otemplate, DB_VALUE * value, PT_NODE * name,
10793  DB_ATTDESC * attr_desc)
10794 {
10795  int error = NO_ERROR;
10796 
10797  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (value) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT && !DB_IS_NULL (value))
10798  {
10799  /* we may need to check for value coming in from a parameter or host variable as a
10800  * not-yet-translated-to-real-class value. This must be done at run time in general. */
10801  db_make_object (value, db_real_instance (db_get_object (value)));
10802  }
10803 
10804  if (name->info.name.db_object)
10805  {
10806  error = db_is_vclass (name->info.name.db_object);
10807  }
10808  if (error > 0)
10809  {
10810  /* this is a shared attribute of a view. this means this cannot be updated in the template for this real class.
10811  * Its simply done separately by a db_put. */
10812  error = obj_set_shared (name->info.name.db_object, name->info.name.original, value);
10813  }
10814  else if (!error)
10815  {
10816  /* the normal case */
10817  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
10818 
10819  att = db_get_attribute (otemplate->classobj, name->info.name.original);
10820  error = dbt_dput_internal (otemplate, attr_desc, value);
10821  }
10822 
10823  return error;
10824 }

10826 
10827 /*
10828  * do_prepare_insert_internal () - Prepares insert statement for server
10829  * execution.
10830  *
10831  * return : Error code.
10832  * parser (in) : Parser context.
10833  * statement (in) : Parse tree node for insert statement.
10834  */
10835 static int
10836 do_prepare_insert_internal (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
10837 {
10838  int error = NO_ERROR;
10839  PT_NODE *val = NULL, *head = NULL, *prev = NULL;
10840  PT_NODE *value_list = NULL;
10841 
10842  COMPILE_CONTEXT *contextp;
10843  XASL_STREAM stream;
10844 
10845  contextp = &parser->context;
10846 
10847  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
10848 
10849  if (!parser || !statement || statement->node_type != PT_INSERT)
10850  {
10851  assert (false);
10852  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10853  }
10854 
10855  contextp->sql_user_text = statement->sql_user_text;
10856  contextp->sql_user_text_len = statement->sql_user_text_len;
10857 
10858  /* insert value auto parameterize */
10859  for (value_list = statement->info.insert.value_clauses; value_list != NULL; value_list = value_list->next)
10860  {
10861  head = NULL;
10862  prev = NULL;
10863  for (val = value_list->info.node_list.list; val != NULL; val = val->next)
10864  {
10865  if (pt_is_const_not_hostvar (val) && !PT_IS_NULL_NODE (val))
10866  {
10867  val = pt_rewrite_to_auto_param (parser, val);
10868  if (prev != NULL)
10869  {
10870  prev->next = val;
10871  }
10872 
10873  if (val == NULL)
10874  {
10875  break;
10876  }
10877  }
10878 
10879  if (head == NULL)
10880  {
10881  head = val;
10882  }
10883 
10884  prev = val;
10885  }
10886  value_list->info.node_list.list = head;
10887  }
10888 
10889  /* make query string */
10890  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 1;
10891  parser->long_string_skipped = 0;
10892  parser->print_type_ambiguity = 0;
10893  PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS (parser, statement, (PT_CONVERT_RANGE | PT_PRINT_QUOTES | PT_PRINT_USER));
10894  contextp->sql_hash_text = (char *) statement->alias_print;
10895  error =
10896  SHA1Compute ((unsigned char *) contextp->sql_hash_text, (unsigned) strlen (contextp->sql_hash_text),
10897  &contextp->sha1);
10898  if (error != NO_ERROR)
10899  {
10900  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10901  return error;
10902  }
10903  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 0;
10904  if (parser->long_string_skipped || parser->print_type_ambiguity)
10905  {
10906  statement->cannot_prepare = 1;
10907  return NO_ERROR;
10908  }
10909 
10910  /* look up server's XASL cache for this query string and get XASL file id (XASL_ID) returned if found */
10911  contextp->recompile_xasl = statement->recompile;
10912  if (statement->recompile == 0)
10913  {
10914  error = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
10915  if (error != NO_ERROR)
10916  {
10917  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error);
10918  }
10919  else if (contextp->recompile_xasl == true)
10920  {
10921  /* recompile requested by server */
10922  if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
10923  {
10924  free_and_init (stream.xasl_id);
10925  }
10926  }
10927  }
10928 
10929  if (stream.xasl_id == NULL && error == NO_ERROR)
10930  {
10931  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
10932  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
10933  contextp->xasl = pt_to_insert_xasl (parser, statement);
10934 
10935  if (contextp->xasl)
10936  {
10937  assert (contextp->xasl->dptr_list == NULL);
10938 
10939  if (error == NO_ERROR)
10940  {
10941  error = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (contextp->xasl, &stream);
10942  if (error != NO_ERROR)
10943  {
10944  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
10945  }
10946  }
10947  }
10948  else
10949  {
10950  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10951  error = er_errid ();
10952  }
10953 
10954  if (stream.buffer && (error >= NO_ERROR))
10955  {
10956  error = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
10957  if (error != NO_ERROR)
10958  {
10959  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
10960  error = er_errid ();
10961  }
10962  }
10963 
10964  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
10965  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
10966 
10967  /* As a result of query preparation of the server, the XASL cache for this query will be created or updated. */
10968 
10969  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
10970  if (stream.buffer)
10971  {
10972  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
10973  }
10974 
10975  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
10976  }
10977  else
10978  {
10979  if (error == NO_ERROR)
10980  {
10981  statement->use_plan_cache = 1;
10982  }
10983  else
10984  {
10985  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
10986  }
10987  }
10988 
10989  /* save the XASL_ID that is allocated and returned by prepare_query() into 'statement->xasl_id' to be used by
10990  * do_execute_update() */
10991  statement->xasl_id = stream.xasl_id;
10992 
10993  return NO_ERROR;
10994 }
10995 
10996 /*
10997  * do_insert_at_server () - Builds an xasl tree for a server insert and
10998  * executes it.
10999  *
11000  * return : Error code.
11001  * parser (in) : Parser context.
11002  * statement (in) : Parse tree node for insert statement.
11003  *
11004  * NOTE:
11005  * The xasl tree has an INSERT_PROC node as the top node and
11006  * a BUILDLIST_PROC as its aptr. The BUILDLIST_PROC selects the
11007  * insert values. The INSERT_PROC node scans the BUILDLIST_PROC results.
11008  * The server executes the aptr and then for each instance selected,
11009  * inserts it. The result information is sent back to the
11010  * client as a list file without any pages. The list file tuple count
11011  * is used as the return value from this routine.
11012 
11013  * The instances for the class are flushed from the client before the
11014  * insert is executed.
11015  */
11016 static int
11017 do_insert_at_server (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
11018 {
11019  int error = NO_ERROR;
11020  XASL_NODE *xasl = NULL;
11021  int count = 0;
11022  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
11023  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
11024 
11025  XASL_STREAM stream;
11026 
11027  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
11028 
11029  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
11030 
11031  if (parser == NULL || statement == NULL || statement->node_type != PT_INSERT)
11032  {
11033  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
11034  }
11035 
11036  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
11037  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
11038  xasl = pt_to_insert_xasl (parser, statement);
11039 
11040  if (xasl)
11041  {
11042  error = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (xasl, &stream);
11043  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11044  {
11045  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
11046  }
11047  }
11048  else
11049  {
11050  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
11051  error = er_errid ();
11052  }
11053 
11054  if (error == NO_ERROR && stream.buffer != NULL)
11055  {
11056  int au_save;
11057  QUERY_FLAG query_flag;
11058 
11059  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
11060  /* Do not update LAST_INSERT_ID during executing a trigger. */
11061  if (do_Trigger_involved == true)
11062  {
11063  query_flag |= TRIGGER_IS_INVOLVED;
11064  }
11065 
11066  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
11067  {
11068  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
11069  }
11070 
11071  assert (stream.buffer_size > 0);
11072 
11073  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
11074 
11075  error =
11076  prepare_and_execute_query (stream.buffer, stream.buffer_size, &parser->query_id,
11077  (parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count), parser->host_variables,
11078  &list_id, query_flag);
11079  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
11080  }
11081 
11082  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
11083  if (stream.buffer)
11084  {
11085  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
11086  }
11087 
11088  if (list_id)
11089  {
11090  count = list_id->tuple_cnt;
11091  if (count > 0 && (statement->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL || statement->info.insert.do_replace))
11092  {
11093  MOP class_obj = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
11094 
11095  if (statement->use_auto_commit && tran_was_latest_query_committed ())
11096  {
11097  /* Nothing to flush. Avoids flush, since may fetch the class. */
11098  error = sm_decache_instances_after_query_executed_with_commit (class_obj);
11099  }
11100  else
11101  {
11102  error = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (class_obj, true);
11103  }
11104  }
11105 
11106  if (parser->return_generated_keys)
11107  {
11108  statement->etc = (void *) list_id;
11109  }
11110  else
11111  {
11112  regu_free_listid (list_id);
11113  }
11114  }
11115 
11116  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
11117 
11118  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
11119  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
11120 
11121  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
11122  {
11123  return count;
11124  }
11125  else
11126  {
11127  return error;
11128  }
11129 }
11130 
11131 /*
11132  * check_for_cons() - Determines whether an attribute has not null or unique
11133  * constraints.
11134  *
11135  * return: Error code
11136  * parser(in): Parser context
11137  * has_unique(in/out):
11138  * non_null_attrs(in/out): all the "NOT NULL" attributes except for the
11139  * AUTO_INCREMENT ones
11140  * attr_list(in): Parse tree of an insert statement attribute list
11141  * class_obj(in): Class object
11142 
11143  */
11144 static int
11145 check_for_cons (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, int *has_unique, PT_NODE ** non_null_attrs, const PT_NODE * attr_list,
11146  DB_OBJECT * class_obj)
11147 {
11148  PT_NODE *pointer;
11149 
11150  assert (non_null_attrs != NULL);
11151  if (*non_null_attrs != NULL)
11152  {
11153  /* non_null_attrs already checked */
11154  return NO_ERROR;
11155  }
11156  *has_unique = 0;
11157 
11158  while (attr_list)
11159  {
11160  if (attr_list->node_type != PT_NAME)
11161  {
11162  /* bullet proofing, should not get here */
11163  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
11164  }
11165 
11166  if (*has_unique == 0 && sm_att_unique_constrained (class_obj, attr_list->info.name.original))
11167  {
11168  *has_unique = 1;
11169  }
11170 
11171  if (sm_att_constrained (class_obj, attr_list->info.name.original, SM_ATTFLAG_NON_NULL))
11172  {
11173  /* NULL values are allowed for auto_increment columns. It means that the next auto_increment value will be
11174  * inserted. */
11175  if (sm_att_auto_increment (class_obj, attr_list->info.name.original) == false)
11176  {
11177  pointer = pt_point (parser, attr_list);
11178  if (pointer == NULL)
11179  {
11180  PT_ERRORm (parser, attr_list, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
11181 
11182  if (*non_null_attrs)
11183  {
11184  parser_free_tree (parser, *non_null_attrs);
11185  }
11186  *non_null_attrs = NULL;
11187 
11188  return MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED;
11189  }
11190  *non_null_attrs = parser_append_node (pointer, *non_null_attrs);
11191  }
11192  }
11193 
11194  attr_list = attr_list->next;
11195  }
11196 
11197  if (*has_unique == 0)
11198  {
11199  /* check if the class has an auto-increment attribute which has unique constraint */
11200 
11201  SM_CLASS *class_;
11202  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
11203 
11204  if (au_fetch_class_force (class_obj, &class_, AU_FETCH_READ) == NO_ERROR)
11205  {
11206  for (att = class_->ordered_attributes; att; att = att->order_link)
11207  {
11208  if ((att->flags & SM_ATTFLAG_AUTO_INCREMENT) && classobj_has_unique_constraint (att->constraints))
11209  {
11210  *has_unique = 1;
11211  break;
11212  }
11213  }
11214  }
11215  }
11216 
11217  return NO_ERROR;
11218 }
11219 
11220 /*
11221  * is_server_insert_allowed () - Checks to see if a server-side insert is
11222  * allowed
11223  *
11224  * return : Error code.
11225  * parser (in) : Parser context.
11226  * statement (in) : Parse tree node for insert statement.
11227  */
11228 static int
11229 is_server_insert_allowed (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
11230 {
11231  int error = NO_ERROR;
11232  int trigger_involved;
11233  PT_NODE *attrs = NULL, *attr = NULL;
11234  PT_NODE *value_clauses = NULL, *class_ = NULL;
11235  /* set lock timeout hint if specified */
11236  int server_preference;
11237  int save_au;
11238 
11239  assert (statement != NULL && statement->node_type == PT_INSERT);
11240  if (statement == NULL || statement->node_type != PT_INSERT)
11241  {
11242  return ER_FAILED;
11243  }
11244 
11245  if (statement->info.insert.server_allowed != SERVER_INSERT_NOT_CHECKED)
11246  {
11247  /* already checked */
11248  return NO_ERROR;
11249  }
11250  statement->info.insert.server_allowed = SERVER_INSERT_IS_NOT_ALLOWED;
11251 
11252  AU_DISABLE (save_au);
11253 
11254  class_ = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
11255 
11256  value_clauses = statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
11257  attrs = statement->info.insert.attr_list;
11258  /* server insert cannot handle insert into a shared attribute */
11259  attr = attrs;
11260  while (attr)
11261  {
11262  if (attr->node_type != PT_NAME)
11263  {
11264  /* this can occur when inserting into a view with default values. The name list may not be inverted, and may
11265  * contain expressions, such as (x+2). */
11266  goto end;
11267  }
11268  if (attr->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
11269  {
11270  /* We found a shared attribute, bail out */
11271  goto end;
11272  }
11273  attr = attr->next;
11274  }
11275 
11276  error =
11277  check_for_cons (parser, &statement->info.insert.has_uniques, &statement->info.insert.non_null_attrs, attrs,
11278  class_->info.name.db_object);
11279  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11280  {
11281  goto end;
11282  }
11283 
11284  server_preference = prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_INSERT_MODE);
11285 
11286  if (statement->info.insert.hint & PT_HINT_INSERT_MODE)
11287  {
11288  PT_NODE *mode = statement->info.insert.insert_mode;
11289  if (mode && mode->node_type == PT_NAME)
11290  {
11291  server_preference = atoi (mode->info.name.original);
11292  }
11293  }
11294 
11295  if (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
11296  {
11297  if (!(server_preference & INSERT_SELECT))
11298  {
11299  goto end;
11300  }
11301  }
11302  else if (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_VALUE)
11303  {
11304  int server_allowed = 1;
11305  if (!(server_preference & INSERT_VALUES))
11306  {
11307  goto end;
11308  }
11309  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, value_clauses, do_check_insert_server_allowed, &server_allowed, NULL, NULL);
11310  if (pt_has_error (parser))
11311  {
11312  error = ER_FAILED;
11313  goto end;
11314  }
11315  if (!server_allowed)
11316  {
11317  goto end;
11318  }
11319  }
11320  else
11321  {
11322  assert (false);
11323  }
11324 
11325  if (statement->info.insert.into_var != NULL)
11326  {
11327  goto end;
11328  }
11329 
11330  /* check option could be done on the server by adding another predicate to the insert_info block. However, one must
11331  * also take care that subqueries in this predicate have their xasl blocks properly attached to the insert xasl
11332  * block. Currently, pt_to_pred will do that only if being called from parser_generate_xasl. This may mean that
11333  * do_server_insert should call parser_generate_xasl, and have a portion of its code put. */
11334  if (statement->info.insert.where != NULL)
11335  {
11336  goto end;
11337  }
11338 
11339  if (statement->info.insert.do_replace && statement->info.insert.has_uniques)
11340  {
11341  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_->info.name.db_object, &trigger_involved, TR_EVENT_DELETE);
11342  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11343  {
11344  goto end;
11345  }
11346 
11347  if (trigger_involved)
11348  {
11349  goto end;
11350  }
11351  }
11352 
11353  if (statement->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL && statement->info.insert.has_uniques)
11354  {
11355  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_->info.name.db_object, &trigger_involved, TR_EVENT_UPDATE);
11356  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11357  {
11358  goto end;
11359  }
11360 
11361  if (trigger_involved)
11362  {
11363  goto end;
11364  }
11365  }
11366 
11367  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_->info.name.db_object, &trigger_involved, TR_EVENT_INSERT);
11368  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11369  {
11370  goto end;
11371  }
11372 
11373  /* Even if unique indexes are defined on the class, the operation could be performed on server. */
11374  if (!trigger_involved && !do_Trigger_involved)
11375  {
11376  statement->info.insert.server_allowed = SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED;
11377  }
11378 
11379 end:
11380  /* the entire insert statement must be executed on client or on server. if any sub-insert is not allowed on server,
11381  * or if the root is not allowed on server, all inserts must be executed on client */
11382  if (error == NO_ERROR && statement->info.insert.server_allowed == SERVER_INSERT_IS_NOT_ALLOWED
11383  && value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_VALUE)
11384  {
11385  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, value_clauses, do_set_insert_server_not_allowed, NULL, NULL, NULL);
11386  if (pt_has_error (parser))
11387  {
11388  error = ER_FAILED;
11389  }
11390  }
11391  AU_ENABLE (save_au);
11392  return error;
11393 }
11394 
11395 /*
11396  * do_check_insert_server_allowed () - Parser walk function that checks all
11397  * sub-inserts are allowed on server.
11398  *
11399  * return : Unchanged node argument.
11400  * parser (in) : Parser context.
11401  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
11402  * arg (out) : int * argument that stores server_allowed.
11403  * continue_walk (in) : Continue walk.
11404  */
11405 static PT_NODE *
11406 do_check_insert_server_allowed (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
11407 {
11408  int *server_allowed = (int *) arg;
11409  int error = NO_ERROR;
11410 
11411  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_INSERT)
11412  {
11413  /* stop check */
11414  return node;
11415  }
11416 
11417  *server_allowed = 1;
11418  error = is_server_insert_allowed (parser, node);
11419  if (error != NO_ERROR || node->info.insert.server_allowed != SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED)
11420  {
11421  *server_allowed = 0;
11422  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
11423  }
11424  return node;
11425 }
11426 
11427 /*
11428  * do_set_insert_server_not_allowed () - Parser walk function that should be
11429  * called when top insert is not allowed
11430  * on server. This will force all sub
11431  * inserts to run on client.
11432  *
11433  * return : Unchanged node argument.
11434  * parser (in) : Parser context.
11435  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
11436  * void_arg (in) : Void argument.
11437  * continue_walk (in) : Continue walk.
11438  */
11439 static PT_NODE *
11440 do_set_insert_server_not_allowed (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *void_arg, int *continue_walk)
11441 {
11442  int error = NO_ERROR;
11443 
11444  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_INSERT)
11445  {
11446  return node;
11447  }
11448 
11449  if (node->info.insert.server_allowed == SERVER_INSERT_NOT_CHECKED)
11450  {
11451  /* is_server_insert_allowed was no called for this insert node, must call check_for_cons (). */
11452  DB_OBJECT *class_obj = node->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object;
11453  error =
11454  check_for_cons (parser, &node->info.insert.has_uniques, &node->info.insert.non_null_attrs,
11455  node->info.insert.attr_list, class_obj);
11456  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11457  {
11458  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
11459  return node;
11460  }
11461  }
11462  node->info.insert.server_allowed = SERVER_INSERT_IS_NOT_ALLOWED;
11463  return node;
11464 }
11465 
11466 /*
11467  * do_create_midxkey_for_constraint () - create a MIDX_KEY db_value for the
11468  * specified constraint using the values
11469  * assigned in an object template
11470  * return : error code or NO_ERROR;
11471  * tmpl (in) : object template
11472  * constraint (in) : constraint
11473  * key (in/out) : the MIDX key
11474  */
11475 static int
11476 do_create_midxkey_for_constraint (DB_OTMPL * tmpl, SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT * constraint, DB_VALUE * key)
11477 {
11478  DB_MIDXKEY midxkey;
11479  SM_ATTRIBUTE **attr = NULL;
11480  int buf_size = 0, bitmap_size = 0, i, error = NO_ERROR, attr_count = 0;
11481  unsigned char *bits;
11482  char *bound_bits = NULL, *key_ptr = NULL;
11483  OR_BUF buf;
11484  DB_VALUE *val = NULL;
11485  TP_DOMAIN *attr_dom = NULL, *dom = NULL, *setdomain = NULL;
11486  const int *asc_desc = NULL;
11487 
11488  midxkey.buf = NULL;
11489  midxkey.min_max_val.position = -1;
11490  asc_desc = db_constraint_asc_desc (constraint);
11491 
11492  /* compute key size */
11493  for (attr_count = 0, attr = constraint->attributes; *attr != NULL; attr_count++, attr++)
11494  {
11495  val = NULL;
11496  if (tmpl->assignments[(*attr)->order] != NULL)
11497  {
11498  val = tmpl->assignments[(*attr)->order]->variable;
11499  }
11500 
11501  attr_dom = tp_domain_copy ((*attr)->domain, false);
11502  if (attr_dom == NULL)
11503  {
11504  error = ER_FAILED;
11505  goto error_return;
11506  }
11507 
11508  if (asc_desc != NULL && asc_desc[attr_count] == 1)
11509  {
11510  attr_dom->is_desc = 1;
11511  }
11512 
11513  if (val != NULL && !DB_IS_NULL (val))
11514  {
11515  if (attr_dom->type->index_lengthval != NULL)
11516  {
11517  buf_size += (*(attr_dom->type->index_lengthval)) (val);
11518  }
11519  else
11520  {
11521  buf_size += attr_dom->type->disksize;
11522  }
11523  }
11524 
11525  if (setdomain == NULL)
11526  {
11527  setdomain = attr_dom;
11528  }
11529  else
11530  {
11531  dom->next = attr_dom;
11532  }
11533  dom = attr_dom;
11534  }
11535 
11536  bitmap_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (attr_count);
11537  buf_size += bitmap_size;
11538 
11539  midxkey.buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (NULL, buf_size);
11540  if (midxkey.buf == NULL)
11541  {
11542  error = ER_FAILED;
11543  goto error_return;
11544  }
11545 
11546  bound_bits = midxkey.buf;
11547  key_ptr = bound_bits + bitmap_size;
11548 
11549  OR_BUF_INIT (buf, key_ptr, buf_size - bitmap_size);
11550  if (bitmap_size > 0)
11551  {
11552  bits = (unsigned char *) bound_bits;
11553  for (i = 0; i < bitmap_size; i++)
11554  {
11555  bits[i] = (unsigned char) 0;
11556  }
11557  }
11558 
11559  for (i = 0, attr = constraint->attributes; *attr != NULL; attr++, i++)
11560  {
11561  val = NULL;
11562  if (tmpl->assignments[(*attr)->order] != NULL)
11563  {
11564  val = tmpl->assignments[(*attr)->order]->variable;
11565  }
11566  dom = (*attr)->domain;
11567 
11568  if (val != NULL && !DB_IS_NULL (val))
11569  {
11570  (*((dom->type)->index_writeval)) (&buf, val);
11571  OR_ENABLE_BOUND_BIT (bound_bits, i);
11572  }
11573  else
11574  {
11575  OR_CLEAR_BOUND_BIT (bound_bits, i);
11576  }
11577  }
11578 
11579  midxkey.size = buf_size;
11580  midxkey.ncolumns = attr_count;
11581  midxkey.domain = tp_domain_construct (DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY, NULL, attr_count, 0, setdomain);
11582  if (midxkey.domain == NULL)
11583  {
11584  error = ER_FAILED;
11585  goto error_return;
11586  }
11587  midxkey.domain = tp_domain_cache (midxkey.domain);
11588  midxkey.min_max_val.position = -1;
11589  midxkey.min_max_val.type = MIN_COLUMN;
11590 
11591  error = db_make_midxkey (key, &midxkey);
11592  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11593  {
11594  goto error_return;
11595  }
11596  key->need_clear = true;
11597  return NO_ERROR;
11598 
11599 error_return:
11600  if (midxkey.buf != NULL)
11601  {
11602  db_private_free (NULL, midxkey.buf);
11603  }
11604  dom = setdomain;
11605  while (dom != NULL)
11606  {
11607  attr_dom = dom->next;
11608  dom->next = NULL;
11609  tp_domain_free (dom);
11610  dom = attr_dom;
11611  }
11612  return error;
11613 }
11614 
11615 /*
11616  * do_create_odku_stmt () - create an UPDATE statement for ON DUPLICATE KEY
11617  * UPDATE node
11618  * return : update node or NULL
11619  * parser (in) : parser context
11620  * insert (in) : INSERT statement node
11621  *
11622  * Note: this function alters the flag set on the SPEC node of the INSERT
11623  * statement. Callers should backup the value of the flag and restore it
11624  * when they're finished with the UPDATE statement.
11625  */
11626 static PT_NODE *
11627 do_create_odku_stmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert)
11628 {
11629  PT_NODE *update = NULL;
11630 
11631  if (insert == NULL || insert->node_type != PT_INSERT)
11632  {
11633  assert (false);
11634  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid arguments");
11635  return NULL;
11636  }
11637 
11638  insert->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flag =
11639  (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (insert->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE);
11640 
11641  update = parser_new_node (parser, PT_UPDATE);
11642  if (update == NULL)
11643  {
11644  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11645  goto error_return;
11646  }
11647  update->info.update.assignment = insert->info.insert.odku_assignments;
11648  update->info.update.spec = insert->info.insert.spec;
11649 
11650  if (insert->info.insert.where != NULL)
11651  {
11652  PT_NODE *check_where = parser_new_node (parser, PT_CHECK_OPTION);
11653  if (check_where == NULL)
11654  {
11655  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11656  goto error_return;
11657  }
11658 
11659  check_where->info.check_option.expr = insert->info.insert.where;
11660  check_where->info.check_option.spec_id = insert->info.insert.spec->info.spec.id;
11661 
11662  update->info.update.check_where = check_where;
11663  }
11664 
11665  return update;
11666 
11667 error_return:
11668  if (update != NULL)
11669  {
11670  update->info.update.assignment = NULL;
11671  update->info.update.spec = NULL;
11672  if (update->info.update.check_where != NULL)
11673  {
11674  update->info.update.check_where->info.check_option.expr = NULL;
11675  }
11676  parser_free_tree (parser, update);
11677  }
11678 
11679  return NULL;
11680 }
11681 
11682 /*
11683  * do_find_unique_constraint_violations () - find oids for which unique
11684  * constraints would be violated by
11685  * inserting an object template
11686  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
11687  * tmpl (in) : object template
11688  * for_update (in) : if true, offending OIDs will be updated
11689  * oids (in/out) : array of offending OIDs
11690  * oids_count (in) : number of OIDs in array
11691  */
11692 static int
11693 do_find_unique_constraint_violations (DB_OTMPL * tmpl, bool for_update, OID ** oids, int *oids_count)
11694 {
11695  int error = NO_ERROR;
11696  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *constraint = NULL;
11697  SM_CLASS *class_ = NULL;
11698  int unique_count = 0, key_cnt, i, level, attr_count = 0;
11699  BTID *unique_btids = NULL;
11700  DB_VALUE *unique_keys = NULL;
11701  SM_ATTRIBUTE **attr;
11702  OBJ_TEMPASSIGN *assignment = NULL;
11703  bool should_verify = false;
11704  BTREE_SEARCH result;
11705  SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type = S_UPDATE;
11706 
11707  qo_get_optimization_param (&level, QO_PARAM_LEVEL);
11708  if (level & 0x02)
11709  {
11710  /* User is only interested in query plan. Query will not be executed and we have no plan to show. */
11711  *oids = NULL;
11712  *oids_count = 0;
11713  return NO_ERROR;
11714  }
11715  /* Populate the defaults and auto_increment values here because we need them when building the WHERE clause for the
11716  * SELECT statement. These values will not be reassigned if the template will eventually be inserted as they are
11717  * already populated. */
11718  error = obt_populate_known_arguments (tmpl);
11719  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11720  {
11721  return error;
11722  }
11723 
11724  class_ = tmpl->class_;
11725  for (constraint = class_->constraints; constraint != NULL; constraint = constraint->next)
11726  {
11727  if (!SM_IS_CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE_FAMILY (constraint->type))
11728  {
11729  continue;
11730  }
11731  unique_count++;
11732  }
11733 
11734  if (unique_count == 0)
11735  {
11736  /* class does not have unique constraints */
11737  *oids = NULL;
11738  oids_count = 0;
11739  return NO_ERROR;
11740  }
11741 
11742  unique_btids = (BTID *) db_private_alloc (NULL, unique_count * sizeof (BTID));
11743  if (unique_btids == NULL)
11744  {
11745  error = ER_FAILED;
11746  goto cleanup;
11747  }
11748  unique_keys = (DB_VALUE *) db_private_alloc (NULL, unique_count * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
11749  if (unique_keys == NULL)
11750  {
11751  error = ER_FAILED;
11752  goto cleanup;
11753  }
11754  key_cnt = 0;
11755  for (constraint = class_->constraints; constraint != NULL; constraint = constraint->next)
11756  {
11757  if (!SM_IS_CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE_FAMILY (constraint->type))
11758  {
11759  continue;
11760  }
11761  BTID_COPY (&unique_btids[key_cnt], &constraint->index_btid);
11762  db_make_null (&unique_keys[key_cnt]);
11763  attr_count = 0;
11764  for (attr = constraint->attributes; *attr != NULL; attr++)
11765  {
11766  assignment = tmpl->assignments[(*attr)->order];
11767  if (assignment != NULL && assignment->variable != NULL)
11768  {
11769  /* this constraint may be violated */
11770  should_verify = true;
11771  }
11772  attr_count++;
11773  }
11774 
11775  if (!should_verify || attr_count == 0)
11776  {
11777  continue;
11778  }
11779 
11780  if (attr_count == 1)
11781  {
11782  /* single key handling */
11783  attr = constraint->attributes;
11784  assignment = tmpl->assignments[(*attr)->order];
11785  if (assignment == NULL)
11786  {
11787  /* value not set */
11788  continue;
11789  }
11790  pr_clone_value (assignment->variable, &unique_keys[key_cnt]);
11791  key_cnt++;
11792  continue;
11793  }
11794 
11795  /* multiple key, need to create a MIDXKEY */
11796  error = do_create_midxkey_for_constraint (tmpl, constraint, &unique_keys[key_cnt]);
11797  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11798  {
11799  goto cleanup;
11800  }
11801  key_cnt++;
11802  }
11803 
11804  if (key_cnt == 0)
11805  {
11806  goto cleanup;
11807  }
11808 
11809  if (for_update)
11810  {
11811  op_type = S_UPDATE;
11812  }
11813  else
11814  {
11815  op_type = S_DELETE;
11816  }
11817 
11818  result =
11819  btree_find_multi_uniques (ws_oid (tmpl->classobj), tmpl->pruning_type, unique_btids, unique_keys, key_cnt, op_type,
11820  oids, oids_count);
11821  if (result == BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED)
11822  {
11823  error = ER_FAILED;
11824  }
11825 
11826 cleanup:
11827  if (unique_keys != NULL)
11828  {
11829  for (i = 0; i < key_cnt; i++)
11830  {
11831  pr_clear_value (&unique_keys[i]);
11832  }
11833  db_private_free (NULL, unique_keys);
11834  }
11835  if (unique_btids != NULL)
11836  {
11837  db_private_free (NULL, unique_btids);
11838  }
11839  return error;
11840 }
11841 
11842 /*
11843  * do_on_duplicate_key_update() - runs an update statement instead of an
11844  * insert statement for the cases in which
11845  * the insert would cause a unique constraint
11846  * violation
11847  * return: The number of affected rows if successful, error code otherwise
11848  *
11849  * parser(in) : Parser context
11850  * tmpl(in) : object template to be inserted
11851  * update_stmt(in) : the update statement to run if there are unique
11852  * constraint violations
11853  *
11854  * Notes: This function creates a SELECT statement based on the values
11855  * supplied in the template object and runs update_stmt for one
11856  * of the OIDs with which tmpl would generate unique key conflicts.
11857  * If this function returns 0 then no rows were updated and the caller
11858  * should proceed with the insert.
11859  */
11860 static int
11861 do_on_duplicate_key_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OTMPL * tmpl, PT_NODE * update_stmt)
11862 {
11863  int retval = NO_ERROR;
11864  int ret_code = 0;
11865  OID *oids = NULL;
11866  int oids_count = 0;
11867 
11868  retval = do_find_unique_constraint_violations (tmpl, true, &oids, &oids_count);
11869  if (retval != NO_ERROR)
11870  {
11871  goto cleanup;
11872  }
11873  assert_release (oids_count <= 1);
11874  if (oids_count == 0)
11875  {
11876  assert (oids == NULL);
11877  return NO_ERROR;
11878  }
11879 
11880  update_stmt->info.update.object = ws_mop (oids, NULL);
11881 
11882  ret_code = update_object_by_oid (parser, update_stmt, ON_DUPLICATE_KEY_UPDATE);
11883  update_stmt->info.update.object = NULL;
11884  if (ret_code < NO_ERROR)
11885  {
11886  retval = ret_code;
11887  goto cleanup;
11888  }
11889 
11890  /* one updated row */
11891  retval = 1;
11892 
11893 cleanup:
11894  if (oids != NULL)
11895  {
11896  free_and_init (oids);
11897  }
11898  return retval;
11899 }
11900 
11901 /*
11902  * do_replace_into() - runs an delete statement for the cases in
11903  * which INSERT would cause a unique constraint violation
11904  *
11905  * return: The number of affected rows if successful, error code otherwise
11906  *
11907  * parser(in) : Parser context
11908  * tmpl(in) : object template to be inserted
11909  * spec(in) : the spec used for insert
11910  * class_specs(in) :
11911  *
11912  * Notes: This function creates a SELECT statement based on the values
11913  * supplied in the template object and runs delete for the
11914  * OIDs with which tmpl would generate unique key violations
11915  */
11916 static int
11917 do_replace_into (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OTMPL * tmpl, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * class_specs)
11918 {
11919  int retval = 0, error = NO_ERROR;
11920  OID *oids = NULL;
11921  int oids_count = 0, i;
11922  MOP obj = NULL;
11923 
11924  error = do_find_unique_constraint_violations (tmpl, false, &oids, &oids_count);
11925  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11926  {
11927  retval = error;
11928  goto cleanup;
11929  }
11930  if (oids_count == 0)
11931  {
11932  retval = 0;
11933  goto cleanup;
11934  }
11935 
11936  retval = 0;
11937  for (i = 0; i < oids_count; i++)
11938  {
11939  obj = ws_mop (&oids[i], NULL);
11940  error = db_is_deleted (obj);
11941  if (error < 0)
11942  {
11943  goto cleanup;
11944  retval = error;
11945  }
11946  if (error > 0)
11947  {
11948  error = NO_ERROR;
11949  continue;
11950  }
11951 
11952  error = delete_object_tuple (obj);
11953  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11954  {
11955  retval = error;
11956  goto cleanup;
11957  }
11958  retval++;
11959  }
11960 
11961 cleanup:
11962  if (oids != NULL)
11963  {
11964  free_and_init (oids);
11965  }
11966  return retval;
11967 }
11968 
11969 /*
11970  * is_replace_or_odku_allowed() - checks to see if the class is partitioned or
11971  * part of an inheritance chain
11972  *
11973  * return: error code if unsuccessful, NO_ERROR otherwise
11974  *
11975  * obj(in) : object to be checked
11976  * allowed(out) : 0 if not allowed, 1 if allowed
11977  *
11978  */
11979 static int
11980 is_replace_or_odku_allowed (DB_OBJECT * obj, int *allowed)
11981 {
11982  int error = NO_ERROR;
11983  SM_CLASS *smclass = NULL;
11984 
11985  *allowed = 1;
11986  error = sm_is_partitioned_class (obj);
11987  if (error < 0)
11988  {
11989  return error;
11990  }
11991  if (error > 0)
11992  {
11993  return NO_ERROR;
11994  }
11995 
11996  error = au_fetch_class (obj, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT);
11997  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11998  {
11999  return error;
12000  }
12001 
12002  if (smclass->inheritance != NULL || smclass->users != NULL)
12003  {
12004  *allowed = 0;
12005  }
12006 
12007  return error;
12008 }
12009 
12010 /*
12011  * do_insert_template () - Final step of insert execution on client.
12012  * 1. Checks if insert is allowed on server. If it is,
12013  * calls do_insert_at_server ().
12014  * 2. If INSERT ... SELECT is not allowed on server,
12015  * calls insert_subquery_results ().
12016  * 3. If INSERT ... VALUES is not allowed on server,
12017  * it is handled here.
12018  *
12019  * return : NO_ERROR or error code.
12020  * parser (in) : Parser context.
12021  * otemplate (out) : Class template to be inserted.
12022  * statement (in) : Parse tree of insert statement.
12023  * savepoint_name (in/out) : Name of savepoint (no savepoint if null).
12024  * row_count_ptr (in/out) : Pointer to row counter.
12025  */
12026 int
12027 do_insert_template (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OTMPL ** otemplate, PT_NODE * statement, const char **savepoint_name,
12028  int *row_count_ptr)
12029 {
12030  const char *into_label = NULL;
12031  DB_VALUE *ins_val = NULL, *val = NULL, db_value;
12032  int error = NO_ERROR, flag = 0;
12033  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *vc = NULL;
12034  PT_NODE *into = NULL;
12035  PT_NODE *class_ = NULL;
12036  PT_NODE *update = NULL;
12037  DB_ATTDESC **attr_descs = NULL;
12038  int i, degree, row_count = 0;
12039  int wait_msecs = -2, old_wait_msecs = -2;
12040  float hint_waitsecs;
12041  PT_NODE *hint_arg;
12042  int pruning_type = DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
12043  PT_NODE *value_clauses = statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
12044  PT_NODE *value_list = NULL;
12045  DB_OBJECT *obj = NULL, *vobj = NULL;
12046  unsigned int save_custom;
12047  DB_VALUE *value = NULL;
12048  DB_SEQ *seq = NULL;
12049  int obj_count = 0;
12050 
12051  assert (otemplate != NULL);
12052  if (otemplate == NULL)
12053  {
12054  return ER_FAILED;
12055  }
12056  *otemplate = NULL;
12057 
12058  db_make_null (&db_value);
12059 
12060  if (row_count_ptr != NULL)
12061  {
12062  *row_count_ptr = 0;
12063  }
12064 
12065  degree = 0;
12066  class_ = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
12067  flag = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flag;
