12068  /* clear any previous error indicator because the rest of do_insert is sensitive to er_errid(). */
12069  er_clear ();
12070 
12071  error = do_insert_checks (parser, statement, &class_, &update, value_clauses);
12072  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12073  {
12074  ASSERT_ERROR ();
12075  goto cleanup;
12076  }
12077 
12078  into = statement->info.insert.into_var;
12079  if (into != NULL && PT_IS_NAME_NODE (into) && into->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
12080  {
12081  assert (into->info.name.original != NULL);
12082  into_label = into->info.name.original;
12083  }
12084  else
12085  {
12086  into_label = NULL;
12087  }
12088  if (into_label)
12089  {
12090  ins_val = db_value_create ();
12091  if (ins_val == NULL)
12092  {
12093  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12094  error = er_errid ();
12095  goto cleanup;
12096  }
12097  db_make_object (ins_val, (DB_OBJECT *) NULL);
12098  }
12099 
12100  if (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ && statement->info.insert.server_allowed != SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED)
12101  {
12102  /* We need to make sure snapshot is generated for this execution. */
12103  error = log_get_mvcc_snapshot ();
12104  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12105  {
12106  ASSERT_ERROR ();
12107  goto cleanup;
12108  }
12109  }
12110 
12111  if (statement->info.insert.server_allowed == SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED)
12112  {
12113  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12114  {
12115  goto cleanup;
12116  }
12117  error = do_insert_at_server (parser, statement);
12118  if (error >= 0)
12119  {
12120  row_count = error;
12121  }
12122  }
12123  else if (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY
12124  && (vc = value_clauses->info.node_list.list) != NULL)
12125  {
12126  /* execute sub-query & insert its results into target class */
12127  row_count = insert_subquery_results (parser, statement, value_clauses, class_, savepoint_name);
12128  error = (row_count < 0) ? row_count : NO_ERROR;
12129  if (error == NO_ERROR)
12130  {
12131  if (ins_val != NULL)
12132  {
12133  if (row_count > 1)
12134  {
12135  error = ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY;
12136  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
12137  goto cleanup;
12138  }
12139  val = (DB_VALUE *) statement->etc;
12140  if (val != NULL)
12141  {
12142  db_make_object (ins_val, db_get_object (val));
12143  }
12144  if (into_label != NULL)
12145  {
12146  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, ins_val);
12147  }
12148  }
12149  }
12150  }
12151  else if (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_VALUE
12152  || value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_DEFAULT_VALUE)
12153  {
12154  if (qo_need_skip_execution ())
12155  {
12156  return NO_ERROR;
12157  }
12158 
12159  error = sm_partitioned_class_type (class_->info.name.db_object, &pruning_type, NULL, NULL);
12160  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12161  {
12162  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12163  error = er_errid ();
12164  goto cleanup;
12165  }
12166 
12167  if (parser->return_generated_keys)
12168  {
12169  seq = set_create_sequence (0);
12170  if (seq == NULL)
12171  {
12172  error = ER_FAILED;
12173  goto cleanup;
12174  }
12175  }
12176 
12177  error = do_evaluate_insert_values (parser, statement);
12178  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12179  {
12180  goto cleanup;
12181  }
12182 
12183  for (value_list = value_clauses; value_list != NULL; value_list = value_list->next)
12184  {
12185  /* now create the object using templates, and then dbt_put each value for each corresponding attribute. Of
12186  * course, it is presumed that the order in which attributes are defined in the class as well as in the
12187  * actual insert statement is preserved. */
12188  *otemplate = dbt_create_object_internal (class_->info.name.db_object);
12189  if (*otemplate == NULL)
12190  {
12191  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12192  error = er_errid ();
12193  goto cleanup;
12194  }
12195  (*otemplate)->pruning_type = pruning_type;
12196  if (pruning_type != DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS)
12197  {
12198  /* The reason we're forcing a flush here is to throw an error if the object does belong to any partition.
12199  * If we don't do it here, the error will be thrown when the object is flushed either by the next
12200  * statement or by a commit/rollback call. However, there cases when we don't need to do this. Hash
12201  * partitioning algorithm guarantees that there always is a partition for each record and range
12202  * partitioning using max value/min value does the same. This flushing should be refined. */
12203  obt_set_force_flush (*otemplate);
12204  }
12205 
12206  vc = value_list->info.node_list.list;
12207  attr = statement->info.insert.attr_list;
12208  degree = pt_length_of_list (attr);
12209 
12210  /* allocate attribute descriptors */
12211  if (attr != NULL && attr_descs == NULL)
12212  {
12213  attr_descs = (DB_ATTDESC **) calloc (degree, sizeof (DB_ATTDESC *));
12214  if (attr_descs == NULL)
12215  {
12216  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
12217  (degree * sizeof (DB_ATTDESC *)));
12218  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
12219  goto cleanup;
12220  }
12221  }
12222 
12223  hint_arg = statement->info.insert.waitsecs_hint;
12224  if (statement->info.insert.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
12225  {
12226  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
12227  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
12228  {
12229  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
12230  }
12231  else
12232  {
12233  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
12234  }
12235  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
12236  {
12237  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
12238 
12239  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
12240  }
12241  }
12242  i = 0;
12243  while (attr && vc)
12244  {
12245  assert (vc->node_type == PT_INSERT_VALUE && vc->info.insert_value.is_evaluated);
12246  if (vc->node_type != PT_INSERT_VALUE || !vc->info.insert_value.is_evaluated)
12247  {
12248  error = ER_FAILED;
12249  goto cleanup;
12250  }
12251 
12252  /* don't get descriptors for shared attrs of views */
12253  if (attr_descs[i] == NULL)
12254  {
12255  int is_vclass = 0;
12256 
12257  if (attr->info.name.db_object)
12258  {
12259  is_vclass = db_is_vclass (attr->info.name.db_object);
12260  if (is_vclass < 0)
12261  {
12262  error = is_vclass;
12263  }
12264  }
12265  if (!is_vclass)
12266  {
12267  error =
12268  db_get_attribute_descriptor (class_->info.name.db_object, attr->info.name.original, 0, 1,
12269  &attr_descs[i]);
12270  }
12271  }
12272  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
12273  {
12274  error = insert_object_attr (parser, *otemplate, &vc->info.insert_value.value, attr, attr_descs[i]);
12275  }
12276 
12277  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
12278  {
12279  if (error < NO_ERROR)
12280  {
12281  save_custom = parser->custom_print;
12282  parser->custom_print = parser->custom_print | PT_PRINT_DB_VALUE;
12283 
12284  PT_ERRORmf3 (parser, vc, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_DBT_PUT_ERROR,
12285  pt_short_print (parser, vc), attr->info.name.original,
12286  pt_chop_trailing_dots (parser, db_error_string (3)));
12287 
12288  parser->custom_print = save_custom;
12289 
12290  goto cleanup;
12291  }
12292  }
12293  else
12294  {
12295  goto cleanup;
12296  }
12297 
12298  attr = attr->next;
12299  vc = vc->next;
12300  i++;
12301  }
12302 
12303  /* inserted one more row */
12304  row_count++;
12305 
12306  if ((*otemplate) != NULL && statement->info.insert.odku_assignments)
12307  {
12308  assert (update != NULL);
12309  error = do_on_duplicate_key_update (parser, *otemplate, update);
12310  if (error < 0)
12311  {
12312  dbt_abort_object (*otemplate);
12313  *otemplate = NULL;
12314  goto cleanup;
12315  }
12316  else if (error > 0)
12317  {
12318  /* a successful update, go to finish */
12319  row_count += error;
12320  dbt_abort_object (*otemplate);
12321  *otemplate = NULL;
12322  error = NO_ERROR;
12323  }
12324  else
12325  { /* error == 0 */
12326  int level;
12327  qo_get_optimization_param (&level, QO_PARAM_LEVEL);
12328  if (level & 0x02)
12329  {
12330  /* do not execute, go to finish */
12331  row_count = 0;
12332  dbt_abort_object (*otemplate);
12333  *otemplate = NULL;
12334  error = NO_ERROR;
12335  }
12336  }
12337  }
12338  if ((*otemplate) != NULL && statement->info.insert.do_replace)
12339  {
12340  error =
12341  do_replace_into (parser, *otemplate, statement->info.insert.spec, statement->info.insert.class_specs);
12342  if (error > 0)
12343  {
12344  row_count += error;
12345  error = NO_ERROR;
12346  }
12347  }
12348 
12349  if (error < NO_ERROR)
12350  {
12351  goto cleanup;
12352  }
12353 
12354  if (ins_val != NULL && *otemplate != NULL)
12355  {
12356  if (row_count > 1)
12357  {
12358  error = ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY;
12359  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 0);
12360  goto cleanup;
12361  }
12362  error = dbt_set_label (*otemplate, ins_val);
12363  if (error == NO_ERROR)
12364  {
12365  if (into_label != NULL)
12366  {
12367  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, ins_val);
12368  }
12369  }
12370  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12371  {
12372  goto cleanup;
12373  }
12374  }
12375 
12376  if (*otemplate != NULL)
12377  {
12378  obt_retain_after_finish (*otemplate);
12379 
12380  obj = dbt_finish_object (*otemplate);
12381  if (obj == NULL)
12382  {
12383  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error);
12384 
12385  dbt_abort_object (*otemplate);
12386  *otemplate = NULL;
12387  }
12388  else
12389  {
12390  bool include_new_obj;
12391 
12392  include_new_obj = (parser->return_generated_keys && (*otemplate)->is_autoincrement_set);
12393 
12394  obt_quit (*otemplate); /* free template */
12395 
12396  if (include_new_obj == true)
12397  {
12398  db_make_object (&db_value, obj);
12399  error = set_put_element (seq, obj_count, &db_value);
12400  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12401  {
12402  goto cleanup;
12403  }
12404  obj_count++;
12405  }
12406  }
12407 
12408  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
12409  {
12410  error = mq_evaluate_check_option (parser, statement->info.insert.where, obj, class_);
12411  }
12412  }
12413 
12414  if (parser->abort)
12415  {
12416  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12417  error = er_errid ();
12418  }
12419  if (error < NO_ERROR)
12420  {
12421  break;
12422  }
12423 
12424  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
12425  {
12426  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
12427  }
12428  }
12429  }
12430 
12431  if (error < NO_ERROR)
12432  {
12433  goto cleanup;
12434  }
12435 
12436  if (*otemplate != NULL && parser->return_generated_keys)
12437  {
12438  /* a client side insert with template, with requested generated keys */
12439  value = db_value_create ();
12440  if (value == NULL)
12441  {
12442  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12443  error = er_errid ();
12444  goto cleanup;
12445  }
12446  error = db_make_sequence (value, seq);
12447  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12448  {
12449  goto cleanup;
12450  }
12451  statement->etc = (void *) value;
12452 
12453  goto cleanup;
12454  }
12455  else
12456  {
12457  if (!parser->return_generated_keys && (*otemplate == NULL || value_clauses->next != NULL))
12458  {
12459  /* a client side insert with subquery and no template, a client side insert with multiple insert values or a
12460  * server side insert for which the generated keys have not been requested */
12461  value = db_value_create ();
12462  if (value == NULL)
12463  {
12464  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12465  error = er_errid ();
12466  goto cleanup;
12467  }
12468  db_make_object (value, NULL);
12469  statement->etc = (void *) value;
12470 
12471  goto cleanup;
12472  }
12473  }
12474 
12475  if (*otemplate != NULL && value_clauses->next == NULL)
12476  {
12477  /* If any of the (nested) inserts were view objects we need to find them and create VMOPS for them. Use a post
12478  * walk so that vobj will point to the vmop for the outer insert if one is needed. */
12479  vobj = NULL;
12480  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, NULL, NULL, make_vmops, &vobj);
12481  /* create a DB_VALUE to hold the newly inserted instance */
12482  ins_val = db_value_create ();
12483  if (ins_val == NULL)
12484  {
12485  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12486  error = er_errid ();
12487  }
12488  else
12489  {
12490  if (vobj != NULL)
12491  {
12492  /* use the virtual mop */
12493  db_make_object (ins_val, vobj);
12494  }
12495  else
12496  {
12497  db_make_object (ins_val, obj);
12498  }
12499  statement->etc = (void *) ins_val;
12500  }
12501  }
12502 
12503 cleanup:
12504  /* free attribute descriptors */
12505  if (attr_descs)
12506  {
12507  for (i = 0; i < degree; i++)
12508  {
12509  if (attr_descs[i])
12510  {
12511  db_free_attribute_descriptor (attr_descs[i]);
12512  }
12513  }
12514  free_and_init (attr_descs);
12515  }
12516 
12517  if (update != NULL)
12518  {
12519  update->info.update.assignment = NULL;
12520  update->info.update.spec = NULL;
12521  if (update->info.update.check_where != NULL)
12522  {
12523  update->info.update.check_where->info.check_option.expr = NULL;
12524  }
12525  parser_free_tree (parser, update);
12526  }
12527 
12528  if (statement->info.insert.odku_non_null_attrs != NULL)
12529  {
12530  parser_free_tree (parser, statement->info.insert.odku_non_null_attrs);
12531  statement->info.insert.odku_non_null_attrs = NULL;
12532  }
12533 
12534  do_clear_insert_values (parser, statement);
12535 
12536  /* set NULL on labeled value */
12537  if (into_label != NULL && error != NO_ERROR)
12538  {
12539  DB_VALUE *db_val = pt_find_value_of_label (into_label);
12540 
12541  if (db_val != NULL)
12542  {
12543  db_make_object (db_val, (DB_OBJECT *) NULL);
12544  }
12545  }
12546 
12547  /* restore flags */
12548  statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) flag;
12549 
12550  if (*otemplate != NULL && error != NO_ERROR)
12551  {
12552  dbt_abort_object (*otemplate);
12553  *otemplate = NULL;
12554  }
12555 
12556  if (seq != NULL && error != NO_ERROR)
12557  {
12558  set_free (seq);
12559  }
12560 
12561  if (row_count_ptr != NULL)
12562  {
12563  *row_count_ptr = row_count;
12564  }
12565  return error;
12566 }
12567 
12568 /*
12569  * insert_subquery_results() - Execute sub-query & insert its results into
12570  * a target class
12571  * return: Error code
12572  * parser(in): Handle to the parser used to process & derive sub-query qry
12573  * statement(in/out):
12574  * values_list(in): The list of values to insert.
12575  * class(in):
12576  * savepoint_name(in):
12577  *
12578  * Note:
12579  * The function requires parser is the handle to the parser used to derive qry
12580  * qry is an error-free abstract syntax tree derived from a CUBRID
12581  * nested SELECT, UNION, DIFFERENCE, INTERSECTION subquery.
12582  * qry's select_list attributes have been expanded & type-checked.
12583  * qry's select_list and attrs have the same number of elements.
12584  * It modifies database state of target class and
12585  * effects that executes subquery and inserts its results as new instances of
12586  * target class.
12587  */
12588 static int
12589 insert_subquery_results (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_NODE * values_list, PT_NODE * class_,
12590  const char **savepoint_name)
12591 {
12592  int error = NO_ERROR;
12593  CURSOR_ID cursor_id;
12594  DB_OTMPL *otemplate = NULL;
12595  DB_OBJECT *obj = NULL;
12596  PT_NODE *attr, *qry, *attrs, *update = NULL;
12597  DB_VALUE *vals = NULL, *val = NULL;
12598  int degree, k, cnt, i, flag = 0;
12599  DB_ATTDESC **attr_descs = NULL;
12600  ODKU_TUPLE_VALUE_ARG odku_arg;
12601  int pruning_type = DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
12602  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
12603  int obj_count = 0;
12604  DB_SEQ *seq = NULL;
12605  DB_VALUE db_value;
12606  DB_VALUE *value = NULL;
12607 
12608  assert (parser != NULL);
12609 
12610  if (values_list == NULL || values_list->node_type != PT_NODE_LIST
12611  || values_list->info.node_list.list_type != PT_IS_SUBQUERY || (qry = values_list->info.node_list.list) == NULL
12612  || (statement->node_type != PT_INSERT && statement->node_type != PT_MERGE))
12613  {
12614  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
12615  }
12616  attrs = statement->node_type == PT_MERGE ? statement->info.merge.insert.attr_list : statement->info.insert.attr_list;
12617  if (attrs == NULL)
12618  {
12619  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
12620  }
12621  error = sm_partitioned_class_type (class_->info.name.db_object, &pruning_type, NULL, NULL);
12622  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12623  {
12624  return error;
12625  }
12626 
12627  cnt = 0;
12628 
12629  if (parser->return_generated_keys)
12630  {
12631  seq = set_create_sequence (0);
12632  if (seq == NULL)
12633  {
12634  error = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
12635  return error;
12636  }
12637  }
12638 
12639  switch (qry->node_type)
12640  {
12641  default: /* preconditions not met */
12642  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR; /* so, nothing doing. */
12643 
12644  case PT_SELECT:
12645  case PT_UNION:
12646  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
12647  case PT_INTERSECTION:
12648  /* count elements in the select list before we modify it for ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE statements */
12649  degree = pt_length_of_select_list (pt_get_select_list (parser, qry), EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
12650  if (degree <= 0)
12651  {
12652  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY, 0);
12653  return ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY;
12654  }
12655  if (qry->etc == NULL)
12656  {
12657  if (statement->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL)
12658  {
12659  /* Add nodes referenced in odku_assignments to the select list because we need those values when
12660  * evaluating values for update. */
12661  odku_arg.insert_stmt = statement;
12662  odku_arg.cursor_p = &cursor_id;
12663 
12664  statement->info.insert.odku_assignments =
12665  parser_walk_tree (parser, statement->info.insert.odku_assignments, pt_append_odku_references,
12666  (void *) (&odku_arg), NULL, NULL);
12667  if (statement->info.insert.odku_assignments == NULL || pt_has_error (parser))
12668  {
12669  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12670  error = er_errid ();
12671  if (error == NO_ERROR)
12672  {
12673  error = ER_FAILED;
12674  }
12675  return error;
12676  }
12677  }
12678 
12679  /* execute the subquery */
12680  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
12681  parser->query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
12682  error = do_select (parser, qry);
12683  if (error < NO_ERROR || qry->etc == NULL)
12684  {
12685  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
12686  return error;
12687  }
12688  }
12689 
12690  /* insert subquery results into target class */
12691  if (cursor_open (&cursor_id, (QFILE_LIST_ID *) qry->etc, false, false))
12692  {
12693  cursor_id.query_id = parser->query_id;
12694 
12695  vals = (DB_VALUE *) malloc (degree * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
12696  if (vals == NULL)
12697  {
12698  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, degree * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
12699  cnt = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
12700  goto cleanup;
12701  }
12702 
12703  for (i = 0; i < degree; i++)
12704  {
12705  db_make_null (&vals[i]);
12706  }
12707 
12708  /* allocate attribute descriptor array */
12709  if (degree)
12710  {
12711  attr_descs = (DB_ATTDESC **) malloc ((degree) * sizeof (DB_ATTDESC *));
12712  if (attr_descs == NULL)
12713  {
12714  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
12715  degree * sizeof (DB_ATTDESC *));
12716  cnt = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
12717  goto cleanup;
12718  }
12719  for (i = 0; i < degree; i++)
12720  {
12721  attr_descs[i] = NULL;
12722  }
12723  }
12724 
12725  /* if the list file contains more than 1 object we need to savepoint the statement to guarantee statement
12726  * atomicity. */
12727  if ((((QFILE_LIST_ID *) qry->etc)->tuple_cnt > 1 && !*savepoint_name)
12728  || (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ && statement->node_type == PT_INSERT
12729  && statement->info.insert.odku_assignments))
12730  {
12731  *savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UisP", &insert_savepoint_number);
12732  error = tran_system_savepoint (*savepoint_name);
12733  }
12734 
12735  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
12736  {
12737  /* for each tuple in subquery result do */
12738  while (cursor_next_tuple (&cursor_id) == DB_CURSOR_SUCCESS)
12739  {
12740  /* get current tuple of subquery result */
12741  if (cursor_get_tuple_value_list (&cursor_id, degree, vals) != NO_ERROR)
12742  {
12743  break;
12744  }
12745 
12746  /* create an instance of the target class using templates */
12747  otemplate = dbt_create_object_internal (class_->info.name.db_object);
12748  if (otemplate == NULL)
12749  {
12750  break;
12751  }
12752  otemplate->pruning_type = pruning_type;
12753  if (pruning_type != DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS)
12754  {
12755  obt_set_force_flush (otemplate);
12756  }
12757  /* update new instance with current tuple of subquery result */
12758  for (attr = attrs, val = vals, k = 0; attr != NULL && k < degree; attr = attr->next, val++, k++)
12759  {
12760  /* if this is the first tuple, get the attr descriptor */
12761  if (attr_descs != NULL)
12762  {
12763  if (attr_descs[k] == NULL)
12764  {
12765  int is_vclass = 0;
12766 
12767  /* don't get descriptors for shared attrs of views */
12768  if (attr->info.name.db_object)
12769  {
12770  is_vclass = db_is_vclass (attr->info.name.db_object);
12771 
12772  if (is_vclass < 0)
12773  {
12774  error = is_vclass;
12775  }
12776  }
12777  if (!is_vclass)
12778  {
12779  error =
12780  db_get_attribute_descriptor (class_->info.name.db_object, attr->info.name.original,
12781  0, 1, &attr_descs[k]);
12782  }
12783  }
12784  }
12785 
12786  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
12787  {
12788  error = insert_object_attr (parser, otemplate, val, attr, attr_descs[k]);
12789  }
12790 
12791  if (error < NO_ERROR)
12792  {
12793  dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
12794  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
12795  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12796  cnt = er_errid ();
12797  goto cleanup;
12798  }
12799  }
12800 
12801  if (statement->node_type == PT_INSERT && statement->info.insert.odku_assignments)
12802  {
12803  if (update == NULL)
12804  {
12805  flag = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flag;
12806  update = do_create_odku_stmt (parser, statement);
12807  if (update == NULL)
12808  {
12809  error = ER_FAILED;
12810  goto cleanup;
12811  }
12812  }
12813  error = do_on_duplicate_key_update (parser, otemplate, update);
12814  if (error < 0)
12815  {
12816  /* there was an error, cleanup and return */
12817  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
12818  if (obj == NULL)
12819  {
12820  dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
12821  }
12822  cnt = error;
12823  goto cleanup;
12824  }
12825  if (error > 0)
12826  {
12827  /* a successful update, go to finish */
12828  cnt += error;
12829  dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
12830  otemplate = NULL;
12831  error = NO_ERROR;
12832  }
12833  }
12834 
12835  if (statement->node_type == PT_INSERT && statement->info.insert.do_replace)
12836  {
12837  error =
12838  do_replace_into (parser, otemplate, statement->info.insert.spec,
12839  statement->info.insert.class_specs);
12840  if (error < 0)
12841  {
12842  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
12843  if (obj == NULL)
12844  {
12845  dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
12846  }
12847  cnt = error;
12848  goto cleanup;
12849  }
12850 
12851  cnt += error;
12852  }
12853 
12854  if (otemplate != NULL)
12855  {
12856  /* apply the object template */
12857  bool include_new_obj;
12858 
12859  obt_retain_after_finish (otemplate);
12860 
12861  obj = dbt_finish_object (otemplate); /* flush template */
12862 
12863  include_new_obj = (obj && parser->return_generated_keys && otemplate->is_autoincrement_set);
12864 
12865  obt_quit (otemplate); /* free template */
12866 
12867  if (include_new_obj == true)
12868  {
12869  db_make_object (&db_value, obj);
12870  error = set_put_element (seq, obj_count, &db_value);
12871  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12872  {
12873  cnt = error;
12874  goto cleanup;
12875  }
12876  obj_count++;
12877  }
12878 
12879  if (obj && error >= NO_ERROR)
12880  {
12881  if (statement->node_type == PT_INSERT)
12882  {
12883  error = mq_evaluate_check_option (parser, statement->info.insert.where, obj, class_);
12884  }
12885  else if (statement->node_type == PT_MERGE && statement->info.merge.check_where)
12886  {
12887  error =
12888  mq_evaluate_check_option (parser,
12889  statement->info.merge.check_where->info.check_option.expr,
12890  obj, class_);
12891  }
12892  }
12893 
12894  if (obj == NULL || error < NO_ERROR)
12895  {
12896  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
12897  if (obj == NULL)
12898  {
12899  dbt_abort_object (otemplate);
12900  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12901  cnt = er_errid ();
12902  }
12903  else
12904  {
12905  cnt = error;
12906  }
12907  goto cleanup;
12908  }
12909 
12910  }
12911 
12912  /* keep track of how many we have inserted */
12913  cnt++;
12914  }
12915  }
12916 
12917  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
12918  }
12919  }
12920 
12921  if (parser->return_generated_keys && seq != NULL)
12922  {
12923  value = db_value_create ();
12924  if (value == NULL)
12925  {
12926  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12927  error = er_errid ();
12928  goto cleanup;
12929  }
12930  error = db_make_sequence (value, seq);
12931  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12932  {
12933  goto cleanup;
12934  }
12935  statement->etc = (void *) value;
12936  }
12937 
12938 cleanup:
12939  if (update != NULL)
12940  {
12941  /* restore flags */
12942  statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) flag;
12943  update->info.update.assignment = NULL;
12944  update->info.update.spec = NULL;
12945  if (update->info.update.check_where != NULL)
12946  {
12947  update->info.update.check_where->info.check_option.expr = NULL;
12948  }
12949  parser_free_tree (parser, update);
12950  }
12951  if (vals != NULL)
12952  {
12953  for (val = vals, k = 0; k < degree; val++, k++)
12954  {
12955  db_value_clear (val);
12956  }
12957  free_and_init (vals);
12958  }
12959 
12960  if (attr_descs != NULL)
12961  {
12962  for (i = 0; i < degree; i++)
12963  {
12964  if (attr_descs[i] != NULL)
12965  {
12966  db_free_attribute_descriptor (attr_descs[i]);
12967  }
12968  }
12969  free_and_init (attr_descs);
12970  }
12971 
12972  if (cnt < 0 && seq != NULL)
12973  {
12974  set_free (seq);
12975  }
12976 
12977  regu_free_listid ((QFILE_LIST_ID *) qry->etc);
12978  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
12979 
12980  return cnt;
12981 }
12982 
12983 /*
12984  * is_attr_not_in_insert_list() - Returns 1 if the name is not on the name_list,
12985  * 0 otherwise. name_list is assumed to be a list of PT_NAME nodes.
12986  * return: Error code
12987  * param1(out): Short description of the param1
12988  * param2(in/out): Short description of the param2
12989  * param2(in): Short description of the param3
12990  *
12991  * Note: If you feel the need
12992  */
12993 static int
12994 is_attr_not_in_insert_list (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * name_list, const char *name)
12995 {
12996  PT_NODE *tmp;
12997  int not_on_list = 1;
12998 
12999  for (tmp = name_list; tmp != NULL; tmp = tmp->next)
13000  {
13001  if (intl_identifier_casecmp (tmp->info.name.original, name) == 0)
13002  {
13003  not_on_list = 0;
13004  break;
13005  }
13006  }
13007 
13008  return not_on_list;
13009 
13010 } /* is_attr_not_in_insert_list */
13011 
13012 /*
13013  * check_missing_non_null_attrs() - Check to see that all attributes of
13014  * the class that have a NOT NULL constraint AND have no default
13015  * value are present in the inserts assign list.
13016  * return: Error code
13017  * parser(in):
13018  * spec(in):
13019  * attr_list(in):
13020  * has_default_values_list(in): whether this statement is used to insert
13021  * default values
13022  */
13023 static int
13024 check_missing_non_null_attrs (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * attr_list,
13025  const bool has_default_values_list)
13026 {
13027  DB_ATTRIBUTE *attr;
13028  DB_OBJECT *class_;
13029  int error = NO_ERROR;
13030  int save_au;
13031 
13032  if (!spec || !spec->info.spec.entity_name || !(class_ = spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object))
13033  {
13034  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
13035  }
13036 
13037  AU_DISABLE (save_au);
13038  attr = db_get_attributes (class_);
13039  while (attr)
13040  {
13041  if (db_attribute_is_non_null (attr) && db_value_is_null (db_attribute_default (attr))
13042  && attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type == DB_DEFAULT_NONE
13043  && (is_attr_not_in_insert_list (parser, attr_list, db_attribute_name (attr)) || has_default_values_list)
13044  && !(attr->flags & SM_ATTFLAG_AUTO_INCREMENT))
13045  {
13046  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_MISSING_NON_NULL_ASSIGN, 1, db_attribute_name (attr));
13047  error = ER_OBJ_MISSING_NON_NULL_ASSIGN;
13048  }
13049  attr = db_attribute_next (attr);
13050  }
13051  AU_ENABLE (save_au);
13052 
13053  return error;
13054 }
13055 
13056 /*
13057  * make_vmops() -
13058  * return: Error code
13059  * parser(in): Short description of the param1
13060  * node(in):
13061  * arg(in/out):
13062  * continue_walk(in/out):
13063  */
13064 static PT_NODE *
13065 make_vmops (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13066 {
13067  DB_OBJECT **vobj = ((DB_OBJECT **) arg);
13068  DB_OBJECT *vclass_mop, *obj;
13069  const char *into_label;
13070  DB_VALUE *val;
13071 
13072  if (node->node_type != PT_INSERT)
13073  {
13074  return node;
13075  }
13076 
13077  /* make a virtual obj if it is a virtual class and has an into label */
13078  if (node->info.insert.into_var
13079  && ((vclass_mop = node->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.virt_object) != NULL))
13080  {
13081  into_label = node->info.insert.into_var->info.name.original;
13082  val = pt_find_value_of_label (into_label);
13083  if (val != NULL)
13084  {
13085  obj = db_get_object (val);
13086  *vobj = vid_build_virtual_mop (obj, vclass_mop);
13087  /* change the label to point to the newly created vmop, we don't need to call pt_associate_label_with_value
13088  * here because we've directly modified the value that has been installed in the table. */
13089  db_make_object (val, *vobj);
13090  }
13091  }
13092  else
13093  {
13094  *vobj = NULL;
13095  }
13096 
13097  return node;
13098 
13099 }
13100 
13101 /*
13102  * test_check_option() - Tests if we are inserting to a class through a view
13103  * with a check option.
13104  * return: Error code
13105  * parser(in): Parser context
13106  * node(in): The PT_NAME node of a potential insert
13107  * arg(in/out): Nonzero iff insert statement has a check option
13108  * continue_walk(in/out):
13109  */
13110 static PT_NODE *
13111 test_check_option (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13112 {
13113  int *found = (int *) arg;
13114  PT_NODE *class_;
13115  DB_OBJECT *view;
13116 
13117  if (node->node_type != PT_INSERT || !node->info.insert.spec)
13118  {
13119  return node;
13120  }
13121 
13122  /* make a virtual obj if it is a virtual class and has an into label */
13123  class_ = node->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
13124  view = class_->info.name.virt_object;
13125  if (view)
13126  {
13127  if (sm_get_class_flag (view, SM_CLASSFLAG_WITHCHECKOPTION) > 0
13128  || sm_get_class_flag (view, SM_CLASSFLAG_LOCALCHECKOPTION) > 0)
13129  {
13130  *found = 1;
13131  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
13132  }
13133  }
13134 
13135  return node;
13136 
13137 }
13138 
13139 /*
13140  * insert_local () - Insert execution checks:
13141  * 1. Updates attribute default expressions.
13142  * 2. Checks for missing attributes that have not null
13143  * constraints.
13144  * 3. Check if inserting a false sub-query.
13145  * 4. Check if a savepoint is needed.
13146  * 5. Calls do_insert_template.
13147  * 6. Revert to savepoint is an error occurred.
13148  *
13149  * return : Error code or row count if no error has occurred.
13150  * parser (in) : Parser context.
13151  * statement (in) : Parse tree node for insert statement.
13152  */
13153 static int
13154 insert_local (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
13155 {
13156  int error = NO_ERROR;
13157  int row_count_total = 0;
13158  PT_NODE *class_ = NULL, *vc = NULL;
13159  int save;
13160  int has_check_option = 0;
13161  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
13162  PT_NODE *crt_list = NULL;
13163  bool has_default_values_list = false;
13164  bool is_multiple_tuples_insert = false;
13165  bool need_savepoint = false;
13166  int has_trigger = 0;
13167  bool is_trigger_involved = false;
13168  DB_OTMPL *otemplate = NULL;
13169 
13170  if (!statement || statement->node_type != PT_INSERT || !statement->info.insert.spec
13171  || !statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list)
13172  {
13173  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
13174  }
13175 
13176  class_ = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
13177 
13178  statement->etc = NULL;
13179 
13180  for (crt_list = statement->info.insert.value_clauses, has_default_values_list = false; crt_list != NULL;
13181  crt_list = crt_list->next)
13182  {
13183  if (crt_list->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_DEFAULT_VALUE)
13184  {
13185  has_default_values_list = true;
13186  break;
13187  }
13188  }
13189 
13190  error = do_evaluate_default_expr (parser, class_);
13191  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13192  {
13193  return error;
13194  }
13195 
13196  error =
13197  check_missing_non_null_attrs (parser, statement->info.insert.spec, statement->info.insert.attr_list,
13198  has_default_values_list);
13199  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13200  {
13201  return error;
13202  }
13203 
13204  crt_list = statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
13205  if (crt_list->next != NULL)
13206  {
13207  is_multiple_tuples_insert = true;
13208  }
13209 
13210  if (crt_list->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY && (vc = crt_list->info.node_list.list)
13211  && pt_false_where (parser, vc))
13212  {
13213  /* 0 tuples inserted. */
13214  return 0;
13215  }
13216 
13217  /*
13218  * It is necessary to add savepoint in the cases as below.
13219  *
13220  * 1. when multiple tuples were inserted (ex: insert into ... values(), (), ();)
13221  * 2. the REPLACE statement (ex: replace into ... values ..;)
13222  * 3. view having 'with check option'
13223  * 4. class/view having trigger
13224  * 5. when there is another insert statement among values.
13225  */
13226 
13227  if (is_multiple_tuples_insert == true || statement->info.insert.do_replace == true)
13228  {
13229  need_savepoint = true;
13230  }
13231 
13232  if (need_savepoint == false)
13233  {
13234  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, NULL, NULL, test_check_option, &has_check_option);
13235  if (has_check_option)
13236  {
13237  need_savepoint = true;
13238  }
13239  }
13240 
13241  /* DO NOT RETURN UNTIL AFTER AU_ENABLE! */
13242  AU_DISABLE (save);
13243  parser->au_save = save;
13244 
13245  if (need_savepoint == false && statement->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL)
13246  {
13247  has_trigger = 0;
13248  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_->info.name.db_object, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_UPDATE);
13249  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13250  {
13251  AU_ENABLE (save);
13252  return error;
13253  }
13254  if (has_trigger != 0)
13255  {
13256  need_savepoint = true;
13257  }
13258  else if (TM_TRAN_ISOLATION () >= TRAN_REP_READ && !statement->info.insert.server_allowed)
13259  {
13260  need_savepoint = true;
13261  }
13262  }
13263 
13264  if (need_savepoint == false)
13265  {
13266  has_trigger = 0;
13267  error = sm_class_has_triggers (class_->info.name.db_object, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_INSERT);
13268  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13269  {
13270  AU_ENABLE (save);
13271  return error;
13272  }
13273  if (has_trigger != 0)
13274  {
13275  need_savepoint = true;
13276  }
13277  }
13278 
13279  if (need_savepoint == false)
13280  {
13281  int arg[2]; /* argument for pt_find_node_type_pre */
13282  arg[0] = PT_INSERT; /* node type */
13283  arg[1] = 0; /* found */
13284  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, statement->info.insert.value_clauses, pt_find_node_type_pre, arg, NULL, NULL);
13285  if (arg[1] == 1)
13286  {
13287  /* sub insert was found */
13288  need_savepoint = true;
13289  }
13290  }
13291 
13292  /*
13293  * if the insert statement contains more than one insert component,
13294  * we savepoint the insert components to try to guarantee insert
13295  * statement atomicity.
13296  */
13297  if (need_savepoint == true)
13298  {
13299  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UisP", &insert_savepoint_number);
13300  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
13301  {
13302  AU_ENABLE (save);
13303  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
13304  }
13305  error = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
13306  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13307  {
13308  AU_ENABLE (save);
13309  return error;
13310  }
13311  }
13312 
13313  /* the do_Trigger_involved will be set as true when execute trigger statement. it will not be set back. we need to
13314  * keep its value to update last insert id. */
13315  is_trigger_involved = do_Trigger_involved;
13316  if (!do_Trigger_involved)
13317  {
13318  obt_begin_insert_values ();
13319  }
13320 
13321  row_count_total = 0;
13322 
13323 
13324 
13325  error = do_insert_template (parser, &otemplate, statement, &savepoint_name, &row_count_total);
13326 
13327  AU_ENABLE (save);
13328 
13329  /* restore the obt_Last_insert_id_generated flag after insert. */
13330  if (!is_trigger_involved && obt_Last_insert_id_generated)
13331  {
13332  obt_Last_insert_id_generated = false;
13333  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13334  {
13335  (void) csession_reset_cur_insert_id ();
13336  }
13337  }
13338 
13339  /* if error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
13340  * transaction. */
13341  if (error < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && (error != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
13342  {
13343  /* savepoint from tran_savepoint() */
13344  (void) tran_internal_abort_upto_savepoint (savepoint_name, SYSTEM_SAVEPOINT, true);
13345  /* Use a special version of rollback which will not clobber cached views. We can do this because we know insert
13346  * can not have created any views. This is instead of the extern function: db_abort_to_savepoint(savepoint_name); */
13347  }
13348 
13349  return error < 0 ? error : row_count_total;
13350 }
13351 
13352 /*
13353  * do_insert() - Checks if insert is already prepared and execute it. If it
13354  * is not prepared, calls insert_local.
13355  *
13356  * return : Error code if insert fails, the row count otherwise.
13357  * parser (in) : Parser context.
13358  * statement(in): Parse tree of a insert statement.
13359  */
13360 int
13361 do_insert (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * root_statement)
13362 {
13363  PT_NODE *statement = root_statement;
13364  int error;
13365 
13366  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
13367 
13368  error = insert_local (parser, statement);
13369  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13370  {
13371  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_EXECUTION);
13372  }
13373 
13374  while (error < NO_ERROR && statement->next)
13375  {
13376  /* assume error was from mismatch of multiple possible translated inserts. Try the next statement in the list.
13377  * Only report the last error. */
13378  parser_free_tree (parser, parser->error_msgs);
13379  parser->error_msgs = NULL;
13380 
13381  statement = statement->next;
13382  error = insert_local (parser, statement);
13383 
13384  /* check whether this transaction is a victim of deadlock during */
13385  /* request to the driver */
13386  if (parser->abort)
13387  {
13388  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
13389  return (er_errid ());
13390  }
13391 
13392  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13393  {
13394  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_EXECUTION);
13395  }
13396 
13397  /* This is to allow the row "counting" to be done in db_execute_and_keep_statement, and also correctly returns
13398  * the "result" of the last insert statement. Only the first insert statement in the list is examined for
13399  * results. */
13400  root_statement->etc = statement->etc;
13401  statement->etc = NULL;
13402  }
13403 
13404  return error;
13405 }
13406 
13407 /*
13408  * do_prepare_insert () - Prepare the INSERT statement
13409  * return: Error code
13410  * parser(in): Parser context
13411  * statement(in):
13412  */
13413 int
13414 do_prepare_insert (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
13415 {
13416  int error = NO_ERROR;
13417  PT_NODE *class_;
13418  PT_NODE *values = NULL;
13419  PT_NODE *attr_list;
13420  PT_NODE *update = NULL;
13421  PT_NODE *with = NULL;
13422  int save_au;
13423 
13424  if (statement == NULL || statement->node_type != PT_INSERT || statement->info.insert.spec == NULL
13425  || statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list == NULL)
13426  {
13427  assert (false);
13428  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
13429  }
13430 
13431  AU_DISABLE (save_au);
13432 
13433  /* We do not allow multi statements. To be checked! */
13434  if (pt_length_of_list (statement) > 1)
13435  {
13436  assert (false);
13437  goto cleanup;
13438  }
13439 
13440  statement->etc = NULL;
13441  class_ = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
13442  values = statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
13443 
13444  error = do_insert_checks (parser, statement, &class_, &update, values);
13445  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13446  {
13447  ASSERT_ERROR ();
13448  goto cleanup;
13449  }
13450 
13451  if (statement->info.insert.server_allowed != SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED)
13452  {
13453  goto cleanup;
13454  }
13455 
13456  /* prevent blob, clob plan cache */
13457  for (attr_list = statement->info.insert.attr_list; attr_list != NULL; attr_list = attr_list->next)
13458  {
13459  if (attr_list->type_enum == PT_TYPE_BLOB || attr_list->type_enum == PT_TYPE_CLOB)
13460  {
13461  goto cleanup;
13462  }
13463  }
13464  /* Checks above are required before any early outs. */
13465 
13466  error = do_prepare_insert_internal (parser, statement);
13467 
13468 cleanup:
13469  /* Free update attribute. */
13470  if (update != NULL)
13471  {
13472  update->info.update.assignment = NULL;
13473  update->info.update.spec = NULL;
13474  if (update->info.update.check_where != NULL)
13475  {
13476  update->info.update.check_where->info.check_option.expr = NULL;
13477  }
13478  parser_free_tree (parser, update);
13479  }
13480 
13481  AU_ENABLE (save_au);
13482 
13483  return error;
13484 }
13485 
13486 /*
13487  * do_execute_insert () - Execute the prepared INSERT statement
13488  * return: Error code
13489  * parser(in): Parser context
13490  * statement(in):
13491  */
13492 int
13493 do_execute_insert (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
13494 {
13495  int err;
13496  PT_NODE *flat;
13497  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
13498  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id;
13499  QUERY_FLAG query_flag;
13500  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
13501 
13502  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
13503 
13504  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
13505 
13506  if (statement->xasl_id == NULL)
13507  {
13508  /* check if it is not necessary to execute this statement */
13509  if (qo_need_skip_execution ())
13510  {
13511  statement->etc = NULL;
13512  return NO_ERROR;
13513  }
13514  return do_insert (parser, statement);
13515  }
13516 
13517  flat = statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
13518  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
13519 
13520  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
13521 
13522  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
13523  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
13524 
13525  if (parser->return_generated_keys)
13526  {
13527  query_flag |= RETURN_GENERATED_KEYS;
13528  }
13529 
13530  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
13531  {
13532  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
13533  }
13534 
13535  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
13536  {
13537  query_flag |= EXECUTE_QUERY_WITH_COMMIT;
13538  }
13539 
13540  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
13541  {
13542  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
13543  }
13544 
13545  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
13546  {
13547  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
13548  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
13549  }
13550 
13551  if (ws_need_flush ())
13552  {
13553  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
13554  {
13555  // When a transaction is under auto-commit mode, flush all dirty objects to server.
13556  err = tran_flush_to_commit ();
13557  if (err != NO_ERROR)
13558  {
13559  return err;
13560  }
13561  /* Nothing to flush. However ws_Num_dirty_mop is not 0 sometimes. We may reset ws_Num_dirty_mop to 0,
13562  * if flushed without errors, but is not necessary. Before sending data to the server, we check that
13563  * the transaction was not finalized, in case of execution with commit.
13564  */
13565  }
13566  }
13567 
13568  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
13569  list_id = NULL;
13570 
13571  err = execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
13572  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, NULL, NULL);
13573 
13574  /* free returned QFILE_LIST_ID */
13575  if (list_id)
13576  {
13577  /* set as result */
13578  err = list_id->tuple_cnt;
13579  if (parser->return_generated_keys)
13580  {
13581  statement->etc = (void *) list_id;
13582  }
13583  else
13584  {
13585  regu_free_listid (list_id);
13586  }
13587  }
13588 
13589  /* end the query; reset query_id and call qmgr_end_query() */
13590  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
13591 
13592  return err;
13593 }
13594 
13595 /*
13596  * Function Group:
13597  * Implement method calls
13598  *
13599  */
13600 
13601 static int call_method (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement);
13602 
13603 /*
13604  * call_method() -
13605  * return: Value returned by method if success, otherwise an error code
13606  * parser(in): Parser context
13607  * node(in): Parse tree of a call statement
13608  *
13609  * Note:
13610  */
13611 static int
13612 call_method (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
13613 {
13614  const char *into_label, *proc;
13615  int error = NO_ERROR;
13616  DB_OBJECT *obj = NULL;
13617  DB_VALUE target_value, *ins_val, ret_val, db_value;
13618  DB_VALUE_LIST *val_list = 0, *vl, **next_val_list;
13619  PT_NODE *vc, *into, *target, *method;
13620 
13621  db_make_null (&ret_val);
13622  db_make_null (&target_value);
13623 
13624  /*
13625  * The method name and ON name are required.
13626  */
13627  if (!statement || !(method = statement->info.method_call.method_name) || method->node_type != PT_NAME
13628  || !(proc = method->info.name.original) || !(target = statement->info.method_call.on_call_target))
13629  {
13630  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
13631  return er_errid ();
13632  }
13633 
13634  /*
13635  * Determine whether the object is a class or instance.
13636  */
13637 
13638  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, target, &target_value, 1);
13639  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13640  {
13641  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SEMANTIC);
13642  return er_errid ();
13643  }
13644 
13645  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&target_value) == DB_TYPE_NULL)
13646  {
13647  /*
13648  * Don't understand the rationale behind this case. What's the
13649  * point here? MRS 4/30/96
13650  */
13651  error = NO_ERROR;
13652  }
13653  else
13654  {
13655  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&target_value) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
13656  {
13657  obj = db_get_object ((&target_value));
13658  }
13659 
13660  if (obj == NULL || pt_has_error (parser))
13661  {
13662  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_TARGET_NOT_OBJ);
13663  return er_errid ();
13664  }
13665 
13666  /*
13667  * Build an argument list.
13668  */
13669  next_val_list = &val_list;
13670  vc = statement->info.method_call.arg_list;
13671  for (; vc != NULL; vc = vc->next)
13672  {
13673  DB_VALUE *db_val;
13674  bool to_break = false;
13675 
13676  *next_val_list = (DB_VALUE_LIST *) calloc (1, sizeof (DB_VALUE_LIST));
13677  if (*next_val_list == NULL)
13678  {
13679  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (DB_VALUE_LIST));
13680  return er_errid ();
13681  }
13682  (*next_val_list)->next = (DB_VALUE_LIST *) 0;
13683 
13684  /*
13685  * Don't clone host vars; they may actually be acting as output
13686  * variables (e.g., a character array that is intended to receive
13687  * bytes from the method), and cloning will ensure that the
13688  * results never make it to the expected area. Since
13689  * pt_evaluate_tree() always clones its db_values we must not
13690  * use pt_evaluate_tree() to extract the db_value from a host
13691  * variable; instead extract it ourselves.
13692  */
13693  if (PT_IS_CONST (vc))
13694  {
13695  db_val = pt_value_to_db (parser, vc);
13696  }
13697  else
13698  {
13699  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, vc, &db_value, 1);
13700  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13701  {
13702  /* to maintain the list to free all the allocated */
13703  to_break = true;
13704  }
13705  db_val = &db_value;
13706  }
13707 
13708  if (db_val != NULL)
13709  {
13710  (*next_val_list)->val = *db_val;
13711 
13712  next_val_list = &(*next_val_list)->next;
13713  }
13714 
13715  if (to_break)
13716  {
13717  break;
13718  }
13719  }
13720 
13721  /*
13722  * Call the method.
13723  */
13724  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13725  {
13726  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SEMANTIC);
13727  error = er_errid ();
13728  }
13729  else
13730  {
13731  error = db_send_arglist (obj, proc, &ret_val, val_list);
13732  }
13733 
13734  /*
13735  * Free the argument list. Again, it is important to be careful
13736  * with host variables. Since we didn't clone them, we shouldn't
13737  * free or clear them.
13738  */
13739  vc = statement->info.method_call.arg_list;
13740  for (; val_list && vc; vc = vc->next)
13741  {
13742  vl = val_list->next;
13743  if (!PT_IS_CONST (vc))
13744  {
13745  db_value_clear (&val_list->val);
13746  }
13747  free_and_init (val_list);
13748  val_list = vl;
13749  }
13750 
13751  if (error == NO_ERROR)
13752  {
13753  /*
13754  * Save the method result.
13755  */
13756  statement->etc = (void *) db_value_copy (&ret_val);
13757 
13758  if ((into = statement->info.method_call.to_return_var) != NULL && into->node_type == PT_NAME
13759  && (into_label = into->info.name.original) != NULL)
13760  {
13761  /* create another DB_VALUE of the new instance for the label_table */
13762  ins_val = db_value_copy (&ret_val);
13763 
13764  /* enter {label, ins_val} pair into the label_table */
13765  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, ins_val);
13766  }
13767  }
13768  }
13769 
13770  db_value_clear (&ret_val);
13771  return error;
13772 }
13773 
13774 /*
13775  * do_call_method() -
13776  * return: Value returned by method if success, otherwise an error code
13777  * parser(in): Parser context
13778  * node(in): Parse tree of a call statement
13779  *
13780  * Note:
13781  */
13782 int
13783 do_call_method (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
13784 {
13785  PT_NODE *method;
13786 
13787  if (!statement || !(method = statement->info.method_call.method_name) || method->node_type != PT_NAME
13788  || !(method->info.name.original))
13789  {
13790  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
13791  return er_errid ();
13792  }
13793 
13794  if (statement->info.method_call.on_call_target)
13795  {
13796  return call_method (parser, statement);
13797  }
13798  else
13799  {
13800  return jsp_call_stored_procedure (parser, statement);
13801  }
13802 }
13803 
13804 /*
13805  * These functions are provided just so we have some builtin gadgets that we can
13806  * use for quick and dirty method testing. To get at them, alter your
13807  * favorite class like this:
13808  *
13809  * alter class foo
13810  * add method pickaname() string
13811  * function dbmeth_class_name;
13812  *
13813  * or
13814  *
13815  * alter class foo
13816  * add method pickaname(string) string
13817  * function dbmeth_print;
13818  *
13819  * After that you should be able to invoke "pickaname" on "foo" instances
13820  * to your heart's content. dbmeth_class_name() will retrieve the class
13821  * name of the target instance and return it as a string; dbmeth_print()
13822  * will print the supplied value on stdout every time it is invoked.
13823  */
13824 
13825 /*
13826  * TODO: The following function names need to be fixed.
13827  * Renaming can affects user interface.
13828  */
13829 
13830 /*
13831  * dbmeth_class_name() -
13832  * return: None
13833  * self(in): Class object
13834  * result(out): DB_VALUE for a class name
13835  *
13836  * Note: Position of function arguments must be kept
13837  * for pre-defined function pointers(au_static_links)
13838  */
13839 void
13840 dbmeth_class_name (DB_OBJECT * self, DB_VALUE * result)
13841 {
13842  const char *cname;
13843 
13844  cname = db_get_class_name (self);
13845 
13846  /*
13847  * Make a string and clone it so that it won't become invalid if the
13848  * underlying class object that gave us the string goes away. Of
13849  * course, this gives the responsibility for freeing the cloned
13850  * string to someone else; is anybody accepting it?
13851  */
13852  db_make_string_by_const_str (result, cname);
13853 }
13854 
13855 /*
13856  * TODO: The functin name need to be fixed.
13857  * it is known system method so must fix corresponding qa first
13858  */
13859 
13860 /*
13861  * dbmeth_print() -
13862  * return: None
13863  * self(in): Class object
13864  * result(out): NULL value
13865  * msg(in): DB_VALUE for a message
13866  *
13867  * Note: Position of function arguments must be kept
13868  * for pre-defined function pointers(au_static_links)
13869  */
13870 void
13871 dbmeth_print (DB_OBJECT * self, DB_VALUE * result, DB_VALUE * msg)
13872 {
13873  db_value_print (msg);
13874  printf ("\n");
13875  db_make_null (result);
13876 }

13883 /*
13884  * Function Group:
13885  * Functions for the implementation of virtual queries.
13886  *
13887  */

13889 
13890 /*
13891  * do_select() -
13892  * return: Error code
13893  * parser(in/out): Parser context
13894  * statement(in/out): A statement to do
13895  *
13896  * Note: Side effects can exist at returned result through application extern
13897  */
13898 int
13899 do_select (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
13900 {
13901  int error;
13902  XASL_NODE *xasl = NULL;
13903  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
13904  int into_cnt, i;
13905  PT_NODE *into;
13906  const char *into_label;
13907  DB_VALUE *vals, *v;
13908  int save;
13909  QUERY_FLAG query_flag;
13910  XASL_STREAM stream;
13911  bool query_trace = false;
13912 
13913  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
13914 
13915  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
13916 
13917  error = NO_ERROR;
13918 
13919  /* click counter check */
13920  if (statement->is_click_counter)
13921  {
13922  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
13923  }
13924 
13925  AU_DISABLE (save);
13926  parser->au_save = save;
13927 
13928  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
13929  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
13930 
13931  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
13932  {
13933  query_trace = true;
13934  }
13935 
13936  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
13937 
13938  if (parser->dont_collect_exec_stats)
13939  {
13940  query_flag |= DONT_COLLECT_EXEC_STATS;
13941  }
13942 
13943  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
13944  {
13945  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
13946  }
13947 
13948 #if defined(CUBRID_DEBUG)
13949  PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS (parser, statement, PT_CONVERT_RANGE);
13950 #endif
13951 
13952  pt_null_etc (statement);
13953 
13954  xasl = parser_generate_xasl (parser, statement);
13955 
13956  if (xasl && !pt_has_error (parser))
13957  {
13958  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
13959  {
13960  /* there is no results, this is a compile time false where clause */
13961  }
13962  else
13963  {
13964  if (query_trace == true)
13965  {
13966  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
13967  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
13968  }
13969 
13970  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
13971  {
13972  error = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (xasl, &stream);
13973  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13974  {
13975  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
13976  }
13977  }
13978 
13979  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
13980  {
13981  error =
13982  prepare_and_execute_query (stream.buffer, stream.buffer_size, &parser->query_id,
13983  parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count, parser->host_variables,
13984  &list_id, query_flag);
13985  }
13986  statement->etc = list_id;
13987 
13988  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
13989  if (stream.buffer)
13990  {
13991  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
13992  }
13993 
13994  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
13995  {
13996  /* if select ... into label ... has some result val then enter {label,val} pair into the label_table */
13997  into = statement->info.query.into_list;
13998 
13999  into_cnt = pt_length_of_list (into);
14000  if (into_cnt > 0 && (vals = (DB_VALUE *) malloc (into_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE))) != NULL)
14001  {
14002  if (pt_get_one_tuple_from_list_id (parser, statement, vals, into_cnt))
14003  {
14004  for (i = 0, v = vals; i < into_cnt && into; i++, v++, into = into->next)
14005  {
14006  if (into->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_label = into->info.name.original) != NULL)
14007  {
14008  error = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, db_value_copy (v));
14009  }
14010  db_value_clear (v);
14011  }
14012  }
14013  else if (into->node_type == PT_NAME)
14014  {
14015  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_PARM_IS_NOT_SET,
14016  into->info.name.original);
14017  }
14018  free_and_init (vals);
14019  }
14020  }
14021  else
14022  {
14023  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14024  error = er_errid ();
14025  if (error == NO_ERROR)
14026  {
14027  error = ER_REGU_SYSTEM;
14028  }
14029  }
14030  } /* else */
14031  }
14032  else
14033  {
14034  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14035  error = er_errid ();
14036  if (error == NO_ERROR)
14037  {
14038  error = ER_FAILED;
14039  }
14040  }
14041 
14042  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
14043  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
14044 
14045  AU_ENABLE (save);
14046  return error;
14047 }
14048 
14049 /*
14050  * do_prepare_select() - Prepare the SELECT statement including optimization and
14051  * plan generation, and creating XASL as the result
14052  * return: Error code
14053  * parser(in/out): Parser context
14054  * statement(in/out): A statement to do
14055  *
14056  * Note:
14057  */
14058 int
14059 do_prepare_select (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14060 {
14061  int err = NO_ERROR;
14062  int au_save;
14063 
14064  COMPILE_CONTEXT *contextp;
14065  XASL_STREAM stream;
14066 
14067  contextp = &parser->context;
14068 
14069  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
14070 
14071  if (parser == NULL || statement == NULL)
14072  {
14073  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
14074  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
14075  }
14076 
14077  contextp->sql_user_text = statement->sql_user_text;
14078  contextp->sql_user_text_len = statement->sql_user_text_len;
14079 
14080  /* click counter check */
14081  if (statement->is_click_counter)
14082  {
14083  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
14084  }
14085 
14086  /* there can be no results, this is a compile time false where clause */
14087  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
14088  {
14089  /* tell to the execute routine that there's no XASL to execute */
14090  statement->xasl_id = NULL;
14091  return NO_ERROR;
14092  }
14093 
14094  /* if already prepared */
14095  if (statement->xasl_id)
14096  {
14097  return NO_ERROR;
14098  }
14099 
14100  /* make query string */
14101  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 1;
14102  parser->long_string_skipped = 0;
14103  parser->print_type_ambiguity = 0;
14104  PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS (parser, statement,
14105  (PT_CONVERT_RANGE | PT_PRINT_QUOTES | PT_PRINT_DIFFERENT_SYSTEM_PARAMETERS | PT_PRINT_USER));
14106  contextp->sql_hash_text = (char *) statement->alias_print;
14107  err =
14108  SHA1Compute ((unsigned char *) contextp->sql_hash_text, (unsigned) strlen (contextp->sql_hash_text),
14109  &contextp->sha1);
14110  if (err != NO_ERROR)
14111  {
14112  ASSERT_ERROR ();
14113  return err;
14114  }
14115  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 0;
14116  if (parser->long_string_skipped || parser->print_type_ambiguity)
14117  {
14118  statement->cannot_prepare = 1;
14119  return NO_ERROR;
14120  }
14121 
14122  /* look up server's XASL cache for this query string and get XASL file id (XASL_ID) returned if found */
14123  contextp->recompile_xasl = statement->recompile;
14124  if (statement->recompile == 0)
14125  {
14126  XASL_NODE_HEADER xasl_header;
14127  stream.xasl_header = &xasl_header;
14128 
14129  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
14130  if (err != NO_ERROR)
14131  {
14132  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (err);
14133  }
14134  else if (contextp->recompile_xasl == true)
14135  {
14136  /* recompile flag was returned by server */
14137  if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
14138  {
14139  free_and_init (stream.xasl_id);
14140  }
14141  }
14142  else if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
14143  {
14144  /* check xasl header */
14145  /* TODO: we can treat the different cases of MRO by hacking query string. */
14146  if (pt_recompile_for_limit_optimizations (parser, statement, stream.xasl_header->xasl_flag))
14147  {
14148  contextp->recompile_xasl = true;
14149  if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
14150  {
14151  free_and_init (stream.xasl_id);
14152  }
14153  }
14154  }
14155  }
14156  if (stream.xasl_id == NULL && err == NO_ERROR)
14157  {
14158  /* cache not found; make XASL from the parse tree including query optimization and plan generation */
14159 
14160  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
14161  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
14162 
14163  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save); /* this prevents authorization checking during generating XASL */
14164  /* parser_generate_xasl() will build XASL tree from parse tree */
14165  contextp->xasl = parser_generate_xasl (parser, statement);
14166  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
14167 
14168  if (contextp->xasl && (err == NO_ERROR) && !pt_has_error (parser))
14169  {
14170  /* convert the created XASL tree to the byte stream for transmission to the server */
14171  err = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (contextp->xasl, &stream);
14172  if (err != NO_ERROR)
14173  {
14174  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
14175  }
14176  }
14177  else
14178  {
14179 #if 0 /* TODO */
14180  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14181 #endif
14182  err = er_errid ();
14183  if (err == NO_ERROR)
14184  {
14185  err = ER_FAILED;
14186  }
14187  }
14188 
14189  /* request the server to prepare the query; give XASL stream generated from the parse tree and get XASL file id
14190  * returned */
14191  if (stream.buffer && (err == NO_ERROR))
14192  {
14193  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
14194  if (err != NO_ERROR)
14195  {
14196  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14197  err = er_errid ();
14198  }
14199  }
14200 
14201  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
14202  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
14203 
14204  /* As a result of query preparation of the server, the XASL cache for this query will be created or updated. */
14205 
14206  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
14207  if (stream.buffer)
14208  {
14209  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
14210  }
14211  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
14212  }
14213  else
14214  {
14215  if (err == NO_ERROR)
14216  {
14217  statement->use_plan_cache = 1;
14218  }
14219  else
14220  {
14221  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
14222  }
14223  }
14224 
14225  /* save the XASL_ID that is allocated and returned by prepare_query() into 'statement->xasl_id' to be used by
14226  * do_execute_select() */
14227  statement->xasl_id = stream.xasl_id;
14228 
14229  return err;
14230 } /* do_prepare_select() */
14231 
14232 /*
14233  * do_prepare_session_statement () - prepare step for a prepared session
14234  * statement
14235  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
14236  * parser (in) : parser context
14237  * statement (in) : prepared statement
14238  */
14239 int
14240 do_prepare_session_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14241 {
14242  assert (statement->node_type == PT_EXECUTE_PREPARE);
14243  if (statement->xasl_id != NULL)
14244  {
14245  /* already "prepared" */
14246  return NO_ERROR;
14247  }
14248  statement->xasl_id = (XASL_ID *) malloc (sizeof (XASL_ID));
14249  if (statement->xasl_id == NULL)
14250  {
14251  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (XASL_ID));
14252  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
14253  }
14254  XASL_ID_COPY (statement->xasl_id, &statement->info.execute.xasl_id);
14255  return NO_ERROR;
14256 }
14257 
14258 /*
14259  * do_execute_session_statement () - execute a prepared session statement
14260  * return :
14261  * parser (in) : parser context
14262  * statement (in) : statement to execute
14263  */
14264 int
14265 do_execute_session_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14266 {
14267  int err;
14268  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id;
14269  int query_flag, into_cnt, i, au_save;
14270  PT_NODE *into;
14271  const char *into_label;
14272  DB_VALUE *vals, *v;
14273  CACHE_TIME clt_cache_time;
14274  CURSOR_ID cursor_id;
14275  bool query_trace = false;
14276 
14277  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
14278  assert (pt_node_to_cmd_type (statement) == CUBRID_STMT_EXECUTE_PREPARE);
14279 
14280  /* check if it is not necessary to execute this statement */
14281  if (statement->xasl_id == NULL)
14282  {
14283  statement->etc = NULL;
14284  return NO_ERROR;
14285  }
14286 
14287  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
14288  {
14289  query_trace = true;
14290  }
14291 
14292  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
14293 
14294  if (parser->is_holdable)
14295  {
14296  query_flag |= RESULT_HOLDABLE;
14297  }
14298  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
14299  {
14300  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
14301  }
14302  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
14303  {
14304  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
14305  }
14306 
14307  if (query_trace == true)
14308  {
14309  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
14310  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
14311  }
14312 
14313  /* flush necessary objects before execute */
14314  if (ws_has_updated ())
14315  {
14316  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_flush_classes, NULL, NULL, NULL);
14317  }
14318 
14319  if (parser->abort)
14320  {
14321  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14322  return er_errid ();
14323  }
14324 
14325  /* Request that the server executes the stored XASL, which is the execution plan of the prepared query, with the host
14326  * variables given by users as parameter values for the query. As a result, query id and result file id
14327  * (QFILE_LIST_ID) will be returned. */
14328 
14329  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
14330  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
14331  list_id = NULL;
14332 
14333  CACHE_TIME_RESET (&clt_cache_time);
14334  if (statement->clt_cache_check)
14335  {
14336  clt_cache_time = statement->cache_time;
14337  statement->clt_cache_check = 0;
14338  }
14339  CACHE_TIME_RESET (&statement->cache_time);
14340  statement->clt_cache_reusable = 0;
14341 
14342  err =
14343  execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
14344  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, &clt_cache_time, &statement->cache_time);
14345 
14346  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
14347 
14348  if (CACHE_TIME_EQ (&clt_cache_time, &statement->cache_time))
14349  {
14350  statement->clt_cache_reusable = 1;
14351  }
14352 
14353  /* save the returned QFILE_LIST_ID into 'statement->etc' */
14354  statement->etc = (void *) list_id;
14355 
14356  if (err < NO_ERROR)
14357  {
14358  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14359  return er_errid ();
14360  }
14361  /* if select ... into label ... has some result val then enter {label,val} pair into the label_table */
14362  into = statement->info.execute.into_list;
14363  into_cnt = pt_length_of_list (into);
14364  if (into_cnt == 0)
14365  {
14366  return err;
14367  }
14368 
14369  vals = (DB_VALUE *) malloc (into_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
14370  if (vals == NULL)
14371  {
14372  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, into_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
14373  return ER_FAILED;
14374  }
14375  if (!cursor_open (&cursor_id, list_id, false, statement->info.execute.oids_included))
14376  {
14377  return err;
14378  }
14379  cursor_id.query_id = parser->query_id;
14380  if (cursor_next_tuple (&cursor_id) != DB_CURSOR_SUCCESS
14381  || cursor_get_tuple_value_list (&cursor_id, into_cnt, vals) != NO_ERROR)
14382  {
14383  free_and_init (vals);
14384  return err;
14385  }
14386  cursor_close (&cursor_id);
14387 
14388  for (i = 0, v = vals; i < into_cnt && into; i++, v++, into = into->next)
14389  {
14390  if (into->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_label = into->info.name.original) != NULL)
14391  {
14392  err = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, db_value_copy (v));
14393  }
14394  db_value_clear (v);
14395  }
14396 
14397  free_and_init (vals);
14398 
14399  return err;
14400 }
14401 
14402 /*
14403  * do_execute_select() - Execute the prepared SELECT statement
14404  * return: Error code
14405  * parser(in/out): Parser context
14406  * statement(in/out): A statement to do
14407  *
14408  * Note:
14409  */
14410 int
14411 do_execute_select (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14412 {
14413  int err;
14414  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id;
14415  int query_flag, into_cnt, i, au_save;
14416  PT_NODE *into;
14417  const char *into_label;
14418  DB_VALUE *vals, *v;
14419  CACHE_TIME clt_cache_time;
14420  bool query_trace = false;
14421 
14422  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
14423 
14424  /* check if it is not necessary to execute this statement, e.g. false where or not prepared correctly */
14425  if (!statement->xasl_id)
14426  {
14427  statement->etc = NULL;
14428  return NO_ERROR;
14429  }
14430 
14431  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
14432  {
14433  query_trace = true;
14434  }
14435 
14436  /* adjust query flag */
14437  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
14438 
14439  if (statement->si_datetime == 1 || statement->si_tran_id == 1)
14440  {
14441  statement->info.query.reexecute = 1;
14442  statement->info.query.do_not_cache = 1;
14443  }
14444 
14445  if (statement->info.query.reexecute == 1)
14446  {
14447  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
14448  }
14449 
14450  if (statement->info.query.do_cache == 1)
14451  {
14452  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_REQUIRED;
14453  }
14454 
14455  if (statement->info.query.do_not_cache == 1)
14456  {
14457  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
14458  }
14459  if (parser->is_holdable)
14460  {
14461  query_flag |= RESULT_HOLDABLE;
14462  }
14463  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
14464  {
14465  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
14466  }
14467 
14468  if (parser->dont_collect_exec_stats)
14469  {
14470  query_flag |= DONT_COLLECT_EXEC_STATS;
14471  }
14472 
14473  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
14474  {
14475  query_flag |= EXECUTE_QUERY_WITH_COMMIT;
14476 
14477  if (ws_need_flush ())
14478  {
14479  if (tm_Use_OID_preflush)
14480  {
14481  (void) locator_assign_all_permanent_oids ();
14482  }
14483 
14484  /* Flush all dirty objects */
14485  /* Flush virtual objects first so that locator_all_flush doesn't see any */
14486  err = locator_all_flush ();
14487  if (err != NO_ERROR)
14488  {
14489  return err;
14490  }
14491  }
14492  }
14493 
14494  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
14495  {
14496  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
14497  }
14498 
14499  if (query_trace == true)
14500  {
14501  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
14502  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
14503  }
14504 
14505  /* flush necessary objects before execute */
14506  if (ws_has_updated ())
14507  {
14508  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_flush_classes, NULL, NULL, NULL);
14509  }
14510 
14511  if (parser->abort)
14512  {
14513  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14514  return er_errid ();
14515  }
14516 
14517  /* Request that the server executes the stored XASL, which is the execution plan of the prepared query, with the host
14518  * variables given by users as parameter values for the query. As a result, query id and result file id
14519  * (QFILE_LIST_ID) will be returned. do_prepare_select() has saved the XASL file id (XASL_ID) in 'statement->xasl_id'
14520  */
14521 
14522  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
14523 
14524  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
14525  list_id = NULL;
14526 
14527  CACHE_TIME_RESET (&clt_cache_time);
14528  if (statement->clt_cache_check)
14529  {
14530  clt_cache_time = statement->cache_time;
14531  statement->clt_cache_check = 0;
14532  }
14533  CACHE_TIME_RESET (&statement->cache_time);
14534  statement->clt_cache_reusable = 0;
14535 
14536  err =
14537  execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
14538  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, &clt_cache_time, &statement->cache_time);
14539 
14540  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
14541 
14542  if (CACHE_TIME_EQ (&clt_cache_time, &statement->cache_time))
14543  {
14544  statement->clt_cache_reusable = 1;
14545  }
14546 
14547  /* save the returned QFILE_LIST_ID into 'statement->etc' */
14548  statement->etc = (void *) list_id;
14549 
14550  if (err < NO_ERROR)
14551  {
14552  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14553  return er_errid ();
14554  }
14555 
14556  /* if SELECT ... INTO label ... has some result val, then enter {label,val} pair into the label_table */
14557  into = statement->info.query.into_list;
14558  if ((into_cnt = pt_length_of_list (into)) > 0 && (vals = (DB_VALUE *) malloc (into_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE))) != NULL)
14559  {
14560  if (pt_get_one_tuple_from_list_id (parser, statement, vals, into_cnt))
14561  {
14562  for (i = 0, v = vals; i < into_cnt && into; i++, v++, into = into->next)
14563  {
14564  if (into->node_type == PT_NAME && (into_label = into->info.name.original) != NULL)
14565  {
14566  err = pt_associate_label_with_value_check_reference (into_label, db_value_copy (v));
14567  }
14568  db_value_clear (v);
14569  }
14570  }
14571  else if (into->node_type == PT_NAME)
14572  {
14573  PT_ERRORmf (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_PARM_IS_NOT_SET,
14574  into->info.name.original);
14575  }
14576  free_and_init (vals);
14577  }
14578 
14579  return err;
14580 } /* do_execute_select() */
14581 
14582

14588  * DO Functions for replication management
14589  *
14590  */
