14593 /*
14594  * do_replicate_schema() -
14595  * return: Error code
14596  * parser(in): Parser context
14597  * statement(in): The parse tree of a DDL statement
14598  *
14599  * Note:
14600  */
14601 int
14602 do_replicate_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14603 {
14604  int error = NO_ERROR;
14605  REPL_INFO repl_info;
14606  REPL_INFO_SBR repl_stmt;
14607  PARSER_VARCHAR *name = NULL;
14608  static const char *unknown_name = "-";
14609  char stmt_separator;
14610  char *stmt_end = NULL;
14611 
14612  if (log_does_allow_replication () == false)
14613  {
14614  return NO_ERROR;
14615  }
14616 
14617  if (statement->sql_user_text == NULL || statement->sql_user_text_len == 0)
14618  {
14619  /* this should be loaddb. */
14620  return NO_ERROR;
14621  }
14622 
14623  switch (statement->node_type)
14624  {
14625  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
14626  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.create_entity.entity_name);
14627  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_CREATE_CLASS;
14628  break;
14629 
14630  case PT_ALTER:
14631  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.alter.entity_name);
14632  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_ALTER_CLASS;
14633  break;
14634 
14635  case PT_RENAME:
14636  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.rename.old_name);
14637  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_RENAME_CLASS;
14638  break;
14639 
14640  case PT_DROP:
14641  /* No replication log will be written when there's no applicable table for "drop if exists" */
14642  if (statement->info.drop.if_exists && statement->info.drop.spec_list == NULL)
14643  {
14644  return NO_ERROR;
14645  }
14646  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DROP_CLASS;
14647  break;
14648 
14649  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
14650  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.index.indexed_class);
14651  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_CREATE_INDEX;
14652  break;
14653 
14654  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
14655  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.index.indexed_class);
14656  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_ALTER_INDEX;
14657  break;
14658 
14659  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
14660  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.index.indexed_class);
14661  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DROP_INDEX;
14662  break;
14663 
14664  case PT_CREATE_SERIAL:
14665  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_CREATE_SERIAL;
14666  break;
14667 
14668  case PT_ALTER_SERIAL:
14669  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_ALTER_SERIAL;
14670  break;
14671 
14672  case PT_DROP_SERIAL:
14673  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DROP_SERIAL;
14674  break;
14675 
14676  case PT_CREATE_STORED_PROCEDURE:
14677  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_CREATE_STORED_PROCEDURE;
14678  break;
14679 
14680  case PT_ALTER_STORED_PROCEDURE:
14681  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_ALTER_STORED_PROCEDURE;
14682  break;
14683 
14684  case PT_DROP_STORED_PROCEDURE:
14685  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DROP_STORED_PROCEDURE;
14686  break;
14687 
14688  case PT_CREATE_USER:
14689  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_CREATE_USER;
14690  break;
14691 
14692  case PT_ALTER_USER:
14693  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_ALTER_USER;
14694  break;
14695 
14696  case PT_DROP_USER:
14697  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DROP_USER;
14698  break;
14699 
14700  case PT_GRANT:
14701  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_GRANT;
14702  break;
14703 
14704  case PT_REVOKE:
14705  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_REVOKE;
14706  break;
14707 
14708  case PT_CREATE_TRIGGER:
14709  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_CREATE_TRIGGER;
14710  break;
14711 
14712  case PT_RENAME_TRIGGER:
14713  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_RENAME_TRIGGER;
14714  break;
14715 
14716  case PT_DROP_TRIGGER:
14717  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DROP_TRIGGER;
14718  break;
14719 
14720  case PT_REMOVE_TRIGGER:
14721  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_REMOVE_TRIGGER;
14722  break;
14723 
14724  case PT_ALTER_TRIGGER:
14725  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_SET_TRIGGER;
14726  break;
14727 
14728  case PT_TRUNCATE:
14729  if (!truncate_need_repl_log (statement))
14730  {
14731  return NO_ERROR;
14732  }
14733 
14734  assert (statement->info.spec.entity_name);
14735  name = pt_print_bytes (parser, statement->info.spec.entity_name->info.spec.entity_name);
14736  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_TRUNCATE;
14737  break;
14738 
14739  case PT_UPDATE_STATS:
14740  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_UPDATE_STATS;
14741  break;
14742 
14743  case PT_INSERT:
14744  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_INSERT;
14745  break;
14746  case PT_DELETE:
14747  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_DELETE;
14748  break;
14749  case PT_UPDATE:
14750  repl_stmt.statement_type = CUBRID_STMT_UPDATE;
14751  break;
14752 
14753  case PT_DROP_VARIABLE: /* DROP VARIABLE statements are not replicated intentionally. */
14754  default:
14755  return NO_ERROR;
14756  }
14757 
14758  repl_info.repl_info_type = REPL_INFO_TYPE_SBR;
14759  if (name == NULL)
14760  {
14761  repl_stmt.name = (char *) unknown_name;
14762  }
14763  else
14764  {
14765  repl_stmt.name = (char *) pt_get_varchar_bytes (name);
14766  }
14767 
14768  /* it may contain multiple statements */
14769  if (strlen (statement->sql_user_text) > statement->sql_user_text_len)
14770  {
14771  stmt_end = &statement->sql_user_text[statement->sql_user_text_len];
14772  stmt_separator = *stmt_end;
14773  *stmt_end = '\0';
14774  }
14775  repl_stmt.stmt_text = statement->sql_user_text;
14776 
14777  repl_stmt.db_user = db_get_user_name ();
14778 
14779  if (pt_is_ddl_statement (statement) != 0)
14780  {
14781  repl_stmt.sys_prm_context = sysprm_print_parameters_for_ha_repl ();
14782  }
14783  else
14784  {
14785  repl_stmt.sys_prm_context = NULL;
14786  }
14787 
14788  assert_release (repl_stmt.db_user != NULL);
14789 
14790  repl_info.info = (char *) &repl_stmt;
14791 
14792  error = locator_flush_replication_info (&repl_info);
14793 
14794  if (stmt_end != NULL)
14795  {
14796  *stmt_end = stmt_separator;
14797  }
14798 
14799  db_string_free (repl_stmt.db_user);
14800  if (repl_stmt.sys_prm_context)
14801  {
14802  free (repl_stmt.sys_prm_context);
14803  }
14804 
14805  return error;
14806 }

14812 /*
14813  * Function Group:
14814  * Implements the scope statement.
14815  *
14816  */
14817 
14818 /*
14819  * do_scope() - scopes a statement
14820  * return: Error code if scope fails
14821  * parser(in/out): Parser context
14822  * statement(in): The parse tree of a scope statement
14823  *
14824  * Note:
14825  */
14826 int
14827 do_scope (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14828 {
14829  int error = NO_ERROR;
14830  PT_NODE *stmt;
14831 
14832  if (!statement || (statement->node_type != PT_SCOPE) || !((stmt = statement->info.scope.stmt))
14833  || (stmt->node_type != PT_TRIGGER_ACTION))
14834  {
14835  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
14836  }
14837  else
14838  {
14839  switch (stmt->info.trigger_action.action_type)
14840  {
14841  case PT_REJECT:
14842  case PT_INVALIDATE_XACTION:
14843  case PT_PRINT:
14844  break;
14845 
14846  case PT_EXPRESSION:
14847  do_Trigger_involved = true;
14848 #if 0
14849  if (prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_XASL_MAX_PLAN_CACHE_ENTRIES) > 0)
14850  {
14851 
14852  /* prepare a statement to execute */
14853  error = do_prepare_statement (parser, stmt->info.trigger_action.expression);
14854  if (error >= NO_ERROR)
14855  {
14856  /* execute the prepared statement */
14857  error = do_execute_statement (parser, stmt->info.trigger_action.expression);
14858  }
14859  }
14860  else
14861  {
14862  error = do_statement (parser, stmt->info.trigger_action.expression);
14863  }
14864 #else
14865  error = do_statement (parser, stmt->info.trigger_action.expression);
14866 #endif
14867  /* Do not reset do_Trigger_involved here. This is intention. */
14868  break;
14869 
14870  default:
14871  break;
14872  }
14873 
14874  return error;
14875  }
14876 }
14877 
14878 
14879 
14880 
14881 
14882 /*
14883  * Function Group:
14884  * Implements the DO statement.
14885  *
14886  */
14887 
14888 /*
14889  * do_execute_do() - execute the DO statement
14890  * return: Error code if scope fails
14891  * parser(in/out): Parser context
14892  * statement(in): The parse tree of the DO statement
14893  *
14894  * Note:
14895  */
14896 int
14897 do_execute_do (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14898 {
14899  int error = NO_ERROR;
14900  XASL_NODE *xasl = NULL;
14901  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
14902  int save;
14903  QUERY_FLAG query_flag;
14904 
14905  XASL_STREAM stream;
14906 
14907  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
14908 
14909  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
14910 
14911  AU_DISABLE (save);
14912  parser->au_save = save;
14913 
14914  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
14915  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
14916 
14917  /* always sync exec */
14918  query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
14919 
14920  /* don't cache anything */
14921  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
14922  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
14923 
14924  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
14925  {
14926  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
14927  }
14928 
14929  pt_null_etc (statement);
14930 
14931  /* generate statement's XASL */
14932  xasl = parser_generate_do_stmt_xasl (parser, statement);
14933 
14934  if (pt_has_error (parser))
14935  {
14936  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_EXECUTION);
14937  error = er_errid ();
14938  goto end;
14939  }
14940  else if (xasl == NULL)
14941  {
14942  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
14943  error = er_errid ();
14944  goto end;
14945  }
14946 
14947  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE) == true && parser->query_trace == true)
14948  {
14949  do_set_trace_to_query_flag (&query_flag);
14950  do_send_plan_trace_to_session (parser);
14951  }
14952 
14953 
14954  /* map XASL to stream */
14955  error = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (xasl, &stream);
14956  if (error != NO_ERROR)
14957  {
14958  goto end;
14959  }
14960 
14961  error =
14962  prepare_and_execute_query (stream.buffer, stream.buffer_size, &parser->query_id,
14963  parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count, parser->host_variables, &list_id,
14964  query_flag);
14965 
14966  if (error != NO_ERROR)
14967  {
14968  goto end;
14969  }
14970 
14971  statement->etc = list_id;
14972 
14973 end:
14974  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
14975  if (stream.buffer)
14976  {
14977  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
14978  }
14979 
14980  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
14981  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
14982  AU_ENABLE (save);
14983 
14984  return error;
14985 }
14986 
14987 /*
14988  * do_set_session_variables () - execute a set session variables statement
14989  * return : error code or no error
14990  * parser (in) : parser
14991  * statement (in) : statement
14992  */
14993 int
14994 do_set_session_variables (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
14995 {
14996  int error = NO_ERROR;
14997  DB_VALUE *variables = NULL;
14998  int count = 0, i = 0;
14999  PT_NODE *assignment = NULL;
15000 
15001  assert (statement != NULL);
15002  assert (statement->node_type == PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES);
15003 
15004  count = 0;
15005  /* count assignments */
15006  assignment = statement->info.set_variables.assignments;
15007  while (assignment)
15008  {
15009  count++;
15010  assignment = assignment->next;
15011  }
15012  /* we will store assignments in an array containing name1, value1, name2, value2... */
15013  variables = (DB_VALUE *) malloc (count * 2 * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
15014  if (variables == NULL)
15015  {
15016  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, count * 2 * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
15017  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
15018  goto cleanup;
15019  }
15020 
15021  /* initialize variables in case we need to exit with error */
15022  for (i = 0; i < count * 2; i++)
15023  {
15024  db_make_null (&variables[i]);
15025  }
15026 
15027  for (i = 0, assignment = statement->info.set_variables.assignments; assignment; i += 2, assignment = assignment->next)
15028  {
15029  pr_clone_value (pt_value_to_db (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg1), &variables[i]);
15030  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg2, &variables[i + 1], 1);
15031 
15032  if (pt_has_error (parser))
15033  {
15034  /* if error occurred, don't send junk to server */
15035  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_EXECUTION);
15036  error = er_errid ();
15037  goto cleanup;
15038  }
15039  }
15040 
15041  error = csession_set_session_variables (variables, count * 2);
15042 
15043 cleanup:
15044  if (variables != NULL)
15045  {
15046  for (i = 0; i < count * 2; i++)
15047  {
15048  pr_clear_value (&variables[i]);
15049  }
15050  free_and_init (variables);
15051  }
15052  return error;
15053 }
15054 
15055 /*
15056  * do_drop_session_variables () - execute a drop session variables statement
15057  * return : error code or no error
15058  * parser (in) : parser
15059  * statement (in) : statement
15060  */
15061 int
15062 do_drop_session_variables (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
15063 {
15064  int error = NO_ERROR;
15065  DB_VALUE *values = NULL;
15066  int count = 0, i = 0;
15067  PT_NODE *variables = NULL;
15068 
15069  assert (statement != NULL);
15070  assert (statement->node_type = PT_DROP_SESSION_VARIABLES);
15071 
15072  count = 0;
15073  /* count assignments */
15074  variables = statement->info.drop_session_var.variables;
15075  while (variables)
15076  {
15077  count++;
15078  variables = variables->next;
15079  }
15080  /* we will store assignments in an array containing name1, value1, name2, value2... */
15081  values = (DB_VALUE *) malloc (count * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
15082  if (values == NULL)
15083  {
15084  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, count * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
15085  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
15086  goto cleanup;
15087  }
15088 
15089  for (i = 0, variables = statement->info.drop_session_var.variables; variables; i++, variables = variables->next)
15090  {
15091  pr_clone_value (pt_value_to_db (parser, variables), &values[i]);
15092  }
15093 
15094  error = csession_drop_session_variables (values, count);
15095 
15096 cleanup:
15097  if (values != NULL)
15098  {
15099  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
15100  {
15101  pr_clear_value (&values[i]);
15102  }
15103  free_and_init (values);
15104  }
15105  return error;
15106 }
15107 
15108 /*
15109  * MERGE STATEMENT
15110  */
15111 
15112 /* used to generate unique savepoint names */
15113 static int merge_savepoint_number = 0;
15114 
15115 /*
15116  * do_check_merge_trigger() -
15117  * return: Error code
15118  * parser(in): Parser context
15119  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement
15120  *
15121  * Note: The function checks if there is any active trigger with event
15122  * TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE defined on the target.
15123  * If there is one, raise the trigger. Otherwise, perform the
15124  * given do_ function.
15125  */
15126 int
15127 do_check_merge_trigger (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_DO_FUNC * do_func)
15128 {
15129  int err;
15130 
15131  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STATEMENT) && statement->info.merge.search_cond == NULL)
15132  {
15133  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STMT, 0);
15134  return ER_BLOCK_NOWHERE_STMT;
15135  }
15136 
15137  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
15138  {
15139  /* no active trigger is involved. Avoid lock and fetch request. */
15140  err = do_func (parser, statement);
15141  }
15142  else
15143  {
15144  err = check_merge_trigger (do_func, parser, statement);
15145  }
15146 
15147  return err;
15148 }
15149 
15150 /*
15151  * check_merge_trigger() -
15152  * return: Error code
15153  * do_func(in): Function to do
15154  * parser(in): Parser context used by do_func
15155  * statement(in): Parse tree of a statement used by do_func
15156  *
15157  * Note: The function checks if there is any active trigger for UPDATE,
15158  * INSERT, or DELETE statements of a MERGE statement.
15159  */
15160 static int
15161 check_merge_trigger (PT_DO_FUNC * do_func, PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
15162 {
15163  int err, result = NO_ERROR;
15164  TR_STATE *state;
15165  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
15166  PT_NODE *flat = NULL;
15167  DB_OBJECT *class_ = NULL;
15168 
15169  /* Prepare a trigger state for any triggers that must be raised in this statement */
15170 
15171  state = NULL;
15172 
15173  flat = (statement->info.merge.into) ? statement->info.merge.into->info.spec.flat_entity_list : NULL;
15174  class_ = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
15175  if (class_ == NULL)
15176  {
15177  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid spec id");
15178  result = ER_FAILED;
15179  goto exit;
15180  }
15181 
15182  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment)
15183  {
15184  /* UPDATE statement triggers */
15185  result = tr_prepare_statement (&state, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE, class_, 0, NULL);
15186  if (result != NO_ERROR)
15187  {
15188  goto exit;
15189  }
15190  /* DELETE statement triggers */
15191  if (statement->info.merge.update.has_delete)
15192  {
15193  result = tr_prepare_statement (&state, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE, class_, 0, NULL);
15194  if (result != NO_ERROR)
15195  {
15196  goto exit;
15197  }
15198  }
15199  }
15200  if (statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15201  {
15202  /* INSERT statement triggers */
15203  result = tr_prepare_statement (&state, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT, class_, 0, NULL);
15204  if (result != NO_ERROR)
15205  {
15206  goto exit;
15207  }
15208  }
15209 
15210  if (state == NULL)
15211  {
15212  /* no triggers */
15213  result = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement, do_func);
15214  }
15215  else
15216  {
15217  /* the operations performed in 'tr_before', 'do_check_internal_statements' and 'tr_after' should be all contained
15218  * in one transaction */
15219  if (tr_Current_depth <= 1)
15220  {
15221  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UtrP", &tr_savepoint_number);
15222  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
15223  {
15224  result = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
15225  goto exit;
15226  }
15227  result = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
15228  if (result != NO_ERROR)
15229  {
15230  goto exit;
15231  }
15232  }
15233 
15234  /* fire BEFORE STATEMENT triggers */
15235  result = tr_before (state);
15236  if (result == NO_ERROR)
15237  {
15238  result = do_check_internal_statements (parser, statement, do_func);
15239  if (result < NO_ERROR)
15240  {
15241  tr_abort (state);
15242  state = NULL; /* state was freed */
15243  }
15244  else
15245  {
15246  /* fire AFTER STATEMENT triggers */
15247  /* try to preserve the usual result value */
15248  err = tr_after (state);
15249  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15250  {
15251  result = err;
15252  }
15253  if (tr_get_execution_state ())
15254  {
15255  state = NULL; /* state was freed */
15256  }
15257  }
15258  }
15259  else
15260  {
15261  /* state was freed */
15262  state = NULL;
15263  }
15264  }
15265 
15266 exit:
15267  if (state)
15268  {
15269  /* We need to free state and decrease the tr_Current_depth. */
15270  tr_abort (state);
15271  }
15272 
15273  if (result < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name != NULL && (result != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED))
15274  {
15275  /* savepoint from tran_savepoint() */
15276  (void) tran_abort_upto_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
15277  }
15278  return result;
15279 }
15280 
15281 /*
15282  * do_merge () - MERGE statement
15283  * return:
15284  * parser(in):
15285  * statement(in):
15286  *
15287  */
15288 int
15289 do_merge (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
15290 {
15291  int err = NO_ERROR;
15292  PT_NODE *not_nulls = NULL, *lhs, *spec = NULL;
15293  int has_unique;
15294  const char *savepoint_name = NULL;
15295  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
15296  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
15297  PT_NODE *upd_select_stmt = NULL;
15298  PT_NODE *ins_select_stmt = NULL;
15299  PT_NODE *select_names = NULL, *select_values = NULL;
15300  PT_NODE *const_names = NULL, *const_values = NULL;
15301  PT_NODE *flat, *values_list = NULL;
15302  PT_NODE **links = NULL;
15303  PT_NODE *hint_arg;
15304  QUERY_ID ins_query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
15305  QUERY_ID upd_query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
15306  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
15307  int no_vals, no_consts;
15308  int wait_msecs = -2, old_wait_msecs = -2;
15309  float hint_waitsecs;
15310  int result = 0;
15311  bool insert_only = false;
15312  PT_NODE *copy_assigns, *save_assigns;
15313 
15314  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
15315 
15316  /* savepoint for statement atomicity */
15317  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UmsP", &merge_savepoint_number);
15318  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
15319  {
15320  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
15321  goto exit;
15322  }
15323  err = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
15324  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15325  {
15326  goto exit;
15327  }
15328 
15329  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
15330 
15331  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
15332  {
15333  insert_only = true;
15334  if (!statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15335  {
15336  /* nothing to execute */
15337  goto exit;
15338  }
15339  }
15340 
15341  spec = statement->info.merge.into;
15342  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
15343  if (flat == NULL)
15344  {
15345  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
15346  goto exit;
15347  }
15348  class_obj = flat->info.name.db_object;
15349 
15350  /* check update part */
15351  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
15352  {
15353  /* check if the target class has UNIQUE constraint */
15354  err = update_check_for_constraints (parser, &has_unique, &not_nulls, statement);
15355  /* not needed */
15356  if (not_nulls)
15357  {
15358  parser_free_tree (parser, not_nulls);
15359  not_nulls = NULL;
15360  }
15361  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15362  {
15363  goto exit;
15364  }
15365  if (has_unique)
15366  {
15367  statement->info.merge.flags |= PT_MERGE_INFO_HAS_UNIQUE;
15368  }
15369 
15370  lhs = statement->info.merge.update.assignment->info.expr.arg1;
15371  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
15372  {
15373  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
15374  }
15375  if (lhs->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR)
15376  {
15377  statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs = true;
15378  }
15379 
15380  if (!statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs)
15381  {
15382  /* make the SELECT statement for OID list to be updated */
15383  no_vals = 0;
15384  no_consts = 0;
15385 
15386  /* make a copy of assignment list to be able to iterate later */
15387  copy_assigns = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, statement->info.merge.update.assignment);
15388 
15389  err =
15390  pt_get_assignment_lists (parser, &select_names, &select_values, &const_names, &const_values, &no_vals,
15391  &no_consts, statement->info.merge.update.assignment, &links);
15392  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15393  {
15394  parser_free_tree (parser, copy_assigns);
15395  goto exit;
15396  }
15397 
15398  /* save assignment list and replace within statement with the copy */
15399  save_assigns = statement->info.merge.update.assignment;
15400  statement->info.merge.update.assignment = copy_assigns;
15401 
15402  upd_select_stmt = pt_to_merge_update_query (parser, select_values, &statement->info.merge);
15403 
15404  /* restore assignment list and destroy the copy */
15405  statement->info.merge.update.assignment = save_assigns;
15406  parser_free_tree (parser, copy_assigns);
15407 
15408  /* restore tree structure; pt_get_assignment_lists() */
15409  pt_restore_assignment_links (statement->info.merge.update.assignment, links, -1);
15410 
15411  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
15412  upd_select_stmt = mq_translate (parser, upd_select_stmt);
15413  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
15414  if (upd_select_stmt == NULL)
15415  {
15416  err = er_errid ();
15417  if (err == NO_ERROR)
15418  {
15419  if (pt_has_error (parser))
15420  {
15421  pt_report_to_ersys_with_statement (parser, PT_SEMANTIC, upd_select_stmt);
15422  err = er_errid ();
15423  }
15424  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (err);
15425  }
15426  goto exit;
15427  }
15428  }
15429  }
15430 
15431  /* check insert part */
15432  if (statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15433  {
15434  PT_NODE *attrs = statement->info.merge.insert.attr_list;
15435 
15436  err = check_for_cons (parser, &has_unique, &not_nulls, attrs, flat->info.name.db_object);
15437  if (not_nulls)
15438  {
15439  parser_free_tree (parser, not_nulls);
15440  not_nulls = NULL;
15441  }
15442  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15443  {
15444  goto exit;
15445  }
15446  if (has_unique)
15447  {
15448  statement->info.merge.flags |= PT_MERGE_INFO_HAS_UNIQUE;
15449  }
15450 
15451  /* check not nulls attrs are present in attr list */
15452  err = check_missing_non_null_attrs (parser, spec, attrs, false);
15453  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15454  {
15455  goto exit;
15456  }
15457 
15458  /* get results from insert's select query */
15459  if (err >= NO_ERROR && (values_list = statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses) != NULL)
15460  {
15461  ins_select_stmt = pt_to_merge_insert_query (parser, values_list->info.node_list.list, &statement->info.merge);
15462  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
15463  ins_select_stmt = mq_translate (parser, ins_select_stmt);
15464  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
15465 
15466  if (ins_select_stmt == NULL)
15467  {
15468  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15469  err = er_errid ();
15470  if (err == NO_ERROR)
15471  {
15472  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
15473  }
15474  goto exit;
15475  }
15476 
15477  ins_select_stmt->etc = NULL;
15478 
15479  /* enable authorization checking during methods in queries */
15480  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
15481 
15482  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
15483  parser->query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
15484  err = do_select (parser, ins_select_stmt);
15485  ins_query_id = parser->query_id;
15486  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
15487 
15488  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
15489 
15490  if (err < NO_ERROR)
15491  {
15492  goto exit;
15493  }
15494 
15495  if (ins_select_stmt->etc == NULL)
15496  {
15497  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15498  err = er_errid ();
15499  if (err == NO_ERROR)
15500  {
15501  if (qo_need_skip_execution () == false)
15502  {
15503  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
15504  }
15505  }
15506 
15507  goto exit;
15508  }
15509  }
15510  }
15511 
15512  /* IX lock on the class */
15513  if (locator_fetch_class (class_obj, DB_FETCH_CLREAD_INSTWRITE) == NULL)
15514  {
15515  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15516  err = er_errid ();
15517  if (err == NO_ERROR)
15518  {
15519  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
15520  }
15521  goto exit;
15522  }
15523 
15524  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
15525  {
15526  if (!statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs)
15527  {
15528  /* flush necessary objects before execute */
15529  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
15530  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15531  {
15532  goto exit;
15533  }
15534 
15535  /* enable authorization checking during methods in queries */
15536  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
15537 
15538  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
15539  parser->query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
15540  err = do_select (parser, upd_select_stmt);
15541  upd_query_id = parser->query_id;
15542  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
15543 
15544  AU_DISABLE (parser->au_save);
15545 
15546  if (err < NO_ERROR)
15547  {
15548  /* query failed, an error has already been set */
15549  goto exit;
15550  }
15551 
15552  list_id = (QFILE_LIST_ID *) upd_select_stmt->etc;
15553  parser_free_tree (parser, upd_select_stmt);
15554  upd_select_stmt = NULL;
15555  }
15556  }
15557 
15558  hint_arg = statement->info.merge.waitsecs_hint;
15559  if ((statement->info.merge.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT) && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
15560  {
15561  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
15562  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
15563  {
15564  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
15565  }
15566  else
15567  {
15568  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
15569  }
15570  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
15571  {
15572  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
15573  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
15574  }
15575  }
15576 
15577  /* do update part */
15578  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
15579  {
15580  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
15581  parser->query_id = upd_query_id;
15582  if (statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs)
15583  {
15584  /* update class attributes */
15585  err = update_class_attributes (parser, statement);
15586  }
15587  else
15588  {
15589  /* OID list update */
15590  err = update_objs_for_list_file (parser, list_id, statement, true);
15591  }
15592 
15593  /* set result count */
15594  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
15595  {
15596  result += err;
15597  }
15598 
15599  parser->query_id = upd_query_id;
15600  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
15601  }
15602 
15603  /* do insert part */
15604  if (err >= NO_ERROR && (values_list = statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses) != NULL)
15605  {
15606  PT_NODE *save_list;
15607  PT_MISC_TYPE save_type;
15608 
15609  /* save node list */
15610  save_type = values_list->info.node_list.list_type;
15611  save_list = values_list->info.node_list.list;
15612 
15613  values_list->info.node_list.list_type = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
15614  values_list->info.node_list.list = ins_select_stmt;
15615 
15616  obt_begin_insert_values ();
15617  /* execute subquery & insert its results into target class */
15618  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
15619  parser->query_id = ins_query_id;
15620  err = insert_subquery_results (parser, statement, values_list, flat, &savepoint_name);
15621  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
15622  if (parser->abort)
15623  {
15624  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15625  err = er_errid ();
15626  }
15627  else if (err >= NO_ERROR)
15628  {
15629  result += err;
15630  }
15631 
15632  /* restore node list */
15633  values_list->info.node_list.list_type = save_type;
15634  values_list->info.node_list.list = save_list;
15635 
15636  parser_free_tree (parser, ins_select_stmt);
15637  ins_select_stmt = NULL;
15638 
15639  /* pt_end_query() already called by insert_subquery_results() */
15640  }
15641 
15642  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
15643  {
15644  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
15645  }
15646 
15647  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
15648  {
15649  err = db_is_vclass (class_obj);
15650  if (err > 0)
15651  {
15652  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
15653  }
15654  }
15655 
15656 exit:
15657  if (upd_select_stmt != NULL)
15658  {
15659  parser_free_tree (parser, upd_select_stmt);
15660  }
15661 
15662  if (list_id != NULL)
15663  {
15664  regu_free_listid (list_id);
15665  if (upd_query_id != NULL_QUERY_ID && !tran_was_latest_query_ended ())
15666  {
15667  qmgr_end_query (upd_query_id);
15668  }
15669  }
15670 
15671  if (ins_select_stmt != NULL)
15672  {
15673  if (ins_select_stmt->etc != NULL)
15674  {
15675  regu_free_listid ((QFILE_LIST_ID *) ins_select_stmt->etc);
15676  if (ins_query_id != NULL_QUERY_ID && !tran_was_latest_query_ended ())
15677  {
15678  qmgr_end_query (ins_query_id);
15679  }
15680  }
15681  parser_free_tree (parser, ins_select_stmt);
15682  }
15683 
15684  if ((err < NO_ERROR) && er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
15685  {
15686  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number, er_msg (),
15687  NULL);
15688  }
15689  /* If error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
15690  * transaction. */
15691  if (err < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && err != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
15692  {
15693  (void) db_abort_to_savepoint (savepoint_name);
15694  }
15695 
15696  AU_ENABLE (parser->au_save);
15697 
15698  return (err < NO_ERROR) ? err : result;
15699 }
15700 
15701 /*
15702  * do_prepare_merge() - Prepare the MERGE statement
15703  * return: Error code
15704  * parser(in): Parser context
15705  * statement(in/out): Parse tree of a MERGE statement
15706  *
15707  */
15708 int
15709 do_prepare_merge (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
15710 {
15711  int err = NO_ERROR;
15712  PT_NODE *non_nulls_upd = NULL, *non_nulls_ins = NULL, *lhs, *flat, *spec;
15713  int has_unique = 0, has_trigger = 0, has_virt = 0, au_save;
15714  bool server_insert, server_update, server_op, insert_only = false;
15715 
15716  PT_NODE *select_statement = NULL;
15717  PT_NODE *select_names = NULL, *select_values = NULL;
15718  PT_NODE *const_names = NULL, *const_values = NULL;
15719  PT_NODE **links = NULL;
15720  PT_NODE *default_expr_attrs = NULL;
15721  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
15722  PT_NODE *copy_assigns, *save_assigns;
15723 
15724  int no_vals, no_consts, is_vclass = 0;
15725 
15726  COMPILE_CONTEXT *contextp;
15727  XASL_STREAM stream;
15728 
15729  contextp = &parser->context;
15730 
15731  init_xasl_stream (&stream);
15732 
15733  if (parser == NULL || statement == NULL)
15734  {
15735  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
15736  return ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
15737  }
15738 
15739  contextp->sql_user_text = statement->sql_user_text;
15740  contextp->sql_user_text_len = statement->sql_user_text_len;
15741 
15742  if (pt_false_where (parser, statement))
15743  {
15744  statement->info.merge.flags |= PT_MERGE_INFO_INSERT_ONLY;
15745  if (!statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15746  {
15747  /* nothing to prepare */
15748  goto cleanup;
15749  }
15750  insert_only = true;
15751  }
15752 
15753  if (statement->xasl_id)
15754  {
15755  /* already prepared */
15756  goto cleanup;
15757  }
15758 
15759  /* check into for triggers and virtual class */
15760  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
15761 
15762  spec = statement->info.merge.into;
15763  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
15764  class_obj = (flat) ? flat->info.name.db_object : NULL;
15765 
15766  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
15767  {
15768  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_UPDATE);
15769  if (err == NO_ERROR && !has_trigger)
15770  {
15771  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_UPDATE);
15772  }
15773  if (err == NO_ERROR && !has_trigger && statement->info.merge.update.has_delete)
15774  {
15775  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_DELETE);
15776  if (err == NO_ERROR && !has_trigger)
15777  {
15778  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_DELETE);
15779  }
15780  }
15781  }
15782  if (err == NO_ERROR && !has_trigger && statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15783  {
15784  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_INSERT);
15785  if (err == NO_ERROR && !has_trigger)
15786  {
15787  err = sm_class_has_triggers (class_obj, &has_trigger, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT);
15788  }
15789  }
15790 
15791  if (err == NO_ERROR)
15792  {
15793  is_vclass = db_is_vclass (class_obj);
15794  if (is_vclass < 0)
15795  {
15796  err = is_vclass;
15797  }
15798  else
15799  {
15800  has_virt = is_vclass || ((flat) ? (flat->info.name.virt_object != NULL) : false);
15801  }
15802  }
15803 
15804  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
15805 
15806  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15807  {
15808  goto cleanup;
15809  }
15810 
15811  err = do_evaluate_default_expr (parser, flat);
15812  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15813  {
15814  goto cleanup;
15815  }
15816 
15817  /* check update part */
15818  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
15819  {
15820  /* check if the target class has UNIQUE constraint */
15821  err = update_check_for_constraints (parser, &has_unique, &non_nulls_upd, statement);
15822  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15823  {
15824  goto cleanup;
15825  }
15826  if (has_unique)
15827  {
15828  statement->info.merge.flags |= PT_MERGE_INFO_HAS_UNIQUE;
15829  }
15830 
15831  server_update = (!has_trigger && !has_virt
15832  && !update_check_having_meta_attr (parser, statement->info.merge.update.assignment));
15833 
15834  lhs = statement->info.merge.update.assignment->info.expr.arg1;
15835  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
15836  {
15837  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
15838  }
15839 
15840  /* if we are updating class attributes, not need to prepare */
15841  if (lhs->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR)
15842  {
15843  statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs = true;
15844  goto cleanup;
15845  }
15846  }
15847  else
15848  {
15849  server_update = !has_trigger && !has_virt;
15850  }
15851 
15852  /* check insert part */
15853  if (statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15854  {
15855  PT_NODE *attr, *attrs = statement->info.merge.insert.attr_list;
15856 
15857  if (prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_INSERT_MODE) & INSERT_SELECT)
15858  {
15859  /* server insert cannot handle insert into a shared attribute */
15860  server_insert = true;
15861  attr = attrs;
15862  while (attr)
15863  {
15864  if (attr->node_type != PT_NAME || attr->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
15865  {
15866  server_insert = false;
15867  break;
15868  }
15869  attr = attr->next;
15870  }
15871  }
15872  else
15873  {
15874  server_insert = false;
15875  }
15876 
15877  err = check_for_cons (parser, &has_unique, &non_nulls_ins, attrs, flat->info.name.db_object);
15878  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15879  {
15880  goto cleanup;
15881  }
15882  if (has_unique)
15883  {
15884  statement->info.merge.flags |= PT_MERGE_INFO_HAS_UNIQUE;
15885  }
15886 
15887  /* check not nulls attrs are present in attr list */
15888  err = check_missing_non_null_attrs (parser, spec, attrs, false);
15889  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15890  {
15891  goto cleanup;
15892  }
15893  }
15894  else
15895  {
15896  server_insert = !has_trigger && !has_virt;
15897  }
15898 
15899  server_op = (server_insert && server_update);
15900 
15901  if (server_op)
15902  {
15903  statement->info.merge.flags |= PT_MERGE_INFO_SERVER_OP;
15904 
15905  /* make query string */
15906  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 1;
15907  parser->long_string_skipped = 0;
15908  parser->print_type_ambiguity = 0;
15909  PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS (parser, statement, (PT_CONVERT_RANGE | PT_PRINT_QUOTES | PT_PRINT_USER));
15910  contextp->sql_hash_text = (char *) statement->alias_print;
15911  err = SHA1Compute ((unsigned char *) contextp->sql_hash_text, (unsigned) strlen (contextp->sql_hash_text),
15912  &contextp->sha1);
15913  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15914  {
15915  ASSERT_ERROR ();
15916  return err;
15917  }
15918  parser->dont_prt_long_string = 0;
15919  if (parser->long_string_skipped || parser->print_type_ambiguity)
15920  {
15921  statement->cannot_prepare = 1;
15922  goto cleanup;
15923  }
15924 
15925  /* lookup in XASL cache */
15926  contextp->recompile_xasl = statement->recompile;
15927  if (statement->recompile == 0)
15928  {
15929  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
15930  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15931  {
15932  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (err);
15933  }
15934  else if (contextp->recompile_xasl == true)
15935  {
15936  /* recompile requested by server */
15937  if (stream.xasl_id != NULL)
15938  {
15939  free_and_init (stream.xasl_id);
15940  }
15941  }
15942  }
15943 
15944  if (stream.xasl_id == NULL && err == NO_ERROR)
15945  {
15946  if (statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
15947  {
15948  err = pt_find_omitted_default_expr (parser, flat->info.name.db_object,
15949  statement->info.merge.insert.attr_list, &default_expr_attrs);
15950  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15951  {
15952  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
15953  statement->xasl_id = NULL;
15954  goto cleanup;
15955  }
15956  }
15957 
15958  /* mark the beginning of another level of xasl packing */
15959  pt_enter_packing_buf ();
15960 
15961  /* generate MERGE XASL */
15962  contextp->xasl = pt_to_merge_xasl (parser, statement, &non_nulls_upd, &non_nulls_ins, default_expr_attrs);
15963 
15964  stream.buffer = NULL;
15965 
15966  if (contextp->xasl && (err >= NO_ERROR))
15967  {
15968  err = xts_map_xasl_to_stream (contextp->xasl, &stream);
15969  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15970  {
15971  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_RESOURCES_EXHAUSTED);
15972  }
15973 
15974  /* clear constant values */
15975  if (contextp->xasl->proc.merge.update_xasl)
15976  {
15977  int i;
15978  UPDATE_PROC_NODE *update = &contextp->xasl->proc.merge.update_xasl->proc.update;
15979 
15980  for (i = update->num_assigns - 1; i >= 0; i--)
15981  {
15982  if (update->assigns[i].constant)
15983  {
15984  pr_clear_value (update->assigns[i].constant);
15985  }
15986  }
15987  }
15988  }
15989  else
15990  {
15991 #if 0 /* TODO */
15992  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
15993 #endif
15994  err = er_errid ();
15995  if (err != NO_ERROR)
15996  {
15997  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number,
15998  er_msg (), NULL);
15999  }
16000  }
16001 
16002  /* cache the XASL */
16003  if (stream.buffer && (err >= NO_ERROR))
16004  {
16005  err = prepare_query (contextp, &stream);
16006  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16007  {
16008  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
16009  err = er_errid ();
16010  }
16011  }
16012 
16013  /* mark the end of another level of xasl packing */
16014  pt_exit_packing_buf ();
16015 
16016  /* free 'stream' that is allocated inside of xts_map_xasl_to_stream() */
16017  if (stream.buffer)
16018  {
16019  free_and_init (stream.buffer);
16020  }
16021  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
16022  statement->xasl_id = stream.xasl_id;
16023  }
16024  else
16025  {
16026  if (err == NO_ERROR)
16027  {
16028  statement->use_plan_cache = 1;
16029  statement->xasl_id = stream.xasl_id;
16030  }
16031  else
16032  {
16033  statement->use_plan_cache = 0;
16034  }
16035 
16036  goto cleanup;
16037  }
16038  }
16039  else
16040  {
16041  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
16042  {
16043  /* make the SELECT statement for OID list to be updated */
16044  no_vals = 0;
16045  no_consts = 0;
16046 
16047  /* make a copy of assignment list to be able to iterate later */
16048  copy_assigns = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, statement->info.merge.update.assignment);
16049 
16050  err =
16051  pt_get_assignment_lists (parser, &select_names, &select_values, &const_names, &const_values, &no_vals,
16052  &no_consts, statement->info.merge.update.assignment, &links);
16053  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16054  {
16055  parser_free_tree (parser, copy_assigns);
16056  goto cleanup;
16057  }
16058 
16059  /* save assignment list and replace within statement with the copy */
16060  save_assigns = statement->info.merge.update.assignment;
16061  statement->info.merge.update.assignment = copy_assigns;
16062 
16063  select_statement = pt_to_merge_update_query (parser, select_values, &statement->info.merge);
16064 
16065  /* restore assignment list and destroy the copy */
16066  statement->info.merge.update.assignment = save_assigns;
16067  parser_free_tree (parser, copy_assigns);
16068 
16069  /* restore tree structure; pt_get_assignment_lists() */
16070  pt_restore_assignment_links (statement->info.merge.update.assignment, links, -1);
16071 
16072  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save);
16073  select_statement = mq_translate (parser, select_statement);
16074  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
16075  if (select_statement)
16076  {
16077  /* get XASL_ID by calling do_prepare_select() */
16078  err = do_prepare_select (parser, select_statement);
16079 
16080  /* save the XASL_ID to be used by do_execute_merge() */
16081  statement->xasl_id = select_statement->xasl_id;
16082  select_statement->xasl_id = NULL;
16083 
16084  /* deallocate the SELECT statement */
16085  parser_free_tree (parser, select_statement);
16086  }
16087  else
16088  {
16089  err = er_errid ();
16090  if (err == NO_ERROR)
16091  {
16092  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
16093 
16094  err = ER_FAILED;
16095  }
16096  goto cleanup;
16097  }
16098  }
16099 
16100  /* nothing to do for merge insert part */
16101  }
16102 
16103 cleanup:
16104  if (non_nulls_upd)
16105  {
16106  parser_free_tree (parser, non_nulls_upd);
16107  non_nulls_upd = NULL;
16108  }
16109  if (non_nulls_ins)
16110  {
16111  parser_free_tree (parser, non_nulls_ins);
16112  non_nulls_ins = NULL;
16113  }
16114  return err;
16115 }
16116 
16117 /*
16118  * do_execute_merge() - Execute the prepared MERGE statement
16119  * return: Error code
16120  * parser(in): Parser context
16121  * statement(in): Parse tree of a MERGE statement
16122  *
16123  */
16124 int
16125 do_execute_merge (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
16126 {
16127  int err = NO_ERROR, result = 0, error = NO_ERROR;
16128  PT_NODE *flat, *spec = NULL, *values_list = NULL;
16129  const char *savepoint_name;
16130  DB_OBJECT *class_obj;
16131  QFILE_LIST_ID *list_id = NULL;
16132  int au_save;
16133  int wait_msecs = -2, old_wait_msecs = -2;
16134  float hint_waitsecs;
16135  PT_NODE *ins_select_stmt = NULL, *hint_arg;
16136  QUERY_ID ins_query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
16137  QUERY_ID query_id_self = parser->query_id;
16138  bool insert_only = (statement->info.merge.flags & PT_MERGE_INFO_INSERT_ONLY);
16139 
16140  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
16141 
16142  CHECK_MODIFICATION_ERROR ();
16143 
16144  if (insert_only && !statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
16145  {
16146  /* nothing to execute */
16147  goto exit;
16148  }
16149 
16150  /* savepoint for statement atomicity */
16151  savepoint_name = mq_generate_name (parser, "UmsP", &merge_savepoint_number);
16152  if (savepoint_name == NULL)
16153  {
16154  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
16155  goto exit;
16156  }
16157  err = tran_system_savepoint (savepoint_name);
16158  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16159  {
16160  goto exit;
16161  }
16162 
16163  spec = statement->info.merge.into;
16164  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
16165  if (flat == NULL)
16166  {
16167  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
16168  goto exit;
16169  }
16170  class_obj = flat->info.name.db_object;
16171 
16172  if (statement->info.merge.flags & PT_MERGE_INFO_SERVER_OP)
16173  {
16174  /* server side execution */
16175  int query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
16176 
16177  /* check if it is not necessary to execute this statement */
16178  if (statement->xasl_id == NULL)
16179  {
16180  statement->etc = NULL;
16181  goto exit;
16182  }
16183 
16184  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
16185  {
16186  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
16187  }
16188 
16189  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
16190  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
16191 
16192  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
16193  {
16194  query_flag |= EXECUTE_QUERY_WITH_COMMIT;
16195  }
16196 
16197  if (parser->is_auto_commit)
16198  {
16199  query_flag |= TRAN_AUTO_COMMIT;
16200  }
16201 
16202  if (ws_need_flush ())
16203  {
16204  // When a transaction is under auto-commit mode, flush all dirty objects to server.
16205  // Otherwise, flush associated objects.
16206 
16207  if (statement->use_auto_commit)
16208  {
16209  err = tran_flush_to_commit ();
16210  }
16211  else
16212  {
16213  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
16214  }
16215 
16216  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16217  {
16218  // flush error
16219  goto exit;
16220  }
16221  }
16222 
16223  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
16224 
16225  if (statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
16226  {
16227  obt_begin_insert_values ();
16228  }
16229 
16230  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
16231  list_id = NULL;
16232 
16233  err = execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
16234  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, NULL, NULL);
16235 
16236  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
16237  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16238  {
16239  goto exit;
16240  }
16241 
16242  /* free returned QFILE_LIST_ID */
16243  if (list_id)
16244  {
16245  if (list_id->tuple_cnt > 0)
16246  {
16247  if (statement->use_auto_commit && tran_was_latest_query_committed ())
16248  {
16249  /* Nothing to flush. Avoids flush, since may fetch the class. */
16250  err = sm_decache_instances_after_query_executed_with_commit (class_obj);
16251  }
16252  else
16253  {
16254  err = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (class_obj, true);
16255  }
16256 
16257  }
16258  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
16259  {
16260  result += list_id->tuple_cnt;
16261  }
16262  regu_free_listid (list_id);
16263  list_id = NULL;
16264  }
16265 
16266  /* end the query; reset query_id and call qmgr_end_query() */
16267  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
16268  }
16269  else
16270  {
16271  /* client side execution */
16272 
16273  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only && !statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs)
16274  {
16275  int query_flag = DEFAULT_EXEC_MODE;
16276 
16277  /* flush necessary objects before execute */
16278  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
16279  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16280  {
16281  goto exit;
16282  }
16283 
16284  if (parser->is_xasl_pinned_reference)
16285  {
16286  query_flag |= XASL_CACHE_PINNED_REFERENCE;
16287  }
16288 
16289  query_flag |= NOT_FROM_RESULT_CACHE;
16290  query_flag |= RESULT_CACHE_INHIBITED;
16291 
16292  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save); /* this insures authorization checking for method */
16293 
16294  assert (parser->query_id == NULL_QUERY_ID);
16295  list_id = NULL;
16296  err =
16297  execute_query (statement->xasl_id, &parser->query_id, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count,
16298  parser->host_variables, &list_id, query_flag, NULL, NULL);
16299  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
16300  if (err != NO_ERROR)
16301  {
16302  goto exit;
16303  }
16304  }
16305 
16306  /* make sure we have a correct lock on the class */
16307  if (locator_fetch_class (class_obj, DB_FETCH_CLREAD_INSTWRITE) == NULL)
16308  {
16309  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
16310  err = er_errid ();
16311  goto exit;
16312  }
16313 
16314  /* get results from insert's select query */
16315  if (err >= NO_ERROR && (values_list = statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses) != NULL)
16316  {
16317  ins_select_stmt = pt_to_merge_insert_query (parser, values_list->info.node_list.list, &statement->info.merge);
16318  AU_SAVE_AND_ENABLE (au_save);
16319  ins_select_stmt = mq_translate (parser, ins_select_stmt);
16320  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
16321 
16322  if (ins_select_stmt == NULL)
16323  {
16324  err = er_errid ();
16325  if (err == NO_ERROR)
16326  {
16327  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
16328 
16329  err = ER_FAILED;
16330  }
16331  goto exit;
16332  }
16333 
16334  ins_select_stmt->etc = NULL;
16335 
16336  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
16337  parser->query_id = NULL_QUERY_ID;
16338  err = do_select (parser, ins_select_stmt);
16339  ins_query_id = parser->query_id;
16340  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
16341 
16342  if (err < NO_ERROR)
16343  {
16344  goto exit;
16345  }
16346 
16347  if (ins_select_stmt->etc == NULL)
16348  {
16349  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
16350  err = er_errid ();
16351  if (err == NO_ERROR)
16352  {
16353  err = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
16354  }
16355  goto exit;
16356  }
16357  }
16358 
16359  hint_arg = statement->info.merge.waitsecs_hint;
16360  if ((statement->info.merge.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT) && PT_IS_HINT_NODE (hint_arg))
16361  {
16362  hint_waitsecs = (float) atof (hint_arg->info.name.original);
16363  if (hint_waitsecs > 0)
16364  {
16365  wait_msecs = (int) (hint_waitsecs * 1000);
16366  }
16367  else
16368  {
16369  wait_msecs = (int) hint_waitsecs;
16370  }
16371  if (wait_msecs >= -1)
16372  {
16373  old_wait_msecs = TM_TRAN_WAIT_MSECS ();
16374  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (wait_msecs);
16375  }
16376  }
16377 
16378  /* update part */
16379  if (statement->info.merge.update.assignment && !insert_only)
16380  {
16381  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
16382 
16383  if (statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs)
16384  {
16385  /* update class attributes */
16386  err = update_class_attributes (parser, statement);
16387  }
16388  else
16389  {
16390  /* OID list update */
16391  err = update_objs_for_list_file (parser, list_id, statement, true);
16392  }
16393 
16394  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
16395 
16396  /* set result count */
16397  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
16398  {
16399  result += err;
16400  }
16401 
16402  if (!statement->info.merge.update.do_class_attrs)
16403  {
16404  /* free returned QFILE_LIST_ID */
16405  if (list_id)
16406  {
16407  if (err >= NO_ERROR && list_id->tuple_cnt > 0)
16408  {
16409  err = sm_flush_and_decache_objects (class_obj, true);
16410  }
16411  regu_free_listid (list_id);
16412  list_id = NULL;
16413  }
16414  }
16415  pt_end_query (parser, query_id_self);
16416  }
16417 
16418  /* insert part */
16419  if (err >= NO_ERROR && (values_list = statement->info.merge.insert.value_clauses) != NULL)
16420  {
16421  PT_NODE *save_list;
16422  PT_MISC_TYPE save_type;
16423 
16424  /* save node list */
16425  save_type = values_list->info.node_list.list_type;
16426  save_list = values_list->info.node_list.list;
16427 
16428  values_list->info.node_list.list_type = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
16429  values_list->info.node_list.list = ins_select_stmt;
16430 
16431  AU_SAVE_AND_DISABLE (au_save);
16432 
16433  obt_begin_insert_values ();
16434  query_id_self = parser->query_id;
16435  parser->query_id = ins_query_id;
16436  /* execute subquery & insert its results into target class */
16437  err = insert_subquery_results (parser, statement, values_list, flat, &savepoint_name);
16438  parser->query_id = query_id_self;
16439  if (parser->abort)
16440  {
16441  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
16442  err = er_errid ();
16443  }
16444  else if (err >= NO_ERROR)
16445  {
16446  result += err;
16447  }
16448 
16449  AU_RESTORE (au_save);
16450 
16451  /* restore node list */
16452  values_list->info.node_list.list_type = save_type;
16453  values_list->info.node_list.list = save_list;
16454 
16455  parser_free_tree (parser, ins_select_stmt);
16456  ins_select_stmt = NULL;
16457  }
16458 
16459  if (old_wait_msecs >= -1)
16460  {
16461  (void) tran_reset_wait_times (old_wait_msecs);
16462  }
16463 
16464  if (err >= NO_ERROR)
16465  {
16466  err = db_is_vclass (class_obj);
16467  if (err > 0)
16468  {
16469  err = sm_flush_objects (class_obj);
16470  }
16471  }
16472  }
16473 
16474 exit:
16475  if (ins_select_stmt != NULL)
16476  {
16477  if (ins_select_stmt->etc != NULL)
16478  {
16479  regu_free_listid ((QFILE_LIST_ID *) ins_select_stmt->etc);
16480  if (ins_query_id != NULL_QUERY_ID && !tran_was_latest_query_ended ())
16481  {
16482  qmgr_end_query (ins_query_id);
16483  }
16484  }
16485  parser_free_tree (parser, ins_select_stmt);
16486  }
16487 
16488  if (list_id != NULL)
16489  {
16490  regu_free_listid (list_id);
16491  }
16492 
16493  /* If err == er_errid () and parser has error, we already record the parser error to sys error, no need to call
16494  * pt_record_error (..) */
16495  if ((err < NO_ERROR) && (error = er_errid ()) != NO_ERROR && (err != error || !pt_has_error (parser)))
16496  {
16497  pt_record_error (parser, parser->statement_number, statement->line_number, statement->column_number, er_msg (),
16498  NULL);
16499  }
16500  /* If error and a savepoint was created, rollback to savepoint. No need to rollback if the TM aborted the
16501  * transaction. */
16502  if (err < NO_ERROR && savepoint_name && err != ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
16503  {
16504  db_abort_to_savepoint (savepoint_name);
16505  }
16506 
16507  return (err < NO_ERROR) ? err : result;
16508 }
16509 
16510 /*
16511  * do_set_names() - Set the client charset and collation.
16512  * return: Error code if it fails
16513  * parser(in): Parser context
16514  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set transaction statement
16515  *
16516  * Note:
16517  */
16518 int
16519 do_set_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
16520 {

16522  int charset_id, collation_id;
16523 
16524  if (statement->info.set_names.charset_node != NULL)
16525  {

16527  pt_check_grammar_charset_collation (parser, statement->info.set_names.charset_node,
16528  statement->info.set_names.collation_node, &charset_id, &collation_id);
16529  }
16530 
16531  if (error == NO_ERROR)
16532  {
16533  /* size of ('intl_collation=') + collation name */
16534  char sys_prm_chg[15 + COLL_NAME_SIZE];
16535 
16536  snprintf (sys_prm_chg, sizeof (sys_prm_chg) - 1, "intl_collation=%s", lang_get_collation_name (collation_id));
16537  error = db_set_system_parameters (sys_prm_chg);
16538  }
16539 
16540  return (error != NO_ERROR) ? ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS : NO_ERROR;
16541 }

16570 
16571 /*
16572  * pt_append_odku_references () - append references to SELECT specs from
16573  * on duplicate key assignments to the SELECT
16574  * list
16575  * return :
16576  * parser (in) :
16577  * node (in) :
16578  * arg (in) :
16579  * continue_walk (in) :
16580  *
16581  * Note: This function rewrites the update assignments of an
16582  * INSERT...SELECT... ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE statement so that they can be
16583  * evaluated as constants. In order for this to be done, all right hand
16584  * references to attributes from the SELECT specs are added to the
16585  * SELECT list and replaced in assignments with PT_TUPLE_VALUE nodes. We can
16586  * only handle PT_NAME and PT_DOT_ (PT_NAME.PT_NAME) nodes here. We should
16587  * not encounter complex path expressions here but we will not throw an error
16588  * if we do. Complex path expression will either be foldable or we will throw
16589  * an error when we try to evaluate them.
16590  */
16591 static PT_NODE *
16592 pt_append_odku_references (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
16593 {
16594  ODKU_TUPLE_VALUE_ARG *odku_arg;
16595  PT_NODE *insert_spec = NULL;
16596  PT_NODE *select = NULL, *select_list = NULL, *select_spec = NULL, *spec = NULL;
16597  PT_NODE *name_node = NULL;
16598 
16599  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
16600 
16601  if (node == NULL || arg == NULL)
16602  {
16603  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
16604  return node;
16605  }
16606 
16607  odku_arg = (ODKU_TUPLE_VALUE_ARG *) arg;
16608 
16609  if (odku_arg->insert_stmt->node_type != PT_INSERT)
16610  {
16611  assert (false);
16612  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
16613  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
16614  return NULL;
16615  }
16616 
16617  if (odku_arg->insert_stmt->info.insert.value_clauses->node_type != PT_NODE_LIST)
16618  {
16619  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
16620  return node;
16621  }
16622 
16623  insert_spec = odku_arg->insert_stmt->info.insert.spec;
16624 
16625  select = odku_arg->insert_stmt->info.insert.value_clauses->info.node_list.list;
16626  if (!PT_IS_SELECT (select))
16627  {
16628  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
16629  return node;
16630  }
16631 
16632  select_list = pt_get_select_list (parser, select);
16633  if (select_list == NULL)
16634  {
16635  assert (false);
16636  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS, 0);
16637  return NULL;
16638  }
16639 
16640  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME)
16641  {
16642  name_node = node;
16643  }
16644  else if (node->node_type == PT_DOT_)
16645  {
16646  if (node->info.dot.arg1 == NULL || node->info.dot.arg1->node_type != PT_NAME)
16647  {
16648  return node;
16649  }
16650 
16651  /* do not visit leaves */
16652  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
16653  name_node = node->info.dot.arg1;
16654  }
16655  else
16656  {
16657  return node;
16658  }
16659 
16660  if (name_node->info.name.spec_id == insert_spec->info.spec.id)
16661  {
16662  /* node belongs to the insert class, nothing to be done here */
16663  return node;
16664  }
16665 
16666  select_spec = select->info.query.q.select.from;
16667  for (spec = select_spec; spec != NULL; spec = spec->next)
16668  {
16669  if (name_node->info.name.spec_id == spec->info.spec.id)
16670  {
16671  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
16672  return pt_make_tuple_value_reference (parser, node, select_list, odku_arg->cursor_p);
16673  }
16674  }
16675 
16676  /* There might be names which do not belong to either the select specs or the insert specs: ON DUPLICATE UPDATE set
16677  * column = (SELECT ...) */
16678  return node;
16679 }
16680 
16681 /*
16682  * do_evaluate_insert_values () - Evaluates list of values for insert.
16683  *
16684  * return : Error code.
16685  * parser (in) : Parser context.
16686  * insert_statement (in) : Parse tree node for insert statement.
16687  *
16688  * NOTE: The values corresponding to each attribute are evaluated from "left"
16689  * to "right", in the order given by user.
16690  * First step is to replace attribute names with values (see
16691  * do_replace_names_for_insert_values_pre).
16692  * Nodes in values list will be replaced with PT_INSERT_VALUES nodes
16693  * that store the original node (for reevaluation) and the evaluated
16694  * value.
16695  */
16696 static int
16697 do_evaluate_insert_values (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert_statement)
16698 {
16699  PT_NODE *val = NULL, *prev = NULL;
16700  PT_NODE *result = NULL, *save_next = NULL;
16701  EVAL_INSERT_VALUE eval;
16702  DB_VALUE eval_value;
16703  PT_NODE *attr_list = NULL, *value_list = NULL, *value_clause = NULL;
16704  PT_NODE *temp = NULL;
16705  bool free_temp = false;
16706 
16707  attr_list = insert_statement->info.insert.attr_list;
16708  value_clause = insert_statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
16709  if (attr_list == NULL || value_clause == NULL || value_clause->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
16710  {
16711  /* nothing to evaluate */
16712  return NO_ERROR;
16713  }
16714 
16715  /* initialize attr_list in EVAL_INSERT_VALUE object */
16716  eval.spec_id = insert_statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.id;
16717  eval.attr_list = attr_list;
16718  eval.value_list = NULL;
16719  eval.reevaluate_needed = false;
16720  eval.replace_names = false;
16721  eval.crt_attr_index = 0;
16722 
16723  db_make_null (&eval_value);
16724 
16725  /* evaluate lists of values */
16726  for (value_list = value_clause; value_list != NULL; value_list = value_list->next)
16727  {
16728  if (value_list->info.node_list.list_type != PT_IS_VALUE)
16729  {
16730  continue;
16731  }
16732  assert (value_list->node_type == PT_NODE_LIST);
16733  assert (value_list->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_VALUE);
16734  eval.value_list = value_list->info.node_list.list;
16735  eval.crt_attr_index = 0;
16736 
16737  /* evaluate values in val_list */
16738  for (prev = NULL, val = value_list->info.node_list.list; val != NULL; val = save_next, eval.crt_attr_index++)
16739  {
16740  save_next = val->next;
16741 
16742  if (PT_IS_INSERT_VALUE_NODE (val))
16743  {
16744  /* this is not the first evaluation */
16745  if (val->info.insert_value.is_evaluated)
16746  {
16747  /* already evaluated, do nothing */
16748  continue;
16749  }
16750  /* need to reevaluate */
16751  if (val->info.insert_value.replace_names)
16752  {
16753  /* duplicate original node because it will be altered */
16754  temp = parser_copy_tree (parser, val->info.insert_value.original_node);
16755  if (temp == NULL)
16756  {
16757  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
16758  {
16759  PT_ERRORmf (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_OUT_OF_MEMORY,
16760  sizeof (PT_NODE));
16761  }
16762  goto end_error;
16763  }
16764  free_temp = true;
16765  /* replace names */
16766  temp =
16767  parser_walk_tree (parser, temp, do_replace_names_for_insert_values_pre, &eval, pt_continue_walk,
16768  NULL);
16769  if (pt_has_error (parser))
16770  {
16771  goto end_error;
16772  }
16773  }
16774  else
16775  {
16776  temp = val->info.insert_value.original_node;
16777  }
16778  /* obtain evaluated value */
16779  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, temp, &val->info.insert_value.value, 1);
16780  if (free_temp)
16781  {
16782  /* free temp */
16783  parser_free_tree (parser, temp);
16784  temp = NULL;
16785  free_temp = false;
16786  }
16787  if (pt_has_error (parser))
16788  {
16789  /* evaluation failed */
16790  goto end_error;
16791  }
16792  val->info.insert_value.is_evaluated = true;
16793  /* evaluation ok, continue to next value */
16794  continue;
16795  }
16796 
16797  /* this must be first evaluation */
16798  val->next = NULL;
16799  eval.reevaluate_needed = false;
16800  eval.replace_names = false;
16801 
16802  if (!PT_IS_CONST (val))
16803  {
16804  /* duplicate value as it may be altered when names are replaced */
16805  temp = parser_copy_tree (parser, val);
16806 
16807  free_temp = true;
16808  temp =
16809  parser_walk_tree (parser, temp, do_replace_names_for_insert_values_pre, &eval, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
16810  if (pt_has_error (parser))
16811  {
16812  /* error replacing names */
16813  val->next = save_next;
16814  goto end_error;
16815  }
16816  }
16817  else
16818  {
16819  temp = val;
16820  free_temp = false;
16821  if (!PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (temp))
16822  {
16823  eval.reevaluate_needed = true;
16824  }
16825  }
16826 
16827  assert (temp != NULL);
16828  /* evaluate temp to obtain a value */
16829  db_value_clear (&eval_value);
16830  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, temp, &eval_value, 1);
16831  if (pt_has_error (parser))
16832  {
16833  val->next = save_next;
16834  goto end_error;
16835  }
16836 
16837  if (free_temp)
16838  {
16839  parser_free_tree (parser, temp);
16840  temp = NULL;
16841  free_temp = false;
16842  }
16843 
16844  result = pt_insert_value (parser, NULL);
16845  if (result == NULL)
16846  {
16847  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
16848  {
16849  PT_ERRORmf (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
16850  pt_short_print (parser, val));
16851  }
16852  val->next = save_next;
16853  goto end_error;
16854  }
16855  if (db_value_clone (&eval_value, &result->info.insert_value.value) != NO_ERROR)
16856  {
16857  PT_ERRORmf (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
16858  pt_short_print (parser, val));
16859  parser_free_tree (parser, result);
16860  val->next = save_next;
16861  goto end_error;
16862  }
16863  result->info.insert_value.is_evaluated = true;
16864  if (eval.reevaluate_needed || PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (val))
16865  {
16866  /* save original node */
16867  result->info.insert_value.original_node = val;
16868  }
16869  else
16870  {
16871  /* save a PT_VALUE node instead of original node in order to avoid reevaluation */
16872  result->info.insert_value.original_node = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &eval_value);
16873  if (result->info.insert_value.original_node == NULL)
16874  {
16875  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
16876  {
16877  PT_ERRORmf (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
16878  pt_short_print (parser, val));
16879  }
16880  parser_free_tree (parser, result);
16881  val->next = save_next;
16882  goto end_error;
16883  }
16884  }
16885  result->info.insert_value.replace_names = eval.replace_names;
16886 
16887  result->line_number = val->line_number;
16888  result->column_number = val->column_number;
16889 
16890  /* replace val */
16891  result->next = save_next;
16892 
16893  if (prev == NULL)
16894  {
16895  eval.value_list = value_list->info.node_list.list = result;
16896  }
16897  else
16898  {
16899  prev->next = result;
16900  }
16901  prev = result;
16902  }
16903  pr_clear_value (&eval_value);
16904  }
16905  return NO_ERROR;
16906 
16907 end_error:
16908  pr_clear_value (&eval_value);
16909  if (temp != NULL && free_temp)
16910  {
16911  parser_free_tree (parser, temp);
16912  }
16913  if (er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
16914  {
16915  return er_errid ();
16916  }
16917  return ER_FAILED;
16918 }
16919 
16920 /*
16921  * do_clear_insert_values () - Resets PT_INSERT_VALUE nodes in value clauses
16922  * to be reevaluation on next execution.
16923  *
16924  * return : Void.
16925  * parser (in) : Parser context.
16926  * insert_statement (in) : Parse tree node for insert statement.
16927  *
16928  * Note: Only some nodes are reseted. If the evaluated value is never changing
16929  * the node remains "evaluated".
16930  */
16931 static void
16932 do_clear_insert_values (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert_statement)
16933 {
16934  PT_NODE *value_list = NULL, *value = NULL;
16935  if (insert_statement == NULL || insert_statement->node_type != PT_INSERT)
16936  {
16937  return;
16938  }
16939  if (insert_statement->info.insert.value_clauses == NULL)
16940  {
16941  return;
16942  }
16943 
16944  for (value_list = insert_statement->info.insert.value_clauses; value_list != NULL; value_list = value_list->next)
16945  {
16946  if (value_list->info.node_list.list_type != PT_IS_VALUE)
16947  {
16948  continue;
16949  }
16950  for (value = value_list->info.node_list.list; value != NULL; value = value->next)
16951  {
16952  if (PT_IS_INSERT_VALUE_NODE (value) && !PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (value->info.insert_value.original_node))
16953  {
16954  /* prepare node for reevaluation */
16955  value->info.insert_value.is_evaluated = false;
16956  db_value_clear (&value->info.insert_value.value);
16957  db_make_null (&value->info.insert_value.value);
16958  }
16959  }
16960  }
16961 }
16962 
16963 /*
16964  * insert_rewrite_names_in_value_clauses () - Rewrites some names in insert
16965  * VALUE clause.
16966  *
16967  * return : void.
16968  * parser (in) : Parser context.
16969  * insert_statement (in) : Insert statement.
16970  *
16971  * NOTE: Names that are replaced:
16972  * 1. References to attribute from insert spec that are unassigned are
16973  * replaced with default values.
16974  * e.g.: INSERT INTO t (a, b) VALUES (b, a + 1) => In a = b, b is not
16975  * assigned yet and is replaced with DEFAULT(b). In b = a + 1,
16976  * a is assigned and is not replaced here.
16977  * 2. META_CLASS names are replaced with class object.
16978  * 3. PT_PARAMETER names that point to object type values are replaced.
16979  */
16980 void
16981 insert_rewrite_names_in_value_clauses (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert_statement)
16982 {
16983  PT_NODE *attr_list = NULL, *value_clauses = NULL, *value_list = NULL;
16984  PT_NODE *value = NULL, *value_tmp = NULL, *save_next = NULL, *prev = NULL;
16985 
16986  EVAL_INSERT_VALUE eval;
16987  if (insert_statement == NULL || insert_statement->node_type != PT_INSERT)
16988  {
16989  return;
16990  }
16991 
16992  attr_list = insert_statement->info.insert.attr_list;
16993  value_clauses = insert_statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
16994  if (attr_list == NULL || value_clauses == NULL)
16995  {
16996  return;
16997  }
16998 
16999  eval.spec_id = insert_statement->info.insert.spec->info.spec.id;
17000  eval.attr_list = attr_list;
17001  eval.value_list = NULL;
17002 
17003  for (value_list = value_clauses; value_list != NULL; value_list = value_list->next)
17004  {
17005  if (value_list->info.node_list.list_type != PT_IS_VALUE)
17006  {
17007  continue;
17008  }
17009  prev = NULL;
17010  for (value = value_list->info.node_list.list, eval.crt_attr_index = 0; value != NULL;
17011  value = save_next, eval.crt_attr_index++)
17012  {
17013  save_next = value->next;
17014  if (PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (value) || PT_IS_HOSTVAR (value))
17015  {
17016  prev = value;
17017  continue;
17018  }
17019  value->next = NULL;
17020 
17021  value = parser_walk_tree (parser, value, do_replace_names_for_insert_values_pre, &eval, NULL, NULL);
17022  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
17023  {
17024  value_tmp = pt_semantic_type (parser, value, NULL);
17025  if (value_tmp == NULL)
17026  {
17027  /* In this case, pt_has_error (parser) is true, we need recovery the link list firstly, then return. */
17028  ;
17029  }
17030  else
17031  {
17032  value = value_tmp;
17033  }
17034  }
17035  value->next = save_next;
17036  if (prev == NULL)
17037  {
17038  value_list->info.node_list.list = value;
17039  }
17040  else
17041  {
17042  prev->next = value;
17043  }
17044  if (pt_has_error (parser))
17045  {
17046  return;
17047  }
17048  prev = value;
17049  }
17050  }
17051 }
17052 
17053 /*
17054  * do_replace_names_for_insert_values_pre () - Used by parser_walk_tree to
17055  * evaluate names in insert values
17056  *
17057  * return : node or replaced name .
17058  * parser (in) : parser context.
17059  * node (in) : node in parse tree.
17060  * arg (in) : EVAL_INSERT_VALUE.
17061  * continue_walk (in) : continue walk.
17062  *
17063  * NOTE: Name replacement will be done after the next rules:
17064  * 1. If name belongs to insert attribute list and if name was assigned
17065  * before current attribute, use the assigned value to replace name.
17066  * 2. If name was not assigned yet, replace it with default value.
17067  * 3. If could not find a default value for name, then
17068  * pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial will have to evaluate the name.
17069  */
17070 static PT_NODE *
17071 do_replace_names_for_insert_values_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
17072 {
17073  int count, found, error = NO_ERROR;
17074  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *val = NULL, *result = NULL;
17075  EVAL_INSERT_VALUE *eval = (EVAL_INSERT_VALUE *) arg;
17076  DB_OBJECT *obj;
17077  DB_VALUE db_value;
17078  int is_class = 0;
17079 
17080  if (node == NULL || *continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK || pt_has_error (parser))
17081  {
17082  return node;
17083  }
17084 
17085  switch (node->node_type)
17086  {
17087  case PT_NAME:
17088  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
17089  if (node->info.name.spec_id != eval->spec_id)
17090  {
17091  eval->reevaluate_needed = true;
17092  switch (node->info.name.meta_class)
17093  {
17094  case PT_META_CLASS:
17095  case PT_CLASSOID_ATTR:
17096  /* object is the class itself */
17097  obj = node->info.name.db_object;
17098  if (obj == NULL)
17099  {
17100  /* do nothing */
17101  return node;
17102  }
17103  is_class = db_is_any_class (obj);
17104  if (is_class < 0)
17105  {
17106  return node;
17107  }
17108  if (!is_class)
17109  {
17110  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
17111  pt_short_print (parser, node));
17112  return node;
17113  }
17114  db_make_object (&db_value, obj);
17115  break;
17116  case PT_PARAMETER:
17117  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, node, &db_value, 1);
17118  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&db_value) == DB_TYPE_VOBJ)
17119  {
17120  error = vid_vobj_to_object (&db_value, &obj);
17121  if (error != NO_ERROR)
17122  {
17123  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
17124  pt_short_print (parser, node));
17125  }
17126  db_make_object (&db_value, obj);
17127  }
17128  else if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&db_value) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
17129  {
17130  obj = db_get_object (&db_value);
17131  obj = db_real_instance (obj);
17132  db_make_object (&db_value, obj);
17133  }
17134  break;
17135  default:
17136  /* do nothing here */
17137  return node;
17138  }
17139  /* replace node with value in db_value */
17140  result = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &db_value);
17141  if (result == NULL)
17142  {
17143  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
17144  {
17145  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
17146  pt_short_print (parser, node));
17147  }
17148  return node;
17149  }
17150  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (result, node);
17151  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
17152  return result;
17153  }
17154  /* look for node in attr list and stop when count reaches node_index */
17155  found = 0;
17156  val = eval->value_list;
17157  for (attr = eval->attr_list, count = 0; attr != NULL && count < eval->crt_attr_index; attr = attr->next, count++)
17158  {
17159  if (pt_name_equal (parser, node, attr))
17160  {
17161  found = true;
17162  break;
17163  }
17164  if (val != NULL)
17165  {
17166  val = val->next;
17167  }
17168  }
17169  /* replace found attributes with the corresponding values in value_list. if attribute is not found, it is
17170  * replaced with default value. if value_list is NULL, only default values are replaced */
17171  if (found && val != NULL)
17172  {
17173  /* replace node with value */
17174  if (!PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (val) && (!PT_IS_INSERT_VALUE_NODE (val) || !val->info.insert_value.is_evaluated))
17175  {
17176  /* cannot evaluate */
17177  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME__CAN_NOT_EVALUATE,
17178  pt_short_print (parser, node));
17179  /* do not replace node */
17180  return node;
17181  }
17182  if (PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (val))
17183  {
17184  /* value node */
17185  result = parser_copy_tree (parser, val);
17186  }
17187  else
17188  {
17189  /* insert_value node */
17190  eval->reevaluate_needed = true;
17191  eval->replace_names = true;
17192  result = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &val->info.insert_value.value);
17193  }
17194  if (result == NULL)
17195  {
17196  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
17197  {
17198  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_OUT_OF_MEMORY, sizeof (PT_NODE));
17199  }
17200  /* do not replace node */
17201  return node;
17202  }
17203  /* replace node */
17204  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (result, node);
17205  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
17206  return result;
17207  }
17208  else if (!found)
17209  {
17210  /* try to replace node with default value */
17211  if (pt_resolve_default_value (parser, node) == NO_ERROR)
17212  {
17213  if (node->info.name.default_value != NULL)
17214  {
17215  /* replace node with default value */
17216  result = node->info.name.default_value;
17217  node->info.name.default_value = NULL;
17218  }
17219  else
17220  {
17221  /* replace with a NULL value */
17222  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
17223  if (result == NULL)
17224  {
17225  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
17226  {
17227  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_OUT_OF_MEMORY,
17228  sizeof (PT_NODE));
17229  }
17230  return node;
17231  }
17232  result->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
17233  }
17234  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (result, node);
17235  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
17236  return result;
17237  }
17238  }
17239  /* could not assign a value, leave the node as it is */
17240  break;
17241 
17242  case PT_EXPR:
17243  case PT_FUNCTION:
17244  /* continue walk if current node is expression or function */
17245  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
17246  break;
17247 
17248  /* stop advancing in the tree if node is not a name, expression or function */
17249 
17250  case PT_VALUE:
17251  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
17252  break;
17253 
17254  default:
17255  /* reevaluation may be needed for each execution */
17256  eval->reevaluate_needed = true;
17257  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
17258  break;
17259  }
17260 
17261  return node;
17262 }

17265  * do_vacuum () - Executes a VACUUM statement.
17266  *
17267  * return : Error code.
17268  * parser (in) : Parser context.
17269  * statement (in) : VACUUM parse tree node.
17270  */
17271 static int
17272 do_vacuum (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
17273 {
17274  int error = NO_ERROR;
17275 
17276  assert (parser != NULL && statement != NULL && PT_IS_VACUUM_NODE (statement));
17277 
17278  error = cvacuum ();
17279 
17280  return error;
17281 }

17284  * do_set_query_trace() - Set query trace

17286  * parser(in): Parser context
17287  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set statement
17288  *
17289  */
17290 int
17291 do_set_query_trace (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
17292 {

17299

17307  }

17309  else
17310  {
17311  prm_set_bool_value (PRM_ID_QUERY_TRACE, false);

17314  return NO_ERROR;
