17318 /*
17319  * do_kill() - Kill transaction or query
17320  * return: Error code or number of killed transaction
17321  * parser(in): Parser context
17322  * statement(in): Parse tree of a set statement
17323  *
17324  */
17325 int
17326 do_kill (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
17327 {
17328 #if defined(SA_MODE)
17329  return NO_ERROR;
17330 #else
17331  int error;
17332  PT_NODE *id_list;
17333  bool interrupt_only;
17334  int i = 0;
17335  int num_killed;
17336  int *tran_index_array;
17337  int array_size;
17338  bool is_dba_group_member;
17339 
17340  id_list = statement->info.killstmt.tran_id_list;
17341  array_size = pt_length_of_list (id_list);
17342 
17343  assert (array_size >= 1); /* verified in syntax check */
17344 
17345  is_dba_group_member = au_is_dba_group_member (Au_user);
17346 
17347  tran_index_array = (int *) malloc (sizeof (int) * array_size);
17348  if (tran_index_array == NULL)
17349  {
17350  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
17351  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, sizeof (int) * array_size);
17352  return error;
17353  }
17354 
17355  for (i = 0; id_list != NULL; id_list = id_list->next, i++)
17356  {
17357  assert (i < array_size);
17358  assert (id_list->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER);
17359 
17360  tran_index_array[i] = id_list->info.value.data_value.i;
17361  }
17362 
17363  interrupt_only = statement->info.killstmt.kill_type == KILLSTMT_QUERY ? true : false;
17364 
17365  error =
17366  thread_kill_or_interrupt_tran (tran_index_array, array_size, is_dba_group_member, interrupt_only, &num_killed);
17367  if (error == NO_ERROR)
17368  {
17369  error = num_killed;
17370  }
17371 
17372  free_and_init (tran_index_array);
17373 
17374  return error;
17375 #endif
17376 }

17400 /*
17401  * do_send_plan_trace_to_session() - send plan dump to server session
17402  * return: void
17403  * parser(in):
17404  */
17405 static void
17406 do_send_plan_trace_to_session (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
17407 {
17408  DB_VALUE var[2];
17409  char *plan_str = NULL;
17410  int i = 0;
17411  QUERY_TRACE_FORMAT format;
17412  size_t sizeloc;
17413  FILE *fp;
17414 
17415  if (parser->num_plan_trace < 1)
17416  {
17417  return;
17418  }
17419 
17420  format = parser->plan_trace[0].format;
17421 
17422  if (format == QUERY_TRACE_TEXT)
17423  {
17424  if (parser->num_plan_trace > 1)
17425  {
17426  fp = port_open_memstream (&plan_str, &sizeloc);
17427 
17428  if (fp)
17429  {
17430  for (i = 0; i < parser->num_plan_trace; i++)
17431  {
17432  assert (parser->plan_trace[i].format == format);
17433  fprintf (fp, "%s\n", parser->plan_trace[i].trace.text_plan);
17434  free_and_init (parser->plan_trace[i].trace.text_plan);
17435  }
17436 
17437  port_close_memstream (fp, &plan_str, &sizeloc);
17438  }
17439  }
17440  else
17441  {
17442  plan_str = parser->plan_trace[0].trace.text_plan;
17443  parser->plan_trace[0].trace.text_plan = NULL;
17444  }
17445  }
17446  else if (format == QUERY_TRACE_JSON)
17447  {
17448  json_t *jplan;
17449 
17450  if (parser->num_plan_trace > 1)
17451  {
17452  jplan = json_array ();
17453 
17454  for (i = 0; i < parser->num_plan_trace; i++)
17455  {
17456  assert (parser->plan_trace[i].format == format);
17457  json_array_append_new (jplan, parser->plan_trace[i].trace.json_plan);
17458  parser->plan_trace[i].trace.json_plan = NULL;
17459  }
17460  }
17461  else
17462  {
17463  jplan = parser->plan_trace[0].trace.json_plan;
17464  parser->plan_trace[0].trace.json_plan = NULL;
17465  }
17466 
17467  plan_str = json_dumps (jplan, JSON_INDENT (2) | JSON_PRESERVE_ORDER);
17468 
17469  json_object_clear (jplan);
17470  json_decref (jplan);
17471  }
17472 
17473  parser->num_plan_trace = 0;
17474 
17475  if (plan_str != NULL)
17476  {
17477  db_make_char (&var[0], 10, "trace_plan", 10, LANG_COERCIBLE_CODESET, LANG_COERCIBLE_COLL);
17478  db_make_string (&var[1], plan_str);
17479 
17480  csession_set_session_variables (var, 2);
17481  free_and_init (plan_str);
17482  }
17483 }

17485 /*
17486  * do_insert_checks () : - Does preliminary checks for an insert statement.
17487  *
17488  * return : NO_ERROR or error code.
17489  * parser(in) : Parser context.
17490  * statement(in) : Parse tree of the insert statement to be checked.
17491  * class_(in) :
17492  * update(in/out) : Update attribute.
17493  * values(in) : Values to be inserted.
17494  */
17495 
17496 static int
17497 do_insert_checks (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, PT_NODE ** class_, PT_NODE ** update, PT_NODE * values)
17498 {
17499  int error = NO_ERROR;
17500  int upd_has_uniques = 0;
17501  bool has_default_values_list = false;
17502  int trigger_involved = 0;
17503  *update = NULL;
17504 
17505  /* Check if server allows an insert. */
17506  error = is_server_insert_allowed (parser, statement);
17507  if (error != NO_ERROR)
17508  {
17509  ASSERT_ERROR ();
17510  goto exit;
17511  }
17512 
17513  /* Check whether the statement can be executed with commit. */
17514  if (statement->info.insert.server_allowed == SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED)
17515  {
17516  /* Check statement insert trigger. */
17517  error = sm_class_has_triggers ((*class_)->info.name.db_object, &trigger_involved, TR_EVENT_STATEMENT_INSERT);
17518  if (error != NO_ERROR)
17519  {
17520  ASSERT_ERROR ();
17521  goto exit;
17522  }
17523 
17524  if (!trigger_involved)
17525  {
17526  statement->info.insert.execute_with_commit_allowed = 1;
17527  }
17528  }
17529 
17530  /* Check non null attrs. */
17531  if (values->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_DEFAULT_VALUE)
17532  {
17533  has_default_values_list = true;
17534  }
17535 
17536  error = check_missing_non_null_attrs (parser, statement->info.insert.spec, statement->info.insert.attr_list,
17537  has_default_values_list);
17538  if (error != NO_ERROR)
17539  {
17540  ASSERT_ERROR ();
17541  goto exit;
17542  }
17543 
17544  /* Test if server UPDATE is allowed */
17545 
17546  if (statement->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL)
17547  {
17548  *update = do_create_odku_stmt (parser, statement);
17549  if (*update == NULL)
17550  {
17551  error = ER_FAILED;
17552  goto exit;
17553  }
17554 
17555  if (statement->info.insert.server_allowed == SERVER_INSERT_IS_ALLOWED)
17556  {
17557  int server_allowed = 0;
17558 
17559  error = is_server_update_allowed (parser, &statement->info.insert.odku_non_null_attrs, &upd_has_uniques,
17560  &server_allowed, *update);
17561  if (error != NO_ERROR)
17562  {
17563  ASSERT_ERROR ();
17564  goto exit;
17565  }
17566 
17567  if (!server_allowed)
17568  {
17569  statement->info.insert.server_allowed = SERVER_INSERT_IS_NOT_ALLOWED;
17570  goto exit;
17571  }
17572  }
17573  }
17574 
17575  /* Check to see if the class into which we are inserting is part of an inheritance chain. We do not allow these
17576  * statements to be executed in these cases as we might have undefined behavior, such as trying to update a
17577  * column that belongs to a child for a duplicate key in the parent table that does not have that column. */
17578 
17579  if (statement->info.insert.do_replace || statement->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL)
17580  {
17581  int allowed = 0;
17582 
17583  error = is_replace_or_odku_allowed ((*class_)->info.name.db_object, &allowed);
17584  if (error != NO_ERROR)
17585  {
17586  ASSERT_ERROR ();
17587  goto exit;
17588  }
17589 
17590  if (!allowed)
17591  {
17592  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_REPLACE_ODKU_NOT_ALLOWED, 0);
17593  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error);
17594  goto exit;
17595  }
17596  }
17597 
17598  /* fetch the class for instance write purpose - IX_LOCK */
17599  if (!locator_fetch_class ((*class_)->info.name.db_object, DB_FETCH_CLREAD_INSTWRITE))
17600  {
17601  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error);
17602  goto exit;
17603  }
17604 
17605 exit:
17606  return error;
17607 }
